ZFA:0000716.label: afferent branchial artery
ZFA:0000716.definition: Artery that is part of the pharyngeal arches 3-5, and forms the afferent portion of a loop off of the aortic arch.

ZFA:0005012.label: afferent filamental artery
ZFA:0005012.definition: Artery that enters the gill filament.

ZFA:0005080.label: anterior mesenteric artery
ZFA:0005080.definition: An artery deep in the trunk that connects the dorsal aorta to the supraintestinal artery.

ZFA:0005004.label: aortic arch
ZFA:0005004.definition: Artery that is part of the pharyngeal arches.

ZFA:0005000.label: basal communicating artery
ZFA:0005000.definition: Artery that extends horizontally across the brain midline which is fed by the caudal division of the internal carotid artery. Three pairs of central arteries extend from the basal communicating artery (BCA), the anterior, middle and  posterior mesencephalic central arteries. The BCA does not correspond to the anterior communicating artery of the mammalian circle of Willis.  The BCA is unpaired.

ZFA:0005002.label: basilar artery
ZFA:0005002.definition: Artery that runs along the ventral keel of the hindbrain.  It lies between the primordial hindbrain channels(PHBC).  It irrigates the hindbrain and is connected, through the hindbrain, to the PHBC by the central arteries.

ZFA:0000097.label: carotid artery
ZFA:0000097.definition: Artery originating at the junction of the first two aortic arches and supplying the anterior brain.

ZFA:0000011.label: caudal artery
ZFA:0000011.definition: Extension of the dorsal aorta in the post-vent region.

ZFA:0001051.label: caudal division of the internal carotid artery
ZFA:0001051.definition: Branch of the internal carotid artery that extends caudally along the sides of the midbrain and eventually drains into the basilar artery via the posterior communicating artery.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: posterior rami of the cerebral carotid artery

ZFA:0005020.label: central artery
ZFA:0005020.definition: Artery that irrigates the forebrain and midbrain.

ZFA:0005098.label: central ray artery
ZFA:0005098.definition: Artery that is positioned in the intraray mesenchyme between the hemirays of the lepidotrichia.

ZFA:0005051.label: communicating vessel palatocerebral artery
ZFA:0005051.definition: Connect the palatocerebral artery with the prosencephalic artery.

ZFA:0005013.label: concurrent branch afferent branchial artery
ZFA:0005013.definition: The branch of the afferent branchial artery that continues posterodorsally.

ZFA:0005812.label: coronary artery
ZFA:0005812.definition: Artery that carries blood from the efferent branchial artery to the cardiac ventricle.  The artery runs along the ventral surface of the bulbus arteriosus.

ZFA:0001059.label: cranial division of the internal carotid artery
ZFA:0001059.definition: Caudal branch of the internal carotid artery that gives rise to the branches that supply the diencephalon and telencephalon.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: anterior rami of the cerebral carotid artery
rostral division of the internal carotid artery

ZFA:0000014.label: dorsal aorta
ZFA:0000014.definition: Principal unpaired, median artery of the trunk, leading from the paired roots (radices) of the dorsal aorta to the caudal artery.

ZFA:0005082.label: dorsal branch nasal ciliary artery
ZFA:0005082.definition: Branch of the nasal ciliary artery (NCA) that splits off of the NCA near the lens and forms the dorsal ciliary vein.

ZFA:0000202.label: efferent branchial artery
ZFA:0000202.definition: Artery that carries blood leaving the gill.  This is on the side of the aortic arch proximal to the lateral dorsal aorta.

ZFA:0005018.label: efferent filamental artery
ZFA:0005018.definition: Artery that exits the gill filament.

ZFA:0005161.label: hepatic artery
ZFA:0005161.definition: Artery that supplies blood to the liver.

ZFA:0005045.label: hyaloid artery
ZFA:0005045.definition: Artery that is internal to the eye.

ZFA:0000673.label: hypobranchial artery
ZFA:0000673.definition: A pair of HA are connect one to each AA1. They run rostromedially until at the extreme rostro-ventral midline the two vessels merge and then run straight caudally along the ventral midline until they reach the cranial end of the ventral aorta (VA). There, the single HA passes just dorsal to the rostral end of the VA and then immediately splits again into a pair of HA. The paired HA continue caudally just to either side of the ventral midline. The HA provide blood supply to the ventral branchial region and the heart.

ZFA:0005787.label: hypophyseal artery
ZFA:0005787.definition: Artery that runs along the midline from anterior to posterior regions of the hypothalamus and splits into two capillary branches (hyc). The formation of the artery is initiated at the hypophysis itself and extends anteriorly until it connects with the palatocerebral arteries at day 2.5.

ZFA:0005054.label: inner optic circle
ZFA:0005054.definition: Vessel that circles the inner rim of the optic capsule.  The inner optic circle drains ventrally into the optic vein and dorsally into the dorsal ciliary vein.

ZFA:0005081.label: internal carotid artery
ZFA:0005081.definition: Artery that originates as rostral extensions of the dorsal aorta and travels through the hypophyseal fossa into the cranium.  The internal carotid artery splits near the hypothalamus and optic nerve to form  caudal and cranial divisions.

ZFA:0001061.label: intersegmental artery
ZFA:0001061.definition: Arteries that connect the dorsal aorta and the dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel. They run along the vertical myotomal boundaries.  At early stages these vessels don't have venous or arterial markers.  They form from the primary sprouts from the dorsal aorta.

ZFA:0001054.label: lateral dorsal aorta
ZFA:0001054.definition: Connect the outflow of the aortic arches to the dorsal aorta. The place where the lateral dorsal aorta fuse is called the radix of the aorta.

ZFA:0001068.label: mesencephalic artery
ZFA:0001068.definition: Artery in the midbrain that develops from the proximal portion of the primitive mesencephalic artery.

ZFA:0005084.label: metencephalic artery
ZFA:0005084.definition: These arteries branch dorsally from both sides of the posterior communicating artery looping up to join with the opposite MtA as well as with both middle cerebral veins at the dorsal midline of the head.

ZFA:0005085.label: nasal artery
ZFA:0005085.definition: The nasal arteries start at the internal carotid artery and travel rostrally, passing along the right and left walls of the nasal sac at the most rostral end of the head. From the nasal sac, the NA flows into the nasal veins.

ZFA:0005053.label: nasal ciliary artery
ZFA:0005053.definition: Artery that branches off the cranial division of the internal carotid artery.  It bifurcates near the eye.

ZFA:0005022.label: opercular artery
ZFA:0005022.definition: The opercular artery arises from the hyoid stump on the first aortic arch, then follows the lateral margin of the operculum (gill covering) ventrally to reconnect into the proximal part of the first aortic arch.

ZFA:0005044.label: optic artery
ZFA:0005044.definition: The artery that carries blood to the eye.  It branches from the primitive internal carotid artery and enters the eye ventrally through the optic fissure.

ZFA:0005050.label: palatocerebral artery
ZFA:0005050.definition: The PLA branches ventrally from the CrDI.  It extends rostrally along the base of mid- and forebrain, then loops medially and links to the corresponding vessel from the other side of the embryo.

ZFA:0005086.label: pectoral artery
ZFA:0005086.definition: The pectoral (subclavian) arteries originate from the dorsal aorta and takes the blood outward into the fin from the paired portion of the dorsal aorta posterior to the last aortic arch Kimmel et al. 1993.

ZFA:0005001.label: posterior communicating artery
ZFA:0005001.definition: An artery that connects caudal division of the internal carotid artery and the basal communicating artery to the basilar artery.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: posterior communicating segment of the basilar artery

ZFA:0005088.label: posterior mesenteric artery
ZFA:0005088.definition: Branch ventrally from the dorsal aorta and anastomose longitudinally along the dorsal wall of the hindgut, forming the caudal part of the supraintestinal artery.

ZFA:0001053.label: primitive internal carotid artery
ZFA:0001053.definition: Artery that originates as rostral extensions of the paired lateral dorsal aorta. The primitive internal carotid artery splits to form caudal and cranial divisions. The primitive internal carotid artery is paired.

ZFA:0001062.label: primitive mesencephalic artery
ZFA:0001062.definition: Artery that branches dorsally from the cranial division of the internal carotid artery, then curves caudally along the dorsal medial wall of the eye capsule to drain into the PMBC just rostral to the midbrain hindbrain boundary.

ZFA:0005048.label: primitive prosencephalic artery
ZFA:0005048.definition: Vessel that branches from cranial division of the internal carotid artery, extending laterally around the rostral end of the head.

ZFA:0005049.label: prosencephalic artery
ZFA:0005049.definition: After the primitive prosencephalic artery forms it becomes disconnected from the  cranial division of the internal carotid artery and instead it connects to the anterior mesencephalic central artery and the communicating vessels of the palatocerebral artery.

ZFA:0005011.label: pseudobranchial artery
ZFA:0005011.definition: A vascular loop attached to the efferent part of the mandibular arch that forms at 3.5 dpf.

ZFA:0005014.label: recurrent branch afferent branchial artery
ZFA:0005014.definition: The anteroventral proceeding branch of the afferent branchial artery.

ZFA:0005036.label: supraintestinal artery
ZFA:0005036.definition: A continuation of the anterior mesenteric artery, which branches out from the dorsal aorta  just caudal to the pronephric glomus.

ZFA:0005089.label: swim bladder artery
ZFA:0005089.definition: An elaborate set of vessels that branch off caudally from the anterior mesenteric artery just after the dorsal aorta.  The SBA vascular loops are located on the ventral side of the swim bladder.

ZFA:0000604.label: ventral aorta
ZFA:0000604.definition: Outflow artery from the heart to the aortic arches.

ZFA:0005033.label: vertebral artery
ZFA:0005033.definition: Is an pair of arteries that form from the intersegmental vessels at the level of the base of the spinal cord, adjacent to the myotome.

ZFA:0001555.label: epibranchial ganglion
ZFA:0001555.definition: Cranial ganglion which develops from an epibranchial placode.

ZFA:0000120.label: lateral line ganglion
ZFA:0000120.definition: Ganglion that develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate a lateral line.

ZFA:0000588.label: statoacoustic (VIII) ganglion
ZFA:0000588.definition: The sensory ganglion of the ear. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for statoacoustic ganglion by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000295.label: trigeminal ganglion
ZFA:0000295.definition: A prominent collection of touch-sensory neurons of the trigeminal or fifth cranial nerve, positioned beside the brain between the eye and the ear.

ZFA:0000943.label: pectoral fin skeleton
ZFA:0000943.definition: Skeleton that consists of the supporting endochondral proximal and distal radials and the dermal fins rays or lepidotrichia. The pectoral fin skeleton is located in the thoracic region of the body and articulates with the scapula and coracoid.

ZFA:0001387.label: pelvic fin skeleton
ZFA:0001387.definition: Skeleton that supports the pelvic fin.  The skeleton consists of consists of supporting endochondral radials and dermal fin rays or lepidotrichia.

ZFA:0001468.label: anterior lateral line system
ZFA:0001468.definition: The anterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated between the eye and the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the anterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The anterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians and are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project to the hindbrain. The anterior lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

ZFA:0005114.label: middle lateral line system
ZFA:0005114.definition: The middle lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the middle lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The middle lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the body  that are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project to the hindbrain. The middle  lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

ZFA:0001471.label: posterior lateral line system
ZFA:0001471.definition: The posterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated behind the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the posterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The posterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians. The neuromasts are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project primarily to the hindbrain. The posterior mechanosensory lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

ZFA:0000382.label: acellular anatomical structure
ZFA:0000382.definition: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

ZFA:0007114.label: anatomical conduit
ZFA:0007114.definition: An anatomical structure that is an opening or tube that connects two distinct anatomical spaces.

ZFA:0001512.label: anatomical group
ZFA:0001512.definition: Anatomical structure consisting of at least two non-overlapping organs, multi-tissue aggregates or portion of tissues or cells of different types that does not constitute an organism, organ, multi-tissue aggregate, or portion of tissue.

ZFA:0009000.label: cell
ZFA:0009000.definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

ZFA:0005499.label: circulus
ZFA:0005499.definition: Fine ridges on surface of scale, often parallel to the circumference of scale.

ZFA:0000496.label: compound organ
ZFA:0000496.definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.

ZFA:0001105.label: embryonic structure
ZFA:0001105.definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells.

ZFA:0000020.label: extraembryonic structure
ZFA:0000020.definition: Anatomical structure that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.

ZFA:0001690.label: groove
ZFA:0001690.definition: Anatomical structure that delineates a furrow or depression in an organ or tissue.

ZFA:0001488.label: multi-tissue structure
ZFA:0001488.definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more portions of tissue of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona-fide boundaries from other distinct structural units of different types.

ZFA:0005593.label: neuraxis flexure
ZFA:0005593.definition: An anatomical structure that is regional part of the central nervous system where there is a significant bend of the axis.

ZFA:0001308.label: organism subdivision
ZFA:0001308.definition: Anatomical structure which is a primary subdivision of whole organism. The mereological sum of these is the whole organism.

ZFA:0001477.label: portion of tissue
ZFA:0001477.definition: Anatomical structure, that consists of similar cells and intercellular matrix, aggregated according to genetically determined spatial relationships.

ZFA:0005899.label: scale focus
ZFA:0005899.definition: The initial growth point of the scale.  In zebrafish the focus is on the anterior edge of the scale.

ZFA:0005900.label: scale radius
ZFA:0005900.definition: Grooves on the scale radiating from the focus. Zebrafish have primary radii that start at the focus and extend to the posterior margin of the scale.

ZFA:0001094.label: whole organism
ZFA:0001094.definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of Danio rerio.

ZFA:0000789.label: mesoderm pectoral fin bud
ZFA:0000789.definition: Mesoderm that is part of the pectoral fin bud.

ZFA:0001386.label: mesoderm pelvic fin bud
ZFA:0001386.definition: Mesoderm part of pelvic fin bud.

ZFA:0000255.label: paraxial mesoderm
ZFA:0000255.definition: Mesoderm which is lateral to the neural tube on both sides.

ZFA:0000067.label: pronephric mesoderm
ZFA:0000067.definition: Intermediate mesoderm that is located beneath the anterior somites and gives rise to the pronephros and pronephric duct.

ZFA:0001648.label: cardiac neural crest
ZFA:0001648.definition: Neural crest that migrates into the pharyngeal arches and heart, forming connective tissue that separates the vessels of the heart.

ZFA:0001194.label: cranial neural crest
ZFA:0001194.definition: Neural crest that is part of the head.

ZFA:0007085.label: migratory neural crest
ZFA:0007085.definition: Migratory neural crest population that develops from premigratory neural crest. This group of neural crest has undergone ectomesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0007083.label: premigratory neural crest
ZFA:0007083.definition: Premigratory neural crest population that develops from the neural plate border. The cells of this group will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delaminate to produce the migratory neural crest.

ZFA:0001024.label: trunk neural crest
ZFA:0001024.definition: Neural crest that is part of the trunk.

ZFA:0000818.label: vagal neural crest
ZFA:0000818.definition: Vagal neural crest is adjacent to the first seven somites gives rise to both ganglionic and ectomesenchymal derivatives.

ZFA:0005582.label: dorsal proneural cluster
ZFA:0005582.definition: Cluster of cells along the edge of  the neural plate that have the potential to become neuroblast.

ZFA:0005583.label: ventral proneural cluster
ZFA:0005583.definition: Cluster of cells along the center of  the neural plate that have the potential to become neuroblast.

ZFA:0000999.label: mesenchyme derived from trunk neural crest

ZFA:0000423.label: anterior cardinal vein
ZFA:0000423.definition: Vein that joins with the posterior cardinal vein to form the common cardinal vein.  The anterior cardinal vein (ACV) connects to the primordial hindbrain channel at early stages. At later stages the posterior cerebral vein (PCeV) and the pectoral vein (PV) drain into ACV.  The rostral portion of the ACV connects to the primary head sinus (PHS) at 2.5dpf, the PHS is sometimes considered an extension of the ACV.

ZFA:0001067.label: anterior cerebral vein
ZFA:0001067.definition: Vein that branches from the primordial hindbrain channel (PHBC) at 1.3 dpf. The primitive prosencephalic artery drains into the anterior cerebral vein (ACeV) as do the prosencephalic artery and the nasal vein.

ZFA:0000180.label: caudal vein
ZFA:0000180.definition: Vein in the tail returning blood from the trunk and tail to the heart, leads directly into the posterior cardinal vein in the posterior trunk.

ZFA:0005168.label: central vein
ZFA:0005168.definition: Vein that is central to a lobule in the liver.

ZFA:0000186.label: common cardinal vein
ZFA:0000186.definition: Bilaterally paired longitudinal vein; the anterior cardinal returns blood from the head, and the posterior cardinal returns it from the trunk; these two vessels join together on each side as the common cardinal vein (duct of Cuvier; misnamed the vitelline vein) that leads across the yolk cell to the heart's sinus venosus.

ZFA:0005814.label: coronary vein
ZFA:0005814.definition: Vein that carries blood from the coronary capillaries to the atrial chamber entering the atrium close to the atrioventricular region.

ZFA:0005030.label: dorsal ciliary vein
ZFA:0005030.definition: Vein that branches off the nasal ciliary artery.  Initially, at 2dpf, the dorsal ciliary vein (DCV) drains into the primordial midbrain channel (PMBC) or the PMBC/PHBC junction.  Later, by 3.5dpf,  the DCV drains into the optic choroid vascular plexus.  The dorsal branch of the inner optic circle drains into the DCV.

ZFA:0005031.label: dorsal longitudinal vein
ZFA:0005031.definition: Vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0005090.label: hepatic portal vein
ZFA:0005090.definition: Vein that collects blood from the small intestine, pancreas and spleen and routes it through the liver.

ZFA:0000670.label: hepatic vein
ZFA:0000670.definition: Vein that carries blood away from the liver.

ZFA:0005788.label: hypophyseal vein
ZFA:0005788.definition: Vein thats tarts posterior of the hypophysis and drains the hypophyseal capillaries.  It empties into the primary head sinus.

ZFA:0001057.label: intersegmental vein
ZFA:0001057.definition: Veins that connect the posterior cardinal vein and the dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel. They run along the vertical myotomal boundaries. They form from primary intersegmental vessels that are contacted by secondary angiogenic sprouts from the posterior cardinal vein and take on the characteristics of veins.  These eventually link with other secondary sprouts from the posterior cardinal vein to form the parachordal vessel.

ZFA:0005055.label: median palatocerebral vein
ZFA:0005055.definition: Drains the PLA loop proceeds straight caudally along the cranial midline just above the pharynx, just below the diencephalon.  Forms a 'T' with the palatocerebral veins.

ZFA:0005092.label: mesencephalic vein
ZFA:0005092.definition: Paired veins that sprout from the dorsal midline junction and dive ventrally.  The mesencephalic veins are fed by the mesencephalic arteries,  after 2.5 dpf, and drain into the dorsal longitudinal vessel after 5dpf.

ZFA:0005010.label: mid cerebral vein
ZFA:0005010.definition: The mesencephalic veins (MsV) enter the mid cerebral veins (MCeV) at the dorsal midline. THe MCeVs originate at the dorsal midline, proceed laterally in a ventral direction to drain into the paired primordial midbrain channels (PHBC).

ZFA:0005093.label: nasal vein
ZFA:0005093.definition: Vein that  is fed by the nasal artery.  It  rises dorsally around the front of the head, draining into the ACeV and eventually into the PMBC on either side.

ZFA:0005032.label: optic vein
ZFA:0005032.definition: Vein that connects to the hyaloid vein that drains the eye.  External to eye.

ZFA:0005056.label: palatocerebral vein
ZFA:0005056.definition: Vein that drains the median palatocerebral vein into the optic vein.

ZFA:0005034.label: parachordal vessel
ZFA:0005034.definition: Vessels run longitudinally along the horizontal myoseptum.  These vessels are not functional until after lumenization which occurs near 4 dpf.

ZFA:0005087.label: pectoral vein
ZFA:0005087.definition: Vein from the pectoral fin that drains into the ACV just cranial to the ACV-CCV junction.

ZFA:0000477.label: posterior cardinal vein
ZFA:0000477.definition: Continuation of the caudal vein cranial to the anal pore. The cardinal vein splits into a pair of vessels in the cranial trunk, just caudal to the radix of the aorta. The posterior cardinals each empty into the common cardinal vein.

ZFA:0005027.label: posterior cerebral vein
ZFA:0005027.definition: Vein that drains the dorsal longitudinal vessel and the caudal portions of the venous capillary network of the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0005026.label: primary head sinus
ZFA:0005026.definition: Main route for venous drainage of the anterior and mid cerebral veins as well as portions of the primordial hindbrain channel.

ZFA:0001052.label: primordial hindbrain channel
ZFA:0001052.definition: The paired vessels that run along the lateral walls of the hindbrain and drain into the anterior cardinal veins.

ZFA:0005017.label: primordial midbrain channel
ZFA:0005017.definition: The vessel between the anterior cerebral vein and the mid cerebral vein.

ZFA:0005099.label: ray vein
ZFA:0005099.definition: Vein that flanks and is just lateral to the fin ray, in the interray mesenchyme.

ZFA:0000577.label: renal portal vein
ZFA:0000577.definition: Afferent vein that supplies the kidney.

ZFA:0005035.label: subintestinal vein
ZFA:0005035.definition: Vein that drains the vascular plexus of the midgut and hindgut.  At early stages the subintestinal vein (SIV) drains into the PCV and the CCV.  At later stages the SIV drains into the hepatic sinusoid.  The SIV are begin as paired veins.   After 4dpf the remains of the left SIV forms separate segments that empty into the right SIV and eventually merge with the right.  At 3dpf the rostral end of  left SIV begins to form the reticular hepatic sinusoids.  The portion of the left SIV caudal to the hepatic sinusoid forms the hepatic portal vein.

ZFA:0005248.label: trans-choroid plexus branch
ZFA:0005248.definition: Vein segment that connects the PCeVs in the choroid plexus.

ZFA:0000052.label: dorsal actinotrichium
ZFA:0000052.definition: Actinotrichium which is part of the dorsal fin fold.

ZFA:0000078.label: ventral actinotrichium
ZFA:0000078.definition: Actinotrichium which is part of the ventral fin fold.

ZFA:0001473.label: deep blastomere
ZFA:0001473.definition: Cells (completely cleaved), located underneath the superficial blastomeres and internal to the marginal blastomeres.

ZFA:0000541.label: marginal blastomere
ZFA:0000541.definition: Cells (incompletely cleaved before the YSL forms), located at the surface just at the rim of the blastodisc, external to the deep blastomeres.

ZFA:0001484.label: superficial blastomere
ZFA:0001484.definition: Cells (completely cleaved), located at the surface of the blastodisc, above the deep blastomeres.

ZFA:0001702.label: apical ectodermal ridge
ZFA:0001702.definition: Proliferative region that is part of the developing fin fold or fin.

ZFA:0005870.label: cerebellar plate ventral proliferative layer
ZFA:0005870.definition: Proliferative zone on the ventral side of the cerebellar plate.

ZFA:0001289.label: ciliary marginal zone
ZFA:0001289.definition: Proliferative region at the periphery of the retina where retinal stem cells are located. After 60 hpf, the CMZ is the source of most retinal growth.

ZFA:0005872.label: external granular layer of the cerebellar plate
ZFA:0005872.definition: Proliferative region that forms on peripheral side of the cerebellar plate.

ZFA:0001083.label: ventricular zone
ZFA:0001083.definition: Proliferative region that is part of the ventricular system.  The cells directly face the ventricle.

ZFA:0001443.label: choroid plexus
ZFA:0001443.definition: A tuft of capillaries that project into the ventricles of the brain and secretes cerebral spinal fluid. The choroid plexus is covered by a cuboidal epithelium which maintains the integrity of the blood-brain barrier.

ZFA:0005219.label: choroid plexus vascular circuit
ZFA:0005219.definition: Cranial vasculature where the posterior cerebral veins and the trans-choroid plexus branch form a circuit around the 4th ventricle choroid plexus.

ZFA:0005597.label: median fin
ZFA:0005597.definition: Fin that is an unpaired fin located in the sagittal plane of the organism.

ZFA:0005596.label: paired fin
ZFA:0005596.definition: Fin that is one of a pair located ventrally on the organism.

ZFA:0001269.label: regenerating fin
ZFA:0001269.definition: Fin undergoing the process of regeneration.

ZFA:0000787.label: mesenchyme derived from head neural crest

ZFA:0005572.label: periocular mesenchyme
ZFA:0005572.definition: Head mesenchyme surrounding the immature eye that  gives rise to specialized structures of the anterior segment of the eye.

ZFA:0001391.label: anterior lateral line ganglion
ZFA:0001391.definition: The anterior lateral line ganglia develops from cranial ectodermal placodes and contain sensory neurons that innervate the anterior lateral line system.

ZFA:0001483.label: middle lateral line ganglion
ZFA:0001483.definition: The middle lateral line ganglion develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate the middle lateral line.

ZFA:0001314.label: posterior lateral line ganglion
ZFA:0001314.definition: The posterior lateral line ganglion develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate the posterior lateral line system.

ZFA:0000072.label: somite 1
ZFA:0000072.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000974.label: somite 10
ZFA:0000974.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000725.label: somite 11
ZFA:0000725.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000851.label: somite 12
ZFA:0000851.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000975.label: somite 13
ZFA:0000975.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000726.label: somite 14
ZFA:0000726.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome.

ZFA:0000852.label: somite 15
