ZFA:0001223.label: basibranchial 1
ZFA:0001223.definition: Basibranchial 1 ossifies posterior to the basihyal and anterior to the first hypobranchials in copula 1 (7.6 mm).

ZFA:0001224.label: basibranchial 2
ZFA:0001224.definition: Basibranchial 2 ossifies in copula 1 posterior to the first hypobranchials and anterior to the second hypobranchials (6.8 mm).  It is the first of the three basibranchials to ossify.

ZFA:0001225.label: basibranchial 3
ZFA:0001225.definition: Basibranchial 3 ossifies in copula 1 posterior to the second hypobranchials, anterior to the third hypobranchials (7.6 mm) and associated with pharyngeal arch 5. Cartilage pads, remnants of copula 1, remain between adjacent basibranchials in the adult.

ZFA:0001226.label: basibranchial 4
ZFA:0001226.definition: Occasionally, a fourth basibranchial ossifies in the narrow copula 2 cartilage, which lies posterior to the third basibranchial and anterior to the anteromedial articulation of the fifth ceratobranchials.

ZFA:0000415.label: esophageal sphincter
ZFA:0000415.definition: Sphincter at the junction of the esophagus and pneumatic duct.

ZFA:0000013.label: cranial ganglion
ZFA:0000013.definition: Ganglion which is located in the head.

ZFA:0001573.label: trunk ganglion
ZFA:0001573.definition: Ganglion which is located in the trunk.

ZFA:0001154.label: anal fin musculature
ZFA:0001154.definition: Musculature part of the anal fin.

ZFA:0000628.label: caudal fin musculature
ZFA:0000628.definition: Fin musculature that is part of the caudal fin.  The musculature is  composed of 12 muscles that are arranged in a superficial and a deep muscle layer. Nerve roots of spinal segments 27-31 supply the caudal fin muscles.

ZFA:0000648.label: dorsal fin musculature
ZFA:0000648.definition: Musculature that is part of the dorsal fin.  The dorsal fin musculature is composed of one unit per fin ray that are arranged in series on each side of the body. Each unit is composed of one fin ray, three supporting pterygophores, and a set of paired depressor, erector, and inclinator muscles.

ZFA:0000563.label: pectoral fin musculature
ZFA:0000563.definition: Musculature that is part of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0000258.label: pelvic fin musculature
ZFA:0000258.definition: Musculature that is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0005117.label: anterior lateral line primordium
ZFA:0005117.definition: A migrating group of cells originating from an anterior lateral line placode.  The primordium deposits neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its migration.

ZFA:0005118.label: middle lateral line primordium
ZFA:0005118.definition: A migrating group of cells originating from the middle lateral line placode.  The primordium deposits neuromasts  with interneuromasts between them.

ZFA:0001157.label: posterior lateral line primordium
ZFA:0001157.definition: A migrating group of cells originating from the posterior lateral line placode.  The primordium deposits seven to nine neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its posterior migration to the tail.

ZFA:0007049.label: adductor mandibulae
ZFA:0007049.definition: Is a mandibular muscle that forms along the palatoquadrates and inserts on Meckel's cartilages and functions in jaw closing.

ZFA:0007050.label: constrictor dorsalis
ZFA:0007050.definition: Dorsal subdivision of the putative mandibular muscle plate. Splits into the dilatator operculi and the levator arcus palatini.

ZFA:0000498.label: dilatator operculi
ZFA:0000498.definition: Mandibular muscle that inserts along the dorsolateral faces of the opercles.  Responsible for opercular abduction.

ZFA:0000369.label: intermandibularis
ZFA:0000369.definition: Is a mandibular muscle that develops into the ventral intermandibularis anterior and posterior muscles.

ZFA:0000384.label: levator arcus palatini
ZFA:0000384.definition: Mandibular muscle that inserts along the dorsolateral faces of the hyosymplectics.

ZFA:0001651.label: sternohyoid
ZFA:0001651.definition: Head muscle that originates on the anterior region of the cleithrum and inserts on the urohyal. The hypobranchial forms initially as left and right parts that later fuse together forming a cone shape.  The muscle is innervated by the occipitospinals.

ZFA:0001472.label: anterior lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0001472.definition: Neuromast that is part of the anterior lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0005113.label: dorsal lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0005113.definition: Neuromast that is part of the dorsal lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000813.label: infraorbital lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000813.definition: Neuromast that is part of the infraorbital lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000125.label: mandibular lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000125.definition: Neuromast that is part of the mandibular lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000939.label: middle lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000939.definition: Neuromast that is part of the middle lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001025.label: occipital lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0001025.definition: Neuromast that is part of the occipital lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000814.label: opercular lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000814.definition: Neuromast that is part of the opercular lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000136.label: otic lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000136.definition: Neuromast that is part of the otic lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000940.label: posterior lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0000940.definition: Neuromast that is part of the posterior lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001026.label: supraorbital lateral line neuromast
ZFA:0001026.definition: Neuromast that is part of the supraorbital lateral line. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001537.label: mesocoracoid cartilage
ZFA:0001537.definition: Cartilage that develops initially on the medial side of the coraco-scapular cartilage.

ZFA:0001456.label: pectoral fin endoskeletal disc
ZFA:0001456.definition: A plate-like chondrogenic condensation within the pectoral fin, which subdivides into individual radials by decomposition of extracellular matrix in the inter-radial mesenchyme (Grandel and Schulte-Merker, 1998).

ZFA:0001455.label: scapulocoracoid
ZFA:0001455.definition: The cartilage from which both the scapula and coracoid develop.

ZFA:0001190.label: Weberian vertebra
ZFA:0001190.definition: The first four vertebrae, which are part of the Weberian apparatus.

ZFA:0001582.label: non-Weberian precaudal vertebra
ZFA:0001582.definition: Precaudal vertebra that is not a Weberian vertebra.  Vertebra 5 through 14.

ZFA:0001646.label: anal fin radial
ZFA:0001646.definition: Internal skeletal supports of the anal fin.

ZFA:0001647.label: dorsal fin radial
ZFA:0001647.definition: Internal skeletal supports of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0001586.label: pectoral fin radial
ZFA:0001586.definition: Radial which develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports the pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia with the primary pectoral girdle.

ZFA:0000508.label: pelvic radial
ZFA:0000508.definition: Internal skeletal supports of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0005530.label: lateral line scale
ZFA:0005530.definition: Scale that is associated with the lateral line sensory canal.

ZFA:0001101.label: gustatory system
ZFA:0001101.definition: Sensory system that uses taste buds to sense chemical compounds.

ZFA:0000034.label: lateral line system
ZFA:0000034.definition: A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001149.label: olfactory system
ZFA:0001149.definition: Sensory system responsible for olfaction.  Olfaction involves the detection of chemical composition of an organism's ambient medium by chemoreceptors.

ZFA:0001138.label: vestibuloauditory system
ZFA:0001138.definition: Sensory system responsible for the perception of spatial orientation and auditory stimuli.

ZFA:0001127.label: visual system
ZFA:0001127.definition: Sensory system responsible for the perception of light.

ZFA:0000622.label: barbel
ZFA:0000622.definition: Surface structure which is a tactile structure found in the branchial region. Barbels are covered with epidermis rich in taste buds, and are innervated by branches of the cranial nerves.

ZFA:0005119.label: barbel primordium
ZFA:0005119.definition: A surface structure that will eventually grow to form a barbel.   The primordium is rich in taste buds. The final location for taste buds present in the primordium is the distal tip of the mature barbel.

ZFA:0005791.label: breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005791.definition: Surface structure that is a keratinized epidermal appendages that is a contact organ and secondary sex organ.

ZFA:0001605.label: caudal fin lower lobe
ZFA:0001605.definition: Surface structure that is the ventral portion of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001604.label: caudal fin upper lobe
ZFA:0001604.definition: Surface structure that is the dorsal portion of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001383.label: fin bud
ZFA:0001383.definition: Surface structure that develops into a paired fin.

ZFA:0000368.label: integument
ZFA:0000368.definition: The outer protective barrier that separates the animal from its aquatic environment.

ZFA:0005792.label: jaw flap
ZFA:0005792.definition: Surface structure that is a protrusion from the rostral end of the jaw, supported by the mandibular projection.

ZFA:0007006.label: lip
ZFA:0007006.definition: Surface structure that is one of the fleshy folds surrounding the opening of the mouth.

ZFA:0000040.label: median fin fold
ZFA:0000040.definition: Surface structure that will develop into one of the median fins.  Extends from dorsal surface of fish, caudal to the 8th somite, to the ventral surface ending at the caudal side of the  vent.

ZFA:0001463.label: melanophore stripe
ZFA:0001463.definition: Surface structure composed of an array of melanophores arranged in a stripe.  Stripes are oriented from rostral to caudal.

ZFA:0000550.label: naris
ZFA:0000550.definition: External openings to the nasal cavity.

ZFA:0000555.label: opercular flap
ZFA:0000555.definition: A large flap, covered by integument,  supported by several flat bones, actuated by muscles, found on the side of the head covering the gill chambers.

ZFA:0000066.label: proctodeum
ZFA:0000066.definition: An inward fold on the surface of the embryonic ectoderm that develops into part of the anal passage.

ZFA:0000277.label: scale
ZFA:0000277.definition: Dermal bone that is thin, flexible, and platelike, and that develops in overlapping skinfolds that cover the body and often the head of fish and the bases of the fins.

ZFA:0001290.label: stomodeum
ZFA:0001290.definition: Anterior part of the embryonic alimentary canal formed as an invagination of the ectoderm; the future mouth.

ZFA:0001118.label: urogenital papilla
ZFA:0001118.definition: A protuberance in front of the gential pore and behind the vent. Mature females have a well developed urogenital papillae whilst in mature males it is poorly developed.

ZFA:0000298.label: vent
ZFA:0000298.definition: Is a surface structure and is the external opening of the cloaca.

ZFA:0005653.label: vagal sensory zone
ZFA:0005653.definition: Portion of tissue in the vagal lobe that contains GABAergic sensory interneurons.

ZFA:0001123.label: axial fin skeleton
ZFA:0001123.definition: Postcranial axial skeleton that is unpaired and located on the sagittal plane of the organism.

ZFA:0000618.label: ansulate commissure
ZFA:0000618.definition: Brainstem commissure located immediately rostral to the interpeduncular nucleus. Many fibers in the tecto-bulbar tract cross the midline through the ansulate commissure. Referred to as the ventral tegmental commissure at embryonic stages, and is the only commissure to change names during development. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000626.label: bulbo-spinal tract
ZFA:0000626.definition: Brainstem and spinal tract which emerges medial to the caudal intermediate reticular formation and runs caudally along the medial edge of the inferior reticular formation. It is displaced laterally and associates with other tracts in the dorsal part of the funiculus lateralis immediately prior to reaching the spinal cord. The bulbo-spinal tract carries descending spinal projections. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000642.label: decussation of the medial octavolateralis nucleus

ZFA:0000534.label: lateral longitudinal fasciculus
ZFA:0000534.definition: The lateral longitudinal fascicule is an ascending bundle of axons. The LLF contains fibers of the auditory and mechanosensory systems which originate in the primary sensory brainstem nuclei and terminate in the torus semicircularis.   The LLF lies dorsal to the superior reticular formation, adjacent to the ventral rhombencephalic commissure.  The LLF becomes displaced more laterally as it approaches the torus semicircularis.  The LLF is homologous to the mammalian lateral lemniscus.

ZFA:0000543.label: medial longitudinal fasciculus
ZFA:0000543.definition: The medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF) is a pair of crossed fiber tracts (group of axons), that begin with in the nucleus of the MLF and run ventral to the rhombencephalic ventricle, towards the caudal end of the medulla oblongata.  The dorsal portion of the MLF including the Mauthner axon continues into the spinal chord while the ventral portion of the MLF associates with other fiber systems in the funiculus ventralis prior to reaching the spinal chord.  Throughout the most of its rhombencephalic extent the MLF is intersected by the ventral rhombencephalic commissure.

ZFA:0000607.label: ventral rhombencephalic commissure
ZFA:0000607.definition: Brainstem commissure that intersects the medial longitudinal fasciculus.

ZFA:0000734.label: preural vertebra
ZFA:0000734.definition: Vertebra which are the three most posterior vertebra supporting the caudal fin.

ZFA:0007098.label: vertebra 15
ZFA:0007098.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 14.

ZFA:0007099.label: vertebra 16
ZFA:0007099.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 15.

ZFA:0007100.label: vertebra 17
ZFA:0007100.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 16.

ZFA:0007101.label: vertebra 18
ZFA:0007101.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 17.

ZFA:0007102.label: vertebra 19
ZFA:0007102.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 18.

ZFA:0007103.label: vertebra 20
ZFA:0007103.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 19.

ZFA:0007104.label: vertebra 21
ZFA:0007104.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 20.

ZFA:0007105.label: vertebra 22
ZFA:0007105.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 21.

ZFA:0007106.label: vertebra 23
ZFA:0007106.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 22.

ZFA:0007107.label: vertebra 24
ZFA:0007107.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 23.

ZFA:0007108.label: vertebra 25
ZFA:0007108.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 24.

ZFA:0007109.label: vertebra 26
ZFA:0007109.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 25.

ZFA:0007110.label: vertebra 27
ZFA:0007110.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 26.

ZFA:0007111.label: vertebra 28
ZFA:0007111.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 27.

ZFA:0007112.label: vertebra 29
ZFA:0007112.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 28.

ZFA:0007113.label: vertebra 30
ZFA:0007113.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 29.

ZFA:0000511.label: extraocular musculature
ZFA:0000511.definition: Muscle system surrounding the eye.  The extraocular musculature is derived from the neural crest. The extraocular muscles assume their adult configuration between 66 and 72 hpf.  They differentiate contemporaneously with the eye vesicle, form precise anatomic attachments to sclera and bone, and are innervated by cranial nerves 3, 4, and 6.

ZFA:0001307.label: pharyngeal musculature
ZFA:0001307.definition: Muscle system of the pharyngeal region.

ZFA:0000320.label: caudal commissure
ZFA:0000320.definition: Diencephalic tract which is located in the vicinity of the dorsal diencephalon and mesencephalon and connects the pretectal nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000491.label: commissure of the caudal tuberculum
ZFA:0000491.definition: Commissure in the  ventral diencephalon that lies rostral to the ventral flexure and caudal of the posterior tuberal nucleus.  Axons from the supraoptic tract extend across the hypothalamus and enter this commissure.

ZFA:0005877.label: commissure of the tract of the commissure of the caudal tuberculum
ZFA:0005877.definition: Commissure that is formed by a subset of TCPT axons that cross the midline in the diencephalon.  The TCPTc does not appear to cross with other commissures.  The initial crossing of the TCPTc occurs at approximately 36 hpf.

ZFA:0001322.label: dorsoventral diencephalic tract
ZFA:0001322.definition: A tract originating in the epiphysis and fasciculating with the tract of the postoptic commissure dorsal to the ventral flexure.

ZFA:0000353.label: fasciculus retroflexus
ZFA:0000353.definition: Paired fasciculus that connects the habenula to the interpeduncular nucleus.  In zebrafish the fascicles seem to gather under the raphe nucleus and don't extend to the medulla.

ZFA:0000379.label: lateral forebrain bundle diencephalon
ZFA:0000379.definition: Portion of the lateral forebrain bundle that lies in the diencephalon.

ZFA:0000556.label: optic chiasm
ZFA:0000556.definition: Decussation of cranial nerve II axons whereby the retinal axons cross the midline, projecting contralaterally through the optic tract.

ZFA:0000252.label: optic tract
ZFA:0000252.definition: Diencephalic white matter (tract) which is comprised of retinal ganglion cell axons after which they have passed through the optic chiasm.

ZFA:0001233.label: hypobranchial 1 bone
ZFA:0001233.definition: Hypobranchial ossifications 1-3 develop in the small hypobranchial cartilages that lie between the medial tips of the ceratobranchials and copula 1. The first and second hypobranchials are small and irregular in shape; one or both ossifications are absent in some adults.

ZFA:0001236.label: hypobranchial 2 bone
ZFA:0001236.definition: Hypobranchial ossifications 1-3 develop in the small hypobranchial cartilages that lie between the medial tips of the ceratobranchials and copula 1. The first and second hypobranchials are small and irregular in shape; one or both ossifications are absent in some adults.

ZFA:0001235.label: hypobranchial 3 bone
ZFA:0001235.definition: Hypobranchial ossifications 1-3 develop in the small hypobranchial cartilages that lie between the medial tips of the ceratobranchials and copula 1. The first and second hypobranchials are small and irregular in shape; one or both ossifications are absent in some adults.

ZFA:0001234.label: hypobranchial 4 bone
ZFA:0001234.definition: Tiny hypobranchial4 cartilages appear at anteromedial tips of ceratobranchial 4; these are not obviously present in mature specimens, due either to resorption or fusion to the cartilaginous anterior tip of ceratobranchial.

ZFA:0001560.label: hypural 1
ZFA:0001560.definition: Ventral most hypural of the caudal fin. Supports the lower lobe of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001561.label: hypural 2
ZFA:0001561.definition: Hypural of the caudal fin dorsal to hypural 1. Supports the lower lobe of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001562.label: hypural 3
ZFA:0001562.definition: Hypural dorsal to hypural 2 that supports the upper lobe of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001563.label: hypural 4
ZFA:0001563.definition: Hypural dorsal to hypural 3 that supports the upper lobe of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001564.label: hypural 5
ZFA:0001564.definition: Dorsal-most hypural, that supports the upper lobe of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005495.label: skin flap
ZFA:0005495.definition: Surface structure that is a portion of skin that projects or hangs from the body.

ZFA:0000223.label: infraorbital 1
ZFA:0000223.definition: Dermal bone that covers the region between the anterior margin of the eye and the upper jaw. Infraorbital 1 (the lachrymal) is the first and largest bone in the infraorbital series. Bears the anterior most part of the infraorbital canal.

ZFA:0001407.label: infraorbital 2
ZFA:0001407.definition: Plate like dermal bone, variable in size, though usually one of the smallest in the series. Bears 2-3 neuromast pores enclosed within the infraorbital canal (Nelson, 1969).

ZFA:0001408.label: infraorbital 3
ZFA:0001408.definition: Plate like dermal bone, variable in size, but usually largest in the series. Usually fused with IO4 (eg. Opsariichthys, Nelson (1969)). Usually bears 3 neuromast pores enclosed within the infraorbital canal (Nelson, 1969).

ZFA:0001409.label: infraorbital 4
ZFA:0001409.definition: Plate like dermal bone. Usually fused with infraorbital 3.

ZFA:0000495.label: infraorbital 5
ZFA:0000495.definition: Plate like dermal bone with usually only one neuromast pore (Nelson, 1969). The last infraorbital bone in the series is referred to as the dermosphenotic (Nelson, 1969). In basal teleosts it is usually the sixth bone in the series but in zebrafish it is the fifth bone.

ZFA:0000480.label: caudal octavolateralis nucleus
ZFA:0000480.definition: Hindbrain nucleus which is part of the medulla oblongata and is a mechanoreceptive area along with the medial octavolateralis nucleus. It is smaller than the medial octavolateralis nucleus and is located lateral to the facial and vagal lobes of the medulla oblongata. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000291.label: medial octavolateralis nucleus
ZFA:0000291.definition: Lateral line sensory nucleus located in the cerebellum that processes sensory input from the lateral line.

ZFA:0001684.label: Bowman's layer
ZFA:0001684.definition: Acellular anatomical structure that is the zone of condensed collagen fibers underneath the basement membrane of the corneal epithelium that overlays the corneal stroma layer.

ZFA:0005562.label: Bruch's membrane
ZFA:0005562.definition: Acellular anatomical structure that is the innermost layer of the optic choroid.

ZFA:0001686.label: Descemet's membrane
ZFA:0001686.definition: Acellular anatomical structure composed of collagen, Descemet's membrane is secreted as a basement membrane of the corneal endothelium.  Located between the stroma and the corneal endothelium, it is approximately 0.15 micrometer thick at 6 months post-fertilization.

ZFA:0001485.label: basal lamina
ZFA:0001485.definition: Acellular anatomical structure that consists of a thin sheet of fibrous proteins that underlie and support the cells of an epithelium. It separates the cells of an epithelium from any underlying tissue.

ZFA:0001186.label: collagenous dermal stroma
ZFA:0001186.definition: Acellular anatomical structure that is a layer of collagen fibrils in the immature integument in a subepidermal space. At first, the fibrils are all oriented in the same direction, later they form the complex plywood-like structure that is characteristic of the dermal deep region.

ZFA:0001029.label: inner limiting membrane
ZFA:0001029.definition: Membrane on the apical surface of the retina.  The retinal vasculature becomes adhered to the apical surface of the ILM by 30dpf.

ZFA:0005286.label: lamina densa
ZFA:0005286.definition: Middle layer of the glomerular basement membrane.

ZFA:0005288.label: lamina rara externa
ZFA:0005288.definition: Layer of the glomerular basement membrane adjacent to the podocytes and capsular space.

ZFA:0005287.label: lamina rara interna
ZFA:0005287.definition: Layer of the glomerular basement membrane adjacent to the glomerular capillary.

ZFA:0005574.label: lens capsule
ZFA:0005574.definition: The lens capsule is a modified basement membrane that completely surrounds the ocular lens.

ZFA:0001331.label: outer limiting membrane
ZFA:0001331.definition: Layer that separates the inner segment portions of the photo receptors from their cell nucleus.

ZFA:0005434.label: tooth cusp
ZFA:0005434.definition: Acellular anatomical structure that is a natural outgrowth, prominence, or point that is part of the surface of a tooth.

ZFA:0001111.label: zona radiata
ZFA:0001111.definition: Acellular anatomic structure that is a layer that  separates the developing oocyte and the granulosa cell layer.

ZFA:0000168.label: anterior macula
ZFA:0000168.definition: Macula that is located in the developing anterior inner ear, and gives rise to the macula utricle. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000116.label: macula lagena
ZFA:0000116.definition: Portion of tissue that is a patch of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium in the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells.  The macula lagena develops from the posterior macula. In juveniles the macula lagena lies in a vertical plane covering most of the medial wall of the lagena.

ZFA:0000234.label: macula neglecta
ZFA:0000234.definition: Portion of tissue that is a patch of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium in the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells.   The macula neglecta a pair of sensory patches positioned on the floor of the utricle adjacent to the utriculosaccular foramen at the base of the common crus.

ZFA:0007000.label: macula saccule
ZFA:0007000.definition: Portion of tissue that is a patch of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium in the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. The macula saccule senses linear acceleration and gravity.  In juveniles the macula saccule is oriented vertically in a plane running along the anterioposterior body axis.  It covers the medial wall of the saccule along most of its length.

ZFA:0000030.label: macula utricle
ZFA:0000030.definition: Portion of tissue that is a patch of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium in the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. The macula utricle senses linear acceleration and gravity.  The macula utricle covers most of the floor of the utricle.

ZFA:0000558.label: posterior macula
ZFA:0000558.definition: Macula that is located in the developing posterior inner ear, and gives rise to the macula neglecta and the macula saccule. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001695.label: dorsolateral motor nucleus of vagal nerve
ZFA:0001695.definition: Motor nucleus of vagal nerve that is located within the dorsolateral portion of rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0001696.label: medial motor nucleus of vagal nerve
ZFA:0001696.definition: Motor nucleus of vagal nerve that is located within the medial portion of rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0000113.label: head mesenchyme
ZFA:0000113.definition: Mesoderm that will give rise, along with cranial neural crest cells, to connective tissue, bone and musculature in the head.

ZFA:0000912.label: mesenchyme median fin fold
ZFA:0000912.definition: Mesenchyme part of median fin fold.

ZFA:0001000.label: mesenchyme pectoral fin
ZFA:0001000.definition: Mesenchyme that is part of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0001449.label: mesenchyme pelvic fin
ZFA:0001449.definition: Mesenchyme that is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001574.label: autonomic nervous system
ZFA:0001574.definition: Nervous system that innervates smooth muscle, cardiac muscle and glands.  Regulates involuntary process such as blood circulation and digestion.  Has subdivisions sympathetic nervous system and parasympathetic nervous system.

ZFA:0000142.label: peripheral nervous system
ZFA:0000142.definition: Nervous structures including ganglia outside of the central nervous system.

ZFA:0000274.label: rostral octaval nucleus
ZFA:0000274.definition: Octaval sensory nucleus located rostral to the magnocellular octaval nucleus and arches dorsally around the descending trigeminal root. Receives some vestibular information and is part of the vestibulo-ocular reflex circuitry and projects to abducens and oculomotor nuclei and descends to the spinal cord. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000693.label: tangential nucleus
ZFA:0000693.definition: The tangential nucleus is located in rhombomere 5 and receives a dense utricular input.   Tangential nucleus neurons project contralaterally to extraocular motoneurons and to multiple sites within the reticulospinal complex; unlike other classes of vestibular neuron, they modulate their firing in response to static head displacements.

ZFA:0000403.label: ovary
ZFA:0000403.definition: Female reproductive organ.  The ovary is a bilobed cavitated organ located ventral to the swim bladder.

ZFA:0000598.label: testis
ZFA:0000598.definition: Male reproductive organ. Adult zebrafish testes are paired organs forming elongated structures, internally organized into tubules. These tubules are formed by seminiferous epithelium containing cysts of spermatogonia and spermatocytes surrounded by somatic support cells, called Sertoli cells. Cysts are arranged around a lumen containing spermatozoa that is connected to the efferent ducts. The interstitial regions between the tubules contain the steroid-producing Leydig cells, connective tissue, and blood vessels.

ZFA:0000314.label: anterior semicircular canal
ZFA:0000314.definition: One of three fluid-filled semicircular tubes, arranged orthogonally to each other in each ear. The anterior semicircular canal is associated with the anterior crista. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for semicircular canals by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000220.label: lateral semicircular canal
ZFA:0000220.definition: One of three fluid-filled semicircular tubes, arranged orthogonally to each other in each ear. The lateral semicircular canal is associated with the lateral crista. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for semicircular canals by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000262.label: posterior semicircular canal
ZFA:0000262.definition: One of three fluid-filled semicircular tubes, arranged orthogonally to each other in each ear. The posterior semicircular canal is associated with the posterior crista. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for semicircular canals by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000222.label: isthmic primary nucleus
ZFA:0000222.definition: Sensory trigeminal nucleus located in the most rostral position.  It lies immediately caudal to the secondary gustatory nucleus.

ZFA:0000997.label: medial funicular nucleus trigeminal nucleus
ZFA:0000997.definition: Sensory trigeminal nucleus located at the end of the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0000312.label: mesencephalic nucleus of trigeminal nerve
ZFA:0000312.definition: Sensory trigeminal nucleus located at the tectal ventricle near the synencephalon and optic tectum  that contains large pyriform neurons.  The sensory fibers of the large pyriform neurons that run peripherally in the trigeminal nerve.

ZFA:0000245.label: nucleus of the descending root
ZFA:0000245.definition: Sensory trigeminal nucleus that lies at the mediodorsal edge of the descending trigeminal root (DV).  This nucleus is not clearly delineated.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: sensory nucleus of the descending trigeminal root

ZFA:0000399.label: secondary gustatory nucleus trigeminal nucleus
ZFA:0000399.definition: Nucleus that lies rostral to the isthmic primary nucleus.

ZFA:0000737.label: cranium
ZFA:0000737.definition: Skeletal system that is part of the head, including the splanchnocranium, chondrocranium, and dermatocranium.

ZFA:0000317.label: postcranial axial skeleton
ZFA:0000317.definition: The post-cranial structural components forming the long axis of the vertebrate body; in Danio, consisting of the notochord, vertebrae, ribs, supraneurals, intermuscular bones, and unpaired median fins.

ZFA:0001397.label: post-Weberian supraneural
ZFA:0001397.definition: Posterior to the Weberian apparatus, otophysan supraneurals form as median, unpaired, rod- or platelike elements, as in other actinopterygians. Supraneural 4 has been lost in zebrafish.

ZFA:0001191.label: supraneural 2
ZFA:0001191.definition: Supraneural 2 is an ovoid cartilage or cartilage replacement bone located above centrum 2. It forms an immovable joint with supraneural 3 and contributes to the neural complex roofing the neural canal.

ZFA:0001192.label: supraneural 3
ZFA:0001192.definition: Supraneural 3 is an elongated cartilage or cartilage replacement bone above vertebrae 3 and 4, developmentally fusing with NA 3 and 4. A crest or blade of membrane bone forms from its dorsal surface.

ZFA:0005158.label: tela chorioidea fourth ventricle
ZFA:0005158.definition: Tela chorioidea that lines the fourth ventricle.

ZFA:0005157.label: tela chorioidea tectal ventricle
ZFA:0005157.definition: Tela chorioidea that lines the tectal ventricle.

ZFA:0005160.label: tela chorioidea telencephalic ventricle
ZFA:0005160.definition: Tela chorioidea that lines the telencephalic ventricle.

ZFA:0005159.label: tela chorioidea third ventricle
ZFA:0005159.definition: Tela chorioidea that lines the third ventricle.

ZFA:0001592.label: claustrum bone
ZFA:0001592.definition: Bone that is bilaterally paired endochondral bone with extensions of membrane bone forming part of a dorsolateral protective wall around the neural canal between the back of the skull and the beginning of the neural arch series. The first Weberian ossicle. Most recently, de Pinna and Grande (2003) have proposed the claustrum is homologous to the accessory neural arch of lower teleosts.

ZFA:0001327.label: abdominal musculature
ZFA:0001327.definition: Trunk musculature that is located in ventral wall of abdomen.

ZFA:0001279.label: branchiostegal ray 1
ZFA:0001279.definition: Branchiostegal ray that is the most anterior ray which ossifies last (5.5 mm NL).

ZFA:0001281.label: branchiostegal ray 2
ZFA:0001281.definition: Branchiostegal ray 2 is between rays 1 and 3 and ossifies second.

ZFA:0001280.label: branchiostegal ray 3
ZFA:0001280.definition: Branchiostegal ray that is the most posterior ray which ossifies first (3.4 mm NL).

ZFA:0001237.label: ceratobranchial 1 bone
ZFA:0001237.definition: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 1 cartilage or bone and medially with the cartilage between the basibranchials. Gill rakers are present on the anterior and posterior margins.

ZFA:0001242.label: ceratobranchial 2 bone
ZFA:0001242.definition: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 2 cartilage or bone and medially with the cartilage between the basibranchials. Gill rakers are present on the anterior and posterior margins.

ZFA:0001241.label: ceratobranchial 3 bone
ZFA:0001241.definition: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone and medially with the cartilage between the basibranchials. Gill rakers are present on the anterior and posterior margins.

ZFA:0001240.label: ceratobranchial 4 bone
ZFA:0001240.definition: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone and medially with copula 2. Gill rakers are present on the anterior and posterior margins.

ZFA:0001239.label: ceratobranchial 5 bone
ZFA:0001239.definition: Ceratobranchial bone that is the most posterior, bilaterally paired ventral pharyngeal arch bone. Ceratobranchial 5 ossifies before ceratobranchials 1-4.  In the adult, ceratobranchial 5 is heavily ossified and crescent-shaped with two to three rows of posteromedially directed teeth. The anteroventral tips of ceratobranchials 5 meet medially and are ligamentously joined.

ZFA:0001490.label: cavitated compound organ
ZFA:0001490.definition: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

ZFA:0000208.label: gall bladder
ZFA:0000208.definition: The compound organ that stores bile.

ZFA:0000354.label: gill
ZFA:0000354.definition: Compound organ that consists of gill filaments, gill lamellae, gill rakers and pharyngeal arches 3-7. The gills are responsible for primary gas exchange between the blood and the surrounding water.

ZFA:0000669.label: head kidney
ZFA:0000669.definition: The zebrafish head kidney consists of fused bilateral lobes located in the anterior part of the kidney.  It is analogous to the mammalian bone marrow and the primary site of definitive hematopoiesis.

ZFA:0000118.label: hypophysis
ZFA:0000118.definition: A compound organ which is an endocrine gland located ventral to the diencephalon and derived from mixed neuroectodermal and non-neuroectodermal origin.

ZFA:0000140.label: pancreas
ZFA:0000140.definition: The pancreas is an organ composed of endocrine and exocrine glandular tissue that produce hormones and digestive enzymes.  Unlike in other studied vertebrates the pancreas in zebrafish develops from two buds, one anterior  and one posterior. In adult fish the main pancreas is located on the right side attached to the lateral aspect of the intestine by the pancreatic duct. Typically, one large islet and 3-6 smaller islets occupy the main pancreas. The tail of the pancreas is embedded with single beta cells or clusters of small islets and extends caudally along the right side of the intestine.

ZFA:0001360.label: parapineal organ
ZFA:0001360.definition: An unpaired left-sided accessory organ which plays a role in establishing lateral brain left right asymmetry.

ZFA:0005494.label: skeletal element
ZFA:0005494.definition: Organ entity that is typically involved in mechanical support and may have different skeletal tissue compositions at different stages.

ZFA:0001491.label: solid compound organ
ZFA:0001491.definition: Compound organ that does not contain macroscopic anatomical spaces.

ZFA:0000436.label: spleen
ZFA:0000436.definition: Organ that filters the blood removing defective blood cells.  The spleen is a dark red organ, located in the peritoneal cavity, adjacent to one of the liver lobes. The spleen consists of red pulp composed of erythrocytes and thrombocytes and white pulp, composed of macrophages, reticular cells and reticulin fibers.

ZFA:0001078.label: thymus
ZFA:0001078.definition: Paired organ where maturation of T-lymphocytes occurs. The adult thymus located on the dorsomedial aspect of the branchial cavity above the third pharyngeal cartilage.  The thymus undergoes a period of rapid growth beginning at about the third week and continuing for several more weeks. Accompanying this growth is a dramatic change in the shape of the thymus. It is ovoid initially and then starts to grow dorsally along the skull, forming a characteristic protrusion. During this growth period the adult pattern of rag1-positive cortex and rag1-negative medulla becomes established. The  protrusions diminish with age and the thymus gradually shrinks; at two years, the thymus is again confined to the pharynx with minimal if any protrusion.

ZFA:0001417.label: pelvic radial 1
ZFA:0001417.definition: First radial of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001415.label: pelvic radial 2
ZFA:0001415.definition: Second radial of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001416.label: pelvic radial 3
ZFA:0001416.definition: Third radial of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0000462.label: abductor hyohyoid
ZFA:0000462.definition: Hyoid muscle that originates at the first branchiostegal ray and inserts in the mesial aponeurosis, meeting its contralateral counterpart.  The abductor hyohyoid is responsible for expansion of the branchiostegal membrane.

ZFA:0000615.label: adductor arcus palatini
ZFA:0000615.definition: Hyoid muscle that originates at the parasphenoid and inserts into the mesial sides of the hyomandibula, metapterygoid and entopterygoid.  The Adductor arcus palatini is responsible for suspensorial adduction.

ZFA:0000715.label: adductor hyohyoid
ZFA:0000715.definition: Hyoid muscle that originates at the opercle and subopercle and inserts into the branchiostegal rays.  The adductor hyohyoid is responsible for constriction of the branchiostegal membrane.

ZFA:0007053.label: adductor hyomandibulae
ZFA:0007053.definition: Is a dorsal, paired hyoid muscle that attaches to the dorsomedial faces of the hyosymplectics.

ZFA:0000465.label: adductor operculi
ZFA:0000465.definition: Is a dorsal, paired hyoid muscle that moves the auditory capsules with the opercles.

ZFA:0007052.label: hyohyoideus
ZFA:0007052.definition: Is a ventral,paired hyoid muscle that inserts at the most anterior basibranchial and also at the posterior ends of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw closure.

ZFA:0000522.label: inferior hyohyoid
ZFA:0000522.definition: Hyoid muscle that originates at the anterior ceratohyals and inserts into the mesial aponeurosis, meeting its contralateral counterpart.  The inferior hyohyoid is responsible for adduction of the hyoid arch.

ZFA:0007051.label: interhyoideus
ZFA:0007051.definition: Is a ventral paired hyoid muscle that has attachment sites on the basihyal and the posterior end of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw opening.

ZFA:0000537.label: levator operculi
ZFA:0000537.definition: Hyoid muscle that originates at the ventrolateral margin of the pterotic and inserts in the dorsomesial edge of the opercle.  The levator operculi is responsible for jaw depression, its force of contraction is transmitted through the opercular series and the interoperculo-mandibular ligament to the lower jaw.

ZFA:0000612.label: protractor hyoidei
ZFA:0000612.definition: Muscle located on ventral side of the head, linking the ventral hyoid arch to the dentary. Innervated by ramus mandibularis V and ramus hyoides VII.  Formed by the intermandibularis posterior and ventral interhyoideus.

ZFA:0000507.label: epineural
ZFA:0000507.definition: Some or all epineural bones ossify free from the neural arches in most teleosts. In some lower teleosts, e.g. Leptolepis, Hiodon, elopiforms and albuliforms, ossification proceeds from the attachment point of the ligament to the arch, and the epineural is a process of the neural arch. In many lower teleosts epineurals are forked proximally.

ZFA:0000350.label: epipleural
ZFA:0000350.definition: Epipleurals lie below the horizontal septum and are posteroventrally directed. There are ossified epipleurals in certain ostariophysans. In many lower elopocephalan teleosts including ostariophysans the epipleural bones develop an anterodorsal branch so that they are forked proximally.

ZFA:0001250.label: pharyngobranchial 2 bone
ZFA:0001250.definition: Pharyngobranchial 2 (misidentified as pharyngobranchial 1 in Cubbage & Mabee, 1993 and Mayden 1989) is present and separate from pharyngobranchial 3.  It (8.0 mm) ossifies after pharyngobranchial 3. In the adult, the cartilaginous anterior end of the ossified pharyngobranchial 2 articulates with the cartilaginous medial tip of epibranchial 1. It articulates anterolaterally and posterolaterally with the anterior and posterior cartilaginous tips of epibranchial2.  In Cyprinidae pb3 overlaps pb2 (Siebert, 1987; Cavender & Coburn, 1992) but does not fuse to it.

ZFA:0001252.label: pharyngobranchial 3 bone
ZFA:0001252.definition: Pharyngobranchial bone of the fifth pharyngeal arch that lies approximately posteromedial to epibranchial 2 and medial to epibranchial 3.

ZFA:0005538.label: rib of vertebra 1
ZFA:0005538.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the first centrum.

ZFA:0005539.label: rib of vertebra 2
ZFA:0005539.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the second centrum.

ZFA:0005540.label: rib of vertebra 3
ZFA:0005540.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the third centrum.

ZFA:0005541.label: rib of vertebra 4
ZFA:0005541.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fourth centrum.

ZFA:0005542.label: rib of vertebra 5
ZFA:0005542.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fifth centrum.

ZFA:0005543.label: rib of vertebra 6
ZFA:0005543.definition: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the sixth centrum.

ZFA:0000328.label: cephalic musculature
ZFA:0000328.definition: Musculature system of the pharyngeal and head regions.

ZFA:0001427.label: anterior naris
ZFA:0001427.definition: Nares that form at 40-44dpf that open to the anterior region of the olfactory pit allowing water to enter the pit.

ZFA:0001426.label: posterior naris
ZFA:0001426.definition: Nares that form at 40-44dpf that open to the posterior region of the olfactory pit allowing water to exit the pit.

ZFA:0001108.label: anterior commissure
ZFA:0001108.definition: Telencephalic white matter (commissure) which connects the two cerebral hemispheres across the midline.

ZFA:0000779.label: lateral forebrain bundle telencephalon
ZFA:0000779.definition: Portion of the lateral forebrain bundle that lies in the telencephalon.

ZFA:0000229.label: lateral olfactory tract
ZFA:0000229.definition: Telencephalic white matter which extends between the olfactory bulb and the ipsilateral dorsal telencephalon and carries secondary olfactory fibers. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000238.label: medial olfactory tract
ZFA:0000238.definition: Telencephalic white matter which extends between the olfactory bulb and the ipsilateral ventral telencephalon and carries secondary olfactory fibers. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005407.label: anterior nasal barbel
ZFA:0005407.definition: Barbel that is associated with the anterior nostril. Anterior nasal barbel is paired.

ZFA:0005408.label: maxillary barbel
ZFA:0005408.definition: Barbel that is attached to the distal end of the maxilla and that originates on the side of the mouth. Maxillary barbel is paired. Maxillary barbel has considerable range of motion, with contraction and protraction motivated by maxillary blood sinus. The maxillary barbel integument has taste buds. Capable of regeneration.

ZFA:0005433.label: mental barbel
ZFA:0005433.definition: Barbel that originates on the chin.

ZFA:0005819.label: deep caudal fin musculature
ZFA:0005819.definition: The layer of caudal fin musculature immediately under the superficial caudal fin musculature that originate from the vertebral column and insert at the base of caudal fin rays.  The three most caudal vertebrae and the hypurals serve as attachment sites for these muscles.

ZFA:0005818.label: superficial caudal fin musculature
ZFA:0005818.definition: The layer of caudal fin musculature immediately under the integument that originate from the vertebral column and insert at the base of caudal fin rays.

ZFA:0000425.label: anterior lateral line nerve
ZFA:0000425.definition: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VI and VII and projects to a dorsal medullary area between cerebellum and vagal lobe. Contains afferents and sensory efferents to the anterior lateral line ganglia. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000435.label: cranial nerve II
ZFA:0000435.definition: Cranial nerve which is comprised of retinal ganglion cell axons running posterior medially towards the optic chiasm, at which the axons cross the midline and after which the structure is termed the optic tract.

ZFA:0000405.label: cranial nerve III
ZFA:0000405.definition: Cranial nerve which innervates muscles of the ocular motor system. The oculomotor nerve innervates the inferior oblique, inferior rectus, medial rectus and superior rectus extraocular muscles.

ZFA:0000600.label: cranial nerve IV
ZFA:0000600.definition: Cranial nerve that innervates the oculomotor system. The trochlear nerve is the only motor nerve to project dorsally and then cross the midline before exiting the neuroepithelium and re-orienting ventrally to project to the contralateral superior oblique extraocular muscle.

ZFA:0000668.label: cranial nerve IX
ZFA:0000668.definition: Cranial nerve that innervates gill muscles.

ZFA:0000697.label: cranial nerve V
ZFA:0000697.definition: Cranial nerve which exits the medulla oblongata and carries both sensory and motor axons to and from the facial region.

ZFA:0000310.label: cranial nerve VI
ZFA:0000310.definition: Cranial nerve which exits the medulla oblongata and controls the lateral movement of the eye. The caudal and rostral roots fuse together and course rostrally once they are outside the brainstem. The abducens nerve innervates the lateral rectus extraocular muscle.

ZFA:0000664.label: cranial nerve VII
ZFA:0000664.definition: Cranial nerve where motor axons innervate muscles derived from the second branchial arch. The motor neurons are generated in rhombomere 4.

ZFA:0000453.label: cranial nerve X
ZFA:0000453.definition: Cranial nerve that innervates gill muscles.

ZFA:0000175.label: posterior lateral line nerve
ZFA:0000175.definition: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VIII and IX; contains afferents and sensory efferents to the posterior lateral line ganglion and middle ganglion. Fibers from the posterior lateral line ganglion innervate the occipital dorsal lateral line and trunk lateral lines.

ZFA:0001356.label: terminal nerve
ZFA:0001356.definition: The terminal nerve, located anterior to cranial nerve I, is comprised of a group of cells with somata adjacent to the olfactory bulb and processes that extend anteriorly to the olfactory epithelium and posteriorly to the telencephalon. In teleost fish an additional group of axons extends along the optic tract and delivers putative neuromodulators to the retina.  It is thought to develop from cranial neural crest.

ZFA:0001243.label: epibranchial 1 bone
ZFA:0001243.definition: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone. The narrowed medial end of epibranchial 1 articulates through cartilage with pharyngobranchial 1.

ZFA:0001246.label: epibranchial 2 bone
ZFA:0001246.definition: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone. The flared medial end of epibranchial 2 articulates with bifurcate lateral projections from pharyngobranchial 1.

ZFA:0001247.label: epibranchial 3 bone
ZFA:0001247.definition: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone. The flared medial end of epibranchial3 articulates with the posterolateral edge of pharyngobranchial2 + 3.

ZFA:0001245.label: epibranchial 4 bone
ZFA:0001245.definition: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone. The narrow end of epibranchial 4 is slightly flared, and it articulates with cartilaginous pharyngobranchial 4.

ZFA:0005770.label: crypt neuron olfactory support cell
ZFA:0005770.definition: Specialized olfactory support cell that surrounds crypt olfactory sensory neurons.   There are one or two support cells for each crypt neuron.  The cytoplasm of crypt neuron olfactory support cells is less electron dense then other support cells.  They also bear numerous microvilli at their apical rim. When two supporting cells are present, they interdigitate with each other  Mitochondria in crypt supporting cells are larger than those in the common supporting cells.

ZFA:0005849.label: ceratobranchial 5 replacement  tooth
ZFA:0005849.definition: Is a multi-tissue structure composed of dentine, enameloid and tooth pulp that develops from the dental organ.  These structures successively replace the primary  ceratobranchial teeth.

ZFA:0000629.label: caudal motor nucleus
ZFA:0000629.definition: Abducens motor nucleus which is located at the level of the intermediate reticular formation.

ZFA:0000654.label: rostral motor nucleus
ZFA:0000654.definition: Abducens motor nucleus which is located at the level of the superior reticular formation.

ZFA:0000557.label: preural 1 vertebra
ZFA:0000557.definition: Vertebra anterior to the urostyle; sometimes termed the 'penultimate' vertebra.

ZFA:0000586.label: preural 2 vertebra
ZFA:0000586.definition: Vertebra anterior to preural centrum 1; sometimes termed the 'antepenultimate' vertebra.

ZFA:0005247.label: CiA
ZFA:0005247.definition: Interneurons of the spinal cord that arise from the V1 proliferation domain.  The CiA neurons inhibit motoneurons, other ventral interneurons and also inhibit dorsal sensory neurons involved in sensory gating,.  CiA have ipsilateral axonal projections in both motor and sensory regions of spinal cord.

ZFA:0005233.label: CiD
ZFA:0005233.definition: A interneuron of the spinal cord with an ipsilateral axon that extends ventral to the Mauthner axon then turns dorsally  and caudally and sometimes has a minor ascending branch.

ZFA:0005234.label: CoLA
ZFA:0005234.definition: A spinal interneuron with a dorsal dendrite that extends caudally. CoLA also has  midlateral process that extend rostrally and caudally, the axon crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner cell and ascends, extending dorsally.  Axon has minor descending branch.

ZFA:0005175.label: CoPA
ZFA:0005175.definition: An interneuron in the spinal cord.  CoPA are bipolar with "T" shaped dorsal dendrites, have contralateral longitudinal axons that crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner neuron and ascends in the dorsal cord.

ZFA:0005176.label: CoSA
ZFA:0005176.definition: An interneuron of the spinal cord. CoSA,  have contralateral longitudinal axons that crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner neuron and ascends in the dorsal cord.

ZFA:0005178.label: DoLA
ZFA:0005178.definition: An interneuron of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0005240.label: Kolmer-Agduhr neuron
ZFA:0005240.definition: Kolmer-Agduhr neurons are ciliated GABAergic neurons that contact the central canal of the spinal cord and have ipsilateral ascending axons.

ZFA:0005232.label: MCoD
ZFA:0005232.definition: A multipolar  interneuron with branching dendrites.  The axon extend ventrally, lateral to the Mauthner axons before crossing the cord and descending ventrally.

ZFA:0005235.label: UCoD
ZFA:0005235.definition: A unipolar spinal interneuron that forms dendritic trunk laterally with extensive dendritic branching.  The axon extends ventrally, lateral to the Mauthner axons before crssoing the cord and descending ventrally.

ZFA:0005177.label: VeLD
ZFA:0005177.definition: An interneuron of the spinal cord. VeLD neurons have an ipsilateral longitudinal axon.

ZFA:0005231.label: bifurcate interneuron
ZFA:0005231.definition: Is a spinal interneuron that has an axon that splits into roughly equal size branches.

ZFA:0000364.label: hypural
ZFA:0000364.definition: Expanded and laterally flattened hemal arches and spines. They support the lepidotrichia of the caudal fin. The hypurals form ventral to the posterior tip of the dorsally-flexed notochord. In zebrafish condensation of the hypurals begins at approximately 6 dpf (4.1 mm NL, notochord length).

ZFA:0001028.label: hypurapophysis
ZFA:0001028.definition: The paired bony lateral extensions off the parhypural.

ZFA:0000438.label: parhypural
ZFA:0000438.definition: Hemal arch and spine of preural centrum 1. The parhypural is defined as the most posterior hemal arch with an open canal through which the dorsal aorta passes.

ZFA:0005372.definition: First distal radial of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0007093.label: migratory trunk neural crest
ZFA:0007093.definition: Migratory trunk neural crest population that develops from premigratory trunk neural crest. This group of neural crest has undergone ectomesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0007092.label: premigratory trunk neural crest
ZFA:0007092.definition: Premigratory trunk neural crest population that develops from the neural plate border. The cells of this group will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delaminate to produce the migratory trunk neural crest.

ZFA:0000525.label: intercalarium
ZFA:0000525.definition: Third Weberian ossicle. The intercalarium is a Y- or T-shaped modification of neural arch 2 in which an anteriolateral process (the manubrium) is embedded in the interossicular ligament; other parts include the ascending and articulating processes.

ZFA:0001394.label: neural arch 3
ZFA:0001394.definition: Neural arch 3 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of a neural complex roofing and protecting the neural canal.

ZFA:0001395.label: neural arch 4
ZFA:0001395.definition: Neural arch 4 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of the neural complex. A reduced neural spine projects from the posterior margin of the neural complex.

ZFA:0001641.label: rudimentary neural arch
ZFA:0001641.definition: Neural arch on the urostyle. It does not support a neural spine. Sanger and McCune 2002.

ZFA:0000429.label: scaphium
ZFA:0000429.definition: The scaphium is a modification of NA 1 in which the neural arch is reduced and fused to a cup-shaped ossification of membrane bone, the concha. The second Weberian ossicle, consisting of three parts: the concha, the ascending process, and the articulating process.

ZFA:0000602.label: uroneural
ZFA:0000602.definition: Neural arch that extends along the dorso-lateral surface of the last preural centra and/or ural centra and the notochord (Arratia & Schultze, 1992). An uroneural develops as a modification of the neural arch of an ural centrum (Patterson, 1968). The series of uroneurals may include from 7 to 1 elements that are numbered from rostral to caudal. An uroneural is a paired membrane bone.

ZFA:0005295.label: axial blood vessel
ZFA:0005295.definition: Blood vessel that runs along the rostral-caudal axis of the fish.

ZFA:0005296.label: axial lymph vessel
ZFA:0005296.definition: Lymph vessel that runs along the rostral-caudal axis of the fish.

ZFA:0000096.label: cardinal system
ZFA:0000096.definition: Blood vasculature comprised of the cardinal veins.

ZFA:0005568.label: iris blood vessels
ZFA:0005568.definition: Blood vessels within the stroma of the iris.  The vessels cluster  and are more dense at the base of the stroma where the iris is thicker.

ZFA:0000671.label: horizontal myoseptum
ZFA:0000671.definition: A connective tissue partition developing at the apex of the chevron-shaped myotome and separating dorsal (epaxial) and ventral (hypaxial) body wall muscle masses.

ZFA:0000610.label: vertical myoseptum
ZFA:0000610.definition: Connective tissue partitions developing between the myotomes.

ZFA:0000303.label: female organism
ZFA:0000303.definition: Gonochoristic organism that can produce female gametes.

ZFA:0000242.label: male organism
ZFA:0000242.definition: Gonochoristic organism that can produce male gametes.

ZFA:0000000.label: Brachet's cleft
ZFA:0000000.definition: The visible division between epiblast and hypoblast in the gastrula.

ZFA:0000711.label: DEL
ZFA:0000711.definition: A multilayer of deep cells of fairly uniform thickness that forms during early epiboly (at dome stage; upon conversion of the blastodisc to the blastoderm); during gastrulation the DEL (deep cell layer) gives rise to the epiblast and hypoblast.

ZFA:0000086.label: EVL
ZFA:0000086.definition: Outermost monolayer of cells surrounding the embryo that become very flattened in the blastula and give rise to the periderm. Sometimes used synonymously with periderm.

ZFA:0000001.label: Kupffer's vesicle
ZFA:0000001.definition: Small but distinctive epithelial sac containing fluid, located midventrally posterior to the yolk cell or its extension, and transiently present during most of the segmentation period. Kupffer's vesicle has been compared to the mouse embryonic node.

ZFA:0001176.label: blastoderm
ZFA:0001176.definition: Embryonic structure that is composed of the cellular part of the embryo, excluding the yolk cell, derived from the blastodisc by early morphogenesis; refers particularly to the time when the cell array is sheet-like, between 30%-epiboly and the end of gastrulation.

ZFA:0001175.label: blastodisc
ZFA:0001175.definition: Embryonic structure that is the dome of cytoplasm that segregates from the yolk toward the animal pole during and after the one cell-stage, and which undergoes cleavage.

ZFA:0000018.label: epiblast
ZFA:0000018.definition: The outer of the two layers of the blastoderm that form during gastrulation, corresponding to primitive ectoderm during gastrulation and to the definitive ectoderm after gastrulation.

ZFA:0000023.label: forerunner cell group
ZFA:0000023.definition: A group of cells that migrate at the leading edge of shield during gastrulation but do not involute. At the end of gastrulation, forerunner cells migrate deep into the embryo and organize to form Kupffer's vesicle.

ZFA:0000111.label: germ ring
ZFA:0000111.definition: Embryonic structure that forms as a thickened annulus at the blastoderm rim.  The germ ring is thickened because it  is the involuting margin of the blastoderm.

ZFA:0000026.label: hatching gland
ZFA:0000026.definition: A transversely oriented set of cells located deep to the EVL on the pericardial membrane, especially prominent during pharyngula period because of the brightly refractile cytoplasmic granules (containing hatching enzymes) of the principal cells of the gland.

ZFA:0000117.label: hypoblast
ZFA:0000117.definition: The inner of the two layers of the blastoderm that forms during gastrulation and give rise to the definitive mesoderm and endoderm.

ZFA:0000124.label: liver primordium
ZFA:0000124.definition: Embryonic primordium that develops into the liver.

ZFA:0000038.label: margin
ZFA:0000038.definition: Embryonic structure, the edge of the blastoderm.

ZFA:0001309.label: neurogenic placode
ZFA:0001309.definition: Neurogenic placodes are transient ectodermal thickenings that form at the border of the neural plate and epidermis and give rise to sensory neurons of the cranial ganglia.

ZFA:0000051.label: otic vesicle
ZFA:0000051.definition: Epithelial sac present beside the fifth rhombomere; forms the semicircular canals dorsally and the otolith organs ventrally, and houses the acoustico-vestibular sensory epithelia (maculae) of hair cells. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000254.label: pancreas primordium
ZFA:0000254.definition: Embryonic structure that develops into the pancreatic bud.

ZFA:0001390.label: pancreatic bud
ZFA:0001390.definition: Embryonic structure that develops from the pancreas primordium and develops into the pancreas.

ZFA:0001453.label: pectoral fin field
ZFA:0001453.definition: Embryonic region that develops into the pectoral fin bud.

ZFA:0000058.label: polster
ZFA:0000058.definition: The hatching gland rudiment at the time it underlies the forebrain during the early segmentation period.

ZFA:0000146.label: presumptive brain
ZFA:0000146.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the brain.

ZFA:0000414.label: presumptive cephalic mesoderm
ZFA:0000414.definition: Embryonic structure that is fated to become cephalic mesoderm.

ZFA:0000574.label: presumptive diencephalon
ZFA:0000574.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the diencephalon.

ZFA:0001218.label: presumptive floor plate
ZFA:0001218.definition: Embryonic structure, the part of the neural plate fated to become floor plate.

ZFA:0000062.label: presumptive forebrain
ZFA:0000062.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the forebrain.

ZFA:0001368.label: presumptive forebrain midbrain boundary
ZFA:0001368.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the forebrain midbrain boundary.

ZFA:0000569.label: presumptive hindbrain
ZFA:0000569.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the hindbrain.

ZFA:0001342.label: presumptive intervening zone
ZFA:0001342.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the intervening zone.

ZFA:0005911.label: presumptive lateral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0005911.definition: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the lateral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon.  The area sometimes called M4 does not express GABA or dlx2a.

ZFA:0000148.label: presumptive midbrain
ZFA:0000148.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the midbrain.

ZFA:0001187.label: presumptive midbrain hindbrain boundary
ZFA:0001187.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary.

ZFA:0005909.label: presumptive preglomerular region
ZFA:0005909.definition: Region that gives rise to various caudal tubercular structures in the preglomerular region This region is non ventricular neural proliferation zone and doesn't express GABA.

ZFA:0005908.label: presumptive pretectum proliferative zone
ZFA:0005908.definition: Region the larval brain that is a forerunner of  the adult central and superficial pretectal regions.  This region is non ventricular neural proliferation zone.

ZFA:0001207.label: presumptive rhombomere 1
ZFA:0001207.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 1.

ZFA:0001208.label: presumptive rhombomere 2
ZFA:0001208.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0001213.label: presumptive rhombomere 3
ZFA:0001213.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 3.

ZFA:0001212.label: presumptive rhombomere 4
ZFA:0001212.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 4.

ZFA:0001211.label: presumptive rhombomere 5
ZFA:0001211.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 5.

ZFA:0001210.label: presumptive rhombomere 6
ZFA:0001210.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 6.

ZFA:0001209.label: presumptive rhombomere 7
ZFA:0001209.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 7.

ZFA:0001214.label: presumptive rhombomere 8
ZFA:0001214.definition: Embryonic structure, part of the neural keel, that gives rise to rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0000053.label: presumptive segmental plate
ZFA:0000053.definition: Embryonic structure part of the mesoderm fated to become segmental plate.

ZFA:0000417.label: presumptive spinal cord
ZFA:0000417.definition: Embryonic structure part of the posterior presumptive neural plate that is fated to become the spinal cord.

ZFA:0001116.label: presumptive structure
ZFA:0001116.definition: Portion of embryonic tissue determined by fate mapping to become a structure.

ZFA:0000571.label: presumptive telencephalon
ZFA:0000571.definition: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the telencephalon.

ZFA:0005910.label: presumptive ventral entopeduncular nucleus
ZFA:0005910.definition: Portion of tissue that is presumed to give rise to the  entopenduncular nucleus.

ZFA:0000068.label: proneural cluster
ZFA:0000068.definition: Cluster of cells in the neural plate that have the potential to become neuroblast.

ZFA:0000071.label: shield
ZFA:0000071.definition: Embryonic structure that is a local accumulation of cells along the germ ring.  The shield marks the dorsal side of the embryo.

ZFA:0005335.label: swim bladder bud
ZFA:0005335.definition: Embryonic structure that forms from the anterior gut epithelium at the level of the second somite that then matures to form the swim bladder.

ZFA:0000088.label: yolk syncytial layer
ZFA:0000088.definition: Peripheral layer of the yolk cell including nuclei and non-yolky cytoplasm.

ZFA:0000638.label: commissura rostral, pars dorsalis
ZFA:0000638.definition: Anterior commissure which is located immediately ventral to the supracommissural nucleus of area ventralis telencephali. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000185.label: commissura rostral, pars ventralis
ZFA:0000185.definition: Anterior commissure which abuts the preoptic region dorsally. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001567.label: oocyte stage I
ZFA:0001567.definition: Oocyte part of stage I ovarian follicle. Stage I oocytes are basophilic, and have relatively large nuclei.

ZFA:0001565.label: oocyte stage II
ZFA:0001565.definition: Oocyte part of stage II ovarian follicle.  The stage II oocytes are characterized by the presence of cortical alveoli, a tripartite zona radiata (vitelline envelope), and a central germinal vesicle.

ZFA:0001566.label: oocyte stage III
ZFA:0001566.definition: Oocyte part of stage III ovarian follicle.  Stage III oocytes contain internal vitellus droplets and peripheral yolk vesicles.

ZFA:0001568.label: oocyte stage IV
ZFA:0001568.definition: Oocyte part of stage IV ovarian follicle. Stage IV oocytes are large and filled with noncrystalline yolky bodies.

ZFA:0001569.label: oocyte stage V
ZFA:0001569.definition: Oocyte part of stage V ovarian follicle.

ZFA:0001263.label: ovarian follicle stage I
ZFA:0001263.definition: Stage I follicles (less than 140 microns) contain a stage 1 oocyte and are in the primary growth stage.

ZFA:0001265.label: ovarian follicle stage II
ZFA:0001265.definition: Stage II follicles (140-340 microns) contain a stage 2 oocyte.

ZFA:0001266.label: ovarian follicle stage III
ZFA:0001266.definition: Stage III follicles (340-690 microns) contain a stage 3 oocyte.

ZFA:0001264.label: ovarian follicle stage IV
ZFA:0001264.definition: Stage IV follicles (690-730 microns) contain a stage 4 oocyte and are considered mature.

ZFA:0001571.label: postovulatory follicle
ZFA:0001571.definition: A follicle that has undergone ovulation and no longer contains an oocyte.

ZFA:0000568.label: presumptive blood
ZFA:0000568.definition: Presumptive structure fated to become blood. Determined by marker expression.

ZFA:0001376.label: presumptive ectoderm
ZFA:0001376.definition: Presumptive structure at the animal poll of the blastula that will develop into ectoderm via the epiblast. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0000416.label: presumptive endoderm
ZFA:0000416.definition: Presumptive structure fated to become endoderm. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0001334.label: presumptive enteric nervous system
ZFA:0001334.definition: Presumptive structure fated to become enteric nervous system.  Develops from the vagal neural crest.

ZFA:0001217.label: presumptive hypochord
ZFA:0001217.definition: Tissue along the  lateral edges of the shield that is fated to develop into the hypochord.

ZFA:0005102.label: presumptive median fin fold
ZFA:0005102.definition: Stripe of tissue fated to become the median fin fold.

ZFA:0001377.label: presumptive mesoderm
ZFA:0001377.definition: Presumptive structure fated to become mesoderm. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0000063.label: presumptive neural plate
ZFA:0000063.definition: Region of the gastrula which gives rise to the neural plate.

ZFA:0001070.label: presumptive pronephric mesoderm
ZFA:0001070.definition: Presumptive structure part of the intermediate mesoderm, that is fated to become pronephric mesoderm.

ZFA:0001121.label: presumptive shield
ZFA:0001121.definition: Presumptive structure fated to become the shield.  Defined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0005336.label: presumptive swim bladder
ZFA:0005336.definition: Portion of the gut endoderm that will eventually develop into the swim bladder.

ZFA:0000016.label: ectoderm
ZFA:0000016.definition: The outer layer of the embryo derived from the epiblast. The definitive ectoderm will give rise to such tissues as epidermis, the central nervous system, neural crest, and sensory placode.

ZFA:0000167.label: anal fin skeleton
ZFA:0000167.definition: Median fin skeleton that is located posterior to the anus.

ZFA:0000862.label: caudal fin skeleton
ZFA:0000862.definition: Median fin skeleton supporting the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001124.label: dorsal fin skeleton
ZFA:0001124.definition: Median fin skeleton located on the dorsal surface of the organism.

ZFA:0005115.label: primary posterior lateral line primordium
ZFA:0005115.definition: Primordium that forms the first neuromasts of the posterior lateral line.  This primordium travels at 1.5-1.7 somites/hour and deposits  neuromast that are polarized along the antero-posterior axis.

ZFA:0005116.label: secondary posterior lateral line primordium
ZFA:0005116.definition: Second lateral line primordium.  These primordia move at 0.2 somites/hour and deposit neuromasts that are polarized in a dorso-ventral direction.

ZFA:0007013.label: preplacodal ectoderm
ZFA:0007013.definition: Non neural ectoderm that surrounds the presumptive neural plate and gives rise to neurogenic placodes.

ZFA:0000326.label: caudal vertebra
ZFA:0000326.definition: Vertebra bearing a hemal arch and spine. The most posterior caudal vertebrae support the caudal fin and are referred to as preural vertebrae.

ZFA:0000263.label: precaudal vertebra
ZFA:0000263.definition: Post-cranial vertebrae lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal.

ZFA:0001583.label: preural centrum 1+ ural centrum 1
ZFA:0001583.definition: Vertebra which is the fused centra of preural 1 and ural 1. These elements do not develop independently in zebrafish.

ZFA:0001579.label: ural vertebra 2
ZFA:0001579.definition: Ural vertebra that is the second vertebra posterior to preural centrum 1.

ZFA:0001167.label: vertebra 1
ZFA:0001167.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to the neurocranium.

ZFA:0001168.label: vertebra 2
ZFA:0001168.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 1.

ZFA:0001169.label: vertebra 3
ZFA:0001169.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 2.

ZFA:0001170.label: vertebra 4
ZFA:0001170.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 3.

ZFA:0000762.label: facio-acoustic neural crest
ZFA:0000762.definition: Cranial neural crest that gives rise to the facio-acoustic ganglion.

ZFA:0007066.label: glossopharyngeal neural crest
ZFA:0007066.definition: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the glossopharyngeal ganglion.

ZFA:0007065.label: hyoid neural crest
ZFA:0007065.definition: Cranial neural crest that migrates into the hyoid arch.

ZFA:0007064.label: mandibular neural crest
ZFA:0007064.definition: Cranial neural crest that migrates into the mandibular arch.

ZFA:0007087.label: migratory cranial neural crest
ZFA:0007087.definition: Migratory cranial neural crest population that develops from premigratory cranial neural crest. This group of neural crest has undergone ectomesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0000811.label: neural crest diencephalon
ZFA:0000811.definition: Cranial neural crest that is part of the diencephalon.

ZFA:0007063.label: neural crest hindbrain
ZFA:0007063.definition: Cranial neural crest that is part of the hindbrain.

ZFA:0000935.label: neural crest midbrain
ZFA:0000935.definition: Neural crest that is part of the midbrain.

ZFA:0000812.label: neural crest telencephalon
ZFA:0000812.definition: Cranial neural crest that is part of the telencephalon.

ZFA:0007088.label: premigratory cranial neural crest
ZFA:0007088.definition: Premigratory cranial neural crest population that develops from the neural plate border. The cells of this group will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delaminate to produce the migratory cranial neural crest.

ZFA:0000080.label: trigeminal neural crest
ZFA:0000080.definition: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the trigeminal ganglion.

ZFA:0001221.label: copula 1
ZFA:0001221.definition: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with pharyngeal arches 3-5. A long slender cartilage extending along the midline from the posterior tip of the basihyal to between the third hypobranchials.

ZFA:0001222.label: copula 2
ZFA:0001222.definition: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with pharyngeal arches 6-7. A cartilage extending from the posterior tip of copula 1 to the anterior tips of the fifth ceratobranchials.

ZFA:0000099.label: brain vasculature
ZFA:0000099.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the brain.

ZFA:0001295.label: facial placode
ZFA:0001295.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to the facial ganglia.

ZFA:0001296.label: glossopharyngeal placode
ZFA:0001296.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to the glossopharyngeal ganglia. Associated with the third pharyngeal arch.

ZFA:0001297.label: vagal placode 1
ZFA:0001297.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to vagal ganglion 1.

ZFA:0001298.label: vagal placode 2
ZFA:0001298.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to vagal ganglion 2.

ZFA:0001299.label: vagal placode 3
ZFA:0001299.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to vagal ganglion 3.

ZFA:0001300.label: vagal placode 4
ZFA:0001300.definition: Epibranchial placode that gives rise to vagal ganglion 4.

ZFA:0001612.label: pharyngeal arch 1
ZFA:0001612.definition: The first pharyngeal arch, also known as the mandibular arch, forms the jaw. The first pharyngeal arch gives rise to elements of the jaw, with the most anteriorly positioned cranial neural crest cells contributing to mandibular arch structures, including Meckel's and palatoquadrate cartilages that constitute the lower and upper jaw respectively.

ZFA:0001611.label: pharyngeal arch 2
ZFA:0001611.definition: The second pharyngeal arch, also known as the hyoid arch, forms jaw support structures.  Anteriorly positioned cranial neural crest cells, which align with rhombomeres 4/5, contribute to the hyoid arch structures including the ceratohyla and hyosymplectic cartilages.

ZFA:0000092.label: axis
ZFA:0000092.definition: Organism subdivision running along the rostral-caudal axis of the early embryo.

ZFA:0000006.label: ball
ZFA:0000006.definition: The anterior round region of the yolk cell present after the yolk extension forms during the segmentation period.

ZFA:0000178.label: caudal peduncle
ZFA:0000178.definition: Portion of the fish's body that is posterior to the vent and anterior to the caudal fin.

ZFA:0000106.label: extension
ZFA:0000106.definition: The posterior elongated region of the yolk cell that forms during the segmentation period.

ZFA:0001114.label: head
ZFA:0001114.definition: Organism subdivision which is the part of the body which consists of the cranial and pharyngeal regions.

ZFA:0001328.label: neuromere
ZFA:0001328.definition: A metameric segment of the central nervous system.

ZFA:0001117.label: post-vent region
ZFA:0001117.definition: Organism subdivision which is the part of the body posterior to the vent which includes the anal and caudal fins.

ZFA:0005496.label: snout
