ZFA:0005496.definition: Surface structure that is the region of the head in front of and between the orbits, and above the lower jaw. Nares are located on the snout.

ZFA:0000292.label: surface structure
ZFA:0000292.definition: Organism subdivision which is the collection of anatomical structures on the body surface.

ZFA:0001115.label: trunk
ZFA:0001115.definition: Organism subdivision which is the part of the body posterior to the head and anterior to the post-vent region.

ZFA:0001310.label: dorsolateral placode
ZFA:0001310.definition: Lateral neurogenic placodes positioned dorsal of the epibranchial placodes.

ZFA:0001294.label: epibranchial placode
ZFA:0001294.definition: Neurogenic placodes that generate neurons of the distal facial, glossopharyngeal and vagal ganglia, which convey sensation from the viscera, including pharyngeal endoderm structures, to the CNS.  The epibranchial placodes are positioned ventrally to the ear and dorsally to the posterior pharyngeal pouches.

ZFA:0000048.label: olfactory placode
ZFA:0000048.definition: Neurogenic placode that gives rise to the olfactory neurons that which convey odor information to the CNS.

ZFA:0001316.label: anterior lateral line placode
ZFA:0001316.definition: Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the anterior lateral line.

ZFA:0005121.label: middle lateral line placode
ZFA:0005121.definition: Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the middle lateral line.

ZFA:0000138.label: otic placode
ZFA:0000138.definition: Primordium of the ear epithelium before it hollows into the otic vesicle, present beside the hindbrain rudiment in the mid-segmentation period. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001156.label: posterior lateral line placode
ZFA:0001156.definition: Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the posterior lateral line.

ZFA:0000162.label: trigeminal placode
ZFA:0000162.definition: The ectodermal rudiment of the trigeminal ganglion, distinguishable during much of the segmentation period.

ZFA:0001614.label: atrial endocardium
ZFA:0001614.definition: Endocardium that is part of the atrium.

ZFA:0001616.label: atrioventricular canal endocardium
ZFA:0001616.definition: Endocardium that is part of the atrioventricular canal.

ZFA:0001615.label: ventricular endocardium
ZFA:0001615.definition: Endocardium that is part of the cardiac ventricle.

ZFA:0001064.label: rhombomere
ZFA:0001064.definition: A segment of the developing hindbrain.

ZFA:0000660.label: epural
ZFA:0000660.definition: A free, modified neural spine of a preural or a ural vertebra that is placed between the last developed neural spine of a preural centrum and the dorsal axis (= anterior margin of first uroneural) of the caudal skeleton . An epural commonly supports one or more dorsal procurrent rays. An epural is an unpaired median perichondrally ossified bone.

ZFA:0001600.label: neural spine 4
ZFA:0001600.definition: Neural spine that is located on the fourth vertebra.

ZFA:0001392.label: parapophysis 1
ZFA:0001392.definition: Lateral projections from the first centrum in cyprinids, absent in catostomids, and absent in characiphysans (Fink and Fink, 1996).

ZFA:0001393.label: parapophysis 2
ZFA:0001393.definition: Lateral projection from the second centrum, absent in Siluriformes (Fink and Fink, 1996).

ZFA:0000502.label: dorsal motor nucleus trigeminal nerve
ZFA:0000502.definition: Trigeminal motor nucleus that is located dorsal to the lateral longitudinal fascicle.

ZFA:0000703.label: ventral motor nucleus trigeminal nerve
ZFA:0000703.definition: Trigeminal motor nucleus that is located at the ventrolateral edge of the lateral longitudinal fascicle.

ZFA:0000265.label: presumptive dorsal mesoderm
ZFA:0000265.definition: Portion of presumptive mesoderm fated to become dorsal mesoderm. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0000591.label: presumptive paraxial mesoderm
ZFA:0000591.definition: Portion of presumptive mesoderm fated to become paraxial mesoderm. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0001714.label: presumptive ventral mesoderm
ZFA:0001714.definition: Portion of presumptive mesoderm fated to become ventral mesoderm. Determined by fate mapping.

ZFA:0000196.label: dorsal hypohyal bone
ZFA:0000196.definition: The dorsal hypohyal is a small cartilage replacement bone ossifying from the anterodorsal ceratohyal cartilage. Ossification begins on the medial surface of the ceratohyal cartilage at a ligamentous connection to basibranchial 1 (6.8 mm).

ZFA:0000300.label: ventral hypohyal bone
ZFA:0000300.definition: The ventral hypohyal ossifies first along the anteroventral tip of the ceratohyal cartilage at the insertion of the tendon from the sternohyoideus (5.7 mm).

ZFA:0000141.label: pectoral fin bud
ZFA:0000141.definition: Fin bud that develops into the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0001384.label: pelvic fin bud
ZFA:0001384.definition: Fin bud that develops into the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001369.label: anterior pancreatic bud
ZFA:0001369.definition: Pancreatic bud that develops from a ridge on the ventral side of the intestinal bulb primordium.

ZFA:0001370.label: posterior pancreatic bud
ZFA:0001370.definition: Pancreatic bud that forms dorsal and adjacent to the developing intestine.

ZFA:0005602.label: supraneural 10
ZFA:0005602.definition: Supraneural located posterior to supraneural 9.  This supraneural does not appear in most specimens.

ZFA:0001432.label: anterior sclerotic bone
ZFA:0001432.definition: Sclerotic bone that is located anterior to the eye.

ZFA:0001433.label: posterior sclerotic bone
ZFA:0001433.definition: Sclerotic bone that is located posterior to the eye.

ZFA:0005534.label: branched dorsal fin ray
ZFA:0005534.definition: Dorsal fin ray that is distally branched.

ZFA:0005364.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 1
ZFA:0005364.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is the rostralmost pterygiophore of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005365.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 2
ZFA:0005365.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 1 of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005366.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 3
ZFA:0005366.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to pterygiophore 2 of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005367.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 4
ZFA:0005367.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 3 of the dorsal fin.  One of the two first radials to ossify.

ZFA:0005368.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 5
ZFA:0005368.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 4 of the dorsal fin. One of the two first radials to ossify.

ZFA:0005369.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 6
ZFA:0005369.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 5 of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005370.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 7
ZFA:0005370.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 6 of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005371.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore 8
ZFA:0005371.definition: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is caudal to  pterygiophore 7 of the dorsal fin. The most caudal pterygiophore of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0005535.label: branched anal fin ray
ZFA:0005535.definition: Anal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

ZFA:0005063.label: cardiac conduction system
ZFA:0005063.definition: Anatomical system located in the heart that initiates and propagates heart contraction.  The cardiac pacemaker.

ZFA:0000010.label: cardiovascular system
ZFA:0000010.definition: Anatomical system that functions in circulation and  has as its parts the heart and vasculature. The lymphatic system is considered part of the cardiovascular system.

ZFA:0000339.label: digestive system
ZFA:0000339.definition: Anatomical system that processes ingested substances.

ZFA:0001158.label: endocrine system
ZFA:0001158.definition: Anatomical system that produces, transports and secretes peptides.

ZFA:0005023.label: hematopoietic system
ZFA:0005023.definition: System responsible for generating hematopoietic cells.

ZFA:0001159.label: immune system
ZFA:0001159.definition: System that provides protection against foreign and abnormal cells and removes cellular debris.

ZFA:0005734.label: lacunocanalicular system
ZFA:0005734.definition: A system of osteocytes connected through canals within the vertebra.  Osteocytes extend processes through canals within ossified bone.  The lacunocanalicular system is poorly developed in zebrafish with most  osteocytes having one or two cytoplasmic processes.

ZFA:0000036.label: liver and biliary system
ZFA:0000036.definition: System responsible for the production and movement of bile.

ZFA:0000385.label: lymphatic system
ZFA:0000385.definition: The lymphatic system consists of blind-ended vessels, fluid and macromolecules collected  from interstitial tissue space that serve as a conduit for the development and transport of lymphoid cells.

ZFA:0000548.label: musculature system
ZFA:0000548.definition: Anatomical system consisting of the cardiac, skeletal and smooth muscles.

ZFA:0000396.label: nervous system
ZFA:0000396.definition: A regulatory system of the body that consists of neurons and neuroglial cells. The nervous system is divided into two parts, the central nervous system (CNS) and the peripheral nervous system (PNS).

ZFA:0001371.label: pancreatic system
ZFA:0001371.definition: System responsible for the production and movement of pancreatic hormones and enzymes.

ZFA:0000163.label: renal system
ZFA:0000163.definition: System that removes and collects metabolic waste from the blood while maintaining ion homeostasis.

ZFA:0000632.label: reproductive system
ZFA:0000632.definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.

ZFA:0000272.label: respiratory system
ZFA:0000272.definition: System responsible for the exchange of gases across the gill membranes.

ZFA:0000282.label: sensory system
ZFA:0000282.definition: Nervous system responsible for transmitting sensory stimuli.

ZFA:0001446.label: choroid plexus fourth ventricle
ZFA:0001446.definition: Choroid plexus that is part of the fourth ventricle.

ZFA:0001445.label: choroid plexus tectal ventricle
ZFA:0001445.definition: Choroid plexus that is part of the tectal ventricle.

ZFA:0001447.label: choroid plexus telencephalic ventricle
ZFA:0001447.definition: Choroid plexus that is part of the telencephalic ventricle.

ZFA:0001444.label: choroid plexus third ventricle
ZFA:0001444.definition: Choroid plexus that is part of the third ventricle.

ZFA:0001060.label: basidorsal
ZFA:0001060.definition: Basidorsals are bilaterally paired cartilages on the dorsolateral side of the notochord which are replaced by ossified neural arches or dorsal arcocentra. In otophysan fishes, basidorsal 1, bd2, bd3, and bd4 give rise to parts of the Weberian apparatus.

ZFA:0001361.label: basiventral
ZFA:0001361.definition: Basiventrals are bilaterally paired cartilages lateral to the notochord which are replaced by ossified parapophyses or hemal arches.

ZFA:0000637.label: claustrum cartilage
ZFA:0000637.definition: Postcranial axial cartilage and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum is bilaterally paired.

ZFA:0001172.label: roofing cartilage
ZFA:0001172.definition: Cartilaginous larval structure dorsal to the four anterior-most vertebrae, which forms the connection between neural arches and supraneurals in the Weberian apparatus.  Located dorsal to the neural tube.

ZFA:0001335.label: supradorsal
ZFA:0001335.definition: Supradorsals are small paired nodules of cartilage positioned at the distal ends of neural arches and the proximal end of neural spines (Arratia et al., 2001).

ZFA:0001539.label: basipterygium cartilage
ZFA:0001539.definition: Bilaterally paired small, rodlike cartilages on the ventral surface of the abdomen (present at 7.9 mm). Their posterior tips expand laterally, forming L-shaped cartilages. Medially, a posterior spur of cartilage develops, which will later ossify as the ischiac process (Weitzman 1962).

ZFA:0001538.label: pelvic radial cartilage
ZFA:0001538.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior edge of the basipterygium.

ZFA:0001205.label: Meckel's cartilage
ZFA:0001205.definition: Meckel's cartilage is the bilaterally paired, rod-like, cartilaginous ventral component of the lower jaw, or ventral mandibular arch. It is typically resorbed in adults.

ZFA:0001644.label: articular cartilage
ZFA:0001644.definition: Cartilage of the lower jaw that give rise to a portion of the anguloarticular compound bone.

ZFA:0001510.label: basihyal cartilage
ZFA:0001510.definition: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is median and is the anterior-most cartilage of the ventral hyoid arch. It chondrifies between the anterior tips of the ceratohyal cartilages, anterior to the first copula.

ZFA:0001516.label: ceratobranchial cartilage
ZFA:0001516.definition: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that forms the largest skeletal element of the ventral branchial arches.

ZFA:0001400.label: ceratohyal cartilage
ZFA:0001400.definition: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired and the largest cartilaginous component of the ventral hyoid arch.

ZFA:0001220.label: copula
ZFA:0001220.definition: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with more than one pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton. The copulae are the precursors of the basibranchials.

ZFA:0001527.label: epibranchial cartilage
ZFA:0001527.definition: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired small rod-like cartilage which articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

ZFA:0005390.label: gill ray
ZFA:0005390.definition: Gill ray is a slender, usually rod-like cartilage within a gill filament and ligamentously tied to its associated pharyngeal arch bone or cartilage.

ZFA:0001422.label: hyosymplectic cartilage
ZFA:0001422.definition: Bilaterally paired large cartilage that articulates with the chondrocranium dorsally, the opercle posteriorly, and the palatoquadrate cartilage anteriorly.

ZFA:0001522.label: hypobranchial cartilage
ZFA:0001522.definition: Small rod-like cartilage that forms between the median copulae and the ceratobranchial cartilages.

ZFA:0001511.label: interhyal cartilage
ZFA:0001511.definition: The interhyal is a small rod-like element that connects the ventral and dorsal parts of the hyoid arch. It articulates laterally with the posterior end of the epihyal and medially at the cartilaginous junction between the hyomandibula and the symplectic. It remains cartilaginous in adult zebrafish and other cypriniforms.

ZFA:0001399.label: palatoquadrate cartilage
ZFA:0001399.definition: Cartilage that is the dorsal component of the first pharyngeal arch.  It is roughly triangular with slightly concave dorsal edges and convex ventral edges.  The anteroventral corner gives rise the quadrate and articulates with the posterior end of  Meckel's cartilage.  The anterodorsal tip articulates with the lateral edge of the ethmoid plate and the posteroventral edge articulates with the anterodorsal edge of the hyosymplectic.

ZFA:0001533.label: pharyngobranchial cartilage
ZFA:0001533.definition: Paired cartilages that project medially from the medial tips of epibranchials.

ZFA:0005886.label: anterior basicapsular commissure
ZFA:0005886.definition: Cartilage that attaches the parachordal cartilage to the auditory capsule anterior to the basicapsular fenestra. The anterior basicapsular commissure are paired.

ZFA:0001500.label: auditory capsule
ZFA:0001500.definition: Bilaterally paired cartilage encasing the semicircular canals of the inner ear.

ZFA:0001502.label: epiphyseal bar
ZFA:0001502.definition: Bilaterally paired medial bar of cartilage formed at midorbit through medial chondrification from triangles of cartilage that later form the junction of the taeniae marginales anterior, taeniae marginales posterior and the epiphyseal bar.

ZFA:0001405.label: ethmoid cartilage
ZFA:0001405.definition: Bilaterally paired neurocranium cartilage which is initially plate-like and formed from the anterior fusion between the bilaterally paired trabecula cranii. It grows dorsally between the laminae orbitonasales to attain a complex shape.

ZFA:0000585.label: kinethmoid cartilage
ZFA:0000585.definition: Cranial cartilage which is a small median cartilage located between the premaxillae and anterodorsal to the ethmoid.

ZFA:0001503.label: lamina orbitonasalis
ZFA:0001503.definition: Cranial cartilage which is bilaterally paired and develops as a dorsal plate-like projection of the anteriolateral ethmoid plate, which are oriented perpendicular to the ethmoid plate. It fuses dorsally to the taenia marginalis anterior, and it joins the ethmoid cartilage medially.

ZFA:0005888.label: lateral basicapsular commissure
ZFA:0005888.definition: Cartilage that grows from the auditory capsule medially toward the anterior end of the parachordal cartilage to enclose the hyomandibular (facial) foramen. The lateral basicapsular commissure are paired.

ZFA:0001504.label: occipital arch cartilage
ZFA:0001504.definition: Cranial cartilage which is a paired anterodorsal projection of the posterior end of the parachordal cartilage. It lies lateral to the notochord, just anterior to the posterior tip of the otic capsule. The bilaterally paired occipital arch cartilages fuse anterodorsally to the posterior edges of the auditory capsules and meet medially as the tectum synoticum (by 12 dpf).

ZFA:0001423.label: parachordal cartilage
ZFA:0001423.definition: Rod-shaped paired cartilages on either side of the notochord. They unite, forming the base of the chondrocranium and are replaced by the prootic bones.

ZFA:0005887.label: posterior basicapsular commissure
ZFA:0005887.definition: Cartilage that attaches the parachordal cartilage to the auditory capsule posterior of the  basicapsular fenestra. The posterior basicapsular commissure are paired.

ZFA:0001509.label: sclerotic cartilage
ZFA:0001509.definition: Bilaterally paired thin continuous band of cartilage that sagitally encircles the eye.  It lies between t lies between the sclera and the optic choroid.

ZFA:0001505.label: taenia marginalis anterior
ZFA:0001505.definition: Cartilage bar (bilaterally paired) that grows anteroventrally from the epiphyseal bar to join the anteriolateral edge of the ethmoid plate.

ZFA:0001515.label: taenia marginalis posterior
ZFA:0001515.definition: Cartilage bar (bilaterally paired) that is first visible as an anterior extension of the auditory capsule. It grows anteriorly toward the middle of the orbit where it is connected to its mate on the other side by the epiphyseal bar.

ZFA:0001506.label: tectum synoticum
ZFA:0001506.definition: Unpaired thin dorsal sheet of cartilage that partially covers the posterior chondrocranium.

ZFA:0001508.label: trabecula communis
ZFA:0001508.definition: Cartilage formed via medial fusion between bilaterally paired trabecula cranii.

ZFA:0001507.label: trabecula cranii
ZFA:0001507.definition: Paired thin medially aligned bar of cartilage that extends from the anterior end of the chondrocranium to just anterior to the anterior end of the notochord. The posterior ends of the trabeculae cranii are continuous with the parachordal cartilages, and they enclose the hypophyseal fenestra.

ZFA:0005220.label: larval melanophore stripe
ZFA:0005220.definition: A melanophore stripe that forms the immature pigment pattern.

ZFA:0005391.label: head sensory canal system
ZFA:0005391.definition: Lateral line system on head and pectoral girdle.

ZFA:0001470.label: anterior lateral line
ZFA:0001470.definition: The anterior lateral line consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians. The anterior lateral line develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated between the eye and ear.

ZFA:0005112.label: dorsal lateral line
ZFA:0005112.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000524.label: infraorbital lateral line
ZFA:0000524.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000259.label: mandibular lateral line
ZFA:0000259.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000344.label: middle lateral line
ZFA:0000344.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000400.label: occipital lateral line
ZFA:0000400.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000424.label: opercular lateral line
ZFA:0000424.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000464.label: otic lateral line
ZFA:0000464.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000944.label: posterior lateral line
ZFA:0000944.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000443.label: supraorbital lateral line
ZFA:0000443.definition: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001706.label: Purkinje cell layer corpus cerebelli
ZFA:0001706.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the corpus cerebelli and contains Purkinje cells.

ZFA:0001709.label: Purkinje cell layer valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0001709.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the valvula cerebelli and contains Purkinje cells.

ZFA:0005906.label: Reissner's fiber
ZFA:0005906.definition: Thread-like fibrous aggregation of secreted molecules extending from the subcommissural organ (SCO) through the ventricular system and central canal to the end of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0001198.label: adenohypophyseal placode
ZFA:0001198.definition: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the adenohypophysis.

ZFA:0005345.label: adipose tissue
ZFA:0005345.definition: Connective tissue in which fat is stored. All adipose tissue in the zebrafish is white adipose tissue and is comprised of adipocytes, stroma, macrophages and vasculature.  Mature adipocytes express adipokines, such as adipsin, adiponectin, and leptin so white adipose tissue is considered an endocrine organ. The connective tissue is loose and infiltrated by a vascular network.

ZFA:0001357.label: alar plate midbrain region
ZFA:0001357.definition: Portion of tissue that is ventrolateral to the roof plate and part of the midbrain.

ZFA:0000004.label: anterior axial hypoblast
ZFA:0000004.definition: Anterior portion of the axial hypoblast.

ZFA:0007024.label: anterior neural keel
ZFA:0007024.definition: Rostral portion of the neural keel.  Develops into the anterior neural rod.

ZFA:0007016.label: anterior neural plate
ZFA:0007016.definition: Rostral portion of the neural plate.  Develops into the anterior neural keel.

ZFA:0007031.label: anterior neural rod
ZFA:0007031.definition: Rostral portion of the neural rod.  Develops into the anterior neural tube.

ZFA:0007038.label: anterior neural tube
ZFA:0007038.definition: Rostral portion of the neural tube.

ZFA:0007014.label: anterior presumptive neural plate
ZFA:0007014.definition: Rostral portion of embryonic tissue that gives rise to the anterior neural plate.

ZFA:0005337.label: anterior swim bladder bud
ZFA:0005337.definition: Portion of tissue that forms from the swim bladder epithelium at the anterior end of the swim bladder.

ZFA:0005146.label: area postrema
ZFA:0005146.definition: An area of medulla oblongata, outside the blood-brain barrier.  The apical terminals of the neurons are, in a strategic location either to monitor the chemical constitution of the plasma or to release neurogenic substances into the general circulation.

ZFA:0005914.label: argentum
ZFA:0005914.definition: Iridophore layer of iris composed of a outer layer of regularly tiled  iridophores and an inner layer of randomly arranged iridophores.  The outer regularly tiled iridophores reflect blue green light.  The light reflecting crystals in the iris iridophores are composed of anhydrous Beta-guanine.

ZFA:0005774.label: atrial epicardium
ZFA:0005774.definition: The external layer of the atrium bounding the atrial myocardium.

ZFA:0005070.label: atrioventricular node
ZFA:0005070.definition: The portion of tissue in the atrioventricular canal that slows impulse propagation between the atrium and cardiac ventricle.

ZFA:0005073.label: atrioventricular ring
ZFA:0005073.definition: A ring of conduction tissue that forms in the atrioventricular canal.

ZFA:0005796.label: basal layer breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005796.definition: Layer of breeding tubercle proximal to basal lamina of the integument.

ZFA:0000761.label: basal plate midbrain region
ZFA:0000761.definition: Portion of tissue that is dorsolateral to the floor plate and part of the midbrain.

ZFA:0000094.label: blood island
ZFA:0000094.definition: Nests of developing blood cells arising late in the segmentation period from the intermediate mass, and located in the anterior-ventral tail, just posterior to the yolk extension.

ZFA:0005575.label: brain nucleus
ZFA:0005575.definition: Portion of tissue that are compact accumulations of neurons having roughly similar connections and functions.

ZFA:0000319.label: branchiostegal membrane
ZFA:0000319.definition: The portion of tissue forming the membrane connecting the branchiostegals and enclosing the gill chamber.

ZFA:0005066.label: bulbus arteriosus outer layer
ZFA:0005066.definition: The portion of tissue that is the outer layer of the bulbus arteriosus. It is composed of scattered layers of interrupted elastic lamina.

ZFA:0001318.label: cardiac jelly
ZFA:0001318.definition: The extracellular matrix between the myocardium and the endocardium. The cardiac jelly plays a central role in the septation of the heart and comprises most of the thickness of the heart wall at early stages, but disappears as the heart differentiates.

ZFA:0005898.label: caudal hematopoietic tissue
ZFA:0005898.definition: Tissue that lies between the caudal artery and the caudal vein plexus where definitive hematopoiesis occurs after  48hpf and before the hematopoietic progenitors migrate to the thymus and kidney.

ZFA:0000636.label: cerebellar crest
ZFA:0000636.definition: Portion of tissue composed of parallel fibers that originate at the granular eminence that overlays the rhombencephalic lateral line region. Also termed the molecular layer.

ZFA:0001082.label: chordo neural hinge
ZFA:0001082.definition: Portion of tissue that is posterior to the developing notochord during tail bud extension.

ZFA:0001711.label: climbing fiber
ZFA:0001711.definition: Portion of tissue that consists of afferent axons from the inferior olive and synapsing with Purkinje cells within the molecular layer of the valvula cerebelli and corpus cerebelli.

ZFA:0005062.label: compact layer of ventricle
ZFA:0005062.definition: The outer layer the ventricular myocardium, muscle  fibers are arranged in a compact form and involved the entire ventricle.

ZFA:0001688.label: corneal primordium
ZFA:0001688.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the eye and gives rise to the mature, fully layered cornea.

ZFA:0001685.label: corneal stroma
ZFA:0001685.definition: Portion of tissue that is located basal to Bowman's layer and distal to Descemet's membrane and is comprised largely of connective tissue.

ZFA:0001200.label: corpuscles of Stannius
ZFA:0001200.definition: Islands of eosinic cells found on the lateroventral surface of the kidney. Function is thought to be that of the parathyroid gland in other vertebrates, which are lacking in fishes. These cells secrete hypocalcin (teleocalcin) to regulate calcium metabolism.

ZFA:0001663.label: cranial nerve root
ZFA:0001663.definition: The portion of tissue that is the initial segment of one of the cranial nerves leaving the central nervous system.

ZFA:0005140.label: dental papilla
ZFA:0005140.definition: Tissue of the developing tooth. It is composed of pre-odontoblast and undifferentiated mesenchyme cells and connects to the basal lamina.

ZFA:0001182.label: dermal deep region
ZFA:0001182.definition: Portion of the dermis characterized by a well-arranged, plywood-like, collagenous network.

ZFA:0005122.label: dorsal axial hypoblast
ZFA:0005122.definition: Dorsal region of the axial hypoblast.

ZFA:0000652.label: dorsal root
ZFA:0000652.definition: The afferent sensory portion of the spinal nerve root.

ZFA:0007001.label: dorso-rostral cluster
ZFA:0007001.definition: Early-forming telencephalic neural cluster.  Neurons of the dorso-rostral cluster (drc) extend axons to form the supra-optic tract (SOT) and the anterior commissure (AC).

ZFA:0001672.label: dorsolateral septum
ZFA:0001672.definition: Portion of tissue that grows in from the dorsolateral wall of the otic vesicle, forming a dorsolateral partition between the developing anterior and posterior semicircular canals.

ZFA:0005771.label: ectomesenchyme
ZFA:0005771.definition: Portion of tissue that develops from the cranial neural crest and which cells populate a series of pharyngeal arches from which develops the support skeleton of the jaw and gills.

ZFA:0001317.label: endocardial cushion
ZFA:0001317.definition: Swellings of tissue present between the endocardial and myocardial cell layers that will give rise to the interstitial cells of the cardiac valves.

ZFA:0005489.label: endocardial precursor
ZFA:0005489.definition: Is a portion of tissue part of the heart primordium which will give rise to the endocardium.

ZFA:0005072.label: endocardial ring
ZFA:0005072.definition: A portion of endocardial tissue that is part of the atrioventricular ring.

ZFA:0001320.label: endocardium
ZFA:0001320.definition: Layer that lines the lumen of the heart.

ZFA:0005912.label: endolymphatic sac
ZFA:0005912.definition: Pouch at the end of the endolymphatic duct that helps regulates pressure on the inner ear. The endolymphatic sac is separated from the endolymphatic duct by a dynamic lamellar barrier.  The lamellar barrier is composed of long, thin lamellar sheets that form tongue-and-groove structure or interwoven broadly overlapping structures. In adults, the endolymphatic duct and sac are partially encased within the temporal bone such that the distal end of the endolymphatic sac protrudes out of the temporal bone into the cranial cavity .

ZFA:0001180.label: epidermal basal stratum
ZFA:0001180.definition: Lower layer of the epidermis. Composed of a single layer of cells.  The major function of the basal stratum is to keep the epidermis attached to the underlying dermis by means of (hemidesmosomes attached to the basement membrane.

ZFA:0001181.label: epidermal intermediate stratum
ZFA:0001181.definition: The tissue which lies between the basal stratum and the superficial stratum.   This layer is composed of a variable number of cell layers which contain  mucous goblet cells, club cells and sensory cells.  Most of the cells of this region are undifferentiated. They serve as a reservoir to replace dead cells in any of the epidermis regions.

ZFA:0001703.label: epidermal placode
ZFA:0001703.definition: Portion of tissue that is a thickening and reshaping of the epidermal basal stratum cells beneath which fibroblasts accumulate to form the scale primordium.

ZFA:0001179.label: epidermal superficial stratum
ZFA:0001179.definition: The outer layer of the epidermis.  The living cells form single cell layer, the outer surface of which is ornamented with microridges. These outer epidermal cells are not renewed periodically, but are individually replaced when dead.

ZFA:0007004.label: epiphyseal cluster
ZFA:0007004.definition: Early-developing neuronal cluster of the epiphysis.  By 24 hpf the pioneer axon of the dorsoventral diencephalic tract (DVDT) has arisen from the ec and grown ventrally. As this axon encounters axons of the TPOC, it makes a near-90 rostral turn and grows rostrally among axons of the TPOC growing in the opposite direction.

ZFA:0001292.label: epiphyseal stalk
ZFA:0001292.definition: The stalk emanates from the diencephalic roof at a left-of-medial position.

ZFA:0001486.label: epithelium
ZFA:0001486.definition: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of epithelial cells connected to each other by cell junctions and which is underlain by a basal lamina.

ZFA:0000352.label: external cellular layer
ZFA:0000352.definition: Portion of tissue which is located between the glomerular layer and internal cellular layer of the olfactory bulb, and contains large mitral cells whose efferent axons form most of the lateral and medial olfactory tracts. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000309.label: external yolk syncytial layer
ZFA:0000309.definition: The portion of the YSL that is outside of the blastoderm margin during epiboly.

ZFA:0007071.label: flexural organ
ZFA:0007071.definition: Is a portion of tissue that is the most anterior portion of the notochord. The flexural organ secretes Reissner's fiber-related proteins, including F-spondin.

ZFA:0007026.label: forebrain neural keel
ZFA:0007026.definition: Anterior portion of anterior neural keel that gives rise to the forebrain neural rod.

ZFA:0007018.label: forebrain neural plate
ZFA:0007018.definition: Anterior portion of anterior neural plate that gives rise to the forebrain neural keel.

ZFA:0007034.label: forebrain neural rod
ZFA:0007034.definition: Anterior portion of anterior neural rod that gives rise to the forebrain neural tube.

ZFA:0007041.label: forebrain neural tube
ZFA:0007041.definition: Anterior portion of anterior neural rod that gives rise to the forebrain.

ZFA:0000190.label: ganglion
ZFA:0000190.definition: Structures containing a collection of nerve cell bodies.

ZFA:0000210.label: gigantocellular part of magnocellular preoptic nucleus
ZFA:0000210.definition: Portion of tissue that is the caudal gigantocellular portion of the magnocellular preoptic nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000667.label: gill filament
ZFA:0000667.definition: Portion of tissue that projects outward from the gill and is a thread-like, soft, red respiratory and excretory structure.

ZFA:0001262.label: gonad primordium
ZFA:0001262.definition: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the immature gonad.

ZFA:0000358.label: granular layer corpus cerebelli
ZFA:0000358.definition: Portion of tissue which is the innermost layer of the corpus cerebelli and consists of small granule cells and larger Golgi cells. The granule cell receive excitatory input from the mossy fibers, and send parallel fibers to the molecular layer where they synapse with Purkinje cell dendrites.

ZFA:0000766.label: granular layer valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0000766.definition: Portion of tissue which is part of the valvula cerebelli and consists largely of axons and dendrites.

ZFA:0001112.label: granulosa cell layer
ZFA:0001112.definition: Portion of tissue part of the ovarian follicle containing a single layer of granulosa cells that surround the developing oocyte.

ZFA:0000028.label: heart primordium
ZFA:0000028.definition: Bilateral groups of cells consisting of three rows: one row of endocardial precursors medially and two rows of myocardial precursors laterally. The two populations fuse at the midline between 21 and 26 somites to form the heart rudiment or cone.

ZFA:0000115.label: heart rudiment
ZFA:0000115.definition: The migrating myocardial precursors of the heart rudiment form a cone like structure between 19.5 hpf and 22 hpf, and eventually telescope out into the primitive heart tube at 24hpf.

ZFA:0007029.label: hindbrain neural keel
ZFA:0007029.definition: Portion of posterior neural keel that gives rise to the hindbrain neural rod.

ZFA:0007022.label: hindbrain neural plate
ZFA:0007022.definition: Portion of posterior neural plate  that gives rise to the hindbrain neural keel.

ZFA:0007036.label: hindbrain neural rod
ZFA:0007036.definition: Portion of posterior neural rod that gives rise to the hindbrain neural tube.

ZFA:0007043.label: hindbrain neural tube
ZFA:0007043.definition: Portion of posterior neural tube that gives rise to the hindbrain.

ZFA:0000031.label: hypochord
ZFA:0000031.definition: Portion of tissue that arises from the arise from the lateral edges of the shield and is located immediately ventral to the notochord. The hypochord is thought to play a role in positioning the dorsal aorta. Unlike in frogs and axolotl, the hypochord does not appear to be endodermally derived.

ZFA:0001136.label: hypodermis
ZFA:0001136.definition: A layer separating the inner face of the dermis from the subjacent muscle cells. It is covered on both sides by a basement membrane.  It contains pigment cells.

ZFA:0000573.label: internal cellular layer
ZFA:0000573.definition: Portion of tissue which is the innermost layer of the olfactory bulb. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001107.label: internal gill bud
ZFA:0001107.definition: Portion of tissue that develops into a gill.

ZFA:0000712.label: internal yolk syncytial layer
ZFA:0000712.definition: The portion of the YSL that lies deep to the blastoderm during epiboly.

ZFA:0005256.label: intervillus pockets
ZFA:0005256.definition: A portion of tissue formed between the base of the intestinal villi that is part of the intestinal epithelium where intestinal stem cells are located.  In the intestine no crypts are present, but, the regions between the villi, the intervillus pockets, have a crypt-like function. Cells are produced in the intervillus pockets and  shed from the villus tips.

ZFA:0005738.label: intestinal bulb primordium
ZFA:0005738.definition: Portion of the intestinal rod that loops to left between 26-30hpf and gives rise to the intestinal bulb and liver and anterior pancreatic primordium.  The endoderm at this stage is a compact mass of cells with little to no polarization.

ZFA:0005125.label: intestinal villus
ZFA:0005125.definition: The entire digestive tract is lined by well developed villi, which are longest in the intestinal bulb and decrease progressively in size towards the caudal end of the intestine.

ZFA:0005915.label: iris melanophore layer
ZFA:0005915.definition: Layer of melanophores that are positioned behind the argenta.  The melanophore layer absorbs unfocused light preventing it from reaching the retina.

ZFA:0005569.label: iris stroma
ZFA:0005569.definition: Portion of the iris which contains  bundles of fibers, most of which are oriented radially around the pupil. The stroma is innervated by the iris blood vessels and develops from the periocular mesenchyme.

ZFA:0005755.label: islet
ZFA:0005755.definition: Portion of tissue composed of a group of cells in the pancreas producing insulin, glucagon and somatostatin. Part of the endocrine pancreas.

ZFA:0001256.label: lateral floor plate
ZFA:0001256.definition: Portion of tissue that is the lateral part of the floor plate.

ZFA:0001469.label: lateral line
ZFA:0001469.definition: The lateral line consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head and body of all fishes and most amphibians. The lateral line develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated behind the ear and between the eye and ear.

ZFA:0000228.label: lateral line primordium
ZFA:0000228.definition: Is a portion of tissue that migrates and deposits immature neuromasts and interneuromasts.

ZFA:0000993.label: lateral wall neural rod
ZFA:0000993.definition: Portion of tissue located at either side of the neural rod.

ZFA:0001435.label: lateral wall neural tube
ZFA:0001435.definition: Portion of tissue on the side of the lumen of the neural tube.

ZFA:0000035.label: lens
ZFA:0000035.definition: Portion of tissue that is a transparent, biconvex structure located in the eye through which light is focused.

ZFA:0000122.label: lens placode
ZFA:0000122.definition: Ectodermal primordium of the lens of the eye.

ZFA:0000233.label: lower oral valve
ZFA:0000233.definition: Portion of tissue, located on the lower jaw that defines the caudal extent of the labial cavity.  The oral valves control the flow of water into the mouth during routine respiration.

ZFA:0000386.label: macula
ZFA:0000386.definition: Portion of tissue that is a patch of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium in the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. Each patch has its own characteristic shape and polarity pattern. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001257.label: medial floor plate
ZFA:0001257.definition: Portion of tissue that is the medial part of the floor plate and is located adjacent to the notochord.

ZFA:0000393.label: mesenchyme
ZFA:0000393.definition: A mesh-like cell arrangement, less compact than an epithelium.

ZFA:0005251.label: microcirculatory vessel
ZFA:0005251.definition: A portion of tissue that consists of a tube composed of epithelial cells that connects larger vessels.

ZFA:0005757.label: mid diencephalic organizer
ZFA:0005757.definition: Portion of tissue composed of the signal-generating cells within the zona limitans intrathalamica.

ZFA:0007025.label: midbrain neural keel
ZFA:0007025.definition: Portion of  neural keel that gives rise to the midbrain neural rod.

ZFA:0007019.label: midbrain neural plate
ZFA:0007019.definition: Portion of  neural plate that gives rise to the midbrain neural keel.

ZFA:0007032.label: midbrain neural rod
ZFA:0007032.definition: Portion of  neural rod  that gives rise to the midbrain neural tube.

ZFA:0007039.label: midbrain neural tube
ZFA:0007039.definition: Portion of  neural tube that gives rise to the midbrain.

ZFA:0000394.label: molecular layer corpus cerebelli
ZFA:0000394.definition: Portion of tissue which is the outermost layer of the corpus cerebelli and consists largely of axons and dendrites. Other cell types such as stellate and basket neurons are also found in the molecular layer.

ZFA:0000913.label: molecular layer valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0000913.definition: Portion of tissue which is part of the valvula cerebelli and contains neuronal cell bodies.

ZFA:0001710.label: mossy fiber
ZFA:0001710.definition: Portion of tissue that consists of afferent axons from the spinal cord, sensory medullary nuclei, reticular nuclei and dorsal tegmental nuclei into the corpus cerebelli and valvula cerebelli, where they synapse within the granule cell layer.

ZFA:0005145.label: muscle
ZFA:0005145.definition: Portion of tissue composed of contractile fibers.

ZFA:0005490.label: myocardial precursor
ZFA:0005490.definition: Portion of tissue that will develop into the myocardium.

ZFA:0005587.label: nephron progenitor
ZFA:0005587.definition: Cluster of cells comprising a portion of tissue which gives rise to new mesonephric nephrons.  The cluster contains self-renewing stem cells.

ZFA:0007009.label: nerve
ZFA:0007009.definition: A portion of tissue which is a fasciculated group of axons. Many time axons in the nerve are enveloped by the glial cells of the peripheral nervous system, the Schwann cells.

ZFA:0000045.label: neural crest
ZFA:0000045.definition: A cell population arising from the dorsolateral aspect of the central nervous system primordium during the segmentation period, and later migrating along stereotyped pathways to give rise to a diverse and well-defined set of cell types including pigment cells, peripheral neurons and glia, and head cartilage.

ZFA:0000131.label: neural keel
ZFA:0000131.definition: An intermediate stage (between the neural plate and neural rod) during the early segmentation period in the morphogenesis of the central nervous system primordium; the keel is roughly triangular shaped in cross section.

ZFA:0000132.label: neural plate
ZFA:0000132.definition: Portion of tissue that is the earliest recognizable dorsal ectodermal primordium of the central nervous system present near the end of gastrulation before infolding to form the neural keel; consists of a thickened pseudostratified epithelium.

ZFA:0007082.label: neural plate border
ZFA:0007082.definition: Region of the neural plate that will give rise to the neural crest. The neural plate border includes progenitors for the dorsal neural tube, the neural crest, and placodes. It is a broad competence domain, established between neural and non-neural ectoderm within which subtle and sequential cell autonomous and non-cell autonomous molecular interactions will progressively define the neural crest fate from adjacent dorsal neural fates.

ZFA:0000133.label: neural rod
ZFA:0000133.definition: An intermediate stage in the development of the central nervous system present during the segmentation period; the neural rod is roughly cylindrical in shape, forms from the neural keel, and is not yet hollowed out into the neural tube.

ZFA:0001135.label: neural tube
ZFA:0001135.definition: Portion of tissue that is the cavity-containing primordium of the central nervous system, developing from the neural rod in the late segmentation period.

ZFA:0007059.label: neurogenic field
ZFA:0007059.definition: Portion of tissue fated to develop into neurogenic placode.

ZFA:0005043.label: nevus
ZFA:0005043.definition: An ectopic melanophore accumulation analogous to a nevi (mole) in humans.

ZFA:0001126.label: noninvoluting endocytic marginal cell cluster
ZFA:0001126.definition: The NEM cell cluster lies in a superficial position of the dorsal blastoderm margin encompassing EVL cells and one or two layers of underlying deep cells. Unlike other marginal blastomeres, cells in this cluster do not participate in involution.

ZFA:0000135.label: notochord
ZFA:0000135.definition: Rod-like principal supportive element of the embryo and larva, present in the midline just ventral to the neural tube, and differentiating during the segmentation period to form large vacuolated epithelial cells and a surrounding sheath of fibrous and elastic layers. Layering of the sheath may differ in structure, thickness and development among groups; in cypriniforms there are actually three very thin layers to the sheath. A functional, well developed notochord is present throughout life in certain basal fish groups but not in cypriniforms.

ZFA:0001670.label: notochord posterior region
ZFA:0001670.definition: Portion of tissue that is the part of the notochord located in the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005229.label: optic choroid
ZFA:0005229.definition: A portion of tissue that contains the choroid vasculature. It lies at the back of the eye.

ZFA:0001619.label: optic fiber layer
ZFA:0001619.definition: Fiber layer adjacent the retinal ganglion cell layer which is comprised of their axons as they traverse to the optic nerve.

ZFA:0000570.label: optic primordium
ZFA:0000570.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the anterior neural keel and will form the optic vesicle.

ZFA:0000137.label: optic stalk
ZFA:0000137.definition: Portion of tissue that provides a pathway for axon migration from the retina.   The cells of the optic stalk later differentiate into glial cells of the optic  nerve.

ZFA:0000050.label: optic vesicle
ZFA:0000050.definition: Portion of tissue that is comprised of neuroepithelium which has pinched off from the anterior neural keel and will form the optic cup.

ZFA:0001125.label: organizer inducing center
ZFA:0001125.definition: The dorsal marginal region of the YSL where maternal dorsal determinants localize.  Participates in positioning the shield.

ZFA:0001715.label: otic vesicle protrusion
ZFA:0001715.definition: Portion of tissue within the otic vesicle that consists of a thin layer of otic epithelium covering a finger-shaped core of acellular matrix.

ZFA:0005741.label: pancreatic acinar gland
ZFA:0005741.definition: Portion of exocrine pancreas that is comprised of polarized cells containing apical zymogen granules that store digestive enzymes such as trypsin and chymotrypsin and abundant rough endoplasmic reticulum and mitochondria.

ZFA:0001713.label: parallel fiber
ZFA:0001713.definition: Portion of tissue that consists of axons of cerebellar granule cells that synapse onto Purkinje cell dendrites.

ZFA:0001195.label: pars anterior
ZFA:0001195.definition: The anterior portion of the adenohypophysis. Comprised of the proximal and rostral pars anterior.

ZFA:0001454.label: pelvic fin field
ZFA:0001454.definition: Portion of tissue in the pelvic region that develops into the pelvic fin bud.

ZFA:0000516.label: periventricular grey zone
ZFA:0000516.definition: Tissue located on the ventral side of the optic tectum,  that  contains the cell bodies of most tectal neurons. It is adjacent to the tectal ventricle and opposite the eminentia granularis of the cerebellum.  It also contains a neurogenic niche and has hypothalamic inputs.  The dendrites of neurons from the periventricular grey zones  project their apical dendrites to the stratum opticum and stratum fibrosum et griseum superficale and synapse with retinal axons that project to these layers.

ZFA:0001465.label: photoreceptor inner segment layer
ZFA:0001465.definition: Layer of the retina composed of the inner segments of the photoreceptor cells.

ZFA:0001466.label: photoreceptor outer segment layer
ZFA:0001466.definition: Layer of the retina composed of the outer segments of the photoreceptor cells. The photoreceptor outer segment is a specialized primary cilium consisting of a microtubule-based axoneme and regular stacks of membrane folds or disks containing the photopigments (opsins) required for the phototransduction cascade.

ZFA:0001717.label: pillar of the semicircular canal
ZFA:0001717.definition: Portion of tissue around which the semicircular canals flow.

ZFA:0001632.label: portion of connective tissue
ZFA:0001632.definition: Portion of tissue that consists of mesodermally derived cells and intercellular matrix comprised of protein fibers and carbohydrates, which supports, ensheathes and binds together other tissues.

ZFA:0007023.label: posterior neural keel
ZFA:0007023.definition: Posterior portion of the neural keel that gives rise to the posterior neural rod.

ZFA:0007017.label: posterior neural plate
ZFA:0007017.definition: Posterior portion of the neural plate  that gives rise to the posterior neural keel.

ZFA:0007030.label: posterior neural rod
ZFA:0007030.definition: Posterior portion of the neural rod that gives rise to the posterior neural tube.

ZFA:0007037.label: posterior neural tube
ZFA:0007037.definition: Posterior portion of the neural tube that gives rise to the hindbrain and spinal cord.

ZFA:0007015.label: posterior presumptive neural plate
ZFA:0007015.definition: Caudal portion of embryonic tissue that gives rise to the posterior neural plate.

ZFA:0000060.label: prechordal plate
ZFA:0000060.definition: Axial hypoblast located anterior to the chorda mesoderm; the polster is its most anterior region.

ZFA:0001723.label: presumptive atrioventricular canal
ZFA:0001723.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the atrioventricular canal.

ZFA:0001712.label: presumptive bulbus arteriosus
ZFA:0001712.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the bulbus arteriosus.

ZFA:0001724.label: presumptive endocardium
ZFA:0001724.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the endocardium.

ZFA:0001071.label: presumptive neural retina
ZFA:0001071.definition: Portion of tissue that is the inner layer of the optic cup and will become the neural retina.

ZFA:0000064.label: presumptive retinal pigmented epithelium
ZFA:0000064.definition: Portion of tissue that is the outer layer of the optic cup and will become the retinal pigmented epithelium.

ZFA:0001722.label: presumptive sinus venosus
ZFA:0001722.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the sinus venosus.

ZFA:0001122.label: primary germ layer
ZFA:0001122.definition: Portion of tissue that consists of a layer of cells that form during embryogenesis that will give rise to all structures of the organism.

ZFA:0000267.label: primary olfactory fiber layer
ZFA:0000267.definition: Portion of tissue which is the most peripheral layer and present only in the rostroventral olfactory bulb. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005076.label: primordial vasculature
ZFA:0005076.definition: Is a portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.

ZFA:0005808.label: proepicardial cluster
ZFA:0005808.definition: Transient cluster of cardiac progenitor cells that develops adjacent to the heart and migrates onto the heart to form the epicardium.  Proepicardial clusters in Zebrafish form on the pericardial wall, adjacent to the atrioventricular (AV) junction and near the venous pole.

ZFA:0005310.label: pronephric glomerular capsule
ZFA:0005310.definition: Portion of tissue that encapsulates the glomerulus of the pronephros.

ZFA:0005581.label: proximal pars anterior
ZFA:0005581.definition: Caudal portion of pars anterior of the adenohypophysis where somatotropes, thyrotropes and gonadotropes are localized.  The proximal pars anterior has functional homology to the mammalian pars tuberalis, secreting the same hormones.

ZFA:0005147.label: regenerating tissue
ZFA:0005147.definition: A portion of tissue that is regrowing after damage or amputation.

ZFA:0005871.label: region of the nucleus of the medial longitudinal fascicle
ZFA:0005871.definition: Portion of tissue in the midbrain that will develop into the nucleus of the medial longitudinal fasciculus synencephalon.

ZFA:0005254.label: renal glomerular capsule
ZFA:0005254.definition: Portion of tissue that encapsulates the glomerulus of the renal corpuscle.

ZFA:0005586.label: renal vesicle
ZFA:0005586.definition: Hollow cluster of epithelial cells derived from the nephron progenitor.

ZFA:0000024.label: retinal ganglion cell layer
ZFA:0000024.definition: Layer of the retina that contains the ganglion cell bodies.

ZFA:0000119.label: retinal inner nuclear layer
ZFA:0000119.definition: Retinal layer that contains the interneurons, the horizontal, bipolar and amacrine cells.

ZFA:0001329.label: retinal inner plexiform layer
ZFA:0001329.definition: The layer within the retina where the bipolar cells synapse with the dendrites of the ganglion cells.

ZFA:0000046.label: retinal neural layer
ZFA:0000046.definition: Portion of retina composed of  all the neural tissues in the retina.

ZFA:0001464.label: retinal outer nuclear layer
ZFA:0001464.definition: The layer within the retina where the photoreceptor cell bodies reside.

ZFA:0001330.label: retinal outer plexiform layer
ZFA:0001330.definition: The layer within the retina where the bipolar cells synapse with the photoreceptor cells.

ZFA:0000143.label: retinal photoreceptor layer
ZFA:0000143.definition: The layer within the retina where the photoreceptor cell receptor segments reside. This layer is closet to the sclera.

ZFA:0001358.label: roof plate diencephalic region
ZFA:0001358.definition: Roof plate that is part of the diencephalic region.

ZFA:0000355.label: roof plate midbrain region
ZFA:0000355.definition: Roof plate that is part of the midbrain.

ZFA:0001436.label: roof plate neural tube region
ZFA:0001436.definition: Roof plate that is part of the neural tube.

ZFA:0001033.label: roof plate rhombomere 1
ZFA:0001033.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 1.

ZFA:0000824.label: roof plate rhombomere 2
ZFA:0000824.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0000950.label: roof plate rhombomere 3
ZFA:0000950.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 3.

ZFA:0001034.label: roof plate rhombomere 4
ZFA:0001034.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 4.

ZFA:0000828.label: roof plate rhombomere 5
ZFA:0000828.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 5.

ZFA:0000825.label: roof plate rhombomere 6
ZFA:0000825.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 6.

ZFA:0000951.label: roof plate rhombomere 7
ZFA:0000951.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 7.

ZFA:0001035.label: roof plate rhombomere 8
ZFA:0001035.definition: Roof plate that is part of rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0005029.label: rostral blood island
ZFA:0005029.definition: Hematopoietic tissue derived from the cephalic mesoderm.  Predominantly produces myeloid cells.

ZFA:0005580.label: rostral pars anterior
ZFA:0005580.definition: Rostral portion of pars anterior of the adenohypophysis where corticotropes and lactotropes localize.

ZFA:0001704.label: scale primordium
ZFA:0001704.definition: A portion of tissue that gives rise to the scale.  At the  initial stages the primordium  is composed of an accumulation of fibroblast below the basil epidermis.   As the primordium develops the epidermis over the fibroblast alters: the basal epidermal cells become cuboidal and narrow, the collagen matrix remodels and the hemidesmosomes disappear.

ZFA:0001080.label: sclerotome
ZFA:0001080.definition: Portion of somite that gives rise to skeletal elements.

ZFA:0005794.label: second tier layer of breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005794.definition: Cell layer that lies underneath the superficial layer of the breeding tubercle.  Characterized by tight junctions within the layer.

ZFA:0000279.label: segmental plate
ZFA:0000279.definition: Unsegmented field of paraxial mesoderm present posterior to the most recently formed somite pair, from which somites will form.

ZFA:0005069.label: sinoatrial node
ZFA:0005069.definition: Portion of tissue containing  3 and 30 cells  in dorsal right quadrant of atrium that initiate heart beat.

ZFA:0005600.label: sinoatrial region
ZFA:0005600.definition: Region at venious pole of heart tube that initiates heart beat.

ZFA:0005601.label: sinoatrial ring
ZFA:0005601.definition: Ring of cardiac conduction tissue around the sinoatrial region of the heart tube that performs pacemaker function.

ZFA:0001679.label: solid lens vesicle
ZFA:0001679.definition: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the lens. The lens of the zebrafish forms by delamination of lens placodal cells and not through invagination. This results in a solid spherical mass as opposed to a hollow lens vesicle. Detachment of the solid lens vesicle of zebrafish at 24-26 hpf is accomplished in part by apoptosis, similar to mammals.

ZFA:0000155.label: somite
ZFA:0000155.definition: Undifferentiated mesodermal components of early trunk or tail segments or metameres, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms myotomes, sclerotomes and perhaps dermatomes.

ZFA:0005882.label: spermatogenic cyst
ZFA:0005882.definition: Structure in the testis formed by cytoplasmic projections of one or two Sertoli cells that surround a single spermatogonium.  Sperm production occurs with in the cyst and the spermatogonium divides to generate approximately 1300 mature sperm.  A given Sertoli cell is in contact with only one germ cell clone.

ZFA:0007028.label: spinal cord neural keel
ZFA:0007028.definition: Portion of the posterior neural keel that gives rise to the spinal cord neural rod.

ZFA:0007021.label: spinal cord neural plate
ZFA:0007021.definition: Portion of the posterior neural plate that gives rise to the spinal cord neural keel.

ZFA:0007035.label: spinal cord neural rod
ZFA:0007035.definition: Portion of the posterior neural rod that gives rise to the spinal cord neural tube.

ZFA:0007042.label: spinal cord neural tube
ZFA:0007042.definition: Portion of the posterior neural tube that gives rise to the spinal cord.

ZFA:0005795.label: spinous layer of breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005795.definition: Intermediate layer of the breeding tubercles characterized by cells with  loose spinous organization connected to each other via desmosomes, but with wide extracellular spaces in between.

ZFA:0001347.label: stratum fibrosum et griseum superficiale
ZFA:0001347.definition: Layer of the optic tectum that is ventral to the stratum opticum and dorsal to the stratum griseum centrale, contains three sublaminae.  Has hypothalamic and retinal  inputs.

ZFA:0001348.label: stratum marginale
ZFA:0001348.definition: Dorsalmost layer of the tectal neuropile that  does not receive direct retinal inputs, receives axonal projections from the torus longitudinalis.

ZFA:0001349.label: stratum opticum
ZFA:0001349.definition: Portion of tissue that is the most superficial layer of the tectal neuropil closest to the eye target of the retinal axons.

ZFA:0005793.label: superficial layer of breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005793.definition: Layer of smooth cells composing the outer layer of the breeding tubercle.  Cells in this layer have a high keratin content, lamellar bodies, and condensed chromosomes.  This layer is repeatedly shed and regenerated.

ZFA:0005916.label: tapetum lucidum
ZFA:0005916.definition: Iridophore layer that forms along the dorsal region of the poster segment of the eye. The tapetum is formed by a single layer of Iridophores and is proximal to  the  photoreceptors  and is located  in the choroid.   The  tapetum  reflects photons back to the photoreceptors if  they were not initially absorbed by the photoreceptors.

ZFA:0000447.label: tela chorioidea
ZFA:0000447.definition: Portion of tissue that is part of the primitive meninx which forms a fold, roofing a ventricle of the brain and supporting the choroid plexus.

ZFA:0001072.label: thyroid follicle
ZFA:0001072.definition: Portion of tissue formed form thyroid follicle cells that forms along the midline in pharyngeal mesenchyme.  The follicles are not encapsulated by connective tissue.

ZFA:0001081.label: thyroid primordium
ZFA:0001081.definition: Portion of tissue part of the pharyngeal endoderm that is fated to become thyroid follicle.

ZFA:0001153.label: tooth placode
ZFA:0001153.definition: Placode that develops into a tooth. The placode is a thickening of the pharyngeal epithelium.

ZFA:0005059.label: trabecular layer
ZFA:0005059.definition: The layer of the myocardium composed of projections of contractile myocytes.   The trabecular layer is bounded internally by the endocardium.  Unlike the trabeculations of higher vertebrates, both atrial and ventricular trabeculae of the zebrafish have more strut-like character, and are more uniform without apparent regional differences.

ZFA:0005810.label: trabecular layer of the atrium
ZFA:0005810.definition: Trabecular layer of the atrial myocardium.

ZFA:0005883.label: tunica albuginea testis
ZFA:0005883.definition: Membranous sheath that surrounds the testis.

ZFA:0005881.label: tunica propria of seminiferous tubule
ZFA:0005881.definition: The membranous sheath that surrounding the seminiferous tubule.

ZFA:0000451.label: upper oral valve
ZFA:0000451.definition: Portion of tissue, located on the upper jaw that defines the caudal extent of the labial cavity.  The oral valves control the flow of water into the mouth during routine respiration.

ZFA:0005559.label: vascular sprouts
ZFA:0005559.definition: Portion of vessel wall that extends to form a new vessel.

ZFA:0000705.label: ventral root
ZFA:0000705.definition: The efferent motor portion of the spinal nerve root.

ZFA:0005028.label: ventral wall of dorsal aorta
ZFA:0005028.definition: Region where blood progenitor markers are expressed.   Probable site of definitive hematopoiesis between 36hpf and 4dpf.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: dorsal aorta - posterior cardinal vein joint

ZFA:0005058.label: ventricular epicardium
ZFA:0005058.definition: The external layer of the ventricle bounding the ventricular myocardium.  It is formed by a single layer of mesothelial cells supported by a basal lamina, and imbricated with collagen, fibroblasts, and vascular structures in the subepicardial space.

ZFA:0005061.label: ventricular myocardium
ZFA:0005061.definition: Muscular layer of the cardiac ventricle composed of a compact myocardial layer surrounding the trabecular layer.

ZFA:0007118.label: vertebral body end plate
ZFA:0007118.definition: The vertebral body end plate is part of the autocentrum. The anterior and posterior surfaces of the autocentrum constitute the funnel shaped vertebral body end plates. The outer rim of the end plate is the vertebral body growth zone. The anterior and posterior end plates are connected by bony plates that are horizontally attached to the ourter contour of the autocentrum.

ZFA:0001451.label: zone of polarizing activity pectoral fin bud
ZFA:0001451.definition: A small group of mesodermal cells located at the posterior margin of the developing fin bud. The ZPA is thought to produce retinoic acid and  thereby provides positional information to the developing bud.

ZFA:0001452.label: zone of polarizing activity pelvic fin bud
ZFA:0001452.definition: A small group of mesodermal cells located at the posterior margin of the developing fin bud.  The ZPA is thought to produce retinoic acid and thereby provides positional information to the developing bud.

ZFA:0001188.label: Weberian apparatus
ZFA:0001188.definition: The Weberian apparatus consists of the modified anteriormost four vertebrae and associated structures of otophysans which transduce sound or pressure waves from the tunica externa of the swim bladder to the inner ear (Alexander, 1962).

ZFA:0001420.label: anal fin pterygiophore
ZFA:0001420.definition: A range of twelve to fourteen rod-like internal median skeletal support structures of the anal fin, comprised of both bone and cartilage and found between vertebrae 14 and 21.

ZFA:0005566.label: anterior segment eye
ZFA:0005566.definition: Anatomical cluster comprising the rostral portion of the eye;  the cornea, lens, iris, ciliary zone, anterior chamber, and annular ligament.

ZFA:0005531.label: bony shelf above orbit
ZFA:0005531.definition: The bony shelf above orbit is an anatomical cluster formed by the dorsolateral portions of the lateral ethmoid, frontal and sphenotic bones that forms the dorsal margin of the orbit.

ZFA:0001424.label: chondrocranium
ZFA:0001424.definition: Anatomical cluster that is part of the cranium and composed of cartilage and cartilage replacement bones.

ZFA:0005606.label: cranial vault
ZFA:0005606.definition: Anatomical cluster of skeletal elements that forms the roof over the brain.

ZFA:0000863.label: dermatocranium
ZFA:0000863.definition: Anatomical cluster that is part of the cranium and composed of dermally derived bones.

ZFA:0001419.label: dorsal fin pterygiophore
ZFA:0001419.definition: A range of seven to nine rod-like internal median skeletal support structures of the dorsal fin, comprised of both bone and cartilage and found between vertebrae 11 and 18.

ZFA:0001649.label: infraorbital series
ZFA:0001649.definition: Anatomical cluster that is the series of dermal bones associated with the infraorbital sensory canal located under and posterior to the eye.

ZFA:0000217.label: inner ear
ZFA:0000217.definition: The auditory (hearing) and vestibular (balance) organ of the fish, equivalent to the inner ear of amniotes. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001341.label: intervening zone
ZFA:0001341.definition: A zone of delayed differentiation at the midbrain hindbrain boundary.  The IZ separates midbrain from anterior hindbrain neuronal clusters and has been described in all vertebrates.

ZFA:0001596.label: joint
ZFA:0001596.definition: Anatomical cluster which consists of two or more adjacent bones or cartilages, which may be interconnected by various types of tissue.

ZFA:0001627.label: lagenar capsule
ZFA:0001627.definition: Anatomical cluster that consists of a bulla formed by the exoccipital and basioccipital bones, and surrounds the lagena.

ZFA:0001227.label: mandibular arch skeleton
ZFA:0001227.definition: Skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the first pharyngeal arch.

ZFA:0000542.label: medial column
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: medial column of the reticular formation

ZFA:0005282.label: nephron
ZFA:0005282.definition: Functional unit of the kidney that filters waste.

ZFA:0001363.label: neural complex
ZFA:0001363.definition: The neural complex is the collective term for the ossified supraneurals (Sn 2 and Sn 3) and their membrane bone extensions above the first four vertebrae (Hoffmann and Britz, 2006).

ZFA:0001580.label: neurocranium
ZFA:0001580.definition: Anatomical cluster that is the regional skeletal system surrounding the brain.

ZFA:0000243.label: neuromast
ZFA:0000243.definition: Volcano-shaped lateral line sensory organ located in characteristic positions within the skin epithelium and containing hair cells and their support elements. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001414.label: occipital region
ZFA:0001414.definition: Anatomical cluster that is located in the posterior region of the cranium and forms the margin of the foramen magnum and occipital condyle.

ZFA:0000351.label: olfactory region
ZFA:0000351.definition: Anatomical cluster that is located in the anterior region of the cranium and provides structural support for the peripheral olfactory organ.

ZFA:0000590.label: oral region
ZFA:0000590.definition: Region of the head where the mouth and oral structures are located.

ZFA:0001410.label: orbital region
ZFA:0001410.definition: Anatomical cluster that is a anteriolateral part of the cranium and structurally supports the eye.

ZFA:0000189.label: otic region
ZFA:0000189.definition: Anatomical cluster of skeletal elements that is a posterolateral part of the cranium and structurally supports the vestibuloauditory system.

ZFA:0005509.label: palate
ZFA:0005509.definition: Anatomical cluster that is the upper roof of the mouth that is roofed by bones such as the parasphenoid, prevomer, metapterygoid, orbitosphenoid.

ZFA:0001272.label: palatoquadrate arch
ZFA:0001272.definition: The dorsal portion of the first pharyngeal arch, comprising the upper jaw.

ZFA:0005753.label: pancreatic lobule
ZFA:0005753.definition: Cluster of acinar glands surrounding an intralobular duct.

ZFA:0005410.label: pars inferior ear
ZFA:0005410.definition: The ventral portion of the ear.  It contains the saccule and the lagena which are the primary auditory organs.

ZFA:0005409.label: pars superior ear
ZFA:0005409.definition: The dorsal part of the ear. Comprises the three semicircular canals, which connect to the utricle.

ZFA:0000407.label: pectoral girdle
ZFA:0000407.definition: Anatomical cluster of paired dermal and endochondral bones that attaches to the dorso-posterior part of the cranium, and support the radials and pectoral fin. It consists of two components: the primary pectoral girdle consisting of the endochondral coracoid, scapula and mesocoracoid bones, and the secondary pectoral girdle consisting of the dermal posttemporal, supracleithrum, cleithrum and poscleithrum(thra) bones.

ZFA:0000565.label: pelvic girdle
ZFA:0000565.definition: Anatomical cluster that consists of the paired basipterygia which support the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0007115.label: pericardial region
ZFA:0007115.definition: An anatomical cluster composed of the heart and associated structures.

ZFA:0001228.label: pharyngeal arch 3 skeleton
ZFA:0001228.definition: Anatomical cluster made up of skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the third pharyngeal arch, also called first  gill or branchial arch.

ZFA:0000095.label: pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton
ZFA:0000095.definition: Skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the gill arches; the last five of the set of seven pharyngeal arches; the numbering system can be confusing; generally branchial arch #1 is the first gill arch, or the third pharyngeal arch, but some authors do not follow this convention.

ZFA:0001231.label: pharyngeal arch 4 skeleton
ZFA:0001231.definition: Anatomical cluster made up of skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the fourth pharyngeal arch, also called second  gill or branchial arch.

ZFA:0001232.label: pharyngeal arch 5 skeleton
ZFA:0001232.definition: Anatomical cluster made up of skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the fifth pharyngeal arch, also called third gill or branchial arch.

ZFA:0001230.label: pharyngeal arch 6 skeleton
ZFA:0001230.definition: Anatomical cluster made up of skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the sixth pharyngeal arch, also called fourth gill or branchial arch.

ZFA:0001229.label: pharyngeal arch 7 skeleton
ZFA:0001229.definition: Anatomical cluster made up of skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the seventh pharyngeal arch, also called fifth  gill or branchial arch.

ZFA:0007116.label: pleuroperitoneal region
ZFA:0007116.definition: An anatomical cluster composed of the organs of the  pleuroperitoneal cavity and associated structures.

ZFA:0005567.label: posterior segment eye
ZFA:0005567.definition: Anatomical cluster comprising the caudal portion of the eye: the retina, posterior chamber, optic choroid, and vitreous.

ZFA:0000098.label: proliferative region
ZFA:0000098.definition: Anatomical cluster which consists of rapidly dividing cells.

ZFA:0005227.label: protoneuromast
ZFA:0005227.definition: A group of about 20 cells deposited by the migrating lateral line primordium. A few hours after deposition these cells mature to form the neuromast.

ZFA:0000290.label: sphenoid region
ZFA:0000290.definition: Anatomical cluster that forms the floor and sidewalls of the middle part of the cranium.

ZFA:0001216.label: splanchnocranium
ZFA:0001216.definition: Anatomical cluster that is the regional skeletal system of the jaws, hyoid and branchial arches.

ZFA:0001642.label: tooth row
ZFA:0001642.definition: Anatomical cluster consisting of adjacent teeth constituting a row.

ZFA:0001273.label: ventral mandibular arch
ZFA:0001273.definition: The ventral portion of the first pharyngeal arch, comprising the lower jaw.

ZFA:0000611.label: visceromotor column
ZFA:0000611.definition: Collection of the visceromotor nuclei and their fiber tracts in the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0001480.label: dorsal anterior lateral line nerve
ZFA:0001480.definition: Lateral line nerve that originates within the dorsal anterior lateral line ganglion and innervates the otic, supraorbital, and infraorbital neuromasts.

ZFA:0001482.label: middle lateral line nerve
ZFA:0001482.definition: Nerve fibers originating from the middle lateral line ganglion.  These fibers innervate the middle lateral line.

ZFA:0001481.label: ventral anterior lateral line nerve
ZFA:0001481.definition: Lateral line nerve that originates within the ventral anterior lateral line ganglion and innervates the mandibular and opercular neuromasts.

ZFA:0005285.label: glomerular basement membrane
ZFA:0005285.definition: Membrane between the mesonephric podocytes and the renal glomerular capillaries.  It is a trilaminar structure composed of the fused basement membranes of the glomerular capillaries and basement membrane of the podocytes.  The capillary membranes touch the GBM at contact points that are separated by pores.  The membrane is semi-permeable allowing water and small molecules to pass into the renal capsular space.

ZFA:0005313.label: pronephric glomerular basement membrane
ZFA:0005313.definition: Membrane between the pronephric podocytes and the pronephric glomerular capillaries.  It is a trilaminar structure composed of the fused basement membranes of the glomerular capillaries and basement membrane of the podocytes.  The capillary membranes touch the GBM at contact points that are separated by pores.  The membrane is semi-permeable allowing water and small molecules to pass into the renal capsular space.

ZFA:0001493.label: atypical epithelium
ZFA:0001493.definition: Epithelium that consists of epithelial cells not arranged in one or more layers.

ZFA:0005783.label: cloacal epithelium
ZFA:0005783.definition: Epithelium lining the cloaca.  The epithelium is a simple cuboidal epithelium at Prim-5.

ZFA:0001687.label: corneal endothelium
ZFA:0001687.definition: Epithelium that is the innermost layer of the cornea and is comprised of a monolayer of polygonal cells.

ZFA:0001683.label: corneal epithelium
ZFA:0001683.definition: Portion of tissue comprised of four to six layers of nonkeratinized, stratified squamous cells and represents approximately 60% of the thickness of the cornea.
