ZFA:0005134.label: dental epithelium
ZFA:0005134.definition: Epithelium that is part of a developing tooth or dental organ.

ZFA:0001513.label: dermomyotome
ZFA:0001513.definition: Epithelial sheet on the external surface of the somite that gives rise to trunk, muscle and dermis.

ZFA:0000105.label: epidermis
ZFA:0000105.definition: A cellular, multilayered epithelium derived from the ectoderm. Zebrafish epidermis consists only of living cells unlike terrestrial vertebrates in which dead, keratinized cells are present.

ZFA:0005123.label: gut epithelium
ZFA:0005123.definition: Epithelium lining the lumen of the gut.

ZFA:0005780.label: immature thymic epithelium
ZFA:0005780.definition: Epithelium of the thymus primordium composed of cells of immature morphology. The immature thymic epithelium is continuous with the pharyngeal epithelium.  The immature thymic epithelium is composed of electron-lucent epithelial cells of irregular or polygonal shape and contain numerous ribosomes, large electron-lucent mitochondria, and rough endoplasmic reticulum. Nascent desmosomes join these primitive epithelial cells together.

ZFA:0001326.label: lens epithelium
ZFA:0001326.definition: Epithelium which borders the anterior and equitorial region of the lens.  Lens growth in zebrafish occurs via the differentiation of additional fibre cells from lens epithelial cells.

ZFA:0005334.label: lip epithelium
ZFA:0005334.definition: The thick, high squamous-stratified epithelium that covers the lips.  It contains abundant melanocytes, many mucous cells and has well differentiated taste buds.

ZFA:0001671.label: macula communis
ZFA:0001671.definition: Epithelium that is the primary epithelium of the developing inner ear and has anterior and posterior maculae as its parts. These maculae later move apart into distinct regions of epithelium.

ZFA:0005129.label: mesentery
ZFA:0005129.definition: A double layer composed of peritoneum that attaches the visceral organs to the body wall.

ZFA:0001494.label: multilaminar epithelium
ZFA:0001494.definition: Epithelium that consists of more than one layer of epithelial cells.

ZFA:0000554.label: olfactory epithelium
ZFA:0000554.definition: Nasal epithelium wherein ciliated olfactory receptor neurons, supporting cells, and basal cells are located.  The olfactory epithelium bowl-shaped structures surrounding the lumen of the olfactory pit.

ZFA:0000816.label: oral epithelium
ZFA:0000816.definition: The epithelium that lines the oral cavity.  The oral epithelium epithelial cells with many short microvilli as well as mucous cells, rodlet cells and taste buds.

ZFA:0007068.label: otic epithelium
ZFA:0007068.definition: Is an epithelium of the auditory apparatus.

ZFA:0001185.label: periderm
ZFA:0001185.definition: The outermost epidermal layer covering the fish at embryonic stages; derived from the EVL and thought to eventually be replaced by the superficial stratum of the epidermis. Sometimes used synonymously with EVL.

ZFA:0001389.label: regeneration epithelium
ZFA:0001389.definition: Epithelium of the regenerating fin that is formed as part of the healing process.

ZFA:0000144.label: retinal pigmented epithelium
ZFA:0000144.definition: A monolayer of pigmented epithelium covering the neural retina; develops from the outer of the two layers of the optic cup.

ZFA:0005880.label: seminiferous epithelium
ZFA:0005880.definition: Epithelium that lines the seminiferous tubules.

ZFA:0005779.label: thymic epithelium
ZFA:0005779.definition: Epithelium within the thymus where lymphocytes mature.  Cells of the thymic epithelium have cytoplasm that appear devoid of most membrane bound organelles but contain bundles of cytoplasmic filaments, and frequent desmosomes occur between these epithelial cells. There are also secretory epithelial cells that contain a  heterogeneous population of electron-dense, cytoplasmic granules and a well developed Golgi complex.   Epithelial cysts are present after 3 weeks.

ZFA:0001077.label: thymus primordium
ZFA:0001077.definition: A small outgrowth of the pharyngeal epithelium that is the site of lymphocyte cell production.

ZFA:0001495.label: unilaminar epithelium
ZFA:0001495.definition: Epithelium that consists of a single layer of epithelial cells.

ZFA:0005564.label: aqueous humor
ZFA:0005564.definition: Clear ocular fluid in the anterior segment of the eye.  It is produced primarily by dorsal ciliary epithelial cells.

ZFA:0005857.label: bile
ZFA:0005857.definition: Zebrafish bile contains the bile alcohol cyprinol sulfate.

ZFA:0000007.label: blood
ZFA:0000007.definition: A complex mixture of cells suspended in a liquid matrix that delivers nutrients to cells and removes wastes.

ZFA:0005654.label: blood plasma
ZFA:0005654.definition: Portion of organism substance that is the liquid matrix of blood.

ZFA:0001626.label: cerebral spinal fluid
ZFA:0001626.definition: Portion of organism substance that is a clear fluid that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain.

ZFA:0005803.label: cupula
ZFA:0005803.definition: Gelatinous substance surrounding the kinocila of the neuromast.

ZFA:0005414.label: endolymph
ZFA:0005414.definition: The portion of organism substance that is an extracellular fluid that has a high potassium and sodium concentration. It bathes the hair cells and is thought to be generated by the semicircular canal epithelium.

ZFA:0005800.label: extracellular lipid lamellae
ZFA:0005800.definition: Portion of organism substance that is located between the cap and second tier layers of the breeding tubercles.  The lipid lamellae is composed of lipids.

ZFA:0005658.label: lymph
ZFA:0005658.definition: Portion of organism substance found in the lymphatic system.  Lymph usually consists of interstitial fluid that has made its way into the lymphatic system.

ZFA:0001617.label: otolith
ZFA:0001617.definition: Portion of organism substance composed of calcium carbonate located in the otolith organ and positioned over a sensory macula; two form in each vesicle during the late segmentation period. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for otolith by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0005413.label: perilymph
ZFA:0005413.definition: Portion of organism substance that is an extracellular fluid that has a low potassium concentration.

ZFA:0005154.label: synovial fluid
ZFA:0005154.definition: Portion of organism substance that is a clear fluid that occupies the space in synovial joints.

ZFA:0005913.label: urine
ZFA:0005913.definition: Organism substance that is the output of the nephron.

ZFA:0005561.label: vitreous
ZFA:0005561.definition: Portion of organism substance that is a gelatinous extracellular matrix structure that fills the vitreous cavity of the eye.

ZFA:0005573.label: zonule
ZFA:0005573.definition: Modified or toughened vitreous that suspend the lens at the equator to the non-pigmented epithelium of the ciliary zone.  In zebrafish, dorsal zonules are thickened as compared to ventral zonules. In both dorsal and ventral regions, these fibers delimit the vitreous body aqueous humor boundary.

ZFA:0007077.label: accessory chamber of the maxillary blood sinus
ZFA:0007077.definition: Is a multi-tissue structure part of the maxillary barbel blood sinus which is connected to the central chamber of the maxillary blood sinus by a slight isthmus. It is not muscularized, has no dense connective tissue capsule and is not attached to adjacent bone. Is composed of dark tunica intima wrapped by thick, light tunica adventitia; cells within the adventitia are widely separated, with extended cytoplasmic veils. External to the adventitia, a branch of the facial nerve and several smaller nerve bundles appear in cross section just lateral to the isthmus. These nerves are in the dermis, but outside the sinus.

ZFA:0001282.label: adenohypophysis
ZFA:0001282.definition: The anterior lobe of the hypophysis (pituitary gland). This lobe contains cells that produce prolactin, growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone and proopiomelanocortin. In contrast to mammalian vertebrates, the adenohypophysis remains in a subepithelial position and there exists no equivalent of Rathke's pouch in zebrafish.

ZFA:0001277.label: anterior chamber swim bladder
ZFA:0001277.definition: The anterior compartment of the swim bladder is thought to have acoustic resonance properties that play a key role in audition.  It is connected to the posterior chamber via the ductus communicans.

ZFA:0005683.label: anteromedial  zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005683.definition: Anterior portion of the medial region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0001315.label: atrioventricular canal
ZFA:0001315.definition: The part of the heart connecting the atrium to the cardiac ventricle.

ZFA:0007072.label: blood sinus
ZFA:0007072.definition: Is a multitissue structure that accumulates blood.

ZFA:0005314.label: blood vessel
ZFA:0005314.definition: Any of the tubular multi-tissue structures through which blood circulates in the body.

ZFA:0001707.label: brainstem
ZFA:0001707.definition: Multi-tissue structure that has as its parts the medulla oblongata of the hindbrain and the tegmentum of the midbrain.

ZFA:0000173.label: bulbus arteriosus
ZFA:0000173.definition: Multi-tissue structure that consists of three layers and through which the blood exits the heart. The bulbus arteriosus is a pear shaped chamber that functions as a capacitor, maintaining continuous blood flow into the gill arches.

ZFA:0005068.label: bulbus arteriosus inner layer
ZFA:0005068.definition: Composed of subendothelium with longitudinally oriented collagen, reticular fibrils, elastic fibers, and smooth muscle cells bound by a thin endothelial layer.

ZFA:0005067.label: bulbus arteriosus middle layer
ZFA:0005067.definition: Composed of 7-10 layers of helically arranged smooth muscle cells surrounded by a fine network of collagen, reticular, and elastic fibrils.

ZFA:0000634.label: caudal hypothalamic zone
ZFA:0000634.definition: Multi-tissue structure which forms most of the median tuberal portion of the hypothalamus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000479.label: caudal mesencephalo-cerebellar tract
ZFA:0000479.definition: Brainstem tract which carries cerebellar afferents from the dorsal tegmental nucleus and nucleus lateralis valvulae. Fuses with the rostral mesencephalo-cerebellar tract upon entering the cerebellum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000633.label: caudal tuberculum
ZFA:0000633.definition: Brain structure which is part of the diencephalon and is larger than the dorsal thalamus and ventral thalamus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000938.label: central canal
ZFA:0000938.definition: Spinal cord structure that is part of the ventricular system and is filled with cerebral-spinal fluid and runs the length of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0007076.label: central chamber of the maxillary blood sinus
ZFA:0007076.definition: Is a multi-tissue structure that is located outside the maxillary barbel proper and is positioned on the lateral surface of the maxilla, medially attached to the lateral surface of the maxillary bone and is laterally is attached to a hemispheric capsule of dense connective tissue of the distal bulb. It connects with the smaller accessory chamber through a slight isthmus.  It has a smooth muscle tunic from which extend luminally projecting muscular septa.

ZFA:0000183.label: central pretectum
ZFA:0000183.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the central part of the pretectum.

ZFA:0000327.label: central zone of the optic tectum

ZFA:0005673.label: central zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005673.definition: Central region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0000694.label: ceratobranchial 5 tooth
ZFA:0000694.definition: Is a multi-tissue structure composed of dentine, enameloid and tooth pulp. The tips of the ceratobranchial5 teeth form before the ceratobranchial itself (3.0 mm NL). As they grow ventrally, they meet the perichondrally ossified surface of ceratobranchial5 and become firmly ankylosed to the bone. Ceratobranchial teeth are the only teeth present in zebrafish and other cypriniforms.

ZFA:0005869.label: cerebellar plate
ZFA:0005869.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is made up of the external granular layer and the ventral proliferative layer.

ZFA:0000100.label: cerebellum
ZFA:0000100.definition: Brain structure derived from the anterior hindbrain, and perhaps including posterior midbrain. The cerebellum plays a role in somatic motor function, the control of muscle tone, and balance. In zebrafish, with the exception of the cerebellum, the ventral remainder of the metencephalon can be separated only arbitrarily from the more caudal myelencephalic portion of the medulla oblongata and thus these are not distinguished here.

ZFA:0001203.label: ciliary zone
ZFA:0001203.definition: Multi-tissue structure that attach the zonules, that suspend the lens, to the eye.  The ciliary zone secretes aqueous humor.  Unlike mammals zebrafish the ciliary zone dose not contain processes or a circumferential band of muscle.

ZFA:0005781.label: cloaca
ZFA:0005781.definition: Part of the gut where the pronephric tubules come together with the caudal end of the intestine attaching at 4dpf.  The oviduct or sperm duct connect later.

ZFA:0001438.label: coelom
ZFA:0001438.definition: Anatomical space, part of the trunk that contains the pericardial and pleuroperitoneal cavities.

ZFA:0001489.label: compound organ component
ZFA:0001489.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of a compound organ.

ZFA:0000640.label: cornea
ZFA:0000640.definition: Multi-tissue structure that forms the transparent front part of the eye, covering the iris, pupil and anterior chamber.

ZFA:0000188.label: corpus cerebelli
ZFA:0000188.definition: Brain structure which is one of three parts of the cerebellum and is the entry point for a posterior cerebellar tract that carries cerebellar afferents from many brain stem nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000334.label: corpus mamillare
ZFA:0000334.definition: Brain structure which is located ventrolaterally to the caudal preglomerular nucleus and in the dorsomedial aspect of the caudal protrusion of the inferior lobe of the hypothalamus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005138.label: dental organ
ZFA:0005138.definition: A structure that is involved in tooth formation.  A bell shape two layer  epithelial structure that descends toward the ceratobranchial 5 bone, enclosing the dental mesenchyme.  At later times in tooth development the cells at the apex of the bell may be involved in enameloid formation.  This structure remains at the base of the erupted tooth and is the source of replacement teeth.

ZFA:0001183.label: dermal superficial region
ZFA:0001183.definition: Outer portion of the dermis composed of a loose collagenous matrix housing numerous fibroblasts, nerves, some pigment cells, and scales.  Scale development takes place in this layer of the dermis.

ZFA:0001119.label: dermis
ZFA:0001119.definition: A collagenous layer of the skin subjacent to the epidermis and covering the hypodermis. It contains various types of cells (e.g. fibroblasts, pigment cells, nerve, blood vessels and scales.

ZFA:0001659.label: diencephalic nucleus
ZFA:0001659.definition: Brain nucleus part of the diencephalon.

ZFA:0000101.label: diencephalon
ZFA:0000101.definition: The more posterior and ventral of two forebrain neuromeres, the other being the telencephalon; major derivatives are the eye cups, the brain pretectal region, the thalamus, hypothalamus, and epithalamus (including the habenula and epiphysis).

ZFA:0007075.label: distal bulb of the maxillary blood sinus
ZFA:0007075.definition: Is a multi-tissue structure forming the smallest chamber of the maxillary barbel blood sinus. It projects into the barbel shaft and has a blood filled lumen, into which extend irregular septa of vascular smooth muscle cells. Additional smooth muscle cells surround the lumen and attach the bulb to the barbel core. Circumferential to the core, there is a thin band of dermal tissue through with run several smaller capillaries and the barbel branch of the of the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII).  The entire structure is wrapped by a glandular, stratified epithelium.

ZFA:0000102.label: dorsal fin fold
ZFA:0000102.definition: Region of the median fin fold that develops into the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0000347.label: dorsal hypothalamic zone
ZFA:0000347.definition: Brain structure which is the dorsal most region of the hypothalamus and expands laterally and emerges caudal to the ventral zone and is separated from the median tuberal portion by a deep ventral sulcus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000199.label: dorsal periventricular hypothalamus
ZFA:0000199.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the dorsal hypothalamic zone and is located periventricularly. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000505.label: dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000505.definition: Brain structure which is the dorsal part of the telencephalon, most of which is developmentally everted such that the ependymal lining of the unpaired median ventricle becomes located at the apparent periphery of the telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000653.label: dorsal thalamus
ZFA:0000653.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the dorsal part of the thalamus and emerges ventral to the caudal portion of the ventral habenular nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005674.label: dorsal zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005674.definition: Dorsal region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005678.label: dorsolateral zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005678.definition: Lateral region of the dorsal zone of the olfactory bulb. Glomeruli in this zone are tightly clustered in both male and female fish.

ZFA:0005171.label: duct
ZFA:0005171.definition: A tube shaped multi-tissue structure lined with epithelial cells that collects secretions and routes them to their destination.

ZFA:0000019.label: epiphysis
ZFA:0000019.definition: A circumscribed swelling, includes the pineal primordium that appears late in the segmentation period in the dorsal midline of the diencephalon.  It is located directly rostral to the posterior commissure and dorsal to the habenular commissure.

ZFA:0000509.label: epithalamus
ZFA:0000509.definition: Brain structure which is part of the diencephalon and consists of the dorsal and ventral nuclei of the habenula, and two dorsal outgrowths, the epiphysis and the saccus dorsalis. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000204.label: esophagus
ZFA:0000204.definition: Esophagus part of the gut that develops from endodermal precursors at the rostral end of the digestive tract.  The esophagus develops independently from the intestine.

ZFA:0001249.label: exocrine pancreas
ZFA:0001249.definition: The exocrine pancreas is a diffuse organ composed of a branching network of ducts and associated acinar glands that manufacture the proteolytic enzymes and bicarbonate required for digestion.

ZFA:0005316.label: fin fold pectoral fin bud
ZFA:0005316.definition: Fin fold of the pectoral fin bud, resulting from mesenchyme migration into the apical fold.

ZFA:0000022.label: floor plate
ZFA:0000022.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the ventral-most aspect of the developing neural tube.  The floor plate is a specialized glial structure with secretory function that spans the rostral-caudal axis from the midbrain to the tail regions.  The floor plate is one of first structures that differentiate in the developing nervous system.

ZFA:0000871.label: floor plate diencephalic region
ZFA:0000871.definition: Floor plate that is part of the diencephalon.

ZFA:0001677.label: floor plate midbrain region
ZFA:0001677.definition: Floor plate that is part of the midbrain.

ZFA:0000887.label: floor plate neural rod
ZFA:0000887.definition: Floor plate that is part of the neural rod.

ZFA:0001434.label: floor plate neural tube
ZFA:0001434.definition: Floor plate that is part of the neural tube.

ZFA:0000882.label: floor plate rhombomere 1
ZFA:0000882.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 1.

ZFA:0000763.label: floor plate rhombomere 2
ZFA:0000763.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0000888.label: floor plate rhombomere 3
ZFA:0000888.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 3.

ZFA:0000893.label: floor plate rhombomere 4
ZFA:0000893.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 4.

ZFA:0000764.label: floor plate rhombomere 5
ZFA:0000764.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 5.

ZFA:0000889.label: floor plate rhombomere 6
ZFA:0000889.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 6.

ZFA:0000904.label: floor plate rhombomere 7
ZFA:0000904.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 7.

ZFA:0000765.label: floor plate rhombomere 8
ZFA:0000765.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0001258.label: floor plate rhombomere region
ZFA:0001258.definition: Floor plate that is part of the rhombomeres.

ZFA:0000890.label: floor plate spinal cord region
ZFA:0000890.definition: Floor plate that is part of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0000914.label: floor plate telencephalic region
ZFA:0000914.definition: Floor plate that is part of the telencephalon.

ZFA:0000109.label: forebrain
ZFA:0000109.definition: The most anterior region the brain including both the telencephalon and diencephalon.

ZFA:0000211.label: gill lamella
ZFA:0000211.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the transverse vertical platelet on the gill filament, through which capillaries run. The primary gill lamellae carry numerous fine layers called secondary lamellae which are the actual regions of respiration and excretion.

ZFA:0000357.label: glomerular layer
ZFA:0000357.definition: Multi-tissue structure which is located in between the primary olfactory fiber layer and the external cellular layer of the olfactory bulb. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000212.label: granular eminence
ZFA:0000212.definition: Brain structure which is paired and part of the vestibulolateralis lobe of the cerebellum and extends fibers into the cerebellar crest. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001681.label: grey matter
ZFA:0001681.definition: Multi-tissue comprised of neurons, dendrites, axon terminals, glial cells, and capillaries.

ZFA:0000213.label: habenula
ZFA:0000213.definition: The habenula relays impulses from limbic areas of the telencephalon to an unpaired midbrain nucleus, the interpeduncular nucleus.

ZFA:0005065.label: heart valve
ZFA:0005065.definition: Multi-tissue structure composed of leaflets that separate parts of the heart, preventing blood backflow.

ZFA:0000029.label: hindbrain
ZFA:0000029.definition: The most posterior of the three principal regions of the brain. In mammals and birds the hindbrain is divided into a rostral metencephalon and a caudal myelencephalon. In zebrafish, with the exception of the cerebellum, the ventral remainder of the metencephalon can be separated only arbitrarily from the more caudal myelencephalic portion of the medulla oblongata and thus these are not distinguished here. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000032.label: hypothalamus
ZFA:0000032.definition: Multi-tissue structure which is the largest portion of diencephalon and is ventrally located. The hypothalamus arises near the end of the segmentation period and the embryonic hypothalamic region gives rise to the neurohypophysis and other diencephalic nuclei.

ZFA:0001678.label: immature eye
ZFA:0001678.definition: Multi-tissue structure that consists of the structures that develop into the retina and lens.

ZFA:0005272.label: immature gonad
ZFA:0005272.definition: Immature reproductive tissue that has not undergone final maturation into either testis or ovary. During gonadal development, the gonad may be  transiently intersexual where there is a  parallel presence of both oocytes and spermatocytes.

ZFA:0000165.label: inferior lobe
ZFA:0000165.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is a paired nucleus located in the lateral expansion of the dorsal hypothalamic zone.

ZFA:0001199.label: infundibulum
ZFA:0001199.definition: Brain structure which is a short stalk connecting the neurohypophysis with the brain. Axons of secretory cells in the floor of the diencephalon traverse the infundibulum and terminate in the neurohypophysis.

ZFA:0006000.label: intermediate hypothalamus
ZFA:0006000.definition: Brain structure that lies perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the embryonic neural tube, is continuous with the rostral hypothalamic proliferation and whose most lateral extent is deflected dorsally within the inferior lobe.

ZFA:0001345.label: interrenal gland
ZFA:0001345.definition: An bilobed multi-tissue structure lateral to the notochord composed of an epithelium consisting of steroid producing cells interposed with chromaffin cells.  The interrenal gland is embedded within the head kidney.  The interrenal gland is the zebrafish functional equivalent of the mammalian adrenal cortex.

ZFA:0001346.label: interrenal primordium
ZFA:0001346.definition: Multi-tissue structure located in the kidney that develops into the interrenal gland.

ZFA:0001076.label: intestinal bulb
ZFA:0001076.definition: The bulbous anteriormost portion of the intestine has the most digestive enzymes and the greatest epithelial surface area.

ZFA:0005659.label: intestinal lamina propria mucosa
ZFA:0005659.definition: Thin layer of loose connective tissue which lies beneath the intestinal  epithelium. The intestinal lamina propria is less complex then the corresponding mammalian tissue.

ZFA:0005660.label: intestinal mucosa
ZFA:0005660.definition: Multi-tissue structure of the intestine comprising of the intestinal epithelium and the intestinal lamina propria mucosa.

ZFA:0005737.label: intestinal rod
ZFA:0005737.definition: Multicellular structure composed of endodermal cells that forms a continuous rod along the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo in contact with the YSL.  This rod will give rise to the endodermal components of the alimentary canal and its connected organs: liver, gall bladder pancreas and swim bladder. Does not have part pharyngeal endoderm.

ZFA:0001238.label: iris
ZFA:0001238.definition: Multi-tissue structure that consists of pigmented stroma and is connected to a sphincter muscle and a dilator muscle which open and close the pupil located in the center of the iris.

ZFA:0005707.label: lGx
ZFA:0005707.definition: Group of glomerulus located in the lateral region of the olfactory bulb. The  glomeruli that compose lGx are smaller than the lG1-6 and varied in shape, sizes, and locations between olfactory bulbs of the same and different animals. The lGx were located either along the ventral edge of the lateral group or below the lateral olfactory bulb surface.

ZFA:0000374.label: lagena
ZFA:0000374.definition: Otolith organ comprised of the macula lagena and asteriscus.  The lagena is part of the pars inferior. The lagena functions in the detection of sound.

ZFA:0000532.label: lateral valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0000532.definition: Lateral division of the valvula cerebelli.

ZFA:0000780.label: lateral wall diencephalic region
ZFA:0000780.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the diencephalic region of the neural tube.

ZFA:0000906.label: lateral wall midbrain region
ZFA:0000906.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the midbrain region of the neural tube.

ZFA:0000781.label: lateral wall rhombomere 1
ZFA:0000781.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 1.

ZFA:0000907.label: lateral wall rhombomere 2
ZFA:0000907.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0000994.label: lateral wall rhombomere 3
ZFA:0000994.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 3.

ZFA:0000782.label: lateral wall rhombomere 4
ZFA:0000782.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 4.

ZFA:0000908.label: lateral wall rhombomere 5
ZFA:0000908.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 5.

ZFA:0000995.label: lateral wall rhombomere 6
ZFA:0000995.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 6.

ZFA:0000783.label: lateral wall rhombomere 7
ZFA:0000783.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 7.

ZFA:0000909.label: lateral wall rhombomere 8
ZFA:0000909.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the neural tube in rhombomere 8.

ZFA:0000996.label: lateral wall spinal cord
ZFA:0000996.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0000785.label: lateral wall telencephalic region
ZFA:0000785.definition: Multi-tissue structure forming the sides of the lumen of the telencephalic region of the neural tube.

ZFA:0005675.label: lateral zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005675.definition: Lateral region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The lateral region of the olfactory bulb consisted of morphologically diverse glomeruli and a diffuse aggregate of OSN axons, the lateral plexus.

ZFA:0005172.label: left liver lobe
ZFA:0005172.definition: Portion of the liver which develops on the fish's left side.

ZFA:0001441.label: lower rhombic lip
ZFA:0001441.definition: Posterior portion of the rhombic lip contained within rhombomeres 2-8.  Gives rise to several brainstem nuclei and choroid plexus.

ZFA:0005844.label: lymph vessel
ZFA:0005844.definition: Any of the tubular multi-tissue structures through which lymph moves in the body. These vessels collect and drain fluids and macromolecules from interstitial spaces throughout the animal.

ZFA:0005716.label: maGx
ZFA:0005716.definition: Group of small glomeruli located in the anteromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. The arrangements of glomeruli maGx varies between animals and they can't be identified as individual units.

ZFA:0000388.label: medial caudal lobe
ZFA:0000388.definition: Brain structure which is part of the vestibulolateralis lobe of the cerebellum. The medial caudal lobe receives primary octaval (presumably vestibular) as well as lateral line projections. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000280.label: medial valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0000280.definition: Medial division of the valvula cerebelli.

ZFA:0005676.label: medial zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005676.definition: Medial region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0000392.label: median tuberal portion
ZFA:0000392.definition: Multi-tissue structure which is part of the hypothalamus and consists of caudal and ventral zones, and is separated from the dorsal hypothalamic zone by a deep ventral sulcus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005682.label: mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005682.definition: Dorsal part of the medial region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0000545.label: medulla oblongata
ZFA:0000545.definition: Brain structure that is located ventrocaudal to the cerebellum and just anterior to the spinal cord and contains the sensory and motor nuclei of six cranial nerves. In zebrafish, with the exception of the cerebellum, the ventral remainder of the metencephalon can be separated only arbitrarily from the more caudal myelencephalic portion of the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0001323.label: mid intestine
ZFA:0001323.definition: The terminal region of the mid intestine is comprised of specialized enterocytes that appear to play a role in mucosal immunity.  The mid intestine also appears to be involved in iron absorption.

ZFA:0000128.label: midbrain
ZFA:0000128.definition: The brain region between the forebrain anteriorly and the hindbrain posteriorly, including the tectum dorsally and the midbrain tegmentum ventrally.

ZFA:0005507.label: nasal capsule
ZFA:0005507.definition: Multi-tissue structure composed of connective tissue that surrounds, the internal portions of the olfactory epithelium.

ZFA:0000402.label: olfactory bulb
ZFA:0000402.definition: Brain structure which is the paired anteriormost part of the telencephalon and are connected to the telencephalon by two tracts carrying secondary olfactory fibers. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.  The olfactory bulb is a paired structure.

ZFA:0005661.label: olfactory bulb glomerulus
ZFA:0005661.definition: Multi-tissue structure part of the olfactory bulb  that  is roughly spheroidal and encircled by olfactory sensory neuron axons that formed an anatomically distinct stalk  connected to the olfactory nerve.

ZFA:0005668.label: olfactory bulb protoglomerulus
ZFA:0005668.definition: Multi-tissue structure part of the olfactory bulb comprised of ciliated and microvillous olfactory sensory neurons projections that form specialized neuropilar regions comprised of olfactory sensor axons and the dendrites of olfactory bulb neurons.

ZFA:0001202.label: optic cup
ZFA:0001202.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is comprised of neural and non-neural epithelial layers which will form the retina and retinal pigmented epithelium of the mature eye.

ZFA:0000445.label: optic tectum
ZFA:0000445.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the dorsal part of the midbrain and develops from the alar plate and is the most complex layered structure in the zebrafish brain.

ZFA:0001110.label: ovarian follicle
ZFA:0001110.definition: Oocyte development of zebrafish has been divided into five stages based on morphological criteria and on physiological and biochemical events. Stage I follicles (less than 140 microns) are primary growth stage, stage II follicles (140-340 microns) are cortical alveolus stage, stage III (340-690 microns) are vitellogenesis, stage IV (690-730 microns) are oocyte maturation, and stage V follicles are matured egg.

ZFA:0005317.label: pectoral fin fold
ZFA:0005317.definition: The functional webs of the paired fins.  They arise as a consequence of apical fold (AER) expansion and of migration of the distal mesenchyme. The fin folds are delimited by a dorsal and a ventral striated epidermis. The cells of the epidermal basal stratum are positioned on a basement membrane. Directly beneath the basement membrane of each side there is an array of actinotrichs, fibers of the extracellular matrix which act as supportive elements of the larval fin folds.

ZFA:0001306.label: pharyngeal arch
ZFA:0001306.definition: One of a series of paired bony or cartilaginous arches that develop along the lateral walls of the foregut. The pharyngeal arches have developmental contributions from endoderm, mesoderm, and neural crest cells and are separated by anterior lateral endoderm out-pockets known as pharyngeal pouches. There are seven pharyngeal arches.

ZFA:0001106.label: pharyngeal pouch
ZFA:0001106.definition: Outpocketings of pharyngeal endoderm that interdigitate with the neural crest derived pharyngeal arches. The pouches later fuse with the surface ectoderm to form the gill slits.

ZFA:0000056.label: pharynx
ZFA:0000056.definition: Swollen region of the anterior foregut, posterior to the mouth and anterior to the liver; its walls form the jaws and gills.

ZFA:0001278.label: posterior chamber swim bladder
ZFA:0001278.definition: The posterior compartment of the swim bladder plays a key role in buoyancy control.  It is connected to the anterior chamber via the ductus communicans.  This chamber corresponds to the swim bladder found in larval fish.

ZFA:0000706.label: posterior intestine
ZFA:0000706.definition: The posterior intestine has short longitudinally arranged epithelial folds which are similar to the colon of higher vertebrates.

ZFA:0000470.label: preoptic area
ZFA:0000470.definition: Area of the forebrain anterior to the posterior tuberculum and the hypothalamus and ventral to the ventral thalamus. See Figure 7, p. 34 in Atlas of Early Zebrafish Brain Development.

ZFA:0001718.label: presumptive atrium heart tube
ZFA:0001718.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the heart tube and will become the cardiac atrium.

ZFA:0001721.label: presumptive atrium primitive heart tube
ZFA:0001721.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the primitive heart tube and will become the cardiac atrium.

ZFA:0001719.label: presumptive cardiac ventricle heart tube
ZFA:0001719.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the heart tube and will become the cardiac ventricle.

ZFA:0001720.label: presumptive cardiac ventricle primitive heart tube
ZFA:0001720.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the primitive heart tube and will become the cardiac ventricle.

ZFA:0000418.label: pretectum
ZFA:0000418.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the dorsal part of the diencephalon, caudal to the telencephalon, rostral to the midbrain optic tectum; the major sensory input to the pretectum is visual. From The Laboratory Fish.

ZFA:0000149.label: primitive heart tube
ZFA:0000149.definition: Multi-tissue structure that arises from the heart rudiment and will become the heart tube.

ZFA:0001355.label: primitive meninx
ZFA:0001355.definition: The vascularized fibrous sheath that surrounds the central nervous system.

ZFA:0001557.label: pronephric glomerulus
ZFA:0001557.definition: Paired highly vascularized structures of the pronephros which are fused at the midline.  Responsible for blood filtration and begins to function between 40 and 48hpf.

ZFA:0005500.label: prootic bulla
ZFA:0005500.definition: Is a bony partially gas filled sphere located ventral and anterior to the inner ear.  The prootic bulla is paired.

ZFA:0005281.label: renal corpuscle
ZFA:0005281.definition: The part of the nephron that filters blood.

ZFA:0001288.label: renal glomerulus
ZFA:0001288.definition: The multi-tissue structure where the glomerular basement membrane supported by mesonephric podocytes, filters blood from the glomerular capillaries.

ZFA:0000152.label: retina
ZFA:0000152.definition: Multi-tissue structure that contains the retinal neural layer and the retinal pigmented epithelium, and develops from the optic cup.

ZFA:0001440.label: rhombic lip
ZFA:0001440.definition: The interface between the dorsal neuroepithelium and the roof plate of the fourth ventricle. The source of a number of migratory neuron populations of the hindbrain.

ZFA:0005173.label: right liver lobe
ZFA:0005173.definition: Portion of the liver which develops on the fish's right side adjacent to the gall bladder.

ZFA:0007058.label: roof plate
ZFA:0007058.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the dorsal-most aspect of the developing neural tube.

ZFA:0000428.label: saccule
ZFA:0000428.definition: Otolith organ comprised of the macula saccule and sagitta. The lagena is part of the pars inferior. The saccule functions in the detection of sound and movement.

ZFA:0005563.label: sclera
ZFA:0005563.definition: Multi-tissue structure that composes the opaque fibrous outer layer of the eye.

ZFA:0005879.label: seminiferous tubule
ZFA:0005879.definition: Tubules formed by the seminiferous epithelium that contains spermatogenic cyst surrounded by somatic support cells, called Sertoli cells.  The lumen of he seminiferous tubules connects to the sperm or efferent duct.

ZFA:0005443.label: sensory canal
ZFA:0005443.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is a fluid-filled canal in the integument and usually dermal bones, and contains one or more neuromasts.

ZFA:0005425.label: serous membrane
ZFA:0005425.definition: A multi-tissue structure that is comprised of a secretory epithelial layer and a connective tissue layer.

ZFA:0001492.label: simple organ
ZFA:0001492.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is not part of a compound organ.

ZFA:0000154.label: sinus venosus
ZFA:0000154.definition: Heart region collecting blood from the paired common cardinal veins and delivering to the atrium. One of four components of the heart. The sinus venosus also acts as a pacemaker and is the first to contract.

ZFA:0005578.label: spinal nerve root
ZFA:0005578.definition: The multi-tissue structure that is the beginning of the spinal nerve leaving the spinal cord.

ZFA:0000687.label: superficial pretectum
ZFA:0000687.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the superficial part of the pretectum and is embedded in the optic tract.

ZFA:0000293.label: synencephalon
ZFA:0000293.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is located between the dorsal diencephalon and the mesencephalon and contains the caudal commissure. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001074.label: taste bud
ZFA:0001074.definition: Pear or onion-shaped intraepithelial sensory endorgans. They sit on a small dermal papilla and consist of modified epithelial cells of different types.  The taste buds are located in the mouth, in the oropharyngeal cavity, on the head and on the  barbels.  They are innervated by either the facial (VII), the glossopharyngeal (IX), or the vagal (X) cranial nerve.

ZFA:0005907.label: tectal neuropile
ZFA:0005907.definition: Neuronal tissue that is the arborization field for the majority of the ganglion cell axons,  it also holds other incoming axons, for example, from the pretectum and the contralateral tectum, as well as the dendrites and axons of tectal interneurons and projection neurons.

ZFA:0000160.label: tegmentum
ZFA:0000160.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the ventral part of the midbrain and develops from the basal plate. The tegmentum is bordered rostrally by the synencephalon, dorsal thalamus and posterior tuberculum, ventrally by the hypothalamus, and dorsolaterally by the torus semicircularis; caudally the tegmentum is continuous with the medulla oblongata.

ZFA:0000079.label: telencephalon
ZFA:0000079.definition: The anterior and dorsal forebrain neuromere. In ray-finned fishes and most pronounced in teleosts the roof plate of the embryonic telencephalon extends laterally with the effect that the paired alar plates forming the hemispheric walls roll out lateroventrally in a process called eversion. This is unlike the development in other vertebrate groups. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0007010.label: thalamic eminence
ZFA:0007010.definition: Part of the forebrain that is ventral to the ventral thalamus and dorsal to the preoptic area. See page 44 of the Atlas of Early Zebrafish Brain Development.

ZFA:0001215.label: thalamus
ZFA:0001215.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is paired, and is situated one on either side of and forming part of the lateral wall of the third ventricle.

ZFA:0001113.label: thecal cell layer
ZFA:0001113.definition: Multi-tissue structure of the ovarian follicle, composed of stromal cells and capillaries that covers oocytes.  The thecal layer is external to the granulosa cell layer.

ZFA:0005333.label: tongue
ZFA:0005333.definition: A multi-tissue mediosagittal cylinder-shaped structure, clearly isolated from the jaw and adhered by differentiated plicae to the lateral walls.  It is composed of a muscle surrounded by a squamous epithelium.

ZFA:0005141.label: tooth pulp
ZFA:0005141.definition: Material in the center of the dentine of the mature tooth.  In secondary teeth the pulp contains blood vessels and odontoblast.

ZFA:0000449.label: torus longitudinalis
ZFA:0000449.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is a paired longitudinal eminence of granular cells that develops from the alar plate and is attached to the tegmentum in the medial tectal ventricle. The torus longitudinalis only occurs in ray finned fishes.

ZFA:0000599.label: torus semicircularis
ZFA:0000599.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the midbrain and develops from the alar plate. The torus semicircularis is located dorsal to the lateral tegmentum where it extends into the medial tectal ventricle and receives ascending sensory octavolateralis input.

ZFA:0001700.label: tunica externa swim bladder
ZFA:0001700.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the external layer of the swim bladder that is covered by the peritoneum, and made of elastic fibres and ichthyocol (short needles of collagen).

ZFA:0001701.label: tunica interna swim bladder
ZFA:0001701.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is the internal layer of the swim bladder and is comprised of thin endoderm and a smooth muscle layer called the muscularis mucosa with longitudinal and circular fibres with some collagen.

ZFA:0001448.label: ultimobranchial body
ZFA:0001448.definition: Glands that produce calcitonin.  In adult fish the glands lie as two groups of follicles at the transverse septum close to the sinus venosus.

ZFA:0001442.label: upper rhombic lip
ZFA:0001442.definition: Anterior-most region of dorsal hindbrain within rhombomere 1, adjacent the midbrain-hindbrain boundary.

ZFA:0000700.label: utricle
ZFA:0000700.definition: Otolith organ comprised of the macula utricle and lapillus. The lagena is part of the pars superior. The utricle functions in the detection of movement.

ZFA:0000297.label: vagal lobe
ZFA:0000297.definition: The multi-tissue,  vagal lobe is a large, paired brain stem structure flanking the unpaired facial lobe laterally.  The vagal lobe contains motor and gustatory neurons. While some degree of histological segregation is apparent within the vagal lobe, a clear lamination, as seen in goldfish or carp is absent.

ZFA:0000603.label: valvula cerebelli
ZFA:0000603.definition: Brain structure which is caudally attached to the rostral medulla oblongata and extends into the tectal ventricle. The valvula cerebelli consists of a granular and a molecular layer along with aggregations of large Purkinje and eurydendroid cells and is uniquely present in ray-finned fishes. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005249.label: vasculature
ZFA:0005249.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the organism.

ZFA:0001069.label: ventral fin fold
ZFA:0001069.definition: Region of the median fin fold that develops into the anal and caudal fin.

ZFA:0000707.label: ventral hypothalamic zone
ZFA:0000707.definition: Multi-tissue structure which is the ventral region of the median tuberal portion of the hypothalamus and is the most rostral region of the hypothalamus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005174.label: ventral liver lobe
ZFA:0005174.definition: Portion of the liver which develops on the fish's ventral side.

ZFA:0000304.label: ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000304.definition: Brain structure which is the ventral part of the telencephalon and is consists of periventricular nuclei surrounding the unpaired median ventricle and those which have migrated away from the ependyma. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005677.label: ventral zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005677.definition: Ventral region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005680.label: ventroanterior zone of olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005680.definition: Anterior portion of the ventral region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb. In the ventroanterior zone there are  typically seven small glomeruli located 11-20 micrometers beneath the superficial axon bundles  The ganglion differed conspicuously in sizes, shapes, and distribution, and were not individually  identifiable.

ZFA:0005679.label: ventromedial zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005679.definition: Medial portion of the ventral region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005681.label: ventroposterior zone olfactory bulb
ZFA:0005681.definition: Posterior portion of the ventral region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0000307.label: vestibulolateralis lobe
ZFA:0000307.definition: Brain structure which is part of the cerebellum consists of the paired granular eminentia and the medial caudal lobe. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005698.label: vmGx
ZFA:0005698.definition: Group of glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb The vmGx group, is  located 10-50 micrometers from the ventral surface of the olfactory bulb. And were located anywhere between the posteroventral and anteroventral regions of the olfactory bulb. It was not possible to unambiguously identify the vmGx because they displayed varying distributions and numbers in the olfactory bulbs of different animals.

ZFA:0005699.label: vmGy
ZFA:0005699.definition: Group of glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. A cluster of comparatively small glomeruli located near the midline between the two olfactory bulbs The glomeruli in the  vmGy were among the smallest glomeruli in the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0001682.label: white matter
ZFA:0001682.definition: Multi-tissue structure comprised largely of myelinated axons.

ZFA:0001260.label: endocrine pancreas
ZFA:0001260.definition: The zebrafish endocrine pancreas is an compound organ component composed of small groups of islet cells that are distributed throughout the exocrine pancreas.  The islet cells produce insulin, glucagon and somatostatin.

ZFA:0000471.label: atrium
ZFA:0000471.definition: Cavitated compound organ that receives inflow of deoxygenated blood and delivers it to a muscular cardiac ventricle. Valves are present to direct flow. There are only two chambers present in the fish heart.

ZFA:0001079.label: blood vasculature
ZFA:0001079.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains blood that is actively transported around the organism.

ZFA:0000008.label: brain
ZFA:0000008.definition: Cavitated compound organ which is comprised of gray and white matter and surrounds the cerebral ventricular system.

ZFA:0000009.label: cardiac ventricle
ZFA:0000009.definition: Cavitated compound organ that receives blood flow from the atrium and delivers blood to the body via the aorta. Valves are present to direct flow. There are only two chambers present in the fish heart.

ZFA:0000107.label: eye
ZFA:0000107.definition: Cavitated compound organ that consists of the neural retina, lens, cornea and iris and is the sensory apparatus of the visual system.

ZFA:0000413.label: gonad
ZFA:0000413.definition: The part of the reproductive system that produces and releases eggs (ovary) or sperm (testis).

ZFA:0000114.label: heart
ZFA:0000114.definition: Blood pumping organ composed of four components: sinus venosus, atrium, cardiac ventricle and bulbus arteriosus.

ZFA:0000360.label: heart tube
ZFA:0000360.definition: Cavitated compound organ that will become the adult heart following looping morphogenesis and valve formation.

ZFA:0001338.label: intestine
ZFA:0001338.definition: Folded tube that has parts intestinal bulb, mid intestine and posterior intestine.  The intestine is where digestion and nutrient absorption occurs.

ZFA:0000529.label: kidney
ZFA:0000529.definition: Cavitated compound organ located in the pleuroperitoneal cavity where hematopoiesis and filtering of blood occur.

ZFA:0000559.label: otolith organ
ZFA:0000559.definition: Cavitated compound organ that is a fluid filed chamber with  a maculae on one surface and associated otolith tethered to the maculae.

ZFA:0000047.label: peripheral olfactory organ
ZFA:0000047.definition: Organ that is the specialized structure of the face that contains olfactory neurons. The peripheral olfactory organ is paired.

ZFA:0000151.label: pronephros
ZFA:0000151.definition: The embryonic kidney, present at the level of the third somite, is composed of two glomeruli fused at the midline, two pronephric tubules, and paired bilateral pronephric ducts that modify the composition of the blood filtrate before delivering it to the cloaca for excretion.

ZFA:0000076.label: swim bladder
ZFA:0000076.definition: The swim bladder is a double-chambered organ located in the coelom and used to maintain buoyancy and may function as an acoustic resonator. The zebrafish does not appear to have a gas gland, but it is not yet clear if there are gas producing cells distributed more widely.

ZFA:0000461.label: Weberian ossicle
ZFA:0000461.definition: A group of modified neural arches and spines of the first four vertebrae. These include, from anterior to posterior, the claustrum, scaphium, intercalarium, and tripus. The os suspensorium is considered to be a fifth ossicle.

ZFA:0000123.label: liver
ZFA:0000123.definition: Solid compound organ with three lobes that has many functions including bile production, blood detoxification, the production of critical plasma proteins and clotting factors, complement proteins  and the storage of many substances, such as lipids, amino acids, iron, and glycogen. Female fish produce vitellogenins in the liver.

ZFA:0001174.label: pharyngeal epithelium
ZFA:0001174.definition: Epithelium lining the pharynx consisting largely of simple columnar epithelium with a short segment (1mm) of stratified squamous epithelium on the ventral side.

ZFA:0001496.label: simple columnar epithelium
ZFA:0001496.definition: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of columnar cells.

ZFA:0001497.label: simple cuboidal epithelium
ZFA:0001497.definition: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of cuboidal cells.

ZFA:0001498.label: simple squamous epithelium
ZFA:0001498.definition: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of squamous cells.

ZFA:0001499.label: esophageal epithelium
ZFA:0001499.definition: Simple columnar epithelium that lines the esophagus.

ZFA:0005124.label: intestinal epithelium
ZFA:0005124.definition: Simple columnar epithelium that lines the intestine, sometimes pseudostratified, with absorptive brush-border cells and mucous goblet cells clearly visible.

ZFA:0005311.label: pronephric glomerular capsule epithelium
ZFA:0005311.definition: Simple squamous epithelium that lines the capsule of the pronephric glomerulus.

ZFA:0005253.label: renal glomerular capsule epithelium
ZFA:0005253.definition: Simple squamous epithelium that lines the capsule of the renal glomerulus.

ZFA:0001639.label: vascular endothelium
ZFA:0001639.definition: Simple squamous epithelium which lines blood and lymphatic vessels and the heart.

ZFA:0001458.label: cranial cartilage
ZFA:0001458.definition: Cartilage which is part of the cranium.

ZFA:0001543.label: paired fin cartilage
ZFA:0001543.definition: Cartilage which is part of one of the paired fins.

ZFA:0001457.label: postcranial axial cartilage
ZFA:0001457.definition: Cartilage which is part of the axial skeleton.

ZFA:0001478.label: anatomical cluster
ZFA:0001478.definition: Anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.

ZFA:0001439.label: anatomical system
ZFA:0001439.definition: Anatomical group that has as its parts distinct anatomical structures interconnected by anatomical structures at a lower level of granularity.

ZFA:0000112.label: gut
ZFA:0000112.definition: The alimentary or digestive tract, and associated organs.

ZFA:0000421.label: reticular formation
ZFA:0000421.definition: Reticular formation is a complex network of neurons and diffuse nuclei that extends from the spinal cord centrally along the length of the brain to the mesencephalon. It s a dense, almost impenetrable network of seemingly random scattered nerve cells.  The reticular formation integrates sensory inputs.

ZFA:0001635.label: intramembranous bone
ZFA:0001635.definition: Bone that forms directly within mesenchyme, and does not replace other tissues.

ZFA:0001628.label: replacement bone
ZFA:0001628.definition: Bone that forms as a replacement of another structural tissue.

ZFA:0001520.label: ceratobranchial 1 cartilage
ZFA:0001520.definition: Ceratobranchial cartilage that forms between hypobranchial 1 and epibranchial 1.

ZFA:0001517.label: ceratobranchial 2 cartilage
ZFA:0001517.definition: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

ZFA:0001518.label: ceratobranchial 3 cartilage
ZFA:0001518.definition: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

ZFA:0001519.label: ceratobranchial 4 cartilage
ZFA:0001519.definition: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

ZFA:0001521.label: ceratobranchial 5 cartilage
ZFA:0001521.definition: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is the most posterior, bilaterally paired ventral pharyngeal arch cartilage.

ZFA:0001524.label: hypobranchial 1 cartilage
ZFA:0001524.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the anteromedial tip of ceratobranchial 1, lateral to copula 1.

ZFA:0001525.label: hypobranchial 2 cartilage
ZFA:0001525.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the anteromedial tip of ceratobranchial 2, lateral to copula 1.

ZFA:0001526.label: hypobranchial 3 cartilage
ZFA:0001526.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the anteromedial tip of ceratobranchial 3, lateral to copula 1.

ZFA:0001523.label: hypobranchial 4 cartilage
ZFA:0001523.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the anteromedial tip of ceratobranchial 4; these are not obviously present in mature specimens, due either to resorption or fusion to the cartilaginous anterior tip of ceratobranchial 4.

ZFA:0001528.label: epibranchial 1 cartilage
ZFA:0001528.definition: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone and the medial end of pharyngobranchial 1.

ZFA:0001530.label: epibranchial 2 cartilage
ZFA:0001530.definition: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone and the medial end of pharyngobranchial 2.

ZFA:0001529.label: epibranchial 3 cartilage
ZFA:0001529.definition: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone and the medial end of pharyngobranchial 3.

ZFA:0001531.label: epibranchial 4 cartilage
ZFA:0001531.definition: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone and the medial end of pharyngobranchial 4.

ZFA:0001244.label: epibranchial 5
ZFA:0001244.definition: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and appears as a separate center of chondrification (6.2 mm) posterior to the lateral tip of epibranchial 4 and immediately anterior to the upper end of ceratobranchial 5. In the adult, epibranchial 5 persists as a small, cartilaginous rod extending from the cartilaginous junction of the posterodorsal tip of the uncinate process of epibranchial 4 and tip of ceratobranchial 5, to the cartilaginous junction of ceratobranchial 4 and epibranchial 4.

ZFA:0001536.label: pharyngobranchial 2 cartilage
ZFA:0001536.definition: Paired disc-like cartilage lying medial to and between the medial tips of epibranchials 1 and 2.

ZFA:0001534.label: pharyngobranchial 3 cartilage
ZFA:0001534.definition: Paired elongate cartilages that lie posteromedial to epibranchial 2 and medial to epibranchial 3.

ZFA:0001251.label: pharyngobranchial 4 cartilage
ZFA:0001251.definition: Pharyngobranchial cartilage which forms in close proximity to or fused with pharyngobranchial 3; may not be distinguishable as a separate element in the adult. Remains cartilaginous.

ZFA:0001542.label: pelvic radial 1 cartilage
ZFA:0001542.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior and lateral edge of the basipterygium.

ZFA:0001541.label: pelvic radial 2 cartilage
ZFA:0001541.definition: Small cartilage with a long posterior process and a shorter lateral one that forms at the posterior edge of the basipterygium, between radial cartilages 1 and 2.

ZFA:0001540.label: pelvic radial 3 cartilage
ZFA:0001540.definition: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior and medial edge of the basipterygium.

ZFA:0000257.label: pectoral fin cartilage
ZFA:0000257.definition: Cartilage which is part of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0001459.label: pelvic fin cartilage
ZFA:0001459.definition: Cartilage which is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0005533.label: branched caudal fin ray
ZFA:0005533.definition: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

ZFA:0001585.label: caudal fin principal ray
ZFA:0001585.definition: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is adjacent to a branched ray. Caudal principal rays may be segmented but unbranched and the main element forming the dorsal or ventral leading margin of the caudal fin or a ray that may be only segmented and branched and forms part of the middle-posterior region of the fin. A caudal principal ray is an unpaired median bone.  There are 19 principal caudal rays, with 10 in the dorsal lobe and nine in the ventral lobe. The dorsal lobe rays articulate with hypurals 3-5.

ZFA:0001584.label: caudal fin procurrent ray
ZFA:0001584.definition: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is located anterior to the principal caudal fin rays. Caudal procurrent rays are unbranched.

ZFA:0005547.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1
ZFA:0005547.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1 is the leading or marginal ray of the fin and articulates with the scapula.  Lepidotrichium 1 is commonly segmented but unbranched.

ZFA:0005548.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 2
ZFA:0005548.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the second most anterior pectoral ray, usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0005549.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 3
ZFA:0005549.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the third most anterior pectoral ray, usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0005553.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 4
ZFA:0005553.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fourth most anterior pectoral ray, usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0005552.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 5
ZFA:0005552.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fifth most anterior pectoral ray , usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0005550.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 6
ZFA:0005550.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the sixth most anterior pectoral ray, usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0005551.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium 7
ZFA:0005551.definition: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the seventh most anterior pectoral ray, usually branched and segmented.

ZFA:0001421.label: anal fin lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001421.definition: Lepidotrichium which is part of the anal fin.

ZFA:0001550.label: caudal fin lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001550.definition: Lepidotrichium which is part of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0001418.label: dorsal fin lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001418.definition: Lepidotrichium which is part of the dorsal fin.  Bony, bilaterally paired segmented dermal ossification extending distally from the endoskeletal supports.  They develop around actinotrichia as part of the dermal exoskeleton.

ZFA:0001551.label: pectoral fin lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001551.definition: Lepidotrichium which is part of the pectoral fin, forming the pectoral fin skeleton and articulating with the pectoral radials.  A pectoral lepidotrichium is composed of two hemitrichia that surround bundles of actinotrichia distally.

ZFA:0001552.label: pelvic fin lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001552.definition: Lepidotrichium which is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001291.label: facial ganglion
ZFA:0001291.definition: The sensory ganglion of the facial nerve.

ZFA:0000200.label: dorsal root ganglion
ZFA:0000200.definition: Trunk ganglion which is located adjacent to the spine on a dorsal root and contains the cell bodies of afferent sensory nerves.

ZFA:0001572.label: superior cervical ganglion
ZFA:0001572.definition: Trunk ganglion which is bilaterally paired and located at the anterior end of the sympathetic ganglion chain.

ZFA:0001556.label: sympathetic chain ganglion
ZFA:0001556.definition: Trunk ganglion which is part of a bilaterally paired set of sympathetic ganglia located anterior and lateral to the spinal cord.

ZFA:0001155.label: enteric nervous system
ZFA:0001155.definition: Nervous system that  is involved primarily with the internal regulation of the gustatory processes. In most vertebrates the enteric neurons form two layers of ganglionic plexuses located along the entire length of the gastrointestinal tract.

ZFA:0001575.label: parasympathetic nervous system
ZFA:0001575.definition: Autonomic nervous system where the cell bodies lie in the brain and sacral region of the spinal cord.   The neurons are mainly cholinergic.

ZFA:0001576.label: sympathetic nervous system
ZFA:0001576.definition: Autonomic nervous system that originates beginning at the thoracic and lumbar areas of the spinal cord.  Sympathetic neurons are primarily adrenergic producing the neurotransmitter noradrenalin along with other neuropeptides.

ZFA:0005353.label: vertebra 10
ZFA:0005353.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 9.

ZFA:0005354.label: vertebra 11
ZFA:0005354.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 10.

ZFA:0005352.label: vertebra 12
ZFA:0005352.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 11.  May have hemal arch and rib.

ZFA:0007096.label: vertebra 13
ZFA:0007096.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 12.

ZFA:0007097.label: vertebra 14
ZFA:0007097.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 13.

ZFA:0005347.label: vertebra 5
ZFA:0005347.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 4.

ZFA:0005348.label: vertebra 6
ZFA:0005348.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.

ZFA:0005349.label: vertebra 7
ZFA:0005349.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 6.

ZFA:0005350.label: vertebra 8
ZFA:0005350.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 7.

ZFA:0005351.label: vertebra 9
ZFA:0005351.definition: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 8.

ZFA:0005262.label: caudal fin dorsal procurrent ray
ZFA:0005262.definition: Caudal procurrent ray that is dorsally located on the caudal fin skeleton.  There are 6 dorsal procurrent rays in the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005263.label: caudal fin ventral procurrent ray
ZFA:0005263.definition: Caudal procurrent ray that is ventrally located on the caudal fin skeleton.  There are 5 ventral procurrent rays in the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005512.label: caudal fin principal ray 1
ZFA:0005512.definition: Caudal principal ray that is the dorsalmost caudal principal ray of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005521.label: caudal fin principal ray 10
ZFA:0005521.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 9.

ZFA:0005522.label: caudal fin principal ray 11
ZFA:0005522.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 10.

ZFA:0005523.label: caudal fin principal ray 12
ZFA:0005523.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 11.

ZFA:0005595.label: caudal fin principal ray 13
ZFA:0005595.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 12.

ZFA:0005524.label: caudal fin principal ray 14
ZFA:0005524.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 13.

ZFA:0005525.label: caudal fin principal ray 15
ZFA:0005525.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 14.

ZFA:0005526.label: caudal fin principal ray 16
ZFA:0005526.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 15.

ZFA:0005527.label: caudal fin principal ray 17
ZFA:0005527.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 16.

ZFA:0005528.label: caudal fin principal ray 18
ZFA:0005528.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 17.

ZFA:0005529.label: caudal fin principal ray 19
ZFA:0005529.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 18.

ZFA:0005514.label: caudal fin principal ray 2
ZFA:0005514.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 1.

ZFA:0005513.label: caudal fin principal ray 3
ZFA:0005513.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 2.

ZFA:0005515.label: caudal fin principal ray 4
ZFA:0005515.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 3.

ZFA:0005516.label: caudal fin principal ray 5
ZFA:0005516.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 4.

ZFA:0005517.label: caudal fin principal ray 6
ZFA:0005517.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 5.

ZFA:0005518.label: caudal fin principal ray 7
ZFA:0005518.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 6.

ZFA:0005519.label: caudal fin principal ray 8
ZFA:0005519.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 7.

ZFA:0005520.label: caudal fin principal ray 9
ZFA:0005520.definition: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 8.

ZFA:0001588.label: pectoral fin distal radial
ZFA:0001588.definition: Pectoral fin radial, develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, and is located at the proximal region of a lepidotrichium, between its hemitrichia. Pectoral fin distal radial is paired.

ZFA:0001587.label: pectoral fin proximal radial
ZFA:0001587.definition: Pectoral fin radial which develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports a few pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia and distal radials with the primary pectoral girdle (scapula and coracoid).

ZFA:0001589.label: propterygium
ZFA:0001589.definition: The propterygium is the lateralmost or anteriormost basal cartilage that originates from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc. The bases of the pectoral lepidotrichium 1 plus the propterygium articulates with the scapula.

ZFA:0001645.label: angular bone
ZFA:0001645.definition: Dermal bone that is located posterior to the dentary and lateral to the articular and retroarticular bones of the lower jaw. The angular forms the outer dermal sheet of the posterior part of the lower jaw. The angular bears a portion of the mandibular sensory canal. The angular is a paired bone.

ZFA:0000467.label: anguloarticular
ZFA:0000467.definition: Dermal and endochondral compound bone that results from the fusion of the dermal angular and the endochondral articular and forms the posterior part of the lower jaw. It articulates with the dentary anteriorly and with the retroarticular postero-medially. The anguloarticular is paired.

ZFA:0005532.label: bony plate
ZFA:0005532.definition: Dermal bone that is located on or subjacent to the surface anywhere on the body and that is not part of the general complement of scales, dermal bone of the dermatocranium, postcranial axial skeleton or paired fin skeleton. Bony plate may exist singly, or as unpaired or paired clusters or series.

ZFA:0000476.label: branchiostegal ray
ZFA:0000476.definition: Dermal bone that is a bilaterally paired and flattened element that supports the branchiostegal membrane. Three dermal branchiostegal rays form in the branchiostegal membrane ventral to the ceratohyal cartilage. The most posterior ray, branchiostegal 3, ossifies first (3.4 mm NL), and the most anterior ray, branchiostegal 1, ossifies last (5.5 mm NL). The most posterior two branchiostegals (2 and 3) insert externally on the ceratohyal; their anterodorsal tips are thickened triangles, and the rays are expanded. The bifurcated tip of the acinaciform anteriormost ray lies at the ventral margin of the ceratohyal.

ZFA:0000184.label: cleithrum
ZFA:0000184.definition: Transversely oriented bone connecting the occipital region of the skull dorsally and pectoral girdle ventrally; appears near the end of embryogenesis.

ZFA:0001274.label: coronomeckelian
ZFA:0001274.definition: The coronomeckelian is a membrane bone that ossifies on Meckel's cartilage where the tendon from the adductor mandibulae A3 inserts (6.1mm).  In the adult, the coronomeckelian is a small, irregularly shaped bone that is fused to the dorsomedial surface of the anguloarticular, just dorsal to Meckel's cartilage.

ZFA:0000191.label: dentary
ZFA:0000191.definition: Dermal bone that forms the antero-lateral part of the lower jaw. It first appears around the anterior end of Meckel's cartilage (5.1 mm NL). In the adult, the dentary meets its counterpart anteriorly at the mandibular symphysis. The dentary abuts the retroarticular posteriorly, and it surround the anguloarticular. The dentary is connected to the maxilla by the maxillo-mandibular ligament. Dentary teeth are absent in cypriniforms, but are present in other ostariophysans.

ZFA:0000656.label: ectopterygoid
ZFA:0000656.definition: The ectopterygoid is dermal bone located at the anterior part of the palatoquadrate.  It is first visible as a very thin ossification along the anteroventral border of the palatoquadrate cartilage (6.4 mm). In adults it is a long sliver of bone that is narrow anteriorly where it meets the entopterygoid in a synostosis. It is slightly wider at its posterior synostosis with the quadrate.

ZFA:0000657.label: entopterygoid
ZFA:0000657.definition: The entopterygoid is a dermal bone that forms the anteroventral and ventral surface of the orbit. It develops as a long sliver of bone developing in the membrane dorsomedial to the palatoquadrate cartilage (3.8 mm NL).

ZFA:0000663.label: extrascapula
ZFA:0000663.definition: Dermal canal-bearing bone placed at the dorso-posterior region of the skull roof, lying on the posterior region of the pterotic and parietals, or the pterotic and epioccipital, or on the pterotic, epioccipital and occipital bones.

ZFA:0000514.label: frontal bone
ZFA:0000514.definition: Large elongated paired dermal bones that roof the cranium and bear part of the supraorbital canal. The frontal bones cover the upper edge of the lateral ethmoid, orbitosphenoid and pterosphenoids and overlaps the parietal bone posteriorly.

ZFA:0000356.label: gill raker
ZFA:0000356.definition: Dermal bone that is a small anterior projection present on all of pharyngeal arches 3-7.  They support the gills.  The rakers have epithelial denticles and both their gross and fine structure serves to retain food particles in the mouth.

ZFA:0000376.label: infraorbital
ZFA:0000376.definition: Dermal bone that is situated under or posterior to the eye and associated with the infraorbital sensory canal.

ZFA:0000674.label: interopercle
ZFA:0000674.definition: Dermal bone that is located anterior to the subopercle and lying below and slightly ventral to the horizontal limb of the preopercle. The interopercle is a paired bone.

ZFA:0001406.label: kinethmoid bone
ZFA:0001406.definition: Small median unpaired dermal sesamoid bone in the premaxillary-ethmoid ligament between the mesethmoid and the premaxilla that enhances the protractability of the upper jaw. It forms in the premaxillary-ethmoid ligament. The kinethmoid arose de novo in the ancestor of Cypriniformes, the only group within Ostariophysi, in which it is found (Fink and Fink, 1981).

ZFA:0001554.label: lepidotrichium
ZFA:0001554.definition: Dermal bone that is rod-like, formed and usually contained in a fin membrane, and jointed to or adjacent to distal radials. They are bilaterally paired.  Lepidotrichia are formed from paired hemitrichia surrounding actinotrichia. There are usually two more lepidotrichia than distal radials.

ZFA:0000270.label: maxilla
ZFA:0000270.definition: The dermal maxilla forms part of the upper jaw. It is first visible as a small dorsoventrally oriented rod of bone in the lateral region of the upper jaw. Through anterior ossification it becomes S-shaped, with its anteriormost tip directed medially (4.8 mm NL). The posteroventral end of the maxilla is connected to the dentary by a ligament. Maxillary teeth are absent in cypriniforms, but are present in other ostariophysans. Two barbels are present on the maxilla. The presence of two pairs of maxillary barbels is considered by Cavender and Coburn (1992) to be the primitive condition for the Cyprinidae.

ZFA:0000365.label: nasal bone
ZFA:0000365.definition: Paired dermal bones, likened to a bone tube, positioned lateral to the supraethmoid. Nasal bones are transversed by the anterior most part of the supraorbital canals and bear one neuromast foramen in zebrafish.

ZFA:0000250.label: opercle
ZFA:0000250.definition: Dermal bone that articulates anteriorly with the hyomandibula. The opercle is paired and typically the largest bone of the opercular series.  It is derived from the neural crest and is located in 2nd pharyngeal arch.

ZFA:0000561.label: parasphenoid
ZFA:0000561.definition: Long, unpaired median dermal bone that runs almost the entire length of the cranium. Contacts the prevomer anteriorly, and the prootic and basioccipital posteriorly. Anteriorly the parasphenoid is a long, thin bone that widens abruptly at the point of contact with the prootic.

ZFA:0000486.label: parietal bone
ZFA:0000486.definition: Paired dermal bone that covers the hind part of the cranium, overlapping the dorsal edge of the sphenotic, pterotic, epiotic and the anterior edge of the supraoccipital. The parietal are overlapped anteriorly by the frontal.

ZFA:0000410.label: postcleithrum
ZFA:0000410.definition: Dermal bone that is part of the pectoral girdle and located ventral to the supracleithrum and posterior to the cleithrum. Postcleithral bones are paired and can vary up in number from a single pair (such as in zebrafish) to three pairs in other teleosts.

ZFA:0000549.label: posttemporal
ZFA:0000549.definition: Paired fin bone that attaches the pectoral girdle to the skull via two projections contacting the epiotic and intercalar bones, and carry the main laterosensory canal.

ZFA:0000567.label: premaxilla
ZFA:0000567.definition: The premaxilla is a bone of the upper jaw. It is an L-shaped bone first visible as a thin sliver in the anterodorsal region of the upper lip, anterior to the dorsal tip of the maxilla (5.7 mm). In the adult, the premaxilla is ligamentously attached to its counterpart at the midline and the kinethmoid posterodorsally, by the premaxillo-rostroid ligaments. Premaxillary teeth are absent in zebrafish.

ZFA:0001577.label: premaxilla ascending process
ZFA:0001577.definition: Process of the premaxilla that extends posteriorly and overlays the mesethmoid.

ZFA:0000264.label: preopercle
ZFA:0000264.definition: Dermal bone that is part of the opercular flap and bears the preopercular sensory canal. The preopercle is a paired bone and typically L-shaped, with the horizontal limb overlying the interopercle and the vertical limb overlying the opercle.

ZFA:0001594.label: preopercle horizontal limb
ZFA:0001594.definition: A dermal bone that is the lower, horizontal portion of the preopercle bone.

ZFA:0001595.label: preopercle vertical limb
ZFA:0001595.definition: A dermal bone that is the upper, vertical portion of the preopercle bone.

ZFA:0000308.label: prevomer
ZFA:0000308.definition: A thin medial unpaired dermal bone that is kite or paddle-shape. Underlying the ethmoid, and slightly overlapping the parasphenoid posteriorly, the prevomer bears an anterolateral projection that terminates in a concave depression in which the preethmoids sit.
