ZFA:0005511.label: sensory canal tubular ossicle
ZFA:0005511.definition: Dermal bone that is ring-shaped or cylindrical and surrounds a sensory canal.

ZFA:0000284.label: subopercle
ZFA:0000284.definition: Dermal bone lying below the opercle. The subopercle is a paired bone.

ZFA:0000594.label: supracleithrum
ZFA:0000594.definition: Dermal bone that articulates dorsally with the posttemporal and ventrally with the cleithrum. Supracleithrum is part of the secondary pectoral girdle and commonly, carries part of the lateral line canal.

ZFA:0001403.label: supraethmoid
ZFA:0001403.definition: Dermal bone that first appears as paired ossifications in the membrane (dermis) dorsolateral to the ethmoid cartilage and anteriolateral to the lateral ethmoids, later having the appearance of one butterfly-shaped element. Fused to the anterodorsal margin of the mesethmoid. Bordered anteriorly by the kinethmoid and posteriorly by the frontal.

ZFA:0000691.label: supraorbital bone
ZFA:0000691.definition: Paired dermal bones that form the anterodorsal margin of the orbit.

ZFA:0000452.label: urohyal
ZFA:0000452.definition: The urohyal is a median dermal bone that ossifies in the membrane between the paired sternohyoideus muscles ventral to the anterior end of copula 1. It is an unpaired ossification of the tendon of the sternohyoideos muscles in basal teleosts, and it is paired in catfishes (Arratia and Schultze, 1990).

ZFA:0000620.label: autopalatine
ZFA:0000620.definition: The cartilaginous autopalatine forms from the anterior palatoquadrate arch. The first sign of ossification is visible at the anterior tip where it articulates with the maxilla (7.6 mm). In adults there are three processes at the anterior portion of the palatine: a ventromedial process, which forms the socket of the small ball- and- socket joint with the preethmoid; a dorsomedial process, which is connected by a short ligament to the ethmoid; and a lateral process, which extends toward the first infraorbital. Possession of a dorsomedial process, which abuts the ethmoid, is a unique feature shared by Cypriniformes (Fink and Fink, 1981). The palatine has two components, the autopalatine (derived from pars autopalatine) and the dermal component having teeth, the dermopalatine Arratia & Schultze 1990. The element in cypriniforms is only the cartilage part, so that it is more correct to name it autopalatine and not as palatine in general that it implies a fusion of elements (as in perciforms).

ZFA:0000170.label: basibranchial
ZFA:0000170.definition: Median elements that are ossified within copulae and are not assigned to a specific branchial arch number. They articulate posterolaterally with the hypobranchials.

ZFA:0000316.label: basihyal bone
ZFA:0000316.definition: Endochondral bone that is median and is the anterior-most bone of the ventral hyoid arch, the 'tongue' of the a fish. Ossification of the cartilaginous basihyal is first visible at the posterior end of the club-shaped basihyal cartilage (6.0 mm). Ossification spreads throughout the cartilage, except for the anterior tip, which remains cartilaginous. The posteroventral tip extends between the left and right dorsal hypohyals.

ZFA:0000472.label: basioccipital
ZFA:0000472.definition: Large median unpaired cartilage bone that contacts the exoccipital, epiotic and pterotic dorsally, and the parasphenoid anteriorly. Forms the posteroventral hind margin of the cranium, articulates with the centrum of the first vertebra. Bears a posteroventral pharyngeal process that is flattened ventrally and opposes the pharyngeal teeth of the fifth pair of ceratobranchials.

ZFA:0001598.label: basioccipital posterodorsal region
ZFA:0001598.definition: Endochondral bone which is the posterodorsal region of the basioccipital bone.

ZFA:0000623.label: basipterygium
ZFA:0000623.definition: Endochondral bone that is paired and supports the pelvic fin. The basipterygium has a posteromedial process called the ischiac process (Wietzman 1962).

ZFA:0000126.label: centrum
ZFA:0000126.definition: Centra are represented by mineralized, calcified, or ossified portions that surround the notochord. The autocentrum, present in Danio and all other living teleosts, is formed by direct ossification outside the elastica externa of the notochord (Arratia, 1999).

ZFA:0000488.label: ceratobranchial bone
ZFA:0000488.definition: Endochondral bone that is bilaterally paired and forms part of the ventral branchial arches. They articulate medially with the hypobranchials and laterally and dorsally with the epibranchials.

ZFA:0000578.label: ceratohyal bone
ZFA:0000578.definition: Endochondral bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with the hypohyal cartilage or bone, dorsal and ventral hypohyals, and epihyal posteriorly. The ceratohyal bone begins as a ossification in the anterior portion of the ceratohyal cartilage (4.6 mm NL). The posterior end broadens and meets the epihyal in a pad of cartilage. The anterior end broadens and terminates in two heads (8.8 mm). The anterodorsal head forms a synchondrosis with the dorsal hypohyal and the anteroventral head forms a synchondrosis with the ventral hypohyal. All of the branchiostegal rays articulate with the ventral edge of the ceratohyal.

ZFA:0000332.label: coracoid
ZFA:0000332.definition: Endochondral bone that articulates dorsally with the scapula and with the mesocoracoid when the latter is present, posteriorly with the lower two or three proximal radials and antero-ventrally with the cleithrum.  The coracoid develops from the scapulo-coracoid cartilage. The coracoid is paired.

ZFA:0000658.label: epibranchial bone
ZFA:0000658.definition: Pharyngeal arch bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone. Epibranchials are dorsal parts of the gill arches. Epibranchials 1-4 ossify in the epibranchial cartilages in a posterior to anterior progression. Gill rakers are present on the anterior and posterior edges of epibranchials 2 and 4 and the posterior edge of epibranchial 1. A reduced gill raker is present on the anterior margin of epibranchial 1 in some specimens.

ZFA:0001382.label: epibranchial uncinate process
ZFA:0001382.definition: Epibranchials 1-3 in adults are compound elements formed by the fusion of epibranchial cartilages and the so-called uncinate processes.  Posteromedially directed uncinate processes develop on the posterior edge of epibranchials 1-3. These appear as separate centers of chondrification (6.2 mm) that later fuse laterally to the posterior edges of the epibranchial cartilages (6.8 mm).

ZFA:0000627.label: epihyal
ZFA:0000627.definition: Endochondral bone that begins ossifying on the anterior surface of the posterior end of the ceratohyal cartilage near the site of articulation with the interhyal (5.8 mm). It joins the ceratohyal in a pad of persisting cartilage.

ZFA:0001412.label: epiotic
ZFA:0001412.definition: Cartilage bone that contacts the pterotic anteriorly, the supraoccipital and parietal dorsally, and the exoccipital ventrally. The epiotic enclose the posterior semicircular canal of the inner ear and contribute to the hind margin of the cranium.

ZFA:0000661.label: exoccipital
ZFA:0000661.definition: Paired cartilage bone that bears a large foramen (lateral occipital foramen).  Contacts the supraoccipital dorsally, the epiotic laterally and the basioccipital ventrally. Forms the posterior hind margin of the cranium and borders the lateral and posterior margins of the forum (foramen) magnum.

ZFA:0001597.label: exoccipital posteroventral region
ZFA:0001597.definition: Endochondral bone which is the posteroventral region of the exoccipital bone.

ZFA:0000519.label: hemal arch
ZFA:0000519.definition: Hemal arches extend ventrally from the centra of caudal and transitional vertebrae to enclose the caudal artery and vein. In cyprinids, the hemal arch forms directly in membrane bone.

ZFA:0000735.label: hemal postzygapophysis
ZFA:0000735.definition: Paired, ventromedially directed processes on the posterior ends of the centra, ligamentously joined to the hemal postzygapophyses of the immediately posterior vertebra. The most posterior caudal vertebrae lack hemal postzygapophyses.

ZFA:0007005.label: hemal prezygapophysis
ZFA:0007005.definition: Hemal prezygapophyses are paired, anteromedially directed processes arising from the bases of hemal arches, ligamentously joined to the hemal postzygapophyses of the preceding vertebra. Posterior caudal vertebrae close to the caudal fin lack hemal prezygapophyses.

ZFA:0001364.label: hemal spine
ZFA:0001364.definition: Hemal spines are extensions of hemal arches in the ventral skeletogenous septum of the caudal region.

ZFA:0000672.label: hyomandibula
ZFA:0000672.definition: The hyomandibula is the large, dorsal-most member of the hyoid arch.  It begins ossifying in the dorsal edge of the hyosymplectic cartilage near the hyomandibular foramen (4.6 mm NL). Ossification spreads through the cartilage, and sheets of membrane bone form off the cartilage model anteriorly and posteriorly (6.6 mm). In the adult, the hyomandibula has cartilage-capped anterior and posterior articulating heads that meet the sphenotic-prootic fossa and the pterotic fossa, respectively, in synovial joints.  A posterior knob of bone develops, also capped in cartilage, and it forms a synovial joint with the opercle.

ZFA:0000363.label: hypobranchial bone
ZFA:0000363.definition: Hypobranchials are the most medial of the bilaterally paired elements of the gill arches. Hypobranchial ossifications 1-3 (of 4) develop in the small hypobranchial cartilages that lie between the medial tips of the ceratobranchials and copula 2. The hypobranchials articulate anteromedially with the basibranchials.

ZFA:0001381.label: hypohyal bone
ZFA:0001381.definition: Hypohyals are the most anterior of the bilaterally paired ventral hyoid arch elements. The two hypohyals in zebrafish ossify at the anterodorsal and anteroventral tips of the ceratohyal cartilages; no separate hypohyal cartilages are present.

ZFA:0001603.label: intercalarium articulating process
ZFA:0001603.definition: Portion of the intercalarium that  ossifies from the cartilage condensation and articulates with a groove in centrum 2.

ZFA:0001602.label: intercalarium ascending process
ZFA:0001602.definition: Bony process that develops as a dorsally  projecting cartilaginous extension from the basidorsal.  The ascending process is longer relative to the manubrium in larvae (5.1-11.0 mm). By 13.0 mm, the ascending process appears highly reduced in size.

ZFA:0000526.label: intermuscular bone
ZFA:0000526.definition: Axial bone which is a segmental ossification that forms in the myoseptum; found in teleosts fishes only.

ZFA:0000226.label: lateral ethmoid
ZFA:0000226.definition: Large, paired cartilage bones separating the olfactory region from the orbit. Arises from both perichondral and endochondral ossifications (Harrington 1955). Bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly and overlain by the frontal dorsally, each lateral ethmoid extends medially to meet its fellow posteriorly along the midline. Develops from the laminae orbitonasales.

ZFA:0000323.label: mesethmoid bone
ZFA:0000323.definition: Median unpaired cartilage bone that ossifies as a perichondral lamellae ensheathing the nasal septum anterodorsally and laterally (Harrington, 1955). In adult D. rerio, the center of the mesethmoid remains cartilaginous (Cubbage & Mabee, 1996). The mesethmoid meets the supraethmoid dorsally, the lateral ethmoids posterolaterally, and the vomer and parasphenoid ventrally in synostoses. Anterolaterally the mesethmoid meets the preethmoids in synchondroses.

ZFA:0000239.label: mesocoracoid bone
ZFA:0000239.definition: Endochondral bone that articulates laterally with the medial surface of the cleithrum and ventro-medially with the scapula and coracoid. Mesocoracoid bone is a small, arch-like bone that develops from the mesocoracoid cartilage. Mesocoracoid bone is paired.

ZFA:0000240.label: metapterygoid
ZFA:0000240.definition: The metapterygoid is a posterior bone that ossifies in the cartilaginous palatoquadrate arch. It first appears as a rod of bone with an anterodorsally projecting process from the middle of the dorsal surface (6.4 mm). The adult metapterygoid is roughly rectangular in shape with rounded corners and an anterodorsally projecting spine that meets the entopterygoid medially in a synostosis at its posteromedial edge. The posterior end curves dorsally to form the posteroventral surface of the orbit.

ZFA:0001066.label: neural arch
ZFA:0001066.definition: A neural arch encloses the neural canal and typically meets its partner to form a neural spine. The neural arch can be a replacement ossification of the basidorsal cartilage or can form directly in membrane bone.

ZFA:0000681.label: neural postzygapophysis
ZFA:0000681.definition: Paired, dorsomedially directed processes on the posterior ends of the centra, ligamentously joined to the neural prezygapophyses of the immediately posterior vertebra.

ZFA:0001325.label: neural prezygapophysis
ZFA:0001325.definition: Paired, anteromedially directed processes from the neural arches, ligamentously joined to the postzygapophyses of the preceding vertebra.

ZFA:0001336.label: neural spine
ZFA:0001336.definition: Neural spines are extensions of neural arches dorsal to the neural canal in the median skeletogenous septum. Neural spines are typically unpaired median structures but can be paired in some instances, e.g., in the abdominal region of basal teleosts such as Leptolepis, Elops, Megalops, and Hiodon).

ZFA:0000253.label: orbitosphenoid
ZFA:0000253.definition: Large median unpaired cartilage bone consisting of two diverging plates. Positioned medial to the eye. The orbitosphenoid develops from the Trabeculae communis and forms the anterior and anteriolateral boundary of the orbital foramen and constitutes a significant part of the sidewalls and floor of the cranial cavity. Bordered by the lateral ethmoid anteriorly, and the pterosphenoid posteriorly, The orbitosphenoid may extend ventrally to meet the parasphenoid. In the adult, the orbitosphenoid is fused ventrally to the parasphenoid via a thin sheet of bone.

ZFA:0001171.label: os suspensorium
ZFA:0001171.definition: Thin, rod-shaped, anteroventrally directed membrane bone that develops as a separate outgrowth  from the cartilage parapophysis of the fourth vertebra; develops ventrally to curve around the anterior head of the swim bladder. It articulates with the tripus at the tripus-swim bladder connection. Often termed a fifth Weberian ossicle.

ZFA:0001362.label: parapophysis
ZFA:0001362.definition: Parapophyses are lateral or ventrolateral projections of vertebrae to which ribs are attached in Danio rerio. Parapophyses can arise through replacement ossification of a basiventral or form directly in bone. They are separated from the centrum in basal teleosts, e.g., Leptolepis coryphaenoides, Megalops and Elops.

ZFA:0001396.label: parapophysis/rib
ZFA:0001396.definition: The parapophysis + rib, fused to the centrum, extends laterally then angles anteroventrally. A thin plate, the os suspensorium fuses to its median surface.

ZFA:0000527.label: pharyngobranchial bone
ZFA:0000527.definition: The pharyngobranchials are the dorsalmost bones of the branchial arches located immediately dorsal and medial to the epibranchials.

ZFA:0001404.label: preethmoid bone
ZFA:0001404.definition: Small rounded to egg-shaped cartilage bone that sits in an anteriolateral depression on the prevomer. Articulates with the autopalatine in all cypriniforms.

ZFA:0000575.label: prootic
ZFA:0000575.definition: Paired cartilage bone that contacts the pterosphenoid anteriorly, the sphenotic and the pterotic dorsally, and the epiotic and basioccipital posteriorly. The parasphenoid covers the ventral region of each prootic, the upper edge of which contributes to the hyomandibular facet. The prootic bear foramina that accommodate branches of the trigeminal and facial nerves.

ZFA:0000419.label: pterosphenoid
ZFA:0000419.definition: Paired cartilage bones, flat and hexagonal in shape that contact the orbitosphenoid anteriorly. Roofed by the frontal and bordered posteriorly by the prootic and sphenotic, the pterosphenoid bears foramina that accommodate branches of the trigeminal and facial nerves.

ZFA:0000576.label: pterotic
ZFA:0000576.definition: Paired cartilage bone that contacts the autosphenotic anteriorly, the parietal dorsally, the prootic ventrally, and the epiotic and exoccipital posteriorly. The pterotic encloses the horizontal semicircular canal of the inner ear. The lower edge of the pterotic contributes to the hyomandibular facet.

ZFA:0000621.label: quadrate
ZFA:0000621.definition: The quadrate is the dorsal bone in the jaw joint with the anguloarticular of the lower jaw. Ossification of the quadrate, a cartilage bone, begins as a posteriorly projecting membranous spine between the symplectic cartilage and the preopercle (5.1 mm NL). The body of the quadrate ossifies first at the ball-and-socket articulation with the anguloarticular (6.5 mm). The adult quadrate is shaped roughly like an inverted triangle with a long, posteriorly projecting spine off its posteroventral edge. The presence of a posteroventral or posterior process of the quadrate is a synapomorphy of Teleostei.

ZFA:0001593.label: quadrate ventral process
ZFA:0001593.definition: An endochondral bone that is the ventral, posteriorly-oriented bony extension of the quadrate.

ZFA:0000271.label: radial
ZFA:0000271.definition: The  internal skeletal supports of the median and paired fins.

ZFA:0000422.label: retroarticular
ZFA:0000422.definition: The retroarticular is a cartilage bone that forms at the posteroventral tip of Meckel's cartilage where the interoperculomandibular ligament attaches (5.1 mm NL). In the adult it is basically triangular in shape. The retroarticular is ligamentously connected to the interopercle and preopercle posteriorly and abuts the ventral shelf of the dentary anteriorly.

ZFA:0000538.label: rib
ZFA:0000538.definition: Endochondral bone that is intersegmental and rod-shaped, forming in the peritoneal membrane and attached to the vertebral parapophyses. Ribs protect and support internal organs.

ZFA:0000583.label: scapula
ZFA:0000583.definition: Endochondral bone that is located medial to the cleithrum, and articulates ventrally with the coracoid, medially with the mesocoracoid when the later is present and posteriorly with the upper one to three proximal radials. The scapula develops from the scapulocoracoid cartilage and belongs to the primary pectoral girdle. It may be perforated by the scapular foramen or it may be notched ventrally and forms together with a similar notch of the coracoid the scapulocoracoid foramen.

ZFA:0001411.label: sclerotic bone
ZFA:0001411.definition: A pair of small dish-shaped bones that cap the anterior and posterior margin of the eyeball. The sclerotic bones also called scleral ossicles form from the scleral cartilage between the sclera and the optic choroid.  The ossicles develop via unilateral perichondral ossification of the scleral cartilage from two centers opposite one another in the eye.

ZFA:0000859.label: specialized hemal arch and spine
ZFA:0000859.definition: Modified hemal arches and spines that support the caudal fin.  In developing fish they articulate with preural 1, ural1 and ural2; in adults they articulate with the urostyle.

ZFA:0000587.label: sphenotic
ZFA:0000587.definition: Paired cartilage bone that contacts the pterosphenoid anteriorly, the prootic ventrally, and the pterotic posteriorly. Roofed by the frontal bone anteriorly and the parietal bone posteriorly, the sphenotic bears a large anteriolateral process that borders the posterodorsal margin of the orbit. The lower edge of the sphenotic contributes to the hyomandibular facet.

ZFA:0000442.label: supraneural
ZFA:0000442.definition: Supraneurals independent, median, elongate, rod-like cartilages or bones in the dorsal skeletogenous septum between the cranium and the dorsal fin. In actinopterygians, supraneurals develop from cartilages that are independent of the neural spine (Arratia et al., 2001).

ZFA:0000595.label: supraoccipital
ZFA:0000595.definition: Large shield-shaped unpaired median cartilage bone that contact the parietal anteriorly, and the exoccipital and epiotic laterally. Forms the posterodorsal most point of the cranium. The supraoccipital usually bears a crest that extends posterodorsally.

ZFA:0000692.label: symplectic
ZFA:0000692.definition: The symplectic is an irregularly rod-shaped cartilage replacement bone articulating with the hyomandibular and quadrate.

ZFA:0000698.label: tripus
ZFA:0000698.definition: The fourth Weberian ossicle. The tripus is a complex modification of the parapophysis and rib of the third vertebra. Anteriorly it attaches to the interosseus ligament and posteriorly it extends as a transformator process embedded in the tunica externa of the swim bladder.

ZFA:0001581.label: ural centrum 2
ZFA:0001581.definition: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 1. Ural centrum 2 is an unpaired median bone.

ZFA:0000158.label: urostyle
ZFA:0000158.definition: This centrum may be formed via the fusion of the terminal centrum and half-centrum. It is sometimes termed the 'ultimate' vertebra. Develops from the fused preural centrum 1+ ural centrum 1.

ZFA:0001189.label: vertebra
ZFA:0001189.definition: All serially repeated ossified, cartilaginous, and ligamentous elements around the notochord (Schultze and Arratia, 1988).  Adult zebrafish usually 32 vertebrae but may have as few as 30 to as many as 33 vertebrae.

ZFA:0007117.label: Meckel's cartilage-palatoquadrate cartilage joint
ZFA:0007117.definition: Joint between Meckel's cartilage and palatoquadrate cartilage.

ZFA:0005421.label: autopalatine-maxillary joint
ZFA:0005421.definition: Joint that articulates the autopalatine cartilage or bone and maxilla.

ZFA:0005422.label: autopalatine-vomer joint
ZFA:0005422.definition: Joint that articulates autopalatine and vomer bones. Autopalatine vomer joint is paired.

ZFA:0005155.label: cartilaginous joint
ZFA:0005155.definition: Is a joint where the ends of two bones are connected by cartilage.

ZFA:0005465.label: ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint
ZFA:0005465.definition: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

ZFA:0005467.label: ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint
ZFA:0005467.definition: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and dorsal hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005859.label: ceratohyal-interhyal joint
ZFA:0005859.definition: Joint that articulates the interhyal skeletal element and ceratohyal skeletal element.  The ceratohyal-interhyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005466.label: ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
ZFA:0005466.definition: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005464.label: dentary-anguloarticular joint
ZFA:0005464.definition: Joint that articulates the dentary and anguloarticular. Dentary-anguloarticular joint is paired.

ZFA:0005457.label: dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint
ZFA:0005457.definition: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and urohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005458.label: dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
ZFA:0005458.definition: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005498.label: epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint
ZFA:0005498.definition: Joint that articulates the epihyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

ZFA:0005497.label: epihyal-ceratohyal joint
ZFA:0005497.definition: Joint that articulates the epihyal and ceratohyal bones. Epihyal-ceratohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005156.label: fibrous joint
ZFA:0005156.definition: A joint where fibrous tissue such as ligament connects two calcified tissues.

ZFA:0005468.label: frontal-pterotic joint
ZFA:0005468.definition: Joint that articulates the frontal and pterotic. Frontal-pterotic joint is paired.

ZFA:0005469.label: hyomandibula-metapterygoid joint
ZFA:0005469.definition: Joint that articulates the hyomandibula bone and metapterygoid bone.

ZFA:0005471.label: inter-basipterygium joint
ZFA:0005471.definition: Joint that articulates the left and right basipterygium cartilage or bone. Inter-basipterygium joint is unpaired.

ZFA:0005470.label: inter-coracoid joint
ZFA:0005470.definition: Joint between the right and left coracoid bones of the pectoral girdle.

ZFA:0005474.label: inter-hypobranchial 3 joint
ZFA:0005474.definition: Joint that articulates the left and right hypobranchial 3 cartilages or bones. Inter-hypobranchial 3 joint is unpaired.

ZFA:0005475.label: inter-premaxillary joint
ZFA:0005475.definition: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.

ZFA:0005476.label: inter-ventral hypohyal joint
ZFA:0005476.definition: Joint that articulates the contralateral ventral hypohyal bones or the contralateral ceratobranchial cartilages. Inter-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005473.label: interhyal-epihyal joint
ZFA:0005473.definition: Joint that articulates the interhyal and epihyal bones, or interhyal and ceratohyal cartilages. Interhyal-epihyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005860.label: interhyal-hyosymplectic joint
ZFA:0005860.definition: Joint that articulates the interhyal element and the hyosymplectic element.  The interhyal-hyosymplectic joint is paired.

ZFA:0005477.label: lateral ethmoid-frontal joint
ZFA:0005477.definition: Joint that articulates the lateral ethmoid and frontal. Lateral ethmoid-frontal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005634.label: lepidotrichium joint
ZFA:0005634.definition: Joint that articulates segments of the fin ray.

ZFA:0005861.label: opercle-hyosymplectic joint
ZFA:0005861.definition: Joint that articulates the opercle and they hyosymplectic.  The opercle-hyosymplectic joint is paired.

ZFA:0005478.label: opercle-interopercle joint
ZFA:0005478.definition: Joint that articulates the opercle and interopercle. Opercle-interopercle joint is paired.

ZFA:0005479.label: orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint
ZFA:0005479.definition: Joint that articulates the orbitosphenoid cartilage or bone and lateral ethmoid cartilage or bone. Orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

ZFA:0005480.label: orbitosphenoid-prootic joint
ZFA:0005480.definition: Joint that articulates orbitosphenoid and prootic bones. Orbitosphenoid-prootic joint is paired.

ZFA:0005481.label: prootic-exoccipital joint
ZFA:0005481.definition: Joint that articulates the prootic and exoccipital. Prootic-exoccipital joint is paired.

ZFA:0005483.label: pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint
ZFA:0005483.definition: Joint that articulates the pterosphenoid and orbitosphenoid. Pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint is paired.

ZFA:0005485.label: quadrate-hyomandibula joint
ZFA:0005485.definition: Joint that articulates quadrate and hyomandibula bones. Quadrate-hyomandibula joint is paired.

ZFA:0005610.label: synostosis
ZFA:0005610.definition: Joint in which the articulating bones are connected by bone.

ZFA:0005153.label: synovial joint
ZFA:0005153.definition: Is a joint that is located at the point of contact of articulating bones allowing movement. The joint has a capsule containing synovial fluid surrounding the articulating bone surfaces.

ZFA:0005487.label: ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint
ZFA:0005487.definition: Joint that articulates the ventral hypohyal and urohyal bones. Ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

ZFA:0000676.label: sagitta
ZFA:0000676.definition: Otolith that is part of the sacculus.

ZFA:0001693.label: chondral bone
ZFA:0001693.definition: Replacement bone that forms within or surrounding a cartilaginous skeletal element.

ZFA:0001629.label: perichordal bone
ZFA:0001629.definition: Replacement bone that forms within the connective tissue surrounding the notochord.

ZFA:0001631.label: notochordal ossification
ZFA:0001631.definition: Perichordal bone that surrounds the anterior tip of the notochord.

ZFA:0001675.label: ligament
ZFA:0001675.definition: Portion of connective tissue that is a fibrous band connecting bones or cartilages or supporting an organ.

ZFA:0001634.label: perichondrium
ZFA:0001634.definition: Portion of connective tissue which surrounds cartilage.

ZFA:0001633.label: perichordal connective tissue
ZFA:0001633.definition: Portion of connective tissue which surrounds the notochord.

ZFA:0005619.label: skeletal tissue
ZFA:0005619.definition: Connective tissue that functions in mechanical and structural support.

ZFA:0005647.label: tendon
ZFA:0005647.definition: Dense regular connective tissue that connects muscle to bone.

ZFA:0001590.label: dermal bone
ZFA:0001590.definition: Intramembranous bone that forms superficially in the organism.  Dermal bones develop from the direct differentiation of mesenchymal cells into osteoblasts.

ZFA:0001636.label: membrane bone
ZFA:0001636.definition: Intramembranous bone that forms deep in the organism.

ZFA:0000474.label: intercalar
ZFA:0000474.definition: Small membrane bone homologous with a cartilage bone in more basal fishes (Patterson, 1977). Situated between the exoccipital and the pterotic at point of attachment of short ligament that originates on the ventral arm of the posttemporal.

ZFA:0001601.label: manubrium
ZFA:0001601.definition: Anterior branch of the intercalarium.  The manubrium develops as a simple antero-lateral membrane bone extension from basidorsal 2.

ZFA:0001578.label: anterior dorsomedial process of autopalatine
ZFA:0001578.definition: In cypriniforms the anterior portion of the palatine has a dorsomedial process which abuts against the mesethmoid. Such a process is not present in other ostariophysans or in other primitive teleosts.

ZFA:0005657.label: anterior lateral process of autopalatine
ZFA:0005657.definition: Endochondral bone part of autopalatine that extends towards the first infraorbital.

ZFA:0005655.label: anterior ventromedial process of autopalatine
ZFA:0005655.definition: Endochondral process of the autopalatine that forms the socket of the autopalatine-preethmoid joint.

ZFA:0005257.label: blood vessel endothelium
ZFA:0005257.definition: The vascular endothelium that lines blood vasculature.

ZFA:0005258.label: lymph vessel endothelium
ZFA:0005258.definition: The vascular endothelium that lines the lymph vessels.

ZFA:0001140.label: dorsal tooth row
ZFA:0001140.definition: Tooth row that is the dorsalmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.

ZFA:0001139.label: mediodorsal tooth row
ZFA:0001139.definition: Tooth row that is the mediodorsal row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone, located between the dorsal tooth row and ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0001137.label: ventral tooth row
ZFA:0001137.definition: Tooth row that is the ventralmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.

ZFA:0005876.label: anterior chamber eye
ZFA:0005876.definition: The space between the cornea and lens in the anterior segment of the eye where the aqueous humor is located.

ZFA:0005163.label: bile canaliculus
ZFA:0005163.definition: Intercellular space surrounded by the basal surface of the hepatocytes that collect bile.

ZFA:0007073.label: blood sinus cavity
ZFA:0007073.definition: An enlarged chamber in the blood sinus capable of accumulating a large volume of blood.

ZFA:0001075.label: choroidal fissure
ZFA:0001075.definition: The narrow cleft along the medial wall of the lateral ventricle along the margins of which the choroid plexus is attached; it lies between the upper surface of the thalamus and lateral edge of the fornix in the central part of the ventricle and between the terminal stria and fimbria hippocampi in the inferior horn.

ZFA:0000330.label: cloacal chamber
ZFA:0000330.definition: Space proximal to the urogenital pore where the pronephric duct, intestine and the oviduct or sperm duct  empties.

ZFA:0005536.label: fontanel
ZFA:0005536.definition: Anatomical space between bones of the neurocranium.  Frequently closes during development.

ZFA:0005386.label: foramen
ZFA:0005386.definition: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone, usually for passage of blood vessels or nerves.

ZFA:0005388.label: fossa
ZFA:0005388.definition: Anatomical space that is a concavity, shallow depression, or groove on a bone.

ZFA:0005389.label: gill opening
ZFA:0005389.definition: Anatomical space that is the external opening of a gill slit connecting the pharyngeal cavity to the exterior. Gill opening is usually paired and located on the lateral or ventral surfaces of the head.

ZFA:0005782.label: intestinal opening
ZFA:0005782.definition: The juncture where the  intestine empties into the cloaca.

ZFA:0005807.label: intestine lumen
ZFA:0005807.definition: Anatomical space within the intestine where digestion normally occurs.  The intestinal lumen begins as an interconnected web of small space at 43 hpf that over time remodels to form a single continuous tube at 68hpf.  Lumen maturation proceeds from anterior to posterior along the intestine.

ZFA:0000695.label: labial cavity
ZFA:0000695.definition: The anatomical space located between the lips and the oral valves.

ZFA:0005736.label: lacuna
ZFA:0005736.definition: Anatomical space a small cavity, in the matrix of bone tissue. Part of the lacunocanalicular system.

ZFA:0005735.label: lacunocanalicular canal
ZFA:0005735.definition: Anatomical space, part of the lacunocanalicular system that connects lacuna within bone tissue allowing osteocyte projections to connect.

ZFA:0000231.label: lateral recess
ZFA:0000231.definition: Intracranial space formed by confluence of supraorbital, infraorbital, preopercular and temporal sensory canals that forms the lateral protrusion of the third ventricle. See also Di Dario (2004).

ZFA:0001654.label: opercular cavity
ZFA:0001654.definition: Anatomical space which is located beneath the operculum and external to the gills.

ZFA:0005558.label: orbit
ZFA:0005558.definition: Anatomical space that is the concavity containing the eye.

ZFA:0001655.label: pericardial cavity
ZFA:0001655.definition: Anatomical space in which the heart is located and is surrounded by the pericardium.

ZFA:0001656.label: pleuroperitoneal cavity
ZFA:0001656.definition: Anatomical space which contains the abdominal visceral and swim bladder. Located posterior to the pericardial cavity, separated by the transverse septum. From Functional Anatomy of the Vertebrates, third edition.

ZFA:0005449.label: pore
ZFA:0005449.definition: An anatomical space that is an opening, usually at the end of a canal or duct, on the surface of the integument or the lining of an internal anatomical space.

ZFA:0005338.label: posterior recess
ZFA:0005338.definition: Posterior protrusion of the third ventricle.

ZFA:0005312.label: pronephric capsular space
ZFA:0005312.definition: Space between the pronephric glomerulus and the pronephric glomerular capsule.  Renal filtrate collects here then passes into the pronephric tubule.

ZFA:0001055.label: pronephric duct opening
ZFA:0001055.definition: The juncture where the pronephric ducts empty into the cloaca.

ZFA:0001283.label: pupil
ZFA:0001283.definition: Anatomical space that is located in the center of the iris and allows light to impinge on the retina.

ZFA:0005283.label: renal capsular space
ZFA:0005283.definition: Space between the renal glomerulus and the glomerular capsule.  Renal filtrate collects here then passes into the renal tubule.

ZFA:0005884.label: seminiferous tubule lumen
ZFA:0005884.definition: Lumen of the seminiferous tubule.  Mature sperm is stored in the tubular lumen.

ZFA:0005895.label: trigeminal-facial chamber
ZFA:0005895.definition: Chamber  in the prootic where the trunks of the trigeminal facial nerve complex pass from the brain to the outside of the cranium.  In  the  adult,  a  posteromedial extension  from  the  prootic delimits  the  medial  boundary  of  the trigeminal-facial  chamber.  The  anterior opening  of  the  trigeminal-facial  chamber lies between  the  prootic  and  the  pterosphenoid.

ZFA:0000646.label: anal fin distal radial
ZFA:0000646.definition: Rod-like internal median skeletal support bones of the anal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.

ZFA:0000268.label: anal fin proximal radial
ZFA:0000268.definition: Rod-like internal median skeletal support bones of the anal fin, which articulate with the distal radials.

ZFA:0000936.label: dorsal fin distal radial
ZFA:0000936.definition: Rod-like internal median skeletal support bones of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.

ZFA:0000947.label: dorsal fin proximal radial
ZFA:0000947.definition: Rod-like internal median skeletal support bones of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the distal radials.

ZFA:0000172.label: branchial muscle
ZFA:0000172.definition: Muscle that is part of pharyngeal arches 3-7 which are also known as the branchial arches.

ZFA:0000521.label: hyoid muscle
ZFA:0000521.definition: Muscles that insert into skeletal elements of pharyngeal arch 2 (hyoid arch).  Dorsal hyoid muscles are innervated by small, posterior branches of the facial nerve VII. Ventral hyoid muscles are innervated by the hyoides ramus of VII.

ZFA:0000236.label: mandibular muscle
ZFA:0000236.definition: Muscle that are part of the  mandibular arch (pharyngeal arch 1).

ZFA:0000713.label: abducens motor nucleus
ZFA:0000713.definition: Hindbrain motor nucleus which is the origin of motor axons of cranial nerve VI. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000512.label: facial lobe
ZFA:0000512.definition: Hindbrain nucleus that doesn't project to the spinal cord.

ZFA:0000518.label: griseum centrale
ZFA:0000518.definition: Hindbrain nucleus which is longitudinally oriented and situated along the ventral fourth ventricle and extends rostrally up to the level of the tegmentum of the midbrain. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000215.label: inferior olive
ZFA:0000215.definition: Hindbrain nucleus where climbing fibers originate. The neurons in the inferior olive are capable of prolonged oscillatory activity.  The inferior olive is called a precerebellar nucleus since virtually all of the efferent axons terminate in the cerebellum.

ZFA:0000366.label: inferior raphe nucleus
ZFA:0000366.definition: Hindbrain nucleus that provides descending innervation to the brainstem and spinal cord.  Early in development the inferior raphe nucleus emits rostrally and caudally directed projections. However, in the adult, the long projections inferior raphe nucleus are restricted to posterior.

ZFA:0000539.label: locus coeruleus
ZFA:0000539.definition: The locus coeruleus is a widely projecting isthmal noradrenergic nucleus. It consists of between three and ten neurons, most of which have multiple, bilaterally projecting axons.

ZFA:0000398.label: nucleus isthmi
ZFA:0000398.definition: The nucleus isthmi is a hindbrain nucleus located in the tegmentum of rhombomere 1 close to the secondary gustatory nucleus. It projects to and receives excitatory visual input from the ipsilateral optic tectum and the parvocellular and/or magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus.

ZFA:0000551.label: nucleus lateralis valvulae
ZFA:0000551.definition: Hindbrain nucleus in the tegmental region of rhombomere 1.  The cells of the nucleus are granular and lie at the ventral border of the cerebellum and brain stem.

ZFA:0000815.label: nucleus of the medial longitudinal fasciculus medulla oblongata

ZFA:0001697.label: octaval nerve motor nucleus
ZFA:0001697.definition: Hindbrain nucleus which consists of cell bodies whose axons exit the hindbrain via cranial nerve VIII and innervate hair cells of the lateral line and inner ear. The neurons of these nuclei are unusual in that they extend both contra- and ipsilateral dendrites.

ZFA:0001429.label: raphe nucleus
ZFA:0001429.definition: Ventral hindbrain nuclei just caudal to the interpeduncular nucleus.

ZFA:0000440.label: superior raphe nucleus
ZFA:0000440.definition: Hindbrain nucleus that is located in ventral rhombomeres 1-3 and gives rise to ascending fibers innervating most areas of the brain.  Early in development, both the superior raphe nucleus emits rostrally and caudally directed projections. However, in the adult, the long projections of superior raphe nucleus  restricted to anterior.

ZFA:0000714.label: accessory pretectal nucleus
ZFA:0000714.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and lies dorsolateral to the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000324.label: caudal periventricular hypothalamus
ZFA:0000324.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the caudal hypothalamus and surrounds the paired posterior ventricular recesses of the third ventricle. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000631.label: caudal pretectal nucleus
ZFA:0000631.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is rostrally contiguous with the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. Cells of the caudal pretectal nucleus are slightly smaller and less orderly around a central neuropil than those of the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000325.label: caudal thalamic nucleus
ZFA:0000325.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000482.label: caudal tuberal nucleus
ZFA:0000482.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located posterior to the paraventricular organ.

ZFA:0000182.label: central caudal thalamic nucleus
ZFA:0000182.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the caudal portion of the dorsal thalamus, ventral to the dorsal caudal thalamic nucleus.

ZFA:0000485.label: central nucleus inferior lobe
ZFA:0000485.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the inferior lobe of the hypothalamus and consists of masses of large cells presumably migrated from the periventricular cell masses and receives signals from the secondary gustatory nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: central nucleus of the inferior lobe

ZFA:0000635.label: central pretectal nucleus
ZFA:0000635.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and is dorsal to the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus and the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000193.label: diffuse nucleus inferior lobe
ZFA:0000193.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the inferior lobe of the hypothalamus and consists of masses of small cells presumably migrated from the periventricular cell masses. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000194.label: dorsal accessory optic nucleus
ZFA:0000194.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and is ventral to the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus and the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000647.label: dorsal caudal thalamic nucleus
ZFA:0000647.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the caudal portion of the dorsal thalamus, dorsal to the central caudal thalamic nucleus.

ZFA:0001669.label: intermediate nucleus
ZFA:0001669.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located between the dorsal hypothalamus and the caudal tuberal nucleus and does not contain tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactive cells.

ZFA:0000227.label: lateral hypothalamic nucleus
ZFA:0000227.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is the lateral part of the ventral hypothalamic zone. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000248.label: magnocellular preoptic nucleus
ZFA:0000248.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is dorsal to the caudal parvocellular preoptic nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000235.label: magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
ZFA:0000235.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is caudally contiguous with the caudal pretectal nucleus. Cells of the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus are slightly larger and more orderly around a central neuropil than those of the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005850.label: nucleus of the caudal commissure
ZFA:0005850.definition: A cluster of neurons first visible in the embryonic diencephalon located in the dorsolateral brain just posterior to the posterior commissure,  that project growth cones ventrally along the posterior commissure to the anterior tegmentum where the PC intersects two longitudinal tracts, the tract of the postoptic commissure (TPOC) and the medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF). Once at the intersection, nuc PC growth cones turn posteriorly onto the TPOC in the dorsal tegmentum and follow it to the hindbrain.

ZFA:0005339.label: nucleus of the lateral recess
ZFA:0005339.definition: Is a diencephalic nucleus located in the caudal periventricular hypothalamus surrounding the lateral recess of the third ventricle.

ZFA:0000941.label: nucleus of the medial longitudinal fasciculus synencephalon
ZFA:0000941.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the synencephalon, is located adjacent to the caudal commissure, and extends axons into the medial longitudinal fasciculus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005340.label: nucleus of the posterior recess
ZFA:0005340.definition: A diencephalic nucleus that is part of caudal periventricular hypothalmus surrounding the posterior recess of the third ventricle.

ZFA:0001340.label: nucleus of the tract of the postoptic commissure
ZFA:0001340.definition: The nucleus containing the cell bodies of neurons whose axons form the postoptic commissure.

ZFA:0000397.label: nucleus subglomerulosis
ZFA:0000397.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000404.label: paracommissural nucleus
ZFA:0000404.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the synencephalon and is located adjacent to the caudal commissure. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000475.label: paraventricular organ
ZFA:0000475.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located anterior to the caudal tuberal nucleus and contains tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactive CSF contacting bipolar cells.

ZFA:0001680.label: parvocellular preoptic nucleus
ZFA:0001680.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the preoptic area. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000406.label: parvocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
ZFA:0000406.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000260.label: periventricular nucleus
ZFA:0000260.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is the periventricular part of the ventral hypothalamic zone. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000408.label: periventricular nucleus of caudal tuberculum
ZFA:0000408.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located between the ventral thalamus and the hypothalamus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001662.label: preglomerular nucleus
ZFA:0001662.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the caudal tuberculum. The preglomerular nuclei make up most of the migrated nuclei within the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000601.label: pretectal periventricular nucleus
ZFA:0000601.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the synencephalon and the pretectum and is located periventricularly. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000427.label: rostral thalamic nucleus
ZFA:0000427.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the anterior portion of the dorsal thalamus.

ZFA:0000581.label: rostral tuberal nucleus
ZFA:0000581.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is the most anterior and lateral part of the ventral hypothalamic zone. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000683.label: subcommissural organ
ZFA:0000683.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the synencephalon, is located adjacent to the caudal commissure and contains ciliated neurosecretory ependymal cells. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000441.label: suprachiasmatic nucleus
ZFA:0000441.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the preoptic area and is ventrolateral to the caudal parvocellular preoptic nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000448.label: tertiary gustatory nucleus
ZFA:0000448.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is located ventral to the medial preglomerular nucleus in the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000294.label: torus lateralis
ZFA:0000294.definition: Diencephalic nucleus which is part of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000454.label: ventral accessory optic nucleus
ZFA:0000454.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and is ventromedial to the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus and the caudal pretectal nucleus. The ventral accessory optic nucleus is very large in zebrafish as compared to other cyprinids. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005576.label: ventral thalamus nucleus
ZFA:0005576.definition: Brain nuclei located in the ventral thalamus.

ZFA:0000181.label: caudal zone of dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000181.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is the most caudally located part of the dorsal telencephalon and surrounds the central zone of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: posterior zone of dorsal telencephalic area

ZFA:0000487.label: central zone of dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000487.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is centrally located and is surrounded by the other four dorsal telencephalic regions. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000506.label: dorsal zone of dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000506.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is the most dorsally located part of the dorsal telencephalon and surrounds the central zone of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: dorsal zone of dorsal telencephalic area

ZFA:0000536.label: lateral zone of dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000536.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is laterally located and surrounds the central zone of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: lateral zone of dorsal telencephalic area

ZFA:0000391.label: medial zone of dorsal telencephalon
ZFA:0000391.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is medially located and surrounds the central zone of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: medial zone of dorsal telencephalic area

ZFA:0001339.label: nucleus of the tract of the anterior commissure
ZFA:0001339.definition: Telencephalic nucleus from which the axons of the anterior commissure originate.

ZFA:0000246.label: nucleus taeniae
ZFA:0000246.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is located immediately ventral to the caudal zone of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001667.label: peripheral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0001667.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which has migrated away from the ependyma and consists of the central, lateral nuclei and the dorsal and ventral entopeduncular nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001666.label: periventricular nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0001666.definition: Telencephalic nucleus which is in contact with the median ependymal lining of the ventricle and consists of the dorsal, ventral, supracommissural and postcommissural nuclei of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000481.label: caudal preglomerular nucleus
ZFA:0000481.definition: Preglomerular nucleus which is the most caudomedial of the preglomerular nuclei of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000209.label: lateral preglomerular nucleus
ZFA:0000209.definition: Preglomerular nucleus which is located between the rostral and medial preglomerular nuclei of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000390.label: medial preglomerular nucleus
ZFA:0000390.definition: Preglomerular nucleus which is located between the lateral and caudal preglomerular nuclei of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000580.label: rostral preglomerular nucleus
ZFA:0000580.definition: Preglomerular nucleus which is the most rostrolaterally located of the preglomerular nuclei of the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000179.label: caudal root of abducens nerve
ZFA:0000179.definition: Cranial nerve root which is part of the abducens nerve (CN-VI) and is located at the level of the intermediate reticular formation. Fuses with the rostral root of the abducens nerve and courses rostrally once outside the brain stem. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000192.label: descending trigeminal root
ZFA:0000192.definition: The bundle of the sensory root of the trigeminal nerve that descends in the medulla oblongata providing somatosensory input to the nucleus of the descending trigeminal root and to the medial funicular nucleus.

ZFA:0000826.label: central nucleus torus semicircularis
ZFA:0000826.definition: Midbrain nucleus which is part of the torus semicircularis and is the target of ascending octavolateralis systems related to audition. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005868.label: griseum tectale
ZFA:0005868.definition: Rostral cell mass bordering the pretectum.  The cells are stained with the gene nurod and are Hu positive.  The region is named for its presumed  homology to the avian griseum tectale.

ZFA:0000609.label: ventrolateral nucleus
ZFA:0000609.definition: Midbrain nucleus which is part of the torus semicircularis and is the target of ascending octavolateralis systems related to mechanoreception. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000343.label: dorsal nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000343.definition: Periventricular nucleus which lies rostral to the anterior commissure and is contiguous caudally with the supracommissural nucleus of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000819.label: postcommissural nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000819.definition: Periventricular nucleus which is contiguous with the supracommissural nucleus of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000689.label: supracommissural nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000689.definition: Periventricular nucleus which is contiguous with the caudal part of the dorsal nucleus of the ventral telencephalon and the postcommissural nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000456.label: ventral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000456.definition: Periventricular nucleus which lies rostral to the anterior commissure of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001668.label: central nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0001668.definition: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon which is located immediately lateral to the dorsal nucleus of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000340.label: dorsal entopeduncular nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000340.definition: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon which is a band of tightly packed cells starting at the level of the anterior commissure and disappearing more rostrally. May be homologous to the intermediate nucleus of the area ventralis of other species. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000176.label: lateral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000176.definition: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon that has migrated to the periphery of the brain. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000299.label: ventral entopeduncular nucleus of ventral telencephalon
ZFA:0000299.definition: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon that is a band of tightly packed cells starting at the level of the anterior commissure and extends into the telencephalo-diencephalic boundary region. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0001676.label: annular ligament
ZFA:0001676.definition: Ligament that is in the eye and is located at the angle between the cornea and the iris.

ZFA:0005644.label: ceratobranchial 5 ligament
ZFA:0005644.definition: The ligament that connects the anteroventral tips of ceratobranchials 5 medially.

ZFA:0005637.label: intercostal ligament
ZFA:0005637.definition: Ligament that connects one rib to another.

ZFA:0005501.label: interopercular-mandibular ligament
ZFA:0005501.definition: Interopercular-mandibular ligament is a ligament that connects the interopercle to the retroarticular element of the lower jaw.

ZFA:0005636.label: interossicular ligament
ZFA:0005636.definition: Ligament that connects the intercalarium to the  anterior process of the tripus and the scaphium.

ZFA:0007119.label: intervertebral ligament
ZFA:0007119.definition: Ligament that connects adjacent vertebra. The intervertebral ligament (IVL) connects the posterior vertebral end plate to  the anterior vertebral end plate of adjacent vertebra. For example the IVL connects the posterior end plate of vertebra 14 to the anterior end plate of vertebra 15.  It is typically composed of three distinct layers: the notochord sheet which is mainly type II collagen; the outer elastin layer; and a layer of type I collagen fiber bundles.

ZFA:0005502.label: lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament
ZFA:0005502.definition: Lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the autopalatine.

ZFA:0005503.label: lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament
ZFA:0005503.definition: Lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the ectopterygoid.

ZFA:0005641.label: maxillo-mandibular ligament
ZFA:0005641.definition: Ligament that connects the dentary to the maxilla.

ZFA:0005642.label: maxillo-rostroid ligament
ZFA:0005642.definition: Ligament that connects the  rostral process of the maxilla  to the kinethmoid.

ZFA:0005885.label: operculohyoid ligament
ZFA:0005885.definition: Ligament that connects the anterior apex of the opercle to the posterior end of the ceratohyal.  The ligament extends orthogonal and anterior to the opercle.

ZFA:0005265.label: premaxillary-maxillary ligament
ZFA:0005265.definition: Ligament that connects the premaxilla to the maxilla.

ZFA:0005643.label: premaxillo-rostroid ligament
ZFA:0005643.definition: Ligament that, in the adult, attaches the premaxilla to its counterpart at the midline and the kinethmoid posterodorsally.

ZFA:0005646.label: preopercle-retroarticular ligament
ZFA:0005646.definition: Ligament that connects the  preopercle to the retroarticular anteroventrally.

ZFA:0005264.label: primordial ligament
ZFA:0005264.definition: Ligament that connects the maxilla with the lower jaw.

ZFA:0005638.label: scapulo-vertebral ligament
ZFA:0005638.definition: Ligaments that runs from the parapophyses of the anteriormost centrum to the exoccipital.  There are two  scapulo-vertebral ligaments in zebrafish.

ZFA:0005645.label: supracleithrum-intercalar ligament
ZFA:0005645.definition: Short ligament that runs from the hooked anterior end of the supracleithrum to the intercalar.

ZFA:0000630.label: caudal parvocellular preoptic nucleus
ZFA:0000630.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the preoptic area and is the posterior continuation of the rostral parvocellular preoptic nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000426.label: rostral parvocellular preoptic nucleus
ZFA:0000426.definition: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the preoptic area and is the anterior continuation of the caudal parvocellular preoptic nucleus and is ventral to the telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005342.label: anterior catecholaminergic tract
ZFA:0005342.definition: CNS white matter, an axonal tract between ventral diencephalon and ventral telencephalon.  At 3 d, the anterior catecholaminergic tract includes noradrenergic projections from the hindbrain and dopaminergic projections from ventral dopaminergic neurons. During later development, other catecholaminergic projections may also contribute to the anterior catecholaminergic tract.

ZFA:0000318.label: brainstem and spinal white matter
ZFA:0000318.definition: CNS white matter that is part of the brain stem or spinal cord.

ZFA:0001708.label: cerebellar white matter
ZFA:0001708.definition: CNS white matter that is part of the cerebellum.

ZFA:0000338.label: diencephalic white matter
ZFA:0000338.definition: CNS white matter that is part of the diencephalon.

ZFA:0005343.label: endohypothalamic tract
ZFA:0005343.definition: CNS white matter, axonal tract interconnecting catecholaminergic cell groups in the posterior tuberculum and hypothalamus.

ZFA:0001692.label: hindbrain commissure
ZFA:0001692.definition: CNS white matter that crosses the midline within the hindbrain.

ZFA:0000684.label: intertectal commissure
ZFA:0000684.definition: CNS white matter (commissure) that runs between the optic tectal hemispheres.

ZFA:0007012.label: lateral forebrain bundle
ZFA:0007012.definition: In the adult bilaterally paired compact tract located lateral to the medial forebrain bundle that extends to the diencephalon. Formed from several fascicles that  originate in the precommissural telencephalon and converge rostrocaudally.  In the seven day old fish bilaterally paired bundle that runs caudally from the anterior commissure to the forebrain. In the caudal diencephalon the bundle divides into two parts. The thinner part runs more laterally and ventrally, and the thicker part was located more medially and dorsally. Both bundles run in the caudal direction toward the cranial wall of the lateral recess of  the diencephalic ventricle, where they apparently exchange some fibers. Then, they continue in the caudal  direction, surrounding the lateral recess from the ventral and dorsal side, and meet close to the caudal wall of lateral recess at the level of the commissure of the posterior tuberculum.

ZFA:0005111.label: medial forebrain bundle
ZFA:0005111.definition: Tract that originates in the telencephalon lies medial to the lateral forebrain bundle and extends into the diencephalon approaching the posterior tuberal nucleus.  In embryos the tract connects cells in the ventral olfactory bulb to those in the septal area.

ZFA:0005341.label: medial longitudinal catecholaminergic tract
ZFA:0005341.definition: CNS white matter tract, major catecholaminergic tract that originates in the diencephalon, passes the locus coeruleus and projects through the hindbrain into the spinal cord.  Dopaminergic neurons of the posterior tuberculum and lateral hypothalamus provide the predominant contribution to descending mlct projections.

ZFA:0005789.label: preopticohypophyseal tract
ZFA:0005789.definition: Axon tract originating  from the two hemispheres of the neurosecretory preoptic areas  converging into the midline and terminating at the ventral part of the hypothalamus at the presumed location of the pituitary. Analogous to the supraopticohypophyseal tract in mammals.

ZFA:0005344.label: preopticohypothalamic tract
ZFA:0005344.definition: CNS white matter, axonal tract between the preoptic region and ventral diencephalon.

ZFA:0005864.label: retinotectal tract
ZFA:0005864.definition: Portion of optic tract that innervates the optic tectum.

ZFA:0000643.label: rostral cerebellar tract
ZFA:0000643.definition: CNS white matter comprised of the rostral mesencephalo-cerebellar and caudal mesencephalo-cerebellar tracts. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000579.label: rostral mesencephalo-cerebellar tract
ZFA:0000579.definition: Brainstem tract which carries cerebellar afferents from the pretectum and runs medial to the lateral longitudinal fascicle for a distance before turning dorsally to traverse the nucleus lateralis valvulae. Fuses with the caudal mesencephalo-cerebellar tract upon entering the cerebellum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000430.label: secondary gustatory tract
ZFA:0000430.definition: White matter connecting the primary gustatory nuclei to  the secondary gustatory nucleus in the isthmus.

ZFA:0001657.label: supraoptic tract
ZFA:0001657.definition: CNS tract/commissure which extends between the telencephalon and diencephalon and lies along the dorsal edge of the optic stalk.

ZFA:0000597.label: telencephalic white matter
ZFA:0000597.definition: CNS white matter that is part of the telencephalon.

ZFA:0005452.label: tract of the caudal commissure
ZFA:0005452.definition: Tract which originates from several clusters of cell bodies in the rostral midbrain, the anterior tegmentum and the nucleus of the posterior commissure.  The neurons that are part of the nucleus of the posterior commissure have axons which course ventrally toward the anterior tegmentum, while the ventral tegmental clusters of neurons have axons which course dorsally along the posterior commissure and cross the dorsal midline to the contralateral side they then turn posteriorly and extend to the posterior region of the tegmentum and eventually into the hindbrain via the tract of the postoptic commissure. .

ZFA:0005875.label: tract of the commissure of the caudal tuberculum
ZFA:0005875.definition: Tract that extends from the intersection of the tract of the postoptic commissure and supraoptic tract that projects caudally across the hypothalamus and into the commissure of the caudal tuberculum.  The axons appear to originate from a symmetric group of neurons in the forebrain that travel caudally into the diencephalon and then decussate, with some axons continuing  to travel longitudinally and join other axons crossing the midline.   There does not appear to be a clear ortholog of the TCPT in mammals; and the function(s) of the TCPT are not currently known.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: tract of the commissure of the posterior tuberculum

ZFA:0001366.label: tract of the postoptic commissure
ZFA:0001366.definition: Tract that extends from the postoptic commissure through a curved trajectory in the diencephalon into the ventral midbrain. In the anterior diencephalon the TOP is a single tract but caudally the axons of the TPOC diverge and tend to grow in distinct parallel bundles. The more dorsal bundles extend in the dorsolateral tegmentum, the ventral bundles of the TPOC merge into the DLF in the hindbrain.

ZFA:0005570.label: corneo-scleral junction
ZFA:0005570.definition: The line where the cornea and the sclera meet.

ZFA:0001367.label: forebrain midbrain boundary
ZFA:0001367.definition: The boundary between the diencephalon and the mesencephalon.

ZFA:0007027.label: forebrain midbrain boundary neural keel
ZFA:0007027.definition: Portion of anterior neural keel that gives rise to the forebrain midbrain boundary neural rod.

ZFA:0007020.label: forebrain midbrain boundary neural plate
ZFA:0007020.definition: Portion of anterior neural plate that gives rise to the forebrain midbrain boundary neural keel.

ZFA:0007033.label: forebrain midbrain boundary neural rod
ZFA:0007033.definition: Portion of anterior neural rod that gives rise to the forebrain midbrain boundary neural tube.

ZFA:0007040.label: forebrain midbrain boundary neural tube
ZFA:0007040.definition: Portion of anterior neural tube that gives rise to the forebrain midbrain boundary.

ZFA:0000042.label: midbrain hindbrain boundary
ZFA:0000042.definition: The boundary between the mesencephalon and the rhombencephalon.

ZFA:0007045.label: midbrain hindbrain boundary neural keel
ZFA:0007045.definition: Portion of neural keel that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary neural rod.

ZFA:0007044.label: midbrain hindbrain boundary neural plate
ZFA:0007044.definition: Portion of neural plate that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary neural keel.

ZFA:0007046.label: midbrain hindbrain boundary neural rod
ZFA:0007046.definition: Portion of neural rod that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary neural tube.

ZFA:0007047.label: midbrain hindbrain boundary neural tube
ZFA:0007047.definition: Portion of neural tube that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary.

ZFA:0001343.label: telencephalon diencephalon boundary
ZFA:0001343.definition: Boundary between the telencephalon and diencephalon.

ZFA:0001344.label: zona limitans intrathalamica
ZFA:0001344.definition: The border between the dorsal and ventral thalamus.

ZFA:0001284.label: optic fissure
ZFA:0001284.definition: Groove that is in the ventral optic cup and through which blood vessels pass to the enclosed mesenchyme.

ZFA:0005491.label: optic furrow
ZFA:0005491.definition: Groove that is in the ventral optic cup remnant of the optic fissure.

ZFA:0000589.label: sulcus ypsiloniformis
ZFA:0000589.definition: Anatomical groove which separates the dorsal and medial zones of dorsal telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0005901.label: superior ocular sulcus
ZFA:0005901.definition: Transient groove in the dorsal eye lined by basal lamina.  The groove extends across the dorsal retina to partially separate the nasal and temporal retinal lobes.  The sulcus forms soon after optic cup formation and as the eye develops it becomes broader and shallower until it is undetectable.

ZFA:0000305.label: ventral sulcus
ZFA:0000305.definition: Groove that separates the paired inferior (or lateral) lobes of the hypothalamus from the tuberal hypothalamus.

ZFA:0001591.label: endochondral bone
ZFA:0001591.definition: Replacement bone that forms within cartilage.

ZFA:0001630.label: perichondral bone
ZFA:0001630.definition: Replacement bone that forms within the connective tissue surrounding cartilage.

ZFA:0001699.label: caudal octaval nerve motor nucleus
ZFA:0001699.definition: Octaval nerve motor nucleus that is initially located within rhombomere 7.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: rostral cranial nerve VIII motor nucleus

ZFA:0001698.label: rostral octaval nerve motor nucleus
ZFA:0001698.definition: Octaval nerve motor nucleus that is initially located within rhombomere 6.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: rostral cranial nerve VIII motor nucleus

ZFA:0000090.label: apical ectodermal ridge dorsal fin
ZFA:0000090.definition: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the dorsal fin.

ZFA:0000717.label: apical ectodermal ridge median fin fold
ZFA:0000717.definition: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the median fin fold.

ZFA:0000085.label: apical ectodermal ridge pectoral fin bud
ZFA:0000085.definition: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the pectoral fin bud.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: apical ectodermal ridge pectoral fin buds

ZFA:0001450.label: apical ectodermal ridge pelvic fin
ZFA:0001450.definition: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0001385.label: apical ectodermal ridge pelvic fin bud
ZFA:0001385.definition: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the pelvic fin bud.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: apical ectodermal ridge pelvic fin buds

ZFA:0000174.label: cerebellovestibular tract
ZFA:0000174.definition: Cerebellar tract that consists of efferent fibers from the Purkinje cells to the neurons of the vestibular nuclei in the hindbrain. The cerebellovestibular tracts are involved in precise motor controls, such as the vestibulo-ocular reflex.

ZFA:0000490.label: commissura cerebelli
ZFA:0000490.definition: Cerebellar commissure which is located within the ventral boundary zone between valvula and corpus cerebelli. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

ZFA:0000639.label: commissure of the secondary gustatory nucleus
ZFA:0000639.definition: Cerebellar commissure that runs between the bulbo-spinal tract and the vestibulo-spinal tract.

ZFA:0000469.label: otic vesicle anterior protrusion
ZFA:0000469.definition: Otic vesicle protrusion that is anteriorly located and gives rise to the pillar of the anterior semicircular canal.

ZFA:0000232.label: otic vesicle lateral protrusion
ZFA:0000232.definition: Otic vesicle protrusion that is initially laterally located and then bifurcates and fuses anteriorly with the anterior protrusion, and posteriorly with the posterior protrusion.

ZFA:0000412.label: otic vesicle posterior protrusion
ZFA:0000412.definition: Otic vesicle protrusion that is anteriorly located and gives rise to the pillar of the posterior semicircular canal.

ZFA:0001716.label: otic vesicle ventral protrusion
ZFA:0001716.definition: Otic vesicle protrusion that is initially ventrally located and then fuses with the lateral protrusion, giving rise to the pillar of the lateral semicircular canal.

ZFA:0007054.label: pillar of the anterior semicircular canal
ZFA:0007054.definition: Pillar of the semicircular canal around whose perimeter runs the anterior semicircular canal.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: anterior pillar of the semicircular canal
anterior hub of the semicircular canal

ZFA:0007055.label: pillar of the lateral semicircular canal
ZFA:0007055.definition: Pillar of the semicircular canal around whose perimeter runs the lateral semicircular canal.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: lateral hub of the semicircular canal
ventral piller of the semicircular canal

ZFA:0007056.label: pillar of the posterior semicircular canal
ZFA:0007056.definition: Pillar of the semicircular canal around whose perimeter runs the posterior semicircular canal.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: posterior hub of the semicircular canal

ZFA:0005005.label: aortic arch 1
ZFA:0005005.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 1. The paired aortic arch 1 arteries branch off of the ventral aorta, and empty into the right and left lateral dorsal aorta.

ZFA:0005006.label: aortic arch 2
ZFA:0005006.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 2. Aortic arch 2 is paired and is a vestigial structure.

ZFA:0005007.label: aortic arch 3
ZFA:0005007.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 3. The paired aortic arch 3 arteries branch directly from the ventral aorta to the lateral dorsal aorta, and are retained as the branchial arteries providing circulation through the gills in the adult.

ZFA:0005008.label: aortic arch 4
ZFA:0005008.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 4. The paired aortic arch 4 arteries branch directly from the ventral aorta to the lateral dorsal aorta, and are retained as the branchial arteries providing circulation through the gills in the adult.

ZFA:0005009.label: aortic arch 5
ZFA:0005009.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 5. Aortic arch 5 artery is paired and has a common trunk with aortic arch 6 from the ventral aorta, and drains via a separate branch of the lateral dorsal aorta. Aortic arches 5 and 6 supply the trunk and tail with oxygenated blood.

ZFA:0005016.label: aortic arch 6
ZFA:0005016.definition: Aortic arch that is part of pharyngeal arch 6. Aortic arch 6 artery is paired and has a common trunk with aortic arch 5 from the ventral aorta, and drains via a separate branch of the lateral dorsal aorta. Aortic arches 5 and 6 supply the trunk and tail with oxygenated blood.

ZFA:0005052.label: anterior mesencephalic central artery
ZFA:0005052.definition: Arteries that irrigate rostral regions of the midbrain. They extend between the basal communicating artery to the anterior cerebral vein.

ZFA:0005021.label: cerebellar central artery
ZFA:0005021.definition: Extend upward from the PCS, branch to provide an arterial feed to the hindbrain, then drain back down into the PHBC.

ZFA:0005078.label: middle mesencephalic central artery
ZFA:0005078.definition: Projects rostrally and dorsally from the AMCtA to irrigate the midportion of the midbrain.

ZFA:0005079.label: posterior mesencephalic central artery
ZFA:0005079.definition: Project dorsally from BCA to irrigate the caudal part of midbrain.

ZFA:0001286.label: caudal vein plexus
ZFA:0001286.definition: Post-vent vasculature which forms an interconnecting network of venous tubes. The caudal vein plexus forms via a very active period of angiogenic sprouting, beginning at 25 hpf when venous endothelial cells of the posterior cardinal vein sprout and migrate ventrally, then fuse with neighboring tip cells. This process reiterates during a five-hour window, forming a primordial plexus by 30 hpf. By two days of development, the primitive caudal vein plexus has matured into a complex, well-perfused, venous vascular network. Starting at 4 dpf the caudal vein plexus starts to remodel and simplify.

ZFA:0005858.label: hyaloid capillaries
ZFA:0005858.definition: Capillaries that branch from the hyaloid artery and drain into the hyaloid vein.  The hyaloid capillaries are located behind the lens and may be transient.

ZFA:0005074.label: central cardiac conduction system
ZFA:0005074.definition: Cardiac conduction system, characterized by slow impulse propagation and prolonged refractory periods.

ZFA:0005075.label: peripheral cardiac conduction system
ZFA:0005075.definition: Portion of the cardiac conduction system, with rapid impulse propagation.  In the zebrafish fast conduction takes place in the trabecular layer.

ZFA:0005064.label: atrioventricular valve
ZFA:0005064.definition: The atrioventricular valve has four distinct leaflets oriented anterior, posterior, left, and right of the atrioventricular orifice.

ZFA:0000680.label: sinoatrial valve
ZFA:0000680.definition: Heart valve that forms between the atrium and the sinus venosus.

ZFA:0001375.label: ventriculo bulbo valve
ZFA:0001375.definition: A heart valve located between the ventricle and bulbus arteriosus.

ZFA:0005605.label: lymphangioblast cord
ZFA:0005605.definition: The primordial vasculature that will develop into lymph vessels.  The lymphangioblast cord is composed of lymphangioblast or lymph endothelial cells in a solid linear mass called a cord.  The cord then undergoes morphogenesis to form the lumen of the vessel.

ZFA:0005077.label: vascular cord
ZFA:0005077.definition: The primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels  by the process of tubulogenesis.  The  vascular cord is composed of angioblast or vascular endothelial cells in a solid linear mass called a cord.  The cord then undergoes  tubulogenesis to form the lumen of the vessels.

ZFA:0005097.label: caudal fin vasculature
ZFA:0005097.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005104.label: presumptive dorsal fin fold
ZFA:0005104.definition: Stripe of tissue on the dorsal side of the fish, fated to become the dorsal region of the median fin fold.

ZFA:0005103.label: presumptive ventral fin fold
ZFA:0005103.definition: Stripe of tissue on the ventral side of the fish,  fated to become the ventral region of the median fin fold.

ZFA:0005831.label: facial lymphatic network
ZFA:0005831.definition: Interconnected lymph vasculature in the anterior portion of the head.

ZFA:0005319.label: intersegmental lymph vessel
ZFA:0005319.definition: Lymph vessel that is located between the somites.

ZFA:0005126.label: intestinal bulb epithelium
