ZFA:0005126.definition: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the intestinal bulb.

ZFA:0005127.label: mid intestine epithelium
ZFA:0005127.definition: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the mid intestine.

ZFA:0005128.label: posterior intestine epithelium
ZFA:0005128.definition: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the posterior intestine.

ZFA:0005130.label: dorsal mesentery
ZFA:0005130.definition: The mesentery that originates from the dorsal side of the peritoneal cavity.

ZFA:0005133.label: ventral mesentery
ZFA:0005133.definition: The mesentery that originates from the ventral side of the peritoneal cavity.

ZFA:0005136.label: inner dental epithelium
ZFA:0005136.definition: Inner layer of the dental organ, composed of ameloblasts.

ZFA:0005137.label: outer dental epithelium
ZFA:0005137.definition: Outer layer of the dental organ.

ZFA:0005135.label: primary dental epithelium
ZFA:0005135.definition: Epithelium that surrounds a primary tooth.  This epithelium is committed to formation of replacement teeth.

ZFA:0005897.label: anal protractor
ZFA:0005897.definition: Longitudinal muscle that on the anterior end is  continuous with the retractor ischii and on the posterior end inserts into the base of the first anal ray.

ZFA:0005896.label: anal retractor
ZFA:0005896.definition: Longitudinal unpaired muscle that attaches to the base of the  most posterior ray of the anal fin (usually ray 14) and runs posteriorly into he hypaxial musculature of the caudal fin.  The anal retractor pulls the anal fin toward the body.

ZFA:0005280.label: cardiac muscle
ZFA:0005280.definition: Muscle composed of cardiac muscle cells that is part of the heart.

ZFA:0005816.label: dorsal fin protractor
ZFA:0005816.definition: Anterior longitudinal muscles of the dorsal fin.  The dorsal fin protractor  originates from the base of the first soft ray of the dorsal fin, extends along the midline just underneath the skin, and inserts at the posterior portion of the skull.  Contracting the  dorsal protractor will raise the fin.

ZFA:0005817.label: dorsal fin retractor
ZFA:0005817.definition: Anterior longitudinal muscles of the dorsal fin.  That originates from the caudal end of the dorsal fin base, stretches along the midline between the right and left epaxial muscles, and inserts at the dorsal base of the tail fin.  Contracting the dorsal retractor will lower the fin.

ZFA:0000738.label: dorsal oblique extraocular muscle
ZFA:0000738.definition: Extraocular muscle innervated by the trochlear nerve.  The dorsal rectus and dorsal oblique muscles have overlapping insertions at the scleral-corneal junction on the dorsal side of the adult eye, though they have distinct insertion sites in 5dpf fish.   The dorsal oblique originates separately from the rectus muscles. The unsegmented paraxial head mesoderm contributes to the dorsal oblique muscles.   All the oblique extraocular muscles originate together from the anterior ethmoid plate.

ZFA:0000345.label: dorsal rectus
ZFA:0000345.definition: Extraocular muscle that inserts at the scleral corneal junction on the dorsal side of the eye. The dorsal rectus is innervated by the oculomotor nerve.  The dorsal rectus and dorsal oblique muscles have overlapping insertions in the adult eye though they have distinct insertion sites in 5dpf fish.

ZFA:0005785.label: esophageal striated muscle
ZFA:0005785.definition: Striated muscle of the esophogus. Permits voluntary swallowing.

ZFA:0001652.label: head muscle
ZFA:0001652.definition: Muscle which is part of the head.

ZFA:0000362.label: hypaxialis
ZFA:0000362.definition: The hypaxialis consists of that part of the body musculature lying ventral to the midlateral horizontal septum.

ZFA:0000528.label: interradialis caudalis
ZFA:0000528.definition: Muscle of the caudal fin that attaches to the appendicular skeleton and attaches to the first long ray on the dorsal side of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0000383.label: lateral rectus
ZFA:0000383.definition: Extraocular muscle that runs parallel to the long axis of the fish and inserts on the caudal side of the eye at the sclera-corneal .  The lateral rectus muscles originate substantially posterior to the other rectus muscles. The lateral rectus is innervated by the abducens nerve.  The unsegmented paraxial head mesoderm contributes to the lateral rectus.

ZFA:0000230.label: longitudinal hypochordal
ZFA:0000230.definition: Muscle that attaches to the parhypurpophyses. The muscle inserts on the upper three to five caudal fin rays.

ZFA:0000301.label: medial rectus
ZFA:0000301.definition: Extraocular muscle that runs parallel to the long axis of the fish and inserts on the anterior side of the eye at the sclera-corneal (SC) junction.  The medial rectus lies in the same anatomical plane as the lateral rectus.  The medial rectus is innervated by the oculomotor nerve.

ZFA:0001056.label: myotome
ZFA:0001056.definition: Muscle that develops from somite and gives rise to body wall muscle masses.

ZFA:0005863.label: pectoral protractor
ZFA:0005863.definition: Pectoral fin muscle.  Links pectoral fin and branchial movement and stabilizes the pectoral girdle.  Thought to be the teleost homologue of the cucullaris muscle group.

ZFA:0001653.label: pericardial muscle
ZFA:0001653.definition: Muscle which is paired and runs anterio-posteriorly along the heart and is covered with epicardium.

ZFA:0005277.label: skeletal muscle
ZFA:0005277.definition: Muscle, composed of long cylindrical, multinucleated cells that attaches to the skeleton via tendons.

ZFA:0005274.label: smooth muscle
ZFA:0005274.definition: A non-striated muscle that is composed of spindle-shaped cells.  Smooth muscle usually is organized into sheets that line cavitated organs.

ZFA:0007008.label: ventral intermandibularis anterior
ZFA:0007008.definition: Is a mandibular muscle that attaches to Meckel's cartilage and functions during jaw closing.

ZFA:0007048.label: ventral intermandibularis posterior
ZFA:0007048.definition: Is a mandibular muscle that attaches Meckel's cartilage to the basihyal cartilage and functions in jaw opening.

ZFA:0000861.label: ventral oblique extraocular muscle
ZFA:0000861.definition: Extraocular muscle that inserts at the scleral-corneal junction on the ventral side of the eye.  The insertion point of the ventral oblique and the ventral rectus overlap in adult fish.  All the oblique extraocular muscles originate together from the anterior ethmoid plate.  The ventral oblique is innervated by the oculomotor nerve.

ZFA:0000457.label: ventral rectus
ZFA:0000457.definition: Extraocular muscle that inserts at the scleral-corneal junction on the ventral side of the eye.  The insertion point of the ventral oblique and the ventral rectus overlap in adult fish. The ventral rectus is innervated by the oculomotor nerve.

ZFA:0005148.label: apical epidermal cap
ZFA:0005148.definition: Part of the regeneration epithelium closest to the fin.

ZFA:0005150.label: basal regeneration epithelium
ZFA:0005150.definition: Layer of the wound epidermis that surrounds the blastema.

ZFA:0001270.label: blastema
ZFA:0001270.definition: A regenerating tissue composed of a proliferative mass of undifferentiated progenitor cells from which new differentiated structures arise.

ZFA:0005149.label: distal epidermal cap
ZFA:0005149.definition: Part of regeneration epithelium at the tip of the fin.

ZFA:0005656.label: autopalatine-preethmoid joint
ZFA:0005656.definition: Synovial, ball and socket joint that articulates the autopalatine and the preethmoid.

ZFA:0005626.label: hyomandibula-opercle joint
ZFA:0005626.definition: Synovial joint that articulates the hyomandibula and the opercle.

ZFA:0005627.label: hyomandibula-pterotic joint
ZFA:0005627.definition: Synovial joint that articulates the hyomandibula with the pterotic.

ZFA:0005544.label: hyomandibular-otic region joint
ZFA:0005544.definition: Joint that articulates the hyomandibular cartilage or bone and otic region cartilage or sphenotic bone, and often pterotic bone and prootic bone. Hyomandibular-otic region joint is paired.

ZFA:0005484.label: quadrate-anguloarticular joint
ZFA:0005484.definition: Joint that articulates quadrate and anguloarticular bones. Quadrate-articular joint is paired.

ZFA:0005618.label: anguloarticular-retroarticular joint
ZFA:0005618.definition: Cartilaginous joint that articulates the anguloarticular posteroventrally with the retroarticular.

ZFA:0005423.label: basioccipital-exoccipital joint
ZFA:0005423.definition: Joint that articulates the basioccipital and exoccipital. Basioccipital exoccipital joint is paired.

ZFA:0005613.label: basioccipital-prootic joint
ZFA:0005613.definition: Synchondrosis where the basioccipital meets the prootic anteriorly.

ZFA:0005488.label: mandibular symphysis
ZFA:0005488.definition: Joint that articulates the left and right dentary bones. Mandibular symphysis is unpaired.

ZFA:0005616.label: quadrate-entopterygoid joint
ZFA:0005616.definition: Synchondrosis where the quadrate meets the entopterygoid dorsally.

ZFA:0005486.label: quadrate-metapterygoid joint
ZFA:0005486.definition: Joint that articulates quadrate and metapterygoid bones. Quadrate-metapterygoid joint is paired.

ZFA:0005504.label: vertebra 4-vertebra 5 joint
ZFA:0005504.definition: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 4 and vertebra 5.

ZFA:0005505.label: vertebra 5-vertebra 6 joint
ZFA:0005505.definition: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses.

ZFA:0005506.label: vertebra 6 - vertebra 7 joint
ZFA:0005506.definition: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 6 and vertebra 7.

ZFA:0005420.label: autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint
ZFA:0005420.definition: Joint that articulates the autopalatine and lateral ethmoid and bones. Autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

ZFA:0005891.label: epiotic-parietal joint
ZFA:0005891.definition: Syndesmosis that connects the anterior edge epiotic to the parietal.  The epiotic-parietal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005889.label: epiotic-posttemporal joint
ZFA:0005889.definition: Syndesmosis that connects the posterior lateral edge of the epiotic to the posttemporal. The epiotic-posttemporal joint is paired.

ZFA:0005608.label: frontal-parietal joint
ZFA:0005608.definition: Fibrous joint connecting the frontal bone to the parietal bone.  This joint remains patent in zebrafish throughout their lifetime.

ZFA:0005472.label: inter-frontal joint
ZFA:0005472.definition: Joint between the left and right frontal bone.

ZFA:0005607.label: inter-parietal joint
ZFA:0005607.definition: Fibrous joint connecting the parietal bones.

ZFA:0005560.label: parasphenoid-basioccipital joint
ZFA:0005560.definition: Joint that articulates the parasphenoid and basioccipital. Parasphenoid-basioccipital joint is paired.

ZFA:0005631.label: preopercle horizontal limb-symplectic joint
ZFA:0005631.definition: Fibrous joint that articulates the posterior edge of the  preopercle horizontal limb with the symplectic.

ZFA:0005632.label: preopercle vertical limb-hyomandibula joint
ZFA:0005632.definition: Fibrous joint that articulates the anterior edge of the preopercle vertical limb and the  hyomandibula.

ZFA:0005482.label: prootic-pterosphenoid joint
ZFA:0005482.definition: Joint that articulates the prootic and pterosphenoid. Prootic-pterosphenoid joint is paired.  The parasphenoid borders the prootic medially in a syndesmosis.

ZFA:0005609.label: supraoccipital-parietal joint
ZFA:0005609.definition: Fibrous joint connecting the supraoccipital to the parietal bone.

ZFA:0005164.label: bile ductule
ZFA:0005164.definition: Digestive system duct that collects bile from the canaliculus and transports bile through the liver.

ZFA:0005165.label: common bile duct
ZFA:0005165.definition: Digestive system duct that collects bile from the hepatic bile duct and the cystic duct.

ZFA:0005166.label: cystic duct
ZFA:0005166.definition: Duct that connects the gall bladder and the common bile duct.

ZFA:0005170.label: extrahepatic duct
ZFA:0005170.definition: Bile duct that collects from the intrahepatic ducts and feeds into the common bile duct.

ZFA:0005346.label: extrapancreatic duct
ZFA:0005346.definition: Portion of the pancreatic duct, external to the pancreas body that connects the pancreas with the hepatopancreatic ampulla.

ZFA:0001100.label: hepatic duct
ZFA:0001100.definition: A duct that carries bile from the liver to the intestine.

ZFA:0005167.label: hepatopancreatic ampulla
ZFA:0005167.definition: Ampulla formed by the union of the pancreatic duct and the common bile duct where they enter the intestine.

ZFA:0005169.label: intrahepatic bile duct
ZFA:0005169.definition: Duct that collects bile from the bile ductules and connects to the extrahepatic bile duct.

ZFA:0005748.label: intrapancreatic duct
ZFA:0005748.definition: Digestive duct within the pancreas.  The pancreatic duct carries inactive digestive enzymes to the intestine.

ZFA:0001372.label: pancreatic duct
ZFA:0001372.definition: Duct that collects and carries secretions of the exocrine pancreas.

ZFA:0005411.label: common crus
ZFA:0005411.definition: Duct that forms when the nonampullary ends of the posterior and anterior semicircular canals merge.  The common crus descends connecting the semicircular canals to the horizontal canal.

ZFA:0005162.label: digestive system duct
ZFA:0005162.definition: Ducts that transport enzymes between organs in the digestive system.

ZFA:0001437.label: ductus communicans
ZFA:0001437.definition: The constriction between the anterior and posterior chambers of the swim bladder.  There does not appear to be an identifiable sphincter in the ductus, and therefore other musculature may regulate its opening.

ZFA:0001705.label: endolymphatic duct
ZFA:0001705.definition: Duct that is part of the inner ear and connects to the semicircular canals ending in the endolymphatic sac.

ZFA:0000546.label: mesonephric duct
ZFA:0000546.definition: Duct of the adult kidney (mesonephros), present bilaterally ventral to the somites and leading to the cloacal chamber.

ZFA:0000560.label: oviduct
ZFA:0000560.definition: Duct that connects ovary with cloacal chamber.  In zebrafish the oviduct is a continuation of the ovary.

ZFA:0001430.label: pneumatic duct
ZFA:0001430.definition: A duct connecting the esophagus to the posterior chamber of the swim bladder.

ZFA:0001623.label: posterior pronephric duct
ZFA:0001623.definition: Most posterior portion of the pronephric duct (or tubule as described by Wingert et al, 2007) which ends at the cloacal chamber at the pronephric duct opening.

ZFA:0001622.label: pronephric distal early tubule
ZFA:0001622.definition: Portion of the pronephric duct (or tubule as described by Wingert et al, 2007) which is just posterior to the proximal straight tubule.

ZFA:0001624.label: pronephric distal late tubule
ZFA:0001624.definition: Portion of the pronephric duct (or tubule as described by Wingert et al, 2007) which is just posterior to the distal early tubule.

ZFA:0000150.label: pronephric duct
ZFA:0000150.definition: Duct of the embryonic kidney, present bilaterally ventral to the somites and leading to the cloacal chamber. Wingert et al. have suggested that the pronephric duct as described traditionally may consist of subregions which are analogous to portions of the tubule segment of mammalian and other fish nephrons.

ZFA:0001620.label: pronephric proximal convoluted tubule
ZFA:0001620.definition: Most anterior portion of the pronephric duct (or tubule as described by Wingert et al, 2007).

ZFA:0001621.label: pronephric proximal straight tubule
ZFA:0001621.definition: Portion of the pronephric duct (or tubule as described by Wingert et al, 2007) which is just posterior to the proximal convoluted tubule.

ZFA:0001558.label: pronephric tubule
ZFA:0001558.definition: Bilaterally paired tubes connecting the pronephric glomeruli to the pronephric ducts. In zebrafish and other teleosts, the pronephric nephron and tubules form after the pronephric duct, connecting to the anterior-most tip of the pronephric ducts.

ZFA:0005289.label: renal duct
ZFA:0005289.definition: Tubes in the kidney that collect and transport urine.

ZFA:0001268.label: sperm duct
ZFA:0001268.definition: Is a duct part of the testis that carries sperm and fluid to the cloaca.

ZFA:0005412.label: transverse canal
ZFA:0005412.definition: Duct that crosses the midline connecting the sacculi.

ZFA:0005571.label: ventral canal eye
ZFA:0005571.definition: Duct present in the angle where the cornea meets the ciliary zone that absorbs the aqueous humor.

ZFA:0005200.label: RoL2c
ZFA:0005200.definition: A RoL2 interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0005199.label: RoL2r
ZFA:0005199.definition: A RoL2 interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2.

ZFA:0005218.label: CaD
ZFA:0005218.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 7, with 1 dorsal neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005217.label: CaV
ZFA:0005217.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 7, with 2 ventral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005184.label: MiD2cl
ZFA:0005184.definition: Hindbrain interneuron, part of rhombomere 5, with one dorsal, caudal-lateral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.  The fibers pass through the lateral longitudinal fasciculus.

ZFA:0005185.label: MiD2cm
ZFA:0005185.definition: Hindbrain interneuron, part of rhombomere 5, with one dorsal, caudal-medial neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.  The fibers pass through the medial longitudinal fasciculus.

ZFA:0005183.label: MiD2i
ZFA:0005183.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 5 with one dorsal neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.  The axonal projection is ipsilateral.

ZFA:0005195.label: MiD3cl
ZFA:0005195.definition: Hindbrain interneuron, part of rhombomere 6, with one caudal-lateral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.  The fibers pass through the lateral longitudinal fasciculus.

ZFA:0005196.label: MiD3cm
ZFA:0005196.definition: Hindbrain interneuron, part of rhombomere 6, with one caudal-medial neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.  The fibers pass through the medial longitudinal fasciculus.

ZFA:0005197.label: MiD3i
ZFA:0005197.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 6 with one dorsal neuron in each hemi-rhombomere. The axonal projection is ipsilateral.

ZFA:0005187.label: MiM1
ZFA:0005187.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 4, with one medial neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005188.label: MiR1
ZFA:0005188.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 4 with one rostral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005189.label: MiR2
ZFA:0005189.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 5 with one rostral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005190.label: MiV1
ZFA:0005190.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 4 with six ventral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005191.label: MiV2
ZFA:0005191.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 5 with five ventral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005192.label: RoI2C
ZFA:0005192.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2 with two intermediate-caudal  neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005193.label: RoI2R
ZFA:0005193.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2 with one intermediate-rostral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005194.label: RoL1
ZFA:0005194.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 1 with twelve neurons in each hemi-rhombomere. Axon runs in the dorsal spinal cord. The RoL1 stem axon projects ipsilaterally along the brain stem and spinal cord. From the more lateral location of its spinal axon, RoL1's collaterals projected both ventrally and medially.  The branching of RoL1 collaterals within the medulla, occur at multiple levels.

ZFA:0005198.label: RoL2
ZFA:0005198.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2 with 4 lateral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005201.label: RoL3
ZFA:0005201.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 3 with 1 lateral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005202.label: RoM1c
ZFA:0005202.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 1 with one medial-caudal neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005203.label: RoM1r
ZFA:0005203.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 1 with one medial-rostral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005205.label: RoM2l
ZFA:0005205.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2 with one medial-lateral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005206.label: RoM2m
ZFA:0005206.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 2 with one medial neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005207.label: RoM3l
ZFA:0005207.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 3 with one lateral neuron in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005208.label: RoM3m
ZFA:0005208.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 32 with two medial neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005204.label: RoV3
ZFA:0005204.definition: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 3 with three ventral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

ZFA:0005815.label: T interneuron
ZFA:0005815.definition: TARGET DEFINITION: Hindbrain interneurons that are part of the reticular formation.  The T interneurons receive synaptic input from the  Mauthner neuron,  from unidentified axons in the mlf, and perhaps from trigeminal sensory fibers.  .  The axon is T-shaped the proximal segment courses to the midline of the  brain and near the midline bifurcates to form an ascending rostral segment and a descending caudal segment.  The rostral and caudal segments join the dorsal component of the MLF.  The T interneurons are located caudal to CaD and appear to be bilaterally paired. They project to cranial and pectoral motor nuclei.

ZFA:0005874.label: spiral neuron
ZFA:0005874.definition: Spiral neurons are excitatory interneurons located in rhombomere 3 and have contralateral projections that cross the midline forming commissures in rhombomere 3. After crossing the midline the two commissures fuse and project caudally synapsing with the Mauthner neuron.  As they enter the axon cap, spiral fiber neurons lose their myelin and wrap around the axon hillock in a stereotyped spiral, where they make both electrical and glutamatergic synapses on the M cell axon close to the M-cell soma and with one another. Spiral neurons produced biphasic excitatory postsynaptic potentials (EPSPs) in the contralateral M-cell  with a short latency.

ZFA:0005211.label: MeL
ZFA:0005211.definition: Midbrain interneuron in the lateral midbrain.

ZFA:0005214.label: MeLc
ZFA:0005214.definition: Midbrain interneuron at the caudal position in the lateral midbrain.

ZFA:0005215.label: MeLm
ZFA:0005215.definition: Midbrain interneuron at the medial position in the lateral midbrain.

ZFA:0005213.label: MeLr
ZFA:0005213.definition: Midbrain interneuron at the rostral position in the lateral midbrain.

ZFA:0005212.label: MeM
ZFA:0005212.definition: Midbrain interneuron located in the medial midbrain.

ZFA:0005216.label: MeM1
ZFA:0005216.definition: Midbrain interneuron located in the medial midbrain.

ZFA:0005221.label: dorsal larval melanophore stripe
ZFA:0005221.definition: A larval melanophore stripe that forms a band extending from the head to the tail along the dorsal apex of the myotomes.

ZFA:0005223.label: lateral larval melanophore stripe
ZFA:0005223.definition: The larval melanophore stripe that is at the level of the horizontal myoseptum.

ZFA:0005222.label: ventral larval melanophore stripe
ZFA:0005222.definition: A larval melanophore stripe that forms a band, of pigmentation extending from the bases of the eyes on each side of the midline to the top of the tail, that underlies the myotomes bilaterally, still is dorsal to the yolk.

ZFA:0005224.label: yolk larval melanophore stripe
ZFA:0005224.definition: The larval melanophore stripe that forms a band over the ventral surface of the yolk sac.

ZFA:0005186.label: CoB
ZFA:0005186.definition: A bifurcate interneuron.  It is a commissural neuron with both ascending and descending axons in the ventrolateral cord contralateral to its cell body.

ZFA:0005230.label: CoBL
ZFA:0005230.definition: A bifurcate interneuron where the axon projects ventrally, crossing the spinal cord  ventral to the Mauthner axons before bifurcating and extending dorsally.

ZFA:0005236.label: basophilic erythroblast
ZFA:0005236.definition: A nucleated immature erythrocyte, having cytoplasm generally similar to that of the earlier proerythroblast but sometimes even more basophilic, and usually regular in outline. The nucleus is still relatively large, but the chromatin strands are thicker and more deeply staining, giving a coarser appearance; the nucleoli have disappeared.

ZFA:0005241.label: polychromatophilic erythroblast
ZFA:0005241.definition: A nucleated, immature erythrocyte in which the nucleus occupies a relatively smaller part of the cell than in its precursor, the basophilic erythroblast. The cytoplasm is beginning to acquire hemoglobin and thus is no longer a purely blue color, but takes on an acidophilic tint, which becomes progressively more marked as the cell matures. The chromatin of the nucleus is arranged in coarse, deeply staining clumps.

ZFA:0005829.label: Schlemm's canal
ZFA:0005829.definition: Vessel that drains aqueous humor from the eye.

ZFA:0001073.label: axial vasculature
ZFA:0001073.definition: Vasculature that runs along the rostral-caudal axis of the fish.

ZFA:0001267.label: cranial vasculature
ZFA:0001267.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the head.

ZFA:0005095.label: fin vasculature
ZFA:0005095.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the fin.

ZFA:0005811.label: heart vasculature
ZFA:0005811.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the heart.

ZFA:0005305.label: kidney vasculature
ZFA:0005305.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the kidney.

ZFA:0005105.label: lymph vasculature
ZFA:0005105.definition: A network of blunt ended vessels lacking direct connection to the blood vascular system.  These vessels collect and drain fluids and macromolecules from interstitial spaces throughout the animal.  They derive from a subpopulation of endothelial cells and have walls that are much thinner than the blood carrying vessels.  The walls are mostly composed of single layer of irregularly shaped endothelial cells.  Lymphatic vessels are usually classified as either superficial or deep.

ZFA:0007080.label: maxillary barbel vasculature
ZFA:0007080.definition: Is a vasculature that delivers fluid to the maxillary barbel.

ZFA:0005003.label: pharyngeal vasculature
ZFA:0005003.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the pharyngeal region.

ZFA:0005037.label: post-vent vasculature
ZFA:0005037.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the post-vent region. This is frequently referred to as tail vasculature in the zebrafish community.

ZFA:0005024.label: trunk vasculature
ZFA:0005024.definition: Is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around trunk.

ZFA:0005813.label: coronary capillary
ZFA:0005813.definition: Capillaries that innervate the subtrabecular layer of the heart.

ZFA:0005284.label: glomerular capillary
ZFA:0005284.definition: Capillary that is part of the renal glomerulus. Glomerular capillary endothelial membranes in zebrafish normally have a fenestrated morphology that is visible at the ultrastructural level.

ZFA:0005790.label: hypophyseal capillary
ZFA:0005790.definition: Pair of capillaries that bilaterally encompass the hypophysis starting at the anterior aspect of the hypophysis (pituitary).   Directly posterior to the pituitary, the two capillaries fuse with the hypophyseal vein.

ZFA:0005309.label: pronephric glomerular capillary
ZFA:0005309.definition: Capillary that is part of the pronephric glomerulus. Glomerular capillary endothelial membranes in zebrafish normally have a fenestrated morphology that is visible at the ultrastructural level.

ZFA:0005250.label: capillary
ZFA:0005250.definition: Microvessel of the blood circulation system lined with vascular endothelial cells.

ZFA:0005252.label: lymphatic capillary
ZFA:0005252.definition: Microvessel of the lymphatic system lined with a single layer of overlapping endothelial cells.

ZFA:0005307.label: afferent glomerular arteriole
ZFA:0005307.definition: Arteriole that carries blood into the glomerular capillaries.

ZFA:0005015.label: afferent lamellar arteriole
ZFA:0005015.definition: Arterioles which take blood from the afferent filamental arteries to the gill lamella.

ZFA:0005308.label: efferent glomerular arteriole
ZFA:0005308.definition: Arteriole that carries blood out of the glomerular capillaries.

ZFA:0005019.label: efferent lamellar arteriole
ZFA:0005019.definition: Arterioles which take blood from the gill lamella to the efferent  filamental arteries.

ZFA:0005259.label: continuous blood vessel endothelium
ZFA:0005259.definition: Blood vessel endothelium that has tight junctions between the endothelial cells.

ZFA:0005260.label: fenestrated blood vessel endothelium
ZFA:0005260.definition: Blood vessel endothelium that has pores that allow passage small molecules and proteins.

ZFA:0005261.label: sinusoidal blood vessel endothelium
ZFA:0005261.definition: Fenestrated blood vessel endothelium with pores that are large enough for blood cells to pass.  The basal lamina and gap junctions  may be discontinuous.

ZFA:0000617.label: anal erector
ZFA:0000617.definition: Series of muscles that have a distal attachment at the anteriolateral base of each ray and spike and a proximal attachment to the haemal spines.  A tendon runs along one third the dorsoventral length of the muscle toward the attachment at the haemal spine.  These muscles act in opposition to the anal depressors to raise the anal fin rays.

ZFA:0000500.label: dorsal erector
ZFA:0000500.definition: Dorsal fin muscle that moves individual rays the dorsal fin to an erect position.  Antagonistic to dorsal depressor muscle. There is one dorsal erector for each dorsal fin lepidotrichium.

ZFA:0000311.label: adductor mandibulae complex
ZFA:0000311.definition: Is a mandibular muscle that consists of three subdivisions A1, A2, and A3. All three originate on the hyomandibula and suspensorium but each has a distinct insertion. A1 inserts on the maxilla, A2 inserts along the caudal margin of the articular and A3 inserts on the medial surface of the articular.

ZFA:0000616.label: adductor profundus
ZFA:0000616.definition: Small thin adductor muscle that is part of the pectoral fin. The origin of the adductor profundus lies along the developing anterior skeletal flange of the pectoral girdle.  The adductor profundus develops from the primitive pectoral fin adductor.

ZFA:0000497.label: pelvic adductor profundus
ZFA:0000497.definition: Dorsal pelvic fin muscle that originates at the anterior side of the basipterygium, lies mostly parallel to the pelvic fin rays and attaches and inserts on the bases of all the pelvic fin rays.

ZFA:0005650.label: primitive pectoral fin adductor
ZFA:0005650.definition: Adductor that originates at the cleithrum the muscle fibers run in sheets along the endoskeletal disk extending dorsally and caudally from its base. Distally, the muscles insert onto the fin membrane.

ZFA:0000285.label: superficial adductor
ZFA:0000285.definition: Pectoral fin muscle that develops from the primitive pectoral fin adductor.  The adductor superficialis originates at the cleithrum and  inserts on all fins rays except the first. Insertion of the adductor superficialis on fin rays is distal to the fin ray bases.

ZFA:0000592.label: superficial pelvic adductor
ZFA:0000592.definition: Superficial, dorsal pelvic fin muscle that originates at the anterior side of the basipterygium and inserts onto all pelvic fin rays except ray 1.

ZFA:0005820.label: ventral caudal adductor
ZFA:0005820.definition: Paired, deep caudal fin muscles that arise broadly from the hypurals and extends dorsocaudally where the fiber bundles converge into a narrow insertion site on the 5th caudal fin ray.

ZFA:0000614.label: abductor profundus
ZFA:0000614.definition: Abductor muscle that develops from the primitive pectoral fin abductor.  It originates along the anterior skeletal flange of the pectoral girdle.  The abductor profundus bundles insert onto the fin ray base proximal processes of all fin rays.

ZFA:0000564.label: pelvic abductor profundus
ZFA:0000564.definition: Deep pelvic muscle that originates from the basipterygium  and lies manly parallel to the rays and attaches to the base of all the rays except ray 1.

ZFA:0005651.label: primitive pectoral fin abductor
ZFA:0005651.definition: Abductor that originates at the cleithrum the muscle fibers run in sheets along the endoskeletal disk extending dorsally and caudally from its base. Distally, the muscles insert onto the fin membrane.

ZFA:0000685.label: superficial abductor
ZFA:0000685.definition: Abductor muscle that develops from the primitive pectoral fin abductor.  The  abductor superficialis originates along the anterior skeletal flange of the pectoral girdle, the bundles insert to fin ray base distal processes.

ZFA:0000439.label: superficial pelvic abductor
ZFA:0000439.definition: Ventral, superficial, paired muscle that originates from the posterior part of the protractor ishii tendon and the midline.  At the midline the paired muscles contact each other.  These are short muscles that attach to all pelvic fin rays except ray 1 and ray 2.

ZFA:0000466.label: anal depressor
ZFA:0000466.definition: Series of  muscles that  have an anterior attachment  at posteriorlateral base of each ray and posterior attachment at the haemal spines. These muscles act in opposition to the anal erectors to lower the anal fin rays.

ZFA:0000195.label: dorsal depressor
ZFA:0000195.definition: Dorsal fin muscle that moves individual rays the dorsal fin into a lowered position. The dorsal depressors extend from either the right or left base of a dorsal fin ray to the posterior edge of a proximal pterygophore in the median septum. Antagonistic to dorsal erector muscle. There is one dorsal depressor for each dorsal fin lepidotrichium.

ZFA:0000341.label: inferior caudal dorsal flexor
ZFA:0000341.definition: Paired, deep caudal fin muscles that arise from a narrow insertion site at the 28th and 29th vertebrae, then extend toward the dorsal base of the caudal fin where they insert broadly on fin rays.

ZFA:0000269.label: inferior caudal ventral flexor
ZFA:0000269.definition: Paired, deep caudal fin muscles that arise from a narrow insertion site at the 28th and 29th vertebrae then project from the vertebral column to the ventral base of the caudal fin where they attach broadly to ventral caudal fin rays.

ZFA:0000287.label: superior caudal dorsal flexor
ZFA:0000287.definition: Paired, deep caudal fin muscles that originate from the 30th vertebra and extend toward the dorsal base of the caudal fin where they insert broadly on fin rays.

ZFA:0000455.label: superior caudal ventral flexor
ZFA:0000455.definition: Paired, deep caudal fin muscles that originate from the 30th vertebra then project from the vertebral column to the ventral base of the caudal fin where they attach broadly to ventral caudal fin rays.

ZFA:0005279.label: enteric circular muscle
ZFA:0005279.definition: Smooth muscle of the enteric muscle system in which the cells are aligned perpendicular to the lumen of the gut.

ZFA:0005278.label: enteric longitudinal muscle
ZFA:0005278.definition: Smooth muscle of the enteric muscle system in which the cells are aligned parallel to the lumen of the gut.

ZFA:0005273.label: intestinal mucosal muscle
ZFA:0005273.definition: A thin layer of smooth muscle immediately beneath the base of the villi which permits the intestinal mucosa to dynamically move and fold.

ZFA:0005321.label: vascular smooth muscle
ZFA:0005321.definition: Smooth muscle that is part of the blood vessel wall.

ZFA:0000499.label: dorsal arrector
ZFA:0000499.definition: The muscle that acts as an antagonist to the arrector ventralis, reversing the direction of the leading edge of the pectoral fin to initiate the upstroke.

ZFA:0000651.label: dorsal pelvic arrector
ZFA:0000651.definition: Dorsal pelvic fin muscle that originates at the anterior side of the basipterygium and inserts onto the base of the first pelvic fin ray.

ZFA:0000701.label: ventral arrector
ZFA:0000701.definition: Muscle that is important in controlling the leading edge of the pectoral fin in the juvenile zebrafish, particularly during the initiation of the downstroke.

ZFA:0000704.label: ventral pelvic arrector
ZFA:0000704.definition: Deep, narrow muscle that arises anteriorly and laterally of the pelvic abductor profundus. It attaches to the first pelvic ray.

ZFA:0000313.label: anal inclinator
ZFA:0000313.definition: Series of paired muscles that have a distal attachment at the lateral  base of each ray and a proximal attachment  to the hypaxialis.  The left and right inclinators attach the integument and trunk muscles to the base of each ray.

ZFA:0000342.label: dorsal inclinator
ZFA:0000342.definition: Muscle of the dorsal fin that are thin, arise from the lateral edge of fin bases, and attach to the skin just above the epaxial muscle.  The inclinator muscles bend the fin sideways.  There is one dorsal inclinator for each dorsal fin lepidotrichium.

ZFA:0005269.label: abductor muscle
ZFA:0005269.definition: A muscle that moves a body part away  from the sagittal plane of the body.

ZFA:0005268.label: adductor muscle
ZFA:0005268.definition: A muscle that brings a body part closer to the sagittal plane of the body.

ZFA:0005825.label: deep lateral dorsal muscle
ZFA:0005825.definition: Paired superfical caudal fin muscle that is located dorsally and extends from the myoseptum to the dorsal tip of the caudal fin where it attaches in the region of the second upper long fin ray.

ZFA:0005824.label: deep lateral ventral muscle
ZFA:0005824.definition: Paired superficial caudal fin muscle that is located ventrally and extends from the myoseptum to the ventral tip of the caudal fin where it attaches in the region of the second lowest (eighteenth) long fin ray.

ZFA:0005270.label: depressor muscle
ZFA:0005270.definition: A muscle that moves body parts into an inferior direction or lowered position.  Antagonistic to erector muscle.

ZFA:0005822.label: dorsal interfilamental caudal muscle
ZFA:0005822.definition: Paired superficial caudal fin muscle that has a narrow attachment site along the midline posterior to the attachment of the lateralis superficialis dorsalis  and fans out to attach broadly in a region between the 4th and 8th caudal fin ray.

ZFA:0000349.label: epaxialis
ZFA:0000349.definition: Skeletal muscle that is the dorsal-most component of the body musculature. The anterior region attaches to the back of the cranial vault and the dorsal region of the pectoral girdle. The epaxialis is bound to the skin by fibrous connective tissue and internally it inserts over the dorsal portion of the vertebral centra and fin pterygiophores and the neural spines. Posteriorly the epaxialis overlies the modified muscle of the caudal fin and inserts onto the dorsal ray bases of the fin. The anterior epaxial plays a role in feeding and the posterior region is central to locomotion.

ZFA:0005267.label: erector muscle
ZFA:0005267.definition: Muscle that moves parts of the body in a superior direction to an erect position.  Antagonistic to depressor muscle.

ZFA:0005823.label: external lateral dorsal muscle
ZFA:0005823.definition: Paired superficial caudal fin muscle that originates from a broad base at the midline and narrows toward its attachment at the dorsal tip of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0000205.label: external lateral ventral muscle
ZFA:0000205.definition: Paired superficial caudal fin muscle that originates from a broad base at the midline and narrows toward its attachment at the ventral tip of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005271.label: flexor muscle
ZFA:0005271.definition: A muscle that decrease the angle of a joint.

ZFA:0005821.label: ventral interfilamental caudal muscle
ZFA:0005821.definition: Paired superficial caudal fin muscle that has a narrow attachment site along the  midline posterior to the attachment of the lateralis superficialis ventralis  and fans out to attach broadly in a region between the 12th and 16th caudal fin ray.

ZFA:0005809.label: pectinate muscle
ZFA:0005809.definition: Network of heavily branched muscle in the atrium.

ZFA:0005827.label: transverse band
ZFA:0005827.definition: Cardiac muscle  located in the trabecular layer of the ventricle that spans the central lumen near the ventricular apex.  The transverse muscle band superficially resembles the septomarginal trabecula found in reptilian and mammalian hearts in that it spans the ventricle.

ZFA:0005826.label: tri-tipped trabecula
ZFA:0005826.definition: Cardiac muscle  located in the trabecular layer of the ventricle that is attached to the base of the AV and BV valves.  It is similar to the papillary muscle in mammals and birds but,  does not attach to the ends of the valve leaflets.

ZFA:0005584.label: developing mesonephric nephron
ZFA:0005584.definition: Anatomical cluster which give rise to mature mesonephric nephrons.  Zebrafish continously generate new mesonephric nephrons.

ZFA:0005592.label: mesonephric nephron
ZFA:0005592.definition: A branched nephron of the mature kidney.

ZFA:0005294.label: collecting duct
ZFA:0005294.definition: Renal duct that collects the output from renal tubules.

ZFA:0005591.label: developing mesonephric distal tubule
ZFA:0005591.definition: Renal duct that will develop into the mesonephric distal tubule.

ZFA:0005585.label: developing mesonephric proximal tubule
ZFA:0005585.definition: Renal duct that will develop into the mesonephric proximal tubule.

ZFA:0005293.label: distal early tubule
ZFA:0005293.definition: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the proximal straight tubule.

ZFA:0005292.label: distal late tubule
ZFA:0005292.definition: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the distal early tubule.

ZFA:0005290.label: proximal convoluted tubule
ZFA:0005290.definition: Renal tubule that connects to the renal corpuscle.

ZFA:0005291.label: proximal straight tubule
ZFA:0005291.definition: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the proximal convoluted tubule.

ZFA:0001287.label: renal tubule
ZFA:0001287.definition: Renal duct that collects filtrate from the renal corpuscle and transports it to the collecting duct.  Different parts of the renal tubule reabsorb specific components of the filtrate to leave only waste.

ZFA:0005110.label: thoracic duct
ZFA:0005110.definition: The thoracic duct is the first perfused lymphatic, located between the dorsal aorta and posterior cardinal vein.

ZFA:0005304.label: caudal fin blood vessel
ZFA:0005304.definition: Blood vessel located within the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005101.label: interray vessel
ZFA:0005101.definition: Vessels that travel between veins in adjacent rays.

ZFA:0005100.label: intervessel commissure
ZFA:0005100.definition: Vessels that travel between artery and veins or vein and vein in a single ray.

ZFA:0005301.label: pectoral fin blood vessel
ZFA:0005301.definition: Blood vessel part of pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005303.label: caudal fin lymph vessel
ZFA:0005303.definition: Lymph vessel that is located in the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005302.label: pectoral fin lymph vessel
ZFA:0005302.definition: Lymph vessel part of pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005255.label: arteriole
ZFA:0005255.definition: Multi-tissue structure part of the blood vasculature. Feeds into capillaries.   Arterioles carry blood away from the heart.

ZFA:0000005.label: artery
ZFA:0000005.definition: Blood vessels that carry blood away from the heart.

ZFA:0005297.label: cranial blood vessel
ZFA:0005297.definition: Blood vessel part of cranial vasculature.

ZFA:0005025.label: dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel
ZFA:0005025.definition: Paired trunk vessels that run medially along the dorsal-most portion of the trunk and post-vent region. The DLAVs are formed by the longitudinal anastomoses of the intersegmental vessels to form a right and left pair of dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessels. These paired vessels remodel to form a single plexiform vessel beginning at 3dpf continuing until after 7dpf.  The basilar artery connects to the DLAVs at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata.  In the early embryo (2.5-3.5 dpf) the primitive hindbrain channels also connect to the DLAV.

ZFA:0005091.label: hepatic sinusoid
ZFA:0005091.definition: Wide thin-walled blood vessels in the liver. The terminal branches of the hepatic portal vein and hepatic artery empty into the sinusoids where the blood mixes. In mammals they have neither venous or arterial markers.  Sinusoids are scattered throughout the parenchyma and appear small and round.

ZFA:0005801.label: interrenal vessel
ZFA:0005801.definition: The interrenal vessel (IRV) is the blood vessels supplying the interrenal gland. It is formed by sprouting from the dorsal aorta.  The development of the IRV is temporally and spatially correlated with the initiation interrenal gland formation.  After traversing the interrenal tissue, the IRV connects  to the posterior end segment of the anterior mesenteric artery where two branches of swim bladder arteries branched out.  Angiogenic sprout is visible between 34 and 48 hpf with blood flow by 3dpf.

ZFA:0001285.label: intersegmental vessel
ZFA:0001285.definition: Blood vessels that connect the dorsal aorta or the posterior cardinal vein and the dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel. They run along the vertical myotomal boundaries.  At early stages these vessels don't have venous or arterial markers.

ZFA:0007079.label: maxillary barbel blood vessel
ZFA:0007079.definition: Blood vessel that emerges from the maxilla, wraps around the sinus isthmus, then runs alongside the distal bulb to enter the barbel shaft proper. There are two ventral vessels that connect distally in the maxillary barbel forming a complete capillary loop.

ZFA:0000082.label: vein
ZFA:0000082.definition: Vessels that carry blood to the heart.

ZFA:0005315.label: venule
ZFA:0005315.definition: Multi-tissue structure part of the blood vasculature formed by the anastomosis of capillaries.  Venules carry blood toward the heart.

ZFA:0005325.label: integument ionocyte
ZFA:0005325.definition: Ionocyte located in the integument during embryonic and larval stages.

ZFA:0005579.label: NCC ionocyte
ZFA:0005579.definition: Integument ionocyte rich in Na-Cl co-transporter (NCC) activity.

ZFA:0005327.label: vH ionocyte
ZFA:0005327.definition: Integument ionocyte rich in vacuolar-type H+ ATPase and carbonic anhydrase.

ZFA:0005760.label: cranial fat
ZFA:0005760.definition: Adipose tissue in the cranium. Cranial adipocytes are located within the ventral wall of the cranium, situated between the brain and the esophagus.

ZFA:0005764.label: mandibular fat
ZFA:0005764.definition: Adipose tissue deposited along the mandible.

ZFA:0005758.label: pancreatic fat
ZFA:0005758.definition: Adipose tissue interspersed within the pancreatic acini.

ZFA:0005762.label: subcutaneous fat
ZFA:0005762.definition: Adipose tissue between muscle and integument.

ZFA:0005759.label: visceral fat
ZFA:0005759.definition: Adipose tissue on the surface of the organs within the pleuroperitoneal cavity. Visceral adipocytes were observed posterior to the swim bladder and lining the visceral cavity.

ZFA:0005418.label: auditory fenestra
ZFA:0005418.definition: Opening in the neurocranium to allow communication between the swim bladder and the inner ear.

ZFA:0005419.label: auditory foramen
ZFA:0005419.definition: Foramen through which cranial nerve VIII (auditory) exits.

ZFA:0005453.label: basicapsular fenestra
ZFA:0005453.definition: Opening in the prootic.  The basicapsular fenestra is paired.

ZFA:0005890.label: carotid artery canal
ZFA:0005890.definition: Canal where the carotid artery enters the cranium.  Located between the parasphenoid and prootic bones in adult fish.

ZFA:0005426.label: coracoid foramen
ZFA:0005426.definition: Foramen that is located in the coracoid.

ZFA:0005427.label: dentary foramen
ZFA:0005427.definition: Foramen located on the dentary for passage of the mandibular nerve.

ZFA:0005387.label: foramen magnum
ZFA:0005387.definition: Foramen in the occipital region of neurocranium to allow passage of spinal cord.

ZFA:0005893.label: glossopharyngeal foramen
ZFA:0005893.definition: Foramen in the exoccipital through which the glossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX) passes.

ZFA:0005629.label: hyomandibular foramen
ZFA:0005629.definition: Foramen in the hyomandibula that allows passage of the anterior lateral line nerve and the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII). The foramen develop in the hyosymplectic.  The hyomandibular foramen are paired.

ZFA:0005625.label: hypophyseal fenestra
ZFA:0005625.definition: Space enclosed by the trabeculae cranii.  The anterior tip of the notochord extends into the posterior region of the hypophyseal fenestra.

ZFA:0005892.label: lateral occipital foramen
ZFA:0005892.definition: Foramen that has the exoccipital as the anterior and dorsal rim. The occipital forms the anterior rim during early development.

ZFA:0005615.label: metapterygoid-symplectic fenestra
ZFA:0005615.definition: Opening formed between the ventral border of the metapterygoid and the dorsal border of the symplectic.

ZFA:0005446.label: neuromast foramen
ZFA:0005446.definition: Foramen in a bone that is part of a sensory canal.

ZFA:0005429.label: olfactory nerve foramen
ZFA:0005429.definition: Foramen for the passage of the olfactory nerve or cranial nerve 1.

ZFA:0005428.label: optic foramen
ZFA:0005428.definition: Foramen in the orbital region of the neurocranium for the passage of the optic nerve (cranial nerve II).

ZFA:0005430.label: orbital foramen
ZFA:0005430.definition: Foramen in the bone or cartilage comprising the anterior wall of the orbit, and through which passes at least the deep ophthalmic branch of cranial nerve V (trigeminal).

ZFA:0005455.label: prootic foramen
ZFA:0005455.definition: Foramen formed between the anterolateral extension of the prootic that contacts the pterosphenoid the prootic and the pterosphenoid.

ZFA:0005431.label: scapular foramen
ZFA:0005431.definition: Foramen that is located in the scapula. The scapular foramen is paired and formed by a ring of bone.

ZFA:0005432.label: superficial ophthalmic nerve foramen
ZFA:0005432.definition: Foramen through which the superficial ophthalmic nerve passes.

ZFA:0005894.label: vagus foramen
ZFA:0005894.definition: Foramen in the exoccipital through which the vagus nerve (cranial nerve X) passes.

ZFA:0005406.label: anterior myodome
ZFA:0005406.definition: Fossa or chamber on anterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for anterior extrinsic eye musculature.

ZFA:0005442.label: articular fossa of opercle
ZFA:0005442.definition: Fossa of opercle that articulates with hyomandibular condyle for opercle.

ZFA:0005628.label: posttemporal fossa
ZFA:0005628.definition: Fossa where the exoccipital forms the medial portion and the epioccipital forms the lateral margin.

ZFA:0005510.label: prootic depression
ZFA:0005510.definition: Shallow area that exists on the prootic.

ZFA:0005630.label: pterotic fossa
ZFA:0005630.definition: Fossa on the pterotic  where the hyomandibula articulates.

ZFA:0005492.label: sphenotic-prootic fossa
ZFA:0005492.definition: Fossa where the hyomandibula articulates with the sphenotic and prootic to form the hyomandibular-otic region joint.

ZFA:0005454.label: subtemporal fossa
ZFA:0005454.definition: Fossa where the anteromedial rim is formed by the prootic, the remainder of the fossa is formed by the exoccipital and pterotic.

ZFA:0005416.label: sacculoagenar foramen
ZFA:0005416.definition: Inner ear foramen that connects the lagena to the caudal half of the saccule.

ZFA:0005417.label: utriculosaccular foramen
ZFA:0005417.definition: Inner ear foramen that connects the rostral saccula to the utricle.

ZFA:0005131.label: parietal peritoneum
ZFA:0005131.definition: The peritoneum that lines the walls of the peritoneal cavity.

ZFA:0000054.label: pericardium
ZFA:0000054.definition: Serous membrane that surrounds the heart.

ZFA:0005120.label: peritoneum
ZFA:0005120.definition: The serous membrane that lines the peritoneal cavity. The peritoneum secretes serous fluid which allows free movement of the peritoneum and the intraperitoneal organs.

ZFA:0005132.label: visceral peritoneum
ZFA:0005132.definition: The part of peritoneum that is a serous membrane covers the external surfaces of most abdominal organs.

ZFA:0005508.label: inner mental barbel
ZFA:0005508.definition: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in an anteromedial position relative to the outer mental barbel. The inner mental barbel is nearer to the mandibular symphysis than is the outer mental barbel.

ZFA:0005398.label: anal fin actinotrichium
ZFA:0005398.definition: Actinotrichium that is part of the anal fin skeleton.

ZFA:0005424.label: caudal fin actinotrichium
ZFA:0005424.definition: Actinotrichium that is part of the caudal fin skeleton.

ZFA:0000089.label: fin fold actinotrichium
ZFA:0000089.definition: Portion of tissue which is a slender, horny, flexible, unsegmented fibril, which strengthens the embryonic fin fold. Actinotrichia are translucent, exhibit birefringence (double refraction) and are composed of the scleroprotein elastoidine.

ZFA:0005545.label: pectoral fin actinotrichium
ZFA:0005545.definition: Actinotrichium that is part of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005546.label: pelvic fin actinotrichium
ZFA:0005546.definition: Actinotrichium that is part of the pelvic fin.

ZFA:0005437.label: pectoral fin motor nerve
ZFA:0005437.definition: Motor nerve that is located in the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005438.label: pectoral fin sensory nerve
ZFA:0005438.definition: Sensory nerve that innervates the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005439.label: pectoral fin motor nerve 1
ZFA:0005439.definition: Pectoral fin motor nerve that enters the fin from the dorsal side of the fin rostral of all other motor nerves and innervates the dorsal side of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005440.label: pectoral fin motor nerve 2
ZFA:0005440.definition: Pectoral fin motor nerve that enters the fin from the dorsal side of the fin caudal of nerve 1 and rostral of all other motor nerves and innervates the dorsal side of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005441.label: pectoral fin motor nerve 3
ZFA:0005441.definition: Pectoral fin motor nerve that enters the fin from the dorsal side of the fin caudal of nerve 1 and 2 and rostral of nerve 4 and innervates the dorsal side of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005450.label: pectoral fin motor nerve 4
ZFA:0005450.definition: Pectoral fin motor nerve that enters the fin from the ventral side of the fin and innervates the ventral side of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005392.label: infraorbital sensory canal
ZFA:0005392.definition: Sensory canal associated with the infraorbital bones. Located in close proximity to the otic and supraorbital sensory canals at their union. The infraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired.  The canal has 3 pores.  The first opens dorsally below the nasal sac, the second opens laterally posterior to the anterior maxilary barbel, the third pore is present where infraorbital 1 meets infraorbital 2.

ZFA:0005451.label: mandibular sensory canal
ZFA:0005451.definition: Sensory canal associated with the angular and dentary bones.  Located anterior and ventral to and in close proximity with the preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal. The mandible sensory canal is bilaterally paired and does not meet at the mandibular symphysis. The mandibular lateral line canal has 3 neuromast located between the canal pores.  Two neuromast are located in the portion of the can in the dentary bone.  The third neuromast is located in the anguloarticular bone.  The rostral end of the canal has a terminal pore adjacent to the mandibular symphysis. There are three more pores, two, at the posterior of the dentary and the anterior of the anguloarticular share a common epithelial pore.

ZFA:0005393.label: otic sensory canal
ZFA:0005393.definition: Sensory canal between and in close proximity posteriorly with the post-otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals, and anteriorly with the supraorbital and infraorbital sensory canals. The otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

ZFA:0005394.label: post-otic sensory canal
ZFA:0005394.definition: Sensory canal  that forms dorsal to the horizontal semicircular canal of the ear. The anterior end of the canal may span or remain posterior to the pterotic-sphenotic junction. The posterior end of the postotic canal meets the temporal and supratemporal canals. The canal lies between and in close proximity to the trunk sensory canal and anteriorly with the otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals. The post-otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired and when mature is fully enclosed in bone.

ZFA:0005448.label: preopercular sensory canal
ZFA:0005448.definition: Sensory canal associated with the preopercle bone. It lies in close proximity with the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union, and anteroventrally with the mandibular sensory canal. The preopercular sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

ZFA:0005395.label: preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal
ZFA:0005395.definition: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union. The preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle, angular and dentary bones.

ZFA:0005447.label: sensory canal tubule
ZFA:0005447.definition: Sensory canal that is a side branch between a sensory canal proximally and a pore at its distal end. Sensory canal tubule is bilaterally paired although often imperfectly so.

ZFA:0005396.label: supraorbital sensory canal
ZFA:0005396.definition: Sensory canal contained in the nasal and frontal bones.  It contains 4 or 5 neuromast. The first neuromast is positioned in the tubular nasal bone and the other neuromasts are located in the frontal bone.  The canal is anterior to and in close proximity to the otic and infraorbital sensory canals. The supraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

ZFA:0005445.label: supratemporal sensory canal
ZFA:0005445.definition: Sensory canal that crosses over the dorsal midline and in close proximity to the contralateral post-otic sensory canals. The supratemporal sensory canal is unpaired.

ZFA:0005444.label: trunk sensory canal
ZFA:0005444.definition: Sensory canal on trunk which is posterior to the pectoral girdle and often reaching to the caudal fin. The trunk sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

ZFA:0005460.label: atrium of sinus impar
ZFA:0005460.definition: Bilaterally paired perilymphatic chambers posterior to the sinus impar.  These connect to the anterior end of the otic duct.

ZFA:0005456.label: sinus impar
ZFA:0005456.definition: Perilymphatic compartment of the zebrafish ear. Chamber positioned ventral of the medulla, the anterior end surrounds the posterior portion of the transverse canal.

ZFA:0005462.label: otic duct
ZFA:0005462.definition: Pair of perilymphatic ducts that extend from the dorsal ends of the atria of the sinus impar, pass on either side of the medulla and merge and extend dorsally toward the surface of the head.

ZFA:0005435.label: actinotrichium
ZFA:0005435.definition: Skeletal element which is a slender, horny, flexible, unsegmented fibril which provide structural support to fin folds or fins. Actinotrichia are translucent, exhibit birefringence (double refraction) and are composed of the scleroprotein elastoidine.

ZFA:0001514.label: bone element
ZFA:0001514.definition: Skeletal element that is composed of bone tissue.

ZFA:0001501.label: cartilage element
ZFA:0001501.definition: Skeletal element that is composed of cartilage tissue and may be permanent or transient.

ZFA:0005620.label: endochondral element
ZFA:0005620.definition: A skeletal element that has the potential to participate in endochondral ossification, and may participate in intramembranous ossification.

ZFA:0005633.label: lepidotrichium segment
ZFA:0005633.definition: Skeletal element which is part of lepidotrichium articulating with other lepidotrichium segments by lepidotrichium joints.

ZFA:0005624.label: replacement element
ZFA:0005624.definition: Skeletal element that forms as a replacement or substitution of another element or tissue.

ZFA:0005537.label: lateral fontanel of frontal
ZFA:0005537.definition: Fontanel within the frontal bone near the frontal-sphenotic joint. Lateral fontanel of frontal is paired.

ZFA:0005604.label: angiogenic sprout
ZFA:0005604.definition: Portion of vessel wall that extends to form a new blood vessel.

ZFA:0005603.label: lymphangiogenic sprout
ZFA:0005603.definition: Portion of vessel wall that extends to form a new lymph vessel.

ZFA:0000197.label: dorsal habenular nucleus
ZFA:0000197.definition: Habenular nucleus where the efferent projections innervate the interpeduncular nucleus.  The dorsal habenula is structurally homologous to the mammalian medial habenula.

ZFA:0000302.label: ventral habenular nucleus
ZFA:0000302.definition: Habenular nucleus positioned ventromedially to the dorsal habenular nuclei. The ventral habenular nuclei are paired and symmetrical, each have a conical shape defined by a wide rostral end, occupying the entire anterior region of the habenula, and a narrow caudal end. The axons of the ventral habenular nucleus passed laterally through the interpeduncular nucleus and projected to the ventral part of the median raphe.  The ventral habenular nucleus is homolog mammalian lateral habenular nucleus.

ZFA:0007003.label: ventro-caudal cluster
ZFA:0007003.definition: Early-forming neural cluster of the ventral midbrain.  At 16 h, axons of the vcc grow caudally to pioneer the medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF), which is part of the larger ventral longitudinal tract (VLT).  Later, neurons from this cluster project axons rostrally into the tract of the post-optic commissure (TPOC).

ZFA:0007002.label: ventro-rostral cluster
ZFA:0007002.definition: Early-forming neural cluster located in the rostral diencephalon.  At 19 h, axons arising from the vrc grow caudally to pioneer the tract of the postoptic commissure (TPOC).

ZFA:0000276.label: rostrolateral thalamic nucleus of Butler & Saidel

ZFA:0000346.label: dorsal tegmental nucleus
ZFA:0000346.definition: Tegmental nucleus that is immediately adjacent to the nucleus lateralis valvulae (NLV).  This nucleus is sometimes considered part of the NLV but the cells are more densely packed.  The nucleus extends rostrally into the mesencephalon.

ZFA:0000552.label: nucleus ruber
ZFA:0000552.definition: Nucleus located in the midbrain tegmentum that controls motor coordination during locomotion.

ZFA:0005590.label: capillary loop nephron
ZFA:0005590.definition: Developing nephron where the developing glomerular capsule has been invaded by a glomerular capillary loop called the glomerular tuft.

ZFA:0005588.label: comma-shaped body
ZFA:0005588.definition: Developing nephron with a comma shaped appearance.

ZFA:0005589.label: s-shaped body
ZFA:0005589.definition: Developing nephron with a tubular morphology that has a renal corpuscle anlage at the distal end.

ZFA:0001640.label: cephalic flexure
ZFA:0001640.definition: Ventral bend in the brain occurring caudal to the adenohypophyseal placode.

ZFA:0001161.label: pectoral fin
ZFA:0001161.definition: Paired fin that is located in the thoracic region of the body.

ZFA:0001184.label: pelvic fin
ZFA:0001184.definition: Paired fin located in the abdominal position of the body.

ZFA:0001162.label: anal fin
ZFA:0001162.definition: Median fin that is located posterior to the anus.

ZFA:0001058.label: caudal fin
ZFA:0001058.definition: Fin that is the most posterior median fin. It is composed of a complex of three modified centra and modified neural and hemal arches and spines.

ZFA:0001173.label: dorsal fin
ZFA:0001173.definition: Median fin that is located on the dorsal surface of the fish.

ZFA:0005598.label: pancreatic epsilon cell
ZFA:0005598.definition: Ghrelin secreting cells found in the found in the exocrine pancreas.

ZFA:0005836.label: facial lymphatic sprout
ZFA:0005836.definition: Lymphangiogenic sprout that  originates from the common cardinal vein and extends along the primary head sinus.

ZFA:0005802.label: interrenal  angiogenic sprout
ZFA:0005802.definition: Sprout from the dorsal aorta that develops into the interrenal vessel.

ZFA:0005612.label: ectopterygoid-entopterygoid joint
ZFA:0005612.definition: Synostosis where the ectopterygoid meets the entopterygoid.

ZFA:0005611.label: ectopterygoid-quadrate joint
ZFA:0005611.definition: Synostosis where the entopterygoid meets the quadrate.

ZFA:0005614.label: entopterygoid-metapterygoid joint
ZFA:0005614.definition: Synostosis where the entopterygoid meets the metapterygoid. The metapterygoid has an anterodorsally projecting spine that meets the entopterygoid medially in a synostosis at its posteromedial edge.

ZFA:0005617.label: lateral ethmoid-supraethmoid
ZFA:0005617.definition: Synostosis where anteromedial extensions of the lateral ethmoid project to meet the supraethmoid dorsally.

ZFA:0005648.label: mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint
ZFA:0005648.definition: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and lateral ethmoid. Mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

ZFA:0005649.label: mesethmoid-vomer joint
ZFA:0005649.definition: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and vomer. Mesethmoid-vomer joint is unpaired.

ZFA:0005621.label: bone tissue
ZFA:0005621.definition: Skeletal tissue with a collagen-rich extracellular matrix vascularized, mineralized with hydroxyapatite and typically including osteocytes located in lacunae that communicate with one another by cell processes (in canaliculi). Bone is deposited by osteoblasts.

ZFA:0001637.label: bony projection
ZFA:0001637.definition: Portion of connective tissue that is an extension of a bone.

ZFA:0005622.label: cartilage tissue
ZFA:0005622.definition: Skeletal tissue that is avascular, rich in glycosaminoglycans (GAGs) and typically includes chondrocytes within isolated lacunae. Cartilage tissue is deposited by chondroblasts.

ZFA:0005903.label: cartilaginous projection
ZFA:0005903.definition: Skeletal tissue that is an extension of a skeletal element composed of  cartilage.

ZFA:0005623.label: odontoid tissue
ZFA:0005623.definition: Skeletal tissue that is part of the exoskeleton and derived from an odontogenic papilla.

ZFA:0005143.label: dentine
ZFA:0005143.definition: Mineralized collagen containing substance that forms the tooth structure.  The dentine of first-generation teeth of zebrafish is entirely atubular.

ZFA:0005142.label: enameloid
ZFA:0005142.definition: A dentine-like hypermineralized substance that covers the zebrafish tooth tip.

ZFA:0005635.label: predentine
ZFA:0005635.definition: Odontoid tissue formed of a loose matrix of collagen.  The fibrils of the predentine are homogeneously distributed and preferentially oriented along the long axis of the tooth. They are of variable thickness, measuring from 50 to 100 nm in diameter.

ZFA:0005640.label: cleithrum-vertebral ligament
ZFA:0005640.definition: Ligament that run from the dorsal tip of the cleithrum to the exoccipital.

ZFA:0005639.label: supracleithrum-vertebral ligament
ZFA:0005639.definition: Ligament that runs from the ventral third of the supracleithrum to the exoccipital.

ZFA:0005685.label: dG1
ZFA:0005685.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.  It is located in a stereotypic position near the posterior edge of the dorsal glomerular zone and stains with anti-calretinin.

ZFA:0005686.label: dlG1
ZFA:0005686.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsolateral zone of the olfactory bulb.  Dorsalmost of glomeruli located along the caudal edge of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005687.label: dlG2
ZFA:0005687.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsolateral zone of the olfactory bulb.  Ventral to dlG1 and located along the caudal edge of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005688.label: dlG3
ZFA:0005688.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsolateral zone of the olfactory bulb.  Ventral to dlG2 and located along the caudal edge of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005689.label: dlG4
ZFA:0005689.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsolateral zone of the olfactory bulb.  Ventral to dlG3 and located along the caudal edge of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005690.label: dlG5
ZFA:0005690.definition: Glomerulus located in the dorsolateral zone of the olfactory bulb.  Ventral to dlG4,  and located along the caudal edge of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005703.label: lG2
ZFA:0005703.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005704.label: lG3
ZFA:0005704.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005705.label: lG4
ZFA:0005705.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005702.label: lg1
ZFA:0005702.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb. LG1 is surrounded by a diffuse aggregate of OSN axons.

ZFA:0005706.label: lg5
ZFA:0005706.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb. LG5 is surrounded by a diffuse aggregate of OSN axons.

ZFA:0005708.label: lg6
ZFA:0005708.definition: Glomerulus located in the lateral zone of the olfactory bulb. LG6 is located on the ventroposterior edge of the lateral group.

ZFA:0005715.label: maG1
ZFA:0005715.definition: Glomerulus located in the anteromedial  zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005709.label: mdG1
ZFA:0005709.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005710.label: mdG2
ZFA:0005710.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005711.label: mdG3
ZFA:0005711.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005712.label: mdG4
ZFA:0005712.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005713.label: mdG5
ZFA:0005713.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005714.label: mdG6
ZFA:0005714.definition: Glomerulus located in the mediodorsal zone of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005684.label: posteromedial glomerulus
ZFA:0005684.definition: Glomerulus located between ventromedial and medial olfactory bulb surfaces. The mpG is generally  elongated and innervated by a single thick axon.

ZFA:0005691.label: vmG1
ZFA:0005691.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Stains strongly with anti-calretinin. Anteriormost of the triplet of glomeruli strongly expressing calretinin.

ZFA:0005692.label: vmG2
ZFA:0005692.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Stains strongly with anti-calretinin.  Posterior to vmG1 in the triplet of glomeruli strongly expressing calretinin.

ZFA:0005693.label: vmG3
ZFA:0005693.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Stains strongly with anti-calretinin.  Posteriormost glomerulus in the triplet of glomeruli strongly expressing calretinin.

ZFA:0005694.label: vmG4
ZFA:0005694.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Posterior to the triplet of  ventromedial glomeruli strongly expressing calretinin.

ZFA:0005695.label: vmG5
ZFA:0005695.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Posterior to vmG4.

ZFA:0005696.label: vmG6
ZFA:0005696.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. Posterior to vmG4 adjacent to vmG5.

ZFA:0005697.label: vmG7
ZFA:0005697.definition: Glomerulus located in the ventromedial zone of the olfactory bulb. vmG7 is located anteriorly to vmG1-3 and vmG4-6.

ZFA:0005700.label: vpG1
ZFA:0005700.definition: One of two large glomeruli located in the ventroposterior zone olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005701.label: vpG2
ZFA:0005701.definition: One of two large glomeruli located in the ventroposterior zone olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005663.label: dorsal spinal nerve
ZFA:0005663.definition: Dorsal branch of the spinal nerve, coursing dorsally and caudally between the muscle and the vertebrae. It remains in the center of the muscle segment and could be followed to the dorsal aspect of the muscle. MiP primary motoneuron axons extend in this branch.

ZFA:0005664.label: lateral spinal nerve
ZFA:0005664.definition: Ventral branch of the spinal nerve that projects toward the lateral surface of the myotome, initially extending parallel to the horizontal myoseptum. RoP primary motoneuron axons extend in this branch.

ZFA:0005665.label: ventral spinal nerve
ZFA:0005665.definition: Ventral spinal nerve branch that projects to the ventral myotome. The axon of the CaP primary motoneuron extends in this branch.

ZFA:0005667.label: ventral spinal nerve median branch
ZFA:0005667.definition: Ventral spinal nerve sub-branch that projects ventrally in the rostro-caudal center of the myotome. The axon of the CaP primary motoneuron extends in this branch.

ZFA:0005666.label: ventral spinal nerve septal branch
ZFA:0005666.definition: Ventral spinal nerve sub-branch that runs near the rostral end of the myotome near the vertical myoseptum.

ZFA:0005670.label: central zone protoglomerulus
ZFA:0005670.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005669.label: lateral protoglomerulus
ZFA:0005669.definition: Protoglomeruli in the lateral  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005671.label: medial protoglomerulus
ZFA:0005671.definition: Protoglomeruli in the medial  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005672.label: ventral posterior glomerulus
ZFA:0005672.definition: Single large glomerulus located in the ventral posterior region of the maturing glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005717.label: lateral protoglomerulus 1
ZFA:0005717.definition: Protoglomeruli in the lateral  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005718.label: lateral protoglomerulus 2
ZFA:0005718.definition: Protoglomeruli in the lateral  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005719.label: lateral protoglomerulus 3
ZFA:0005719.definition: Protoglomeruli in the lateral  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005720.label: lateral protoglomerulus 4
ZFA:0005720.definition: Protoglomeruli in the lateral  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005721.label: central zone protoglomerulus 1
ZFA:0005721.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005722.label: central zone protoglomerulus 2
ZFA:0005722.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005723.label: central zone protoglomerulus 3
ZFA:0005723.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005724.label: central zone protoglomerulus 4
ZFA:0005724.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005725.label: central zone protoglomerulus 5
ZFA:0005725.definition: Protoglomeruli in the central zone  of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.  The central zone protoglomeruli have somewhat indistinct boundaries.

ZFA:0005726.label: medial protoglomerulus 1
ZFA:0005726.definition: Protoglomeruli in the medial  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005727.label: medial protoglomerulus 2
ZFA:0005727.definition: Protoglomeruli in the medial  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005728.label: medial protoglomerulus 3
ZFA:0005728.definition: Protoglomeruli in the medial  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005729.label: medial protoglomerulus 4
ZFA:0005729.definition: Protoglomeruli in the medial  region of the glomerular layer of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0005731.label: branchiomotor neuron
ZFA:0005731.definition: Cranial motor neuron which innervates muscles derived from the branchial (pharyngeal) arches.

ZFA:0005733.label: somatomotor neuron
ZFA:0005733.definition: Cranial motor neurons found in the midbrain and hindbrain that innervates muscles that control eye and tongue.

ZFA:0005732.label: visceromotor neuron
ZFA:0005732.definition: Cranial motor neurons are found in the hindbrain, and innervate parasympathetic neurons that innervate tear glands, sweat glands, and the smooth muscles and glands of the pulmonary, cardiovascular, and gastrointestinal systems.

ZFA:0005746.label: notochord inner cell
ZFA:0005746.definition: Structural cell of notochord that contain one large fluid-filled intracellular vacuole that occupies most of the cell volume.

ZFA:0005749.label: intercalated duct pancreas
ZFA:0005749.definition: The portion of the intrapancreatic duct leading from the pancreatic acinar gland to the intralobular duct.

ZFA:0005752.label: main intrapancreatic duct
ZFA:0005752.definition: Intrapancreatic duct that connects to the interlobular ducts and drains into the extrapancreatic duct.  The main duct may not be present in all larva and may develop in a segmented fashion.

ZFA:0005751.label: pancreatic interlobular duct
ZFA:0005751.definition: Intrapancreatic duct that connects the intralobular duct to the main pancreatic duct.

ZFA:0005750.label: pancreatic intralobular duct
ZFA:0005750.definition: Intrapancreatic duct within a pancreatic lobe that connects all the  intercalated duct with an interlobular duct.  The intralobular duct is lined with cuboidal cells.

ZFA:0005754.label: primary islet
ZFA:0005754.definition: The primary islet is the first islet to develop.

ZFA:0005756.label: secondary islet
ZFA:0005756.definition: Islet that develops after the primary islet.

ZFA:0005767.label: caudal fin fat
ZFA:0005767.definition: Subcutaneous adipose tissue deposit at the base of the caudal fin.

ZFA:0005766.label: pectoral fin plate fat
ZFA:0005766.definition: Adipose tissue that forms at the base of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005799.label: jaw flap breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005799.definition: Breeding tubercles that cover the surface of the jaw flap.

ZFA:0005798.label: jaw row breeding tubercle
