ZFA:0005798.definition: Surface structures composed of breeding tubercles arranged in a double row in the medial region on each side of the lower jaw.

ZFA:0005797.label: pectoral fin breeding tubercle
ZFA:0005797.definition: Breeding tubercles along the surface of the pectoral fin lepidotrichium of males.

ZFA:0009044.label: blood cell
ZFA:0009044.definition: A cell found predominately in the blood.

ZFA:0009023.label: common lymphoid progenitor
ZFA:0009023.definition: An oligopotent progenitor cell committed to the lymphoid lineage.

ZFA:0009021.label: common myeloid progenitor
ZFA:0009021.definition: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.

ZFA:0009251.label: granulocyte monocyte progenitor cell
ZFA:0009251.definition: A progenitor cell committed to the granulocyte and monocyte lineages.

ZFA:0009354.label: hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell
ZFA:0009354.definition: A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell is multipotent, but not capable of long-term self-renewal. These cells are characterized as lacking lineage cell surface markers and being CD34-positive in both mice and humans.

ZFA:0009309.label: leukocyte
ZFA:0009309.definition: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages, found in blood or other tissue.

ZFA:0009355.label: lymphoid progenitor cell
ZFA:0009355.definition: A progenitor cell restricted to the lymphoid lineage.

ZFA:0009022.label: megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell
ZFA:0009022.definition: A progenitor cell committed to the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.

ZFA:0009324.label: myeloid cell
ZFA:0009324.definition: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

ZFA:0009356.label: myeloid lineage restricted progenitor cell
ZFA:0009356.definition: A progenitor cell restricted to the myeloid lineage.

ZFA:0005846.label: left intestinal lymphatics
ZFA:0005846.definition: Lymph vessels that are on the left side of the intestine.  These do not run as far posteriorly as the right intestinal lymphatics.

ZFA:0005843.label: right intestinal lymphatics
ZFA:0005843.definition: Lymph vessels that are on the right side of the intestine.

ZFA:0005298.label: cranial lymph vessel
ZFA:0005298.definition: Lymph vessel that is located in the head.

ZFA:0005848.label: intestinal interlymphatic vessel
ZFA:0005848.definition: Lymph vessel that connects lymph vessels within the intestinal lymphatic network.

ZFA:0005109.label: jugular lymphatic vessel
ZFA:0005109.definition: Lymph vessel that connects the lateral facial lymph vessel to the thoracic duct near the common cardinal vein.

ZFA:0005837.label: lateral facial lymph vessel
ZFA:0005837.definition: Superfical lymph vessel part of the facial lymphatic network  that develops from the facial lymphatic sprout.  The lateral facial lymph vessel  runs toward the mandibular arch and tracks around the eye toward the jaw.

ZFA:0005845.label: lower left intestinal lymph vessel
ZFA:0005845.definition: Lymph vessel that extends along the left subintestinal vein.

ZFA:0005842.label: lower right intestinal lymph vessel
ZFA:0005842.definition: Pair of lymph vessel that follows the right subintestinal vein. At  6 dpf, the LR-IL appears to bifurcate and form two separate vessels that both run in close proximity to one another along the right sub intestinal vein. These vessels are difficult to distinguish from each other at 6dp.

ZFA:0005832.label: lymphatic branchial arch 1
ZFA:0005832.definition: Superficial lymph vessel that is part of pharyngeal arch 3.   The vessel sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.

ZFA:0005833.label: lymphatic branchial arch 2
ZFA:0005833.definition: Superficial lymph vessel that is part of pharyngeal arch 4.   The vessel sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.

ZFA:0005834.label: lymphatic branchial arch 3
ZFA:0005834.definition: Superficial lymph vessel that is part of pharyngeal arch 5.   The vessel sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.

ZFA:0005835.label: lymphatic branchial arch 4
ZFA:0005835.definition: Superficial lymph vessel that is part of pharyngeal arch 6.   The vessel sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.

ZFA:0007078.label: maxillary barbel lymph vessel
ZFA:0007078.definition: A blind end lymph vessel that emerges from the maxilla, wraps around the sinus isthmus, then runs alongside the distal bulb to enter the barbel shaft proper.

ZFA:0005839.label: medial facial lymph vessel
ZFA:0005839.definition: Facial lymph vessel that sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.  The path of the medial vessel runs ventromedially towards the ventral aorta.

ZFA:0005838.label: otolithic lymph vessel
ZFA:0005838.definition: Facial lymphatic vessel that sprouts from the lateral facial lymph vessel.  The path lies  parallel to the posterior cerebral vein but is not in contact with a blood vessel.

ZFA:0005862.label: ovarian lymph vessel
ZFA:0005862.definition: Lymph vessels within the ovary.  These vessels are located in the interstitium between ovarian follicles and  appear to envelop arterioles.

ZFA:0005747.label: supraintestinal lymphatic vessel
ZFA:0005747.definition: Lymph vessels that are located on either side of the PCV in the posterior region of the intestine.

ZFA:0005847.label: upper left intestinal lymph vessel
ZFA:0005847.definition: Lymph vessel on the left of the intestine that runs parallel to the upper right intestinal lymph vessel.  There does not appear to be an associated blood vessel.

ZFA:0005841.label: upper right intestinal lymph vessel
ZFA:0005841.definition: Lymph vessel that follows the supraintestinal artery.

ZFA:0005854.label: replacement  tooth 3V
ZFA:0005854.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row. This tooth develops from the dental epithelium  at the position of  primary tooth 3V.

ZFA:0005856.label: replacement tooth 1V
ZFA:0005856.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row. This tooth develops from the dental epithelium  at the position of  primary tooth 1V.

ZFA:0005855.label: replacement tooth 2V
ZFA:0005855.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row. This tooth develops from the dental epithelium  at the position of  primary tooth 2V.

ZFA:0005852.label: replacement tooth 4V
ZFA:0005852.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.  This tooth develops from the dental epithelium  at the position of  primary tooth 4V.

ZFA:0005853.label: replacement tooth 5V
ZFA:0005853.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row. This tooth develops from the dental epithelium  at the position of  primary tooth 5V.

ZFA:0001148.label: tooth 1D
ZFA:0001148.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001146.label: tooth 1MD
ZFA:0001146.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001141.label: tooth 1V
ZFA:0001141.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0001150.label: tooth 2D
ZFA:0001150.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001147.label: tooth 2MD
ZFA:0001147.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1MD and anterior to tooth 3MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001144.label: tooth 2V
ZFA:0001144.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0001152.label: tooth 3MD
ZFA:0001152.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2MD and anterior to tooth 4MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001145.label: tooth 3V
ZFA:0001145.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0001151.label: tooth 4MD
ZFA:0001151.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.

ZFA:0001143.label: tooth 4V
ZFA:0001143.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0001142.label: tooth 5V
ZFA:0001142.definition: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

ZFA:0009149.label: Mauthner neuron
ZFA:0009149.definition: Is a hindbrain interneuron.  Giant reticulospinal neurons possessing thick crossed axons and positioned dorsally in the hindbrain tegmentum at the level of entrance of the eighth cranial nerve.  The Mauthner neuron is paired. The M-cell has two large invariant dendrites: The lateral dendrite terminates in the sensory neuropil of the acoustico-lateral area, and the ventral dendrite terminates in the neuropil of the motor tegmentum. Fine dendrites are present, and mostly arise from three regions; from the terminus of each major dendrite and from the ventral surface of the perikaryon.

ZFA:0005905.label: coronoid process
ZFA:0005905.definition: Cartilaginous protrusion on the posterodorsal region of Meckel's cartilage.  The coronoid process of Meckel's cartilage  forms the dorsal portion of the articulation with the  anteroventral corner of  the palatoquadrate.

ZFA:0005902.label: pterygoid process
ZFA:0005902.definition: A medial cartilaginous spur that develops from the dorsomedial edge of the palatoquadrate.  It is derived from cells located in the maxillary prominence of the first pharyngeal arch and gives rise to the metapterygoid.

ZFA:0005904.label: retroarticular  process
ZFA:0005904.definition: A protrusion of cartilage at the posteroventral tip of  Meckel's cartilage that gives rise to the retroarticular.

ZFA:0005225.label: lower lip
ZFA:0005225.definition: Lip that covers the lower portion of the mouth.

ZFA:0005226.label: upper lip
ZFA:0005226.definition: Lip that covers the lower portion of the mouth.

ZFA:0005144.label: ampullary nerve
ZFA:0005144.definition: Nerve that is a branch of cranial nerve VIII and innervates the cristae ampullaris.

ZFA:0000641.label: cranial nerve
ZFA:0000641.definition: Twelve pairs of cranial nerves exit/enter the cranium through openings in the skull. The nerves contain efferent axons with motor and glandular functions, as well as afferent axons from cranial ganglia with sensory functions. The nerves are numbered in a rostral to caudal sequence, with the exception of the lateral line nerves.

ZFA:0005397.label: hyoideomandibular nerve
ZFA:0005397.definition: Nerve that is a branch of cranial nerve VII that passes through or around the suspensorium to innervate muscles and sensory organs on or near pharyngeal arch 2.

ZFA:0001479.label: lateral line nerve
ZFA:0001479.definition: Cranial nerves that carry afferent and efferent fibers for the lateral line system.

ZFA:0001625.label: optic nerve head
ZFA:0001625.definition: Portion of cranial nerve II where large fascicles of axons from the optic fiber layer come together prior to leaving the eye.

ZFA:0005436.label: pectoral fin nerve
ZFA:0005436.definition: Nerve that is part of the pectoral fin.

ZFA:0005662.label: spinal nerve
ZFA:0005662.definition: Bilaterally-paired nerve connecting each segment of the spinal cord to the limbs and organs.

ZFA:0005046.label: hyaloid vessel
ZFA:0005046.definition: Vessels that are associated with the posterior region of the lens.

ZFA:0005094.label: optic choroid vascular plexus
ZFA:0005094.definition: Is an ocular vasculature that develops adjacent to the pigment epithelium of the eye. The optic choroid vascular plexus develops from the primitive mesencephalic artery. Initially blood enters from the mesencephalic central artery, and the dorsal ciliary vein. The plexus drains via the ophthalmic vein. The plexus supplies blood to the retina.

ZFA:0007060.label: dorsolateral field
ZFA:0007060.definition: Neurogenic field fated to develop into a dorsolateral placode.

ZFA:0007061.label: epibranchial field
ZFA:0007061.definition: Neurogenic field fated to develop into an epibranchial placode.

ZFA:0007062.label: olfactory field
ZFA:0007062.definition: Neurogenic field fated to develop into the olfactory placode.

ZFA:0000619.label: anterior crista
ZFA:0000619.definition: Patches of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium of the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. Each patch has its own characteristic shape and polarity pattern. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000468.label: anterior crista primordium
ZFA:0000468.definition: Is an otic epithelium that will mature into the anterior crista.

ZFA:0000166.label: lateral crista
ZFA:0000166.definition: Patches of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium of the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. Each patch has its own characteristic shape and polarity pattern. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000225.label: lateral crista primordium
ZFA:0000225.definition: Is an otic epithelium that will mature into the lateral crista.

ZFA:0007070.label: otic sensory epithelium
ZFA:0007070.definition: Is an otic epithelium that is a neuroepithelium which is pseudostratified and senses sound.

ZFA:0007069.label: otic squamous epithelium
ZFA:0007069.definition: Is an otic epithelium composed of cells with a squamous morphology.

ZFA:0000566.label: posterior crista
ZFA:0000566.definition: Patches of thickened, pseudostratified epithelium of the inner ear, consisting of regular arrays of sensory hair cells interspersed with supporting cells. Each patch has its own characteristic shape and polarity pattern. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000411.label: posterior crista primordium
ZFA:0000411.definition: Is an otic epithelium that will mature into the posterior crista.

ZFA:0001096.label: immature anterior macula
ZFA:0001096.definition: Is an otic sensory epithelium that will develop into the mature anterior macula.

ZFA:0001095.label: immature macula
ZFA:0001095.definition: Is an otic sensory epithelium that will develop into the mature macula.

ZFA:0001097.label: immature posterior macula
ZFA:0001097.definition: Is an otic sensory epithelium that will develop into the mature posterior macula.

ZFA:0007074.label: maxillary barbel blood sinus
ZFA:0007074.definition: Is a three-chambered blood sinus found at the base of the maxillary barbel. Responsible, in part, for the movement of the maxillary barbel.

ZFA:0007081.label: maxillary barbel proximal plexus
ZFA:0007081.definition: Is a vascular plexus at the base, or proximal end, of the developing maxillary barbel.

ZFA:0007090.label: premigratory cranial neural crest cell
ZFA:0007090.definition: Cell that is part of the premigratory cranial neural crest population. Will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination to become part of the migratory cranial neural crest.

ZFA:0007094.label: premigratory trunk neural crest cell
ZFA:0007094.definition: Cell that is part of the premigratory trunk neural crest population. Will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination to become part of the migratory trunk neural crest.

ZFA:0007091.label: migratory cranial neural crest cell
ZFA:0007091.definition: Cell that is part of the migratory cranial neural crest population. Migratory cranial neural crest cells develop from premigratory cranial neural crest cells and have undergone epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0007095.label: migratory trunk neural crest cell
ZFA:0007095.definition: Cell that is part of the migratory trunk neural crest population. Migratory trunk neural crest cells develop from premigratory trunk neural crest cells and have undergone epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0009002.label: early embryonic cell
ZFA:0009002.definition: An embryonic cell that is formed before the germ layers have been formed.

ZFA:0009165.label: neural crest cell
ZFA:0009165.definition: A cell of the neural crest. The neural crest is a strip of specialized ectoderm, the neural plate border, which flanks each side of the embryonic neural plate. Neural crest cells are multipotent. Premigratory neural crest cells are found at the neural plate boarder, some of which will undergo ectomesenchymal transition and delamination to form migratory neural crest cells. Most of the cranial and all of the spinal sensory ganglion cells arise by differentiation of neural crest cells.

ZFA:0000431.label: semicircular canal
ZFA:0000431.definition: Fluid-filled semicircular tubes, arranged orthogonally to each other in the inner ear. Each canal is associated with a crista that detects angular accelerations. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for semicircular canals by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0009146.label: Merkel cell
ZFA:0009146.definition: A modified epidermal cell located in the stratum basale. They are found mostly in areas where sensory perception is acute. Merkel cells are closely associated with an expanded terminal bulb of an afferent myelinated nerve fiber.

ZFA:0009129.label: absorptive cell
ZFA:0009129.definition: A cell that takes up and metabolizes substances.

ZFA:0009277.label: acinar cell
ZFA:0009277.definition: A secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape shaped clusters known as acini (singular acinus).

ZFA:0000003.label: adaxial cell
ZFA:0000003.definition: Muscle precursor cell that is adjacent to the notochord and part of the presomitic mesoderm.

ZFA:0009028.label: ameloblast
ZFA:0009028.definition: A cylindrical epithelial cell in the innermost layer of the enamel organ. Their functions include contribution to the development of the dentinoenamel junction by the deposition of a layer of the matrix, thus producing the foundation for the prisms (the structural units of the dental enamel), and production of the matrix for the enamel prisms and interprismatic substance. (From Jablonski's Dictionary of Dentistry, 1992).

ZFA:0005244.label: auditory epithelial support cell
ZFA:0005244.definition: A non-sensory cell that extends from the basement membrane to the apical surface of the auditory epithelium and provides support for auditory hair cells.

ZFA:0009132.label: barrier cell
ZFA:0009132.definition: A cell whose primary function is to prevent the transport of stuff across compartments.

ZFA:0000093.label: blastomere
ZFA:0000093.definition: Cell that arises during cleavage and is partially cleaved, and located at the blastodisc margin prior to collectively forming the yolk syncytial layer (YSL) in the midblastula.

ZFA:0009259.label: cardiac mesenchymal cell
ZFA:0009259.definition: A mesenchymal cell found in the developing heart.

ZFA:0009030.label: cementoblast
ZFA:0009030.definition: A cell of ectomesenchymal origin concerned with the formation of the layer of cementum on the roots of teeth.

ZFA:0009087.label: cementocyte
ZFA:0009087.definition: An osteocytelike cell with numerous processes, trapped in a lacuna in the cement of the tooth.

ZFA:0009027.label: chondroblast
ZFA:0009027.definition: Skeletogenic cell that is typically non-terminally differentiated, secretes an avascular, GAG rich matrix; is not buried in cartilage tissue matrix, retains the ability to divide, located adjacent to cartilage tissue (including within the perichondrium).

ZFA:0009175.label: choroidal cell of the eye
ZFA:0009175.definition: A cell of the choroid of the eye.

ZFA:0009043.label: circulating cell
ZFA:0009043.definition: A cell which moves among different tissues of the body, via blood, lymph, or other medium.

ZFA:0005332.label: cyanoblast
ZFA:0005332.definition: A non-terminally differentiated cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a cyanophore.

ZFA:0009137.label: ectodermal cell
ZFA:0009137.definition: A cell of the outer of the three germ layers of the embryo.

ZFA:0009128.label: electrically active cell
ZFA:0009128.definition: A cell whose function is determined by the generation or the reception of an electric signal.

ZFA:0009096.label: endocrine cell
ZFA:0009096.definition: A cell of an endocrine gland, ductless glands that secrete substances which are released directly into the circulation and which influence metabolism and other body functions.

ZFA:0009139.label: endodermal cell
ZFA:0009139.definition: A cell of the inner of the three germ layers of the embryo.

ZFA:0009034.label: epithelial cell
ZFA:0009034.definition: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface.

ZFA:0009092.label: exocrine cell
ZFA:0009092.definition: A cell of an exocrine gland, i.e. a gland that discharges its secretion via a duct.

ZFA:0009082.label: fat cell
ZFA:0009082.definition: A fat-storing cell found mostly in the abdominal cavity and subcutaneous tissue of mammals. Fat is usually stored in the form of triglycerides. Cell that stores fat in a unilocular lipid droplet, has a thin circular cytoplasm and pericentral nucleus. The average adult adipocyte diameter is between 30 and 40 micrometers.  No adipocytes were observed in larvae on 6 or 9 dpf.

ZFA:0005772.label: fertilized egg
ZFA:0005772.definition: Diploid cell produced by the fusion of sperm cell nucleus and egg cell.

ZFA:0009026.label: fibroblast
ZFA:0009026.definition: A connective tissue cell which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules.

ZFA:0009016.label: germ line cell
ZFA:0009016.definition: A cell that is within the developmental lineage of gametes and is able to pass along its genetic material to offspring.

ZFA:0009073.label: glial cell
ZFA:0009073.definition: A non-neuronal cell of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu. Guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

ZFA:0005830.label: hematopoietic cell
ZFA:0005830.definition: A cell of a  hematopoietic lineage.

ZFA:0005328.label: iridoblast
ZFA:0005328.definition: A non-terminally differentiated cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into an iridophore.

ZFA:0009401.label: lens fiber cell
ZFA:0009401.definition: A  vertebrate lens cell that is any of the elongated, tightly packed cells that make up the bulk of the mature lens in a camera-type eye.

ZFA:0005329.label: leucoblast
ZFA:0005329.definition: A non-terminally differentiated cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a leucophore.

ZFA:0009249.label: melanoblast
ZFA:0009249.definition: A cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a pigment cell.

ZFA:0009081.label: mesenchymal cell
ZFA:0009081.definition: A cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

ZFA:0009138.label: mesodermal cell
ZFA:0009138.definition: A cell of the middle germ layer of the embryo.

ZFA:0005239.label: micropylar cell
ZFA:0005239.definition: Is a specialized pore forming cell of the follicle, located adjacent to the animal pole of the oocyte.  The micropylar cell makes the single micropyle (pore) through the chorion through which the sperm fertilizes the egg.

ZFA:0001373.label: migratory slow muscle precursor cell
ZFA:0001373.definition: Cells that initially are located adjacent to the spinal cord and notochord that migrate from their initial medial position radially through the myotome to the lateral surface of the somites.

ZFA:0009136.label: motile cell
ZFA:0009136.definition: A cell that moves by its own activities.

ZFA:0009025.label: myoblast
ZFA:0009025.definition: An embryonic (precursor) cell of the myogenic lineage that develops from the mesoderm. They undergo proliferation, migrate to their various sites, and then differentiate into the appropriate form of myocytes.

ZFA:0009362.label: neuromast mantle cell
ZFA:0009362.definition: Neuromast mantle cell is a non-sensory cell. Neuromast mantle cells surround the neuromast support cells and neuromast hair cells, separating the neuromast from the epidermis, and secrete cupula in which the ciliary bundles of all the hair cells are embedded.

ZFA:0009363.label: neuromast support cell
ZFA:0009363.definition: Neuromast support cell is a non-sensory cell of the neuromast that extend between the sensory hair cells from the basement membrane to the apical surface; neuromast support cells are surrounded by neuromast mantle cells.

ZFA:0009257.label: neutrophilic promyelocyte
ZFA:0009257.definition: A neutrophil precursor in the granulocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between a myeloblast and myelocyte, and containing a few, as yet undifferentiated, cytoplasmic granules.

ZFA:0009029.label: odontoblast
ZFA:0009029.definition: Skeletogenic cell that  secretes dentine matrix, is derived from the tooth pulp.

ZFA:0009364.label: olfactory epithelial support cell
ZFA:0009364.definition: Olfactory epithelial support cell is a non ciliated columnar cell that extends from the epithelial free margin to the basement membrane of the olfactory epithelium.

ZFA:0000688.label: olfactory support cell
ZFA:0000688.definition: Supporting cell that is part of the olfactory epithelium. Their cell bodies are more or less cylindrical, often with a pronounced basal part resting on the basal lamina. Their apical surface is covered with microvillous-like protrusions. Nuclei of olfactory support cell lie below the nuclear layer of olfactory sensory neurons,  a feature that is reverse that of other vertebrates.  The nuclei are less electron dense then those of the olfactory sensory neurons.

ZFA:0009031.label: osteoblast
ZFA:0009031.definition: A bone-forming cell which secretes an extracellular matrix. Hydroxyapatite crystals are then deposited into the matrix to form bone.

ZFA:0009047.label: osteoclast
ZFA:0009047.definition: A specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue, which typically differentiates from monocytes.

ZFA:0009083.label: osteocyte
ZFA:0009083.definition: A mature osteoblast that has become embedded in the bone matrix. They occupy a small cavity, called lacuna, in the matrix and are connected to adjacent osteocytes via protoplasmic projections called canaliculi.

ZFA:0009112.label: pericyte
ZFA:0009112.definition: An elongated, contractile cell found wrapped about precapillary arterioles outside the basement membrane. Pericytes are present in capillaries where proper adventitial and muscle layer are missing (thus distinguishing this cell type from adventitial cells). They are relatively undifferentiated and may become fibroblasts, macrophages, or smooth muscle cells.

ZFA:0005331.label: pigment erythroblast
ZFA:0005331.definition: A non-terminally differentiated cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into an erythrophore.

ZFA:0009174.label: scleral cell
ZFA:0009174.definition: A cell of the sclera of the eye.

ZFA:0009386.label: somatic cell
ZFA:0009386.definition: A cell of an organism that does not pass on its genetic material to the organism's offspring (i.e. a non-germ line cell).

ZFA:0009307.label: somatic stem cell
ZFA:0009307.definition: A stem cell that can give rise to cell types of the body other than those of the germ-line.

ZFA:0009226.label: stromal cell
ZFA:0009226.definition: A connective tissue cell of an organ found in the loose connective tissue. These are most often associated with the uterine mucosa and the ovary as well as the hematopoietic system and elsewhere.

ZFA:0005745.label: structural cell
ZFA:0005745.definition: A cell whose primary function is to provide structural support, to provide strength and physical integrity to the organism.

ZFA:0009387.label: supportive cell
ZFA:0009387.definition: A cell whose primary function is to support other cell types.

ZFA:0009302.label: sustentacular cell
ZFA:0009302.definition: Cell that provides some or all mechanical, nutritional and phagocytic support to their neighbors.

ZFA:0009298.label: terminal Schwann cell
ZFA:0009298.definition: A neuroglial cell of the peripheral nervous system inside the basal lamina of the neuromuscular junction providing chemical and physical support to the synapse.

ZFA:0001570.label: unfertilized egg
ZFA:0001570.definition: A female gamete where meiosis has progressed to metaphase II and is able to participate in fertilization.  In zebrafish specified to be outside the body.

ZFA:0005245.label: xanthoblast
ZFA:0005245.definition: A non-terminally differentiated cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a xanthophore.

ZFA:0000084.label: yolk
ZFA:0000084.definition: Giant syncytial uncleaved cell containing nutrient store for embryonic development in the form of semicrystalline phospholipoprotein and contained within yolk granules.

ZFA:0009121.label: auditory receptor cell
ZFA:0009121.definition: A mechanoreceptor cell located in the inner ear that is sensitive to auditory stimuli. The accessory sensory structures are arranged so that appropriate stimuli cause movement of the hair-like projections (stereocilia and kinocilia) which relay the information centrally in the nervous system.

ZFA:0009124.label: chemoreceptor cell
ZFA:0009124.definition: A cell specialized to detect chemical substances and relay that information centrally in the nervous system. Chemoreceptors may monitor external stimuli, as in taste and olfaction, or internal stimuli, such as the concentrations of oxygen and carbon dioxide in the blood.

ZFA:0009120.label: mechanoreceptor cell
ZFA:0009120.definition: A cell specialized to transduce mechanical stimuli and relay that information centrally in the nervous system.

ZFA:0009119.label: pain receptor cell
ZFA:0009119.definition: The peripheral receptor for pain. Includes receptors which are sensitive to painful mechanical stimuli, extreme heat or cold, and chemical stimuli. All mammalian nociceptors are free nerve endings.

ZFA:0009127.label: photoreceptor cell
ZFA:0009127.definition: A cell specialized to detect and transduce light.

ZFA:0009123.label: thermoreceptor cell
ZFA:0009123.definition: A cellular receptor which mediates the sense of temperature. Thermoreceptors in vertebrates are mostly located under the skin. In mammals there are separate types of thermoreceptors for cold and for warmth and pain receptor cells which detect cold or heat extreme enough to cause pain.

ZFA:0009177.label: blastoderm cell
ZFA:0009177.definition: An undifferentiated cell produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote).

ZFA:0009182.label: gastrula cell
ZFA:0009182.definition: A cell of the embryo in the early stage following the blastula, characterized by morphogenetic cell movements, cell differentiation, and the formation of the three germ layers.

ZFA:0009238.label: afferent neuron
ZFA:0009238.definition: A neuron which conveys sensory information centrally from the periphery.

ZFA:0009239.label: efferent neuron
ZFA:0009239.definition: A neuron which sends impulses peripherally to activate muscles or secretory cells.

ZFA:0009156.label: gamete
ZFA:0009156.definition: A mature sexual reproductive cell having a single set of unpaired chromosomes.

ZFA:0001109.label: oocyte
ZFA:0001109.definition: A female germ cell that has entered meiosis.

ZFA:0005878.label: oogonia
ZFA:0005878.definition: An undifferentiated germ cell that proliferates rapidly and gives rise to oocytes. In zebrafish oogonia are round cells, with centrally located nucleoli, which are strongly basophilic. Oogonia in larva zebrafish fish are often found in clusters of two or four cells, corresponding to the second, or third oogonial divisions, presumably arising from mitotic divisions of primordial germ cells.

ZFA:0009288.label: primordial germ cell
ZFA:0009288.definition: A primordial germ cell is a diploid germ cell precursors that transiently exist in the embryo before they enter into close association with the somatic cells of the gonad and become irreversibly committed as germ cells.

ZFA:0009006.label: sperm
ZFA:0009006.definition: A mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

ZFA:0005769.label: spermatid
ZFA:0005769.definition: A male germ cell that develops from the haploid secondary spermatocytes. Without further division, spermatids undergo structural changes and give rise to spermatozoa.

ZFA:0009005.label: spermatocyte
ZFA:0009005.definition: A male germ cell that develops from spermatogonia. The euploid primary spermatocytes undergo meiosis and give rise to the haploid secondary spermatocytes which in turn give rise to spermatids.

ZFA:0009007.label: spermatogonium
ZFA:0009007.definition: An euploid male germ cell of an early stage of spermatogenesis.

ZFA:0009014.label: hematopoietic stem cell
ZFA:0009014.definition: A stem cell from which all cells of the lymphoid and myeloid lineages develop, including blood cells and cells of the immune system.

ZFA:0009398.label: hepatoblast
ZFA:0009398.definition: Multi fate stem cell that gives rise to both hepatocytes and cholangiocytes as descendants.

ZFA:0009234.label: cardiac muscle myoblast
ZFA:0009234.definition: A precursor cell destined to differentiate into cardiac myocytes.

ZFA:0009236.label: skeletal muscle myoblast
ZFA:0009236.definition: A myoblast that differentiates into skeletal muscle fibers.

ZFA:0009235.label: smooth muscle myoblast
ZFA:0009235.definition: A precursor cell destined to differentiate into smooth muscle myocytes.

ZFA:0009296.label: perijunctional fibroblast
ZFA:0009296.definition: A fibroblast-like cell that provides support at neuromuscular junctions in vertebrates and are localized outside the synaptic basal lamina.

ZFA:0005246.label: regeneration fibroblast
ZFA:0005246.definition: Is a fibroblast that differentiates from the de-differentiated cells of the blastema.

ZFA:0009304.label: choroid plexus epithelial cell
ZFA:0009304.definition: Specialized ependymal cell that produces the cerebrospinal fluid from the blood and secretes it into the lumen of the brain and spinal chord.

ZFA:0009293.label: M cell
ZFA:0009293.definition: An absorptive cell of the mammalian gut epithelium that endocytoses microorganisms and intact macromolecules from the gut lumen and transports them to the subepithelial space where they are presented to antigen-presenting cells and lymphocytes.

ZFA:0009385.label: ecto-epithelial cell
ZFA:0009385.definition: An epithelial cell derived from ectoderm.

ZFA:0009383.label: endo-epithelial cell
ZFA:0009383.definition: An epithelial cell derived from endoderm.

ZFA:0009111.label: hepatocyte
ZFA:0009111.definition: The main structural component of the liver. They are specialized epithelial cells that are organized into interconnected plates called lobules.

ZFA:0005323.label: ionocyte
ZFA:0005323.definition: Specialized epithelial cells involved in the maintenance of osmotic homeostasis. They are characterized by abundant mitochondria and ion transporters. In amniotes, they are present in the renal system. In freshwater fish, ionocytes in the skin and gills help maintain osmotic homeostasis by absorbing salt from the external environment.

ZFA:0009374.label: kidney epithelial cell
ZFA:0009374.definition: An epithelial cell of the kidney.

ZFA:0009388.label: meso-epithelial cell
ZFA:0009388.definition: Epithelial cell derived from mesoderm or mesenchyme.

ZFA:0005744.label: notochord outer sheath cell
ZFA:0005744.definition: Cells that  form an epithelial-like sheath around the vacuolated inner notochord cells. Outer cells secrete a thick extracellular perinotochordal basement membrane.

ZFA:0005742.label: pancreatic PP cell
ZFA:0005742.definition: Polypeptide producing cell located in the islets of the pancreas.

ZFA:0009308.label: urothelial cell
ZFA:0009308.definition: A cell of a layer of transitional epithelium in the wall of the bladder, ureter, and renal pelvis, external to the lamina propria.

ZFA:0009033.label: ependymal cell
ZFA:0009033.definition: A neurectoderm derived cell that lines the neural lumen.

ZFA:0005242.label: multi-ciliated epithelial cell
ZFA:0005242.definition: A ciliated epithelial cell with many cilia.

ZFA:0005243.label: single ciliated epithelial cell
ZFA:0005243.definition: A ciliated epithelial cell with a single cilium.

ZFA:0009303.label: endothelial tip cell
ZFA:0009303.definition: A specialized endothelial cell that senses extracellular signals and guides the directed growth of blood vessels.

ZFA:0009384.label: neurecto-epithelial cell
ZFA:0009384.definition: Epithelial cells derived from neural plate and neural crest.

ZFA:0005740.label: pancreatic centroacinar cell
ZFA:0005740.definition: A cuboidal epithelial cell that is continuous with the lining of intercalated ducts that drain the acinus. This cell type secretes a high pH solution to aid in activation of zymogens, and can differentiate into endocrine and exocrine pancreatic cell types.

ZFA:0009375.label: renal intercalated cell
ZFA:0009375.definition: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney that regulates acid/base balance.

ZFA:0005322.label: renal principal cell
ZFA:0005322.definition: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney which regulates sodium and potassium balance. The activity of sodium and potassium channels on the cells apical membrane is regulated by aldosterone and vasopressin. In mammals these cells are located in the renal collecting ducts.

ZFA:0009079.label: corneal endothelial cell
ZFA:0009079.definition: Cell of the single layer of large flattened cells covering the surface of the cornea.

ZFA:0009183.label: epidermal cell
ZFA:0009183.definition: A cell found in the outermost layer of the organism.

ZFA:0009252.label: reticulocyte
ZFA:0009252.definition: An immature erythrocyte showing a basophilic reticulum under vital staining.

ZFA:0009323.label: thrombocyte
ZFA:0009323.definition: A nucleated blood cell involved in coagulation, typically seen in birds and other non-mammalian vertebrates.

ZFA:0009335.label: alpha-beta T cell
ZFA:0009335.definition: A T cell that expresses an alpha-beta T cell receptor complex.

ZFA:0009336.label: gamma-delta T cell
ZFA:0009336.definition: A T cell that expresses a gamma-delta T cell receptor complex.

ZFA:0009342.label: memory T cell
ZFA:0009342.definition: A distinctly differentiated long-lived T cell that has the phenotype CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive.

ZFA:0009329.label: mononuclear osteoclast
ZFA:0009329.definition: A specialized mononuclear osteoclast associated with the absorption and removal of bone, precursor of multinuclear osteoclasts.

ZFA:0009270.label: odontoclast
ZFA:0009270.definition: A specialized osteoclast associated with the absorption and removal of cementum.

ZFA:0009327.label: neutrophil
ZFA:0009327.definition: Any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

ZFA:0009255.label: amacrine cell
ZFA:0009255.definition: Interneuron of the vertebrate retina. They integrate, modulate, and interpose a temporal domain in the visual message presented to the retinal ganglion cells, with which they synapse in the inner plexiform layer.

ZFA:0009055.label: bipolar neuron
ZFA:0009055.definition: A type of interneuron that has two neurites, usually an axon and a dendrite, extending from opposite poles of an ovoid cell body.

ZFA:0009315.label: horizontal cell
ZFA:0009315.definition: A neuron that laterally connects other neurons in the inner nuclear layer of the retina.

ZFA:0005730.label: cranial motor neuron
ZFA:0005730.definition: Motor neuron that innervate muscles that control eye, jaw, and facial movements of the vertebrate head and parasympathetic neurons that innervate certain glands and organs.

ZFA:0009244.label: primary motor neuron
ZFA:0009244.definition: Motor neurons that arise during the first day of development.  Primary motoneurons have larger diameter cell bodies and axons than secondary motoneurons and are positioned more dorsally and medially than secondary motoneurons. Primary motoneurons are present in a single bilateral pair of clusters in each spinal segment and innervate axial muscle fibers in the corresponding pair of myotomes. Axons make a conspicuous loop around the Mauthner axon before entering the ventral root.

ZFA:0009247.label: secondary motor neuron
ZFA:0009247.definition: Motor neurons that develop several hours later than primary motoneurons and sprout axons several hours after the primary motor growth cones have extended to the periphery.  They have smaller cell bodies and are located more ventrally and laterally in the spinal cord than primary motoneurons. Axons usually project directly out of the spinal cord with no apparent contact with the Mauthner axon and are positioned lateral to the Mauthner axon in their path to the ventral root.  Secondary motoneurons have smaller fields, which can overlap one another, and innervate many fewer muscle fibers than primary motoneurons.

ZFA:0009311.label: spinal accessory motor neuron
ZFA:0009311.definition: A motor neuron that is located in the cervical region of the spinal cord and selectively innervates the sternocleidmastoid or trapezius muscle. Unlike other motor neurons, they extend axons dorsally along lateral margins of the spinal cord.

ZFA:0009150.label: Rohon-Beard neuron
ZFA:0009150.definition: Primary sensory neurons with cell bodies located in the dorsal spinal cord, that innervate the integument of the trunk and tail at early larval stages. The cutaneous axons of Rohon-Beard neurons display a broad spectrum of peripheral axon branching patterns.  Most Rohon-Beard neurons undergo apoptosis by 5dpf.

ZFA:0005768.label: trigeminal sensory neuron
ZFA:0005768.definition: Sensory neuron that extends a single axon shaft along the lateral white matter of the hindbrain and spinal cord. Numerous medially projecting branches are later formed and innervate a series of target nuclei along the anteroposterior axis of the hindbrain and spinal cord.  The highly branched axons innervate the integument of the head.  There are several subtypes with different afferent branching morphologies.

ZFA:0009318.label: retinal bipolar neuron
ZFA:0009318.definition: A bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with photoreceptors cells and neurons in the inner plexiform layer.

ZFA:0005775.label: enteric neuron
ZFA:0005775.definition: Neuron that is part of the enteric nervous system.

ZFA:0005776.label: parasympathetic neuron
ZFA:0005776.definition: Parasympathetic neurons are part of the parasympathetic nervous system and the cell bodies lie in the brain and sacral region of the spinal cord. The neurons are mainly cholinergic.

ZFA:0005777.label: sympathetic neuron
ZFA:0005777.definition: Sympathetic neurons are part of the sympathetic nervous system and are primarily adrenergic producing the neurotransmitter noradrenalin along with other neuropeptides.

ZFA:0009141.label: macrophage
ZFA:0009141.definition: A mononuclear phagocyte present in variety of tissues, typically differentiated from monocytes, capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

ZFA:0009265.label: monocyte
ZFA:0009265.definition: Myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

ZFA:0009300.label: Cajal-Retzius cell
ZFA:0009300.definition: One of a transient population of pioneering neurons in the cerebral cortex. These cells are slender bipolar cells of the developing marginal zone. One feature of these cells in mammals is that they express the Reelin gene.

ZFA:0009071.label: Purkinje cell
ZFA:0009071.definition: The output neuron of the cerebellar cortex.

ZFA:0009273.label: pyramidal cell
ZFA:0009273.definition: A projection neuron in the cerebral cortex and the hippocampus. Pyramidal cells have a pyramid-shaped soma with the apex and an apical dendrite pointed toward the pial surface and other dendrites and an axon emerging from the base. The axons may have local collaterals but also project outside their cortical region.

ZFA:0009310.label: retinal ganglion cell
ZFA:0009310.definition: The set of neurons that receives neural inputs via bipolar, horizontal and amacrine cells. The axons of these cells make up the optic nerve.

ZFA:0001691.label: cerebellar granule cell
ZFA:0001691.definition: Granule cell that is part of the cerebellum.

ZFA:0001694.label: olfactory granule cell
ZFA:0001694.definition: Granule cell that is part of the olfactory bulb.

ZFA:0009147.label: glial cell (sensu Vertebrata)
ZFA:0009147.definition: A non-neuronal cells of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu. Form the myelin insulation of nervous pathways, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons. Neuroglia have high-affinity transmitter uptake systems, voltage-dependent and transmitter-gated ion channels, and can release transmitters, but their role in signaling (as in many other functions) is unclear.

ZFA:0009075.label: astrocyte
ZFA:0009075.definition: A class of large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system - the largest and most numerous neuroglial cells in the brain and spinal cord. Astrocytes (from 'star' cells) are irregularly shaped with many long processes, including those with 'end feet' which form the glial (limiting) membrane and directly and indirectly contribute to the blood-brain barrier. They regulate the extracellular ionic and chemical environment, and 'reactive astrocytes' (along with microglia) respond to injury.

ZFA:0009076.label: oligodendrocyte
ZFA:0009076.definition: A class of large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system. Form the insulating myelin sheath of axons in the central nervous system.

ZFA:0009280.label: Muller cell
ZFA:0009280.definition: Glial cell of the retina that forms a support structure stretching radially across the thickness of the retina. Muller cell bodies are found in  the inner nuclear layer and send projection to the outer limiting membrane and inner limiting membrane.

ZFA:0009294.label: ependymoglial cell
ZFA:0009294.definition: A cell that transports hormones from neurosecretory cells.

ZFA:0009365.label: interneuromast cell
ZFA:0009365.definition: Interneuromast cell is a neuroectodermal cell deposited by the migrating lateral line primordium between the neuromasts. Interneuromast cells proliferate and migrate to form additional neuromasts.

ZFA:0009394.label: mesenchymal lymphangioblast
ZFA:0009394.definition: Mesenchymal derived lymphatic progenitor cells that give rise to the superficial lymphatics.

ZFA:0009314.label: columnar chondrocyte
ZFA:0009314.definition: A columnar chondrocyte that differentiates in the late embryonic growth plate of bone. Columnar chondrocytes vigorously proliferate and form columns in the growth plate.

ZFA:0009313.label: hypertrophic chondrocyte
ZFA:0009313.definition: A terminally differentiated chondrocyte that differentiates in the late embryonic growth plate of bone.

ZFA:0009312.label: periarticular chondrocyte
ZFA:0009312.definition: A round chondrocyte that first differentiates in the late embryonic growth plate of bone.

ZFA:0009209.label: dendritic cell
ZFA:0009209.definition: A cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation.

ZFA:0009331.label: mature B cell
ZFA:0009331.definition: A B cell that is mature, having left the bone marrow. Initially, these cells are IgM-positive and IgD-positive, and they can be activated by antigen.

ZFA:0009085.label: amelocyte
ZFA:0009085.definition: Skeletogenic cell that produces enamel, overlies the odontogenic papilla, and arises from the differentiation of a preameloblast cell.

ZFA:0009317.label: cyanophore
ZFA:0009317.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains blue pigment of unknown chemical composition in fibrous organelles termed cyanosomes. This gives a blue appearance.

ZFA:0009263.label: erythrophore
ZFA:0009263.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains pteridine and/or carotenoid pigments in structures called pterinosomes or erythrosomes. This gives an orange to red appearance.

ZFA:0009199.label: iridophore
ZFA:0009199.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. The cell contains flat light-reflecting platelets, probably of guanine, in stacks called reflecting platets or iridisomes. The color-generating components produce a silver, gold, or iridescent color.

ZFA:0009261.label: leucophore
ZFA:0009261.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains uric acid or other purine crystals deposited in stacks called leucosomes. The crystals reflect light and this gives a white appearance under white light.

ZFA:0009091.label: melanocyte
ZFA:0009091.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

ZFA:0009198.label: xanthophore
ZFA:0009198.definition: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains carotenoid pigments in structures called pterinosomes or xanthosomes. This gives an appearance ranging from a golden yellow to orange and red.

ZFA:0009097.label: enteroendocrine cell
ZFA:0009097.definition: An endocrine cell that is located in the epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract.

ZFA:0009281.label: folliculostellate cell
ZFA:0009281.definition: A supportive cell of the vertebrate pituitary that provides macromolecular transport and secretes hormones.

ZFA:0009098.label: neuroendocrine cell
ZFA:0009098.definition: A neuron that has the specialized function to produce and secrete hormones, and that constitutes, in whole or in part, an endocrine organ or system.

ZFA:0009228.label: D cell
ZFA:0009228.definition: A cell found throughout the gastrointestinal tract and in the pancreas. They secrete somatostatin in both an endocrine and paracrine manner. Somatostatin inhibits gastrin, cholecystokinin, insulin, glucagon, pancreatic enzymes, and gastric hydrochloric acid. A variety of substances which inhibit gastric acid secretion (vasoactive intestinal peptide, calcitonin gene-related peptide, cholecystokinin, beta-adrenergic agonists, and gastric inhibitory peptide) are thought to act by releasing somatostatin.

ZFA:0009099.label: chromaffin cell
ZFA:0009099.definition: A cell that stores epinephrine secretory vesicles. During times of stress, the nervous system signals the vesicles to secrete their hormonal content. Their name derives from their ability to stain a brownish color with chromic salts. Characteristically, they are located in the adrenal medulla and paraganglia of the sympathetic nervous system.

ZFA:0009216.label: adrenocorticotropic hormone secreting cell
ZFA:0009216.definition: A basophil cell of the anterior pituitary that produces adrenocorticotropic hormone, or corticotropin.

ZFA:0005599.label: ghrelin secreting cell
ZFA:0005599.definition: A cell that secretes ghrelin, the peptide hormone that stimulates hunger.

ZFA:0009205.label: melanocyte stimulating hormone secreting cell
ZFA:0009205.definition: A cell of the intermediate pituitary that produces melanocyte stimulating hormone.

ZFA:0009204.label: prolactin secreting cell
ZFA:0009204.definition: An acidophilic cell of the anterior pituitary that produces prolactin.

ZFA:0009155.label: somatotropin secreting cell
ZFA:0009155.definition: An acidophilic cell of the anterior pituitary that produces growth hormone, somatotropin.

ZFA:0009218.label: thyroid stimulating hormone secreting cell
ZFA:0009218.definition: A basophil cell of the anterior pituitary that produces thyroid stimulating hormone, thyrotrophin.

ZFA:0009227.label: granulosa cell
ZFA:0009227.definition: A supporting cell for the developing female gamete in the ovary of mammals. They develop from the coelomic epithelial cells of the gonadal ridge. Granulosa cells form a single layer around the mammalian oocyte in the primordial ovarian follicle and advance to form a multilayered cumulus oophorus surrounding the ovum in the Graafian follicle. The major functions of granulosa cells include the production of steroids and LH receptors.

ZFA:0009108.label: Leydig cell
ZFA:0009108.definition: A Leydig cell is a testosterone-secreting cell in the interstitial area, between the seminiferous tubules, in the testis.

ZFA:0001086.label: muscle pioneer
ZFA:0001086.definition: Cells that develop from adaxial cells  that express engrailed and do not migrate completely to the lateral surface of the myotome, and instead extend from the notochord to the lateral surface of the somite, at the level of the future horizontal myoseptum.

ZFA:0009118.label: smooth muscle cell
ZFA:0009118.definition: A non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels. They develop from specialized myoblasts (smooth muscle myoblast).

ZFA:0005784.label: striated muscle cell
ZFA:0005784.definition: Muscle cell which has as its direct parts myofilaments organized into sarcomeres.

ZFA:0009116.label: slow muscle cell
ZFA:0009116.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content.

ZFA:0000963.label: slow muscle cell somite 1
ZFA:0000963.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 1.

ZFA:0001047.label: slow muscle cell somite 10
ZFA:0001047.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 10.

ZFA:0000840.label: slow muscle cell somite 11
ZFA:0000840.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 11.

ZFA:0000964.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 12.

ZFA:0001050.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 19.

ZFA:0000843.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 2.

ZFA:0000967.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 20.

ZFA:0000719.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 21.

ZFA:0000844.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 22.

ZFA:0000969.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 23.

ZFA:0000720.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 24.

ZFA:0000845.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 25.

ZFA:0000970.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 26.

ZFA:0000721.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 27.

ZFA:0000846.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 28.

ZFA:0000971.label: slow muscle cell somite 29
ZFA:0000971.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 29.

ZFA:0000722.label: slow muscle cell somite 3
ZFA:0000722.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 3.

ZFA:0000847.label: slow muscle cell somite 30
ZFA:0000847.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 30.
