ZFA:0000972.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 4.

ZFA:0000723.label: slow muscle cell somite 5
ZFA:0000723.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 5.

ZFA:0000848.label: slow muscle cell somite 6
ZFA:0000848.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 6.

ZFA:0000973.label: slow muscle cell somite 7
ZFA:0000973.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 7.

ZFA:0000724.label: slow muscle cell somite 8
ZFA:0000724.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 8.

ZFA:0000850.label: slow muscle cell somite 9
ZFA:0000850.definition: A muscle cell that is small, darkly colored, with high lipid and mitochondrial content. Slow muscle cells are located superficial to the fast muscle cell in the myotome of somite 9.

ZFA:0005238.label: juxtaglomerular cell
ZFA:0005238.definition: A smooth muscle cell that synthesizes, stores, and secretes the enzyme renin. This cell type are located in the wall of the afferent arteriole at the entrance to the glomerulus. While having a different origin than other kidney smooth muscle cells, this cell type expresses smooth muscle actin upon maturation.

ZFA:0009366.label: hair cell
ZFA:0009366.definition: Hair cell is a mechanoreceptor cell that is sensitive to movement of the hair-like projections (stereocilia and kinocilia) which relay the information centrally in the nervous system.

ZFA:0009358.label: ciliated olfactory receptor neuron
ZFA:0009358.definition: An olfactory receptor cell in which the apical ending of the dendrite is a pronounced ciliated olfactory knob.  The soma is located basally in the olfactory epithelium.

ZFA:0009360.label: crypt olfactory receptor neuron
ZFA:0009360.definition: An olfactory receptor cell with short cilia growing in an invagination bordered by microvilli.  The soma is large and globose located in the apical region of the olfactory epithelium.  The axons project to a single glomerulus mdG2.

ZFA:0005828.label: kappe olfactory receptor neuron
ZFA:0005828.definition: An olfactory receptor cells with apical microvilli.  The pear shaped soma is located in the apical region of the olfactory epithelium. They project to a single glomerulus, mdG5.

ZFA:0009359.label: microvillous olfactory receptor neuron
ZFA:0009359.definition: An olfactory receptor cell in which the apical ending of the dendrite is a knob that bears numerous microvilli. The cell body is plump and the soma is at an  intermediate position in the olfactory epithelium.

ZFA:0009190.label: electrically responsive cell
ZFA:0009190.definition: A cell whose function is determined by its response to an electric signal.

ZFA:0009193.label: electrically signaling cell
ZFA:0009193.definition: A cell that initiates an electrical signal and passes that signal to another cell.

ZFA:0009289.label: gut absorptive cell
ZFA:0009289.definition: Cell of the intestinal epithelium with a brush border made up of many parallel packed microvilli; associated with absorption, particularly of macromolecules.

ZFA:0009133.label: Sertoli cell
ZFA:0009133.definition: A supporting cell projecting inward from the basement membrane of seminiferous tubules. They surround and nourish the developing male germ cells and secrete androgen binding protein. Their tight junctions with the spermatogonia and spermatocytes provide a blood-testis barrier.

ZFA:0009130.label: lining cell
ZFA:0009130.definition: A cell within an epithelial cell sheet whose main function is to act as an internal or external covering for a tissue or an organism.

ZFA:0009135.label: myelinating Schwann cell
ZFA:0009135.definition: A neuroglial cell of the peripheral nervous system which forms the insulating myelin sheaths of peripheral axons.

ZFA:0007086.label: migratory neural crest cell
ZFA:0007086.definition: Cell that is part of the migratory neural crest population. Migratory neural crest cells develop from premigratory neural crest cells and have undergone epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination.

ZFA:0009140.label: phagocyte
ZFA:0009140.definition: Any cell capable of ingesting particulate matter via phagocytosis.

ZFA:0005773.label: embryonic blood vessel endothelial progenitor cell
ZFA:0005773.definition: An endothelial progenitor cell that participates in angiogenesis during development.

ZFA:0009077.label: microglial cell
ZFA:0009077.definition: A central nervous system macrophage found in the parenchyma of the central nervous system.

ZFA:0009267.label: peritoneal macrophage
ZFA:0009267.definition: A macrophage resident in the peritoneum under non-inlfammatory conditions.

ZFA:0009344.label: precursor B cell
ZFA:0009344.definition: A precursor B cell is a B cell with the phenotype CD10-positive.

ZFA:0009345.label: transitional stage B cell
ZFA:0009345.definition: An immature B cell of an intermediate stage between the pre-B cell stage and the mature nave stage. Transitional B cells express surface immunoglobulin, and are subject to the process of B cell selection.

ZFA:0009269.label: enterocyte
ZFA:0009269.definition: An epithelial cell that has its apical plasma membrane folded into microvilli to provide ample surface for the absorption of nutrients from the intestinal lumen.

ZFA:0001725.label: immature Schwann cell
ZFA:0001725.definition: A glial cell that develops from a Schwann cell precursor. The immature Schwann cell is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has a basal lamina. Cells can survive without an axon present. Immature Schwann cell can be found communally ensheathing large groups of axons.

ZFA:0009237.label: perineuronal satellite cell
ZFA:0009237.definition: A non-neuronal cell that surrounds the neuronal cell bodies of the ganglia.

ZFA:0009262.label: retinal cone cell
ZFA:0009262.definition: One of the two photoreceptor cell types in the vertebrate retina. In cones the photopigment is in invaginations of the cell membrane of the outer segment. Cones are less sensitive to light than rods, but they provide vision with higher spatial and temporal acuity, and the combination of signals from cones with different pigments allows color vision.

ZFA:0009275.label: retinal rod cell
ZFA:0009275.definition: One of the two photoreceptor cell types of the vertebrate retina. In rods the photopigment is in stacks of membranous disks separate from the outer cell membrane. Rods are more sensitive to light than cones, but rod mediated vision has less spatial and temporal resolution than cone vision.

ZFA:0009158.label: keratinocyte
ZFA:0009158.definition: An epidermal cell which synthesizes keratin and undergoes a characteristic change as it moves upward from the basal layers of the epidermis to the cornified (horny) layer of the skin. Successive stages of differentiation of the keratinocytes forming the epidermal layers are basal cell, spinous or prickle cell, and the granular cell.

ZFA:0009094.label: goblet cell
ZFA:0009094.definition: A cell of the epithelial lining that produce and secrete mucins.

ZFA:0009279.label: ito cell
ZFA:0009279.definition: A cell that is found in the perisinusoidal space of the liver that is capable of multiple roles including storage of retinol, presentation of antigen to T cells (including CD1d-restricted NKT cells), and upon activation, production of extracellular matrix components that can contribute to liver fibrosis. This activated state has a myofibroblast-like phenotype.

ZFA:0009305.label: leptomeningeal cell
ZFA:0009305.definition: Stromal cell that forms the internal covering of the vertebrate brain and produces ECM for this and the choroid plexus.

ZFA:0009003.label: cranial neural crest cell
ZFA:0009003.definition: A cell of the cranial neural crest.

ZFA:0007084.label: premigratory neural crest cell
ZFA:0007084.definition: Cell that is part of the premigratory neural crest population. Will undergo epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination to become part of the migratory neural crest.

ZFA:0009004.label: trunk neural crest cell
ZFA:0009004.definition: A cell of the trunk neural crest.

ZFA:0009292.label: radial glial cell
ZFA:0009292.definition: A transient cell present only in the developing CNS. Functions as both a precursor cell and as a scaffold to support neuronal migration.

ZFA:0005786.label: cleft cell
ZFA:0005786.definition: Wedge-shaped epidermal cell positioned along the apex of the developing fin fold. Each cleft cell retains a wedge-shaped form during fold formation and develops a basal cleft-shaped invagination. Invaginations are aligned in neighboring cleft cells so that these cells cap the distal boundary of the subepidermal space where collagenous extracellular fibres called actinotrichia run anteroposteriorly along the length of the fin fold.

ZFA:0009114.label: muscle cell
ZFA:0009114.definition: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte, that forms one of three kinds of muscle.

ZFA:0009248.label: neuron
ZFA:0009248.definition: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

ZFA:0005209.label: hindbrain interneuron
ZFA:0005209.definition: Is a CNS interneuron that is part of the hindbrain.

ZFA:0005210.label: midbrain interneuron
ZFA:0005210.definition: CNS interneurons located in the midbrain.

ZFA:0005865.label: reticulospinal neuron
ZFA:0005865.definition: Neuron with the large soma in the brain with an axon projecting caudally to the spinal cord.

ZFA:0000778.label: spinal cord interneuron
ZFA:0000778.definition: A CNS interneuron located in the spinal cord.

ZFA:0005866.label: vestibulospinal neuron
ZFA:0005866.definition: CNS interneuron with a soma located in a cluster  in the lateral wall of the medulla, with dendrites confined to the neuropil,  that has connections to the vestibular and lateral line neurons.

ZFA:0005151.label: gold iridophore
ZFA:0005151.definition: Iridescent iridophore containing gold reflecting platelets.

ZFA:0005152.label: silver iridophore
ZFA:0005152.definition: Iridescent iridophore containing silver reflecting platelets.

ZFA:0009214.label: norepinephrine secreting cell
ZFA:0009214.definition: A cell capable of producting norepinephrine. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine with multiple roles including as a hormone and a neurotransmitter. In addition, epinephrine is synthesized from norepinephrine by the actions of the phenylethanolamine N-methyltransferase enzyme.

ZFA:0005873.label: noradrenergic neuron
ZFA:0005873.definition: A neuron that releases norephinephrine  (noradrenaline) as a neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009229.label: theca cell
ZFA:0009229.definition: A flattened stroma cell forming a sheath or theca outside the basal lamina lining the mature ovarian follicle. Thecal interstitial or stromal cells are steroidogenic, and produce primarily androgens which serve as precursors of estrogens in the granulosa cells.

ZFA:0005743.label: pancreatic D cell
ZFA:0005743.definition: A D cell located in the pancreas. Peripherally placed within the islets like type A cells; contains somatostatin.

ZFA:0009369.label: fast muscle myoblast
ZFA:0009369.definition: A skeletal muscle myoblast that differentiates into fast muscle fibers.

ZFA:0009272.label: skeletal muscle satellite cell
ZFA:0009272.definition: An elongated, spindle-shaped, quiescent myoblast lying in close contact with adult skeletal muscle. They are thought to play a role in muscle repair and regeneration.

ZFA:0009368.label: slow muscle myoblast
ZFA:0009368.definition: A skeletal muscle myoblast that differentiates into slow muscle fibers.

ZFA:0005806.label: diencephalic efferent neurons to the lateral line
ZFA:0005806.definition: Efferent neurons located ventrally in the diencephalon.  The dendrites extend into a large area of the diencephalic neuropil rostral, caudal, lateral and ventral to the cell body.  The axon courses dorsally and then caudally through the midbrain.   As the axon descends through the brain it gives off branches at several levels.   One branch usually exits the brain with the posterior lateral line nerve.  The axon can be traced into the cervical spinal cord.

ZFA:0009052.label: motor neuron
ZFA:0009052.definition: An efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.

ZFA:0005804.label: rhombencephalic efferent neurons to the lateral line
ZFA:0005804.definition: Efferent neuron where the cell body is located in the hindbrain reticular formation immediately adjacent to the medial longitudinal fascicle at the rostrocaudal level between the MiDl and the CaD and adjacent to the descending Mauthner axon.  RELL dendrites are large and extend bilaterally into the ventrolateral neuropil.  The ipsilateral dendrite reaches into a single area of the ventrolateral neuropil whereas the contralateral dendrite branches and extends into two different levels of the same rostrocaudal column of the ventrolateral neuropil. The axon emerges from the ventral part of the perikaryon courses a short distance rostrally to the level of the ROLE  cells and then turns laterally from the CNS accompanying the root of the posterior lateral line nerve.

ZFA:0005805.label: rhombencephalic octavolateral efferent neuron
ZFA:0005805.definition: Efferent neuron located in the hindbrain.  The axon of ROLE cells travels rostrally near the ipsilateral medial longitudinal fascicle to the level of the Mauthner cell where it turns laterally to exit with the eighth nerve.  Outside the brain the  axon continues ventrally  to the base of the saccular macula in the ear then turns caudally to ender the ganglion of the posterior lateral line.   A branch of the axon  turns ventrally before the main axon enters the LLG.  The branch goes ventrally along the wall of the otic capsule.

ZFA:0009243.label: CaP motoneuron
ZFA:0009243.definition: A primary motor neuron part of the spinal cord. The CaP motoneuron is found within 1 soma diameter of the ventral root. The axon of the CaP motoneuron extends ventrally from the ventral root, within the space between the notochord and the medial surface of the axial muscles.  Below the notochord, the axon extends within the ventral median septum to the ventral edge of the axial muscles, where it turns dorsally and laterally to project over the lateral surface of the axial muscles.

ZFA:0005179.label: MiP motor neuron
ZFA:0005179.definition: A primary motor neuron that is part of the spinal cord.   The axon turns caudally and dorsally, coursing between the surface of the spinal cord and the medial surface of the axial muscles to the dorsal median septum. The MiP axon then extends dorsally to the surface of the muscle, where it turns to arborize ventrally over the lateral surface of the axial muscle.

ZFA:0005180.label: RoP motor neuron
ZFA:0005180.definition: A primary motoneuron that is part of the spinal cord.  The axon of the CaP motoneuron on emerging from the ventral root.  At the horizontal septum, however, the RoP axon turns laterally to extend within the horizontal septum to the lateral surface of the muscle.

ZFA:0005181.label: VaP motor neuron
ZFA:0005181.definition: A primary motor neuron of the spinal cord. This cell is present in slightly less than half of the trunk hemisegments. Additionally, this cell has at least 2 different fates: it may become a primary motoneuron and arborize in an exclusive muscle territory, or it may die during embryonic development.

ZFA:0009276.label: GABAergic neuron
ZFA:0009276.definition: A neuron that uses GABA as a vesicular neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009060.label: cholinergic neuron
ZFA:0009060.definition: A neuron that uses acetylcholine as a vesicular neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009301.label: dopaminergic neuron
ZFA:0009301.definition: A neuron that releases dopamine as a neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009396.label: glycinergic neuron
ZFA:0009396.definition: The neurons that utilize glycine as a neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0005778.label: hypocretin-secreting neuron
ZFA:0005778.definition: A neuron that releases hypocretin as a neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009051.label: interneuron
ZFA:0009051.definition: Most generally any neuron which is not motor or sensory. Interneurons may also refer to neurons whose axons remain within a particular brain region as contrasted with projection neurons which have axons projecting to other brain regions.

ZFA:0009240.label: nitrergic neuron
ZFA:0009240.definition: A nerve cell where transmission is mediated by nitric oxide.

ZFA:0009066.label: pioneer neuron
ZFA:0009066.definition: Pioneer neurons establish a pathway in the developing central nervous system and then undergo programmed cell death once the adult axons, which follow them, have made connections with the target site. Thus, they are a transient cell type involved in axon guidance.

ZFA:0009361.label: serotonergic neuron
ZFA:0009361.definition: A neuron that releases serotonin as a neurotransmitter.

ZFA:0009142.label: B cell
ZFA:0009142.definition: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of an immunoglobulin complex.

ZFA:0009046.label: T cell
ZFA:0009046.definition: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

ZFA:0009278.label: natural killer cell
ZFA:0009278.definition: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

ZFA:0009332.label: plasma cell
ZFA:0009332.definition: A terminally differentiated, post-mitotic, antibody secreting cell of the B cell lineage with the phenotype CD138-positive, surface immunonoglobulin-negative, and MHC Class II-negative. Plasma cells are oval or round with extensive rough endoplasmic reticulum, a well-developed Golgi apparatus, and a round nucleus having a characteristic cartwheel heterochromatin pattern and are devoted to producing large amounts of immunoglobulin.

ZFA:0009330.label: mononuclear odontoclast
ZFA:0009330.definition: A specialized mononuclear osteoclast associated with the absorption and removal of cementum.

ZFA:0005739.label: pancreatic acinar cell
ZFA:0005739.definition: A secretory cell found in pancreatic acini that secretes digestive enzymes and mucins. This cell is a typical zymogenic cell, has a basal nucleus and basophilic cytoplasm consisting of regular arrays of granular endoplasmic reticulum with mitochondria and dense secretory granules.

ZFA:0009346.label: immature natural killer cell
ZFA:0009346.definition: A natural killer cell that is developmentally immature, has the phenotype CD34-negative, CD117-positive, CD122-positive, and CD161-positive, and expresses additional natural killer cell receptors (NKR).

ZFA:0009347.label: mature natural killer cell
ZFA:0009347.definition: A natural killer cell that is developmentally mature, has the phenotype CD16-positive, and expresses a variety of inhibitory and activating receptors that recognize NHC class I and other stress related molecules.

ZFA:0001674.label: mesonephric podocyte
ZFA:0001674.definition: Podocyte that is part of the kidney (mesonephros).

ZFA:0001673.label: pronephric podocyte
ZFA:0001673.definition: Podocyte that is part of the pronephros.

ZFA:0009299.label: neuroglioform cell
ZFA:0009299.definition: A stellate interneuron having 7-10 dendrites that may branch.

ZFA:0009020.label: multi fate stem cell
ZFA:0009020.definition: A stem cell that can give rise to mulitple lineages of cells.

ZFA:0009024.label: totipotent stem cell
ZFA:0009024.definition: A stem cell from which all cells of the body can form.

ZFA:0009357.label: mononuclear cell
ZFA:0009357.definition: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.

ZFA:0009326.label: myeloid leukocyte
ZFA:0009326.definition: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, or mast cell lineage.

ZFA:0009088.label: professional antigen presenting cell
ZFA:0009088.definition: A cell capable of processing and presenting lipid and protein antigens to T cells in order to initiate an immune response.

ZFA:0009320.label: OFF-bipolar cell
ZFA:0009320.definition: A bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with photoreceptors cells and neurons in the outer half of the inner plexiform layer. These cells hyperpolarize in response to light stimulation of their corresponding photoreceptors.

ZFA:0009319.label: ON-bipolar cell
ZFA:0009319.definition: A bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with photoreceptors cells and neurons in the inner half of the inner plexiform layer. These cells depolarize in response to light stimulation of their corresponding photoreceptors.

ZFA:0009322.label: cone retinal bipolar cell
ZFA:0009322.definition: A bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with cone photoreceptor cells and neurons in the inner plexiform layer.

ZFA:0009321.label: rod bipolar cell
ZFA:0009321.definition: A bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with rod photoreceptor cells and neurons in the inner plexiform layer.

ZFA:0009325.label: erythroid lineage cell
ZFA:0009325.definition: A immature or mature cell in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

ZFA:0005237.label: erythroblast
ZFA:0005237.definition: A nucleated precursor of an erythrocyte.

ZFA:0009048.label: granulocyte
ZFA:0009048.definition: A leukocyte with abundant granules in the cytoplasm.

ZFA:0009328.label: immature neutrophil
ZFA:0009328.definition: Any of the immature forms of a neutrophil in which neutrophilic specific granules are present but other phenotypic features of the mature form may be lacking. A neutrophil is a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

ZFA:0009049.label: mature neutrophil
ZFA:0009049.definition: A fully differentiated neutrophil, a granular leukocyte having a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

ZFA:0009254.label: band form neutrophil
ZFA:0009254.definition: A late neutrophilic metamyelocyte in which the nucleus is in the form of a curved or coiled band, not having acquired the typical multilobar shape of the mature neutrophil.

ZFA:0009268.label: neutrophilic metamyelocyte
ZFA:0009268.definition: A neutrophil precursor in the granulocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between a myelocyte and the band form neutrophil. The protein synthesis seen in earlier stages decreases or stops; the nucleus becomes indented and its chromatin becomes coarse and clumped; and the cytoplasm becomes pink like that of a mature granulocyte.

ZFA:0009266.label: neutrophilic myelocyte
ZFA:0009266.definition: A neutrophil precursor in the granulocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between a promyelocyte and a metamyelocyte; in this stage, differentiation of cytoplasmic granules has begun.

ZFA:0009333.label: memory B cell
ZFA:0009333.definition: A memory B cell is a mature B cell that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin. This cell type has the phenotype CD19-positive, CD20-positive, MHC Class II-positive, and CD138-negative.

ZFA:0009334.label: naive B cell
ZFA:0009334.definition: A naive B cell is a mature B cell that has the phenotype surface IgD-positive, surface IgM-positive, CD27-negative, and CD38-negative, and that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

ZFA:0009337.label: immature gamma-delta T cell
ZFA:0009337.definition: A gamma-delta T cell that has an immature phenotype.

ZFA:0009338.label: mature gamma-delta T cell
ZFA:0009338.definition: A gamma-delta T cell that has a mature phenotype. These cells can be found in tissues and circulation where they express unique TCR repertoire depending on their location.

ZFA:0009339.label: gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell
ZFA:0009339.definition: A gamma-delta T cell of the columnar epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract. Intraepithelial T cells often have distinct developmental pathways and activation requirements.

ZFA:0009343.label: immature B cell
ZFA:0009343.definition: An immature B cell is a precursor B cell that has the phenotype surface IgM-positive and surface IgD-negative, and have not undergone class immunoglobulin class switching or peripheral encounter with antigen and activation.

ZFA:0009018.label: neutrophilic myeloblast
ZFA:0009018.definition: A myeloblast committed to the neutrophil lineage. A myeloblast is the most primitive precursor in the granulocytic series, having fine, evenly distributed chromatin, several nucleoli, and a nongranular basophilic cytoplasm.

ZFA:0009349.label: pro-B cell
ZFA:0009349.definition: A progenitor cell of the B cell lineage, with some lineage specific activity such as early stages of recombination of B cell receptor genes, but not yet fully committed to the B cell lineage until the expression of PAX5 occurs.

ZFA:0009348.label: pro-NK cell
ZFA:0009348.definition: A progenitor committed to the natural killer cell lineage, expressing certain phenotypic markers of the natural killer cell lineage such as the IL-15 receptor, but lacking many of the phenotypic characteristics of later stages of natural killer cell development such as expression of NK activating and inhibitory molecules.

ZFA:0009350.label: pro-T cell
ZFA:0009350.definition: A progenitor cell of the T cell lineage, with some lineage specific marker expression, but not yet fully committed to the T cell lineage.

ZFA:0009015.label: erythroid progenitor cell
ZFA:0009015.definition: A progenitor cell committed to the erythroid lineage.

ZFA:0009017.label: monoblast
ZFA:0009017.definition: A myeloid progenitor cell committed to the monocyte lineage.

ZFA:0009353.label: myeloblast
ZFA:0009353.definition: The most primitive precursor in the granulocytic series, having fine, evenly distributed chromatin, several nucleoli, and a nongranular basophilic cytoplasm.

ZFA:0009352.label: neutrophil progenitor cell
ZFA:0009352.definition: A progenitor cell of the neutrophil lineage.

ZFA:0009253.label: promonocyte
ZFA:0009253.definition: A precursor in the monocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between the monoblast and monocyte.

ZFA:0009351.label: thromboblast
ZFA:0009351.definition: A progenitor cell of the thrombocyte, a nucleated blood cell involved in coagulation typically seen in birds and other non-mammalian vertebrates.

ZFA:0009250.label: lymphocyte
ZFA:0009250.definition: A cell of the B cell, T cell, or natural killer cell lineage.

ZFA:0009064.label: mononuclear phagocyte
ZFA:0009064.definition: A vertebrate phagocyte with a single nucleus.

ZFA:0000678.label: hair cell anterior macula
ZFA:0000678.definition: Specialized neuronal receptor cells of the anterior macula. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for hair cells by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0000281.label: hair cell posterior macula
ZFA:0000281.definition: Specialized neuronal receptor cells of the posterior macula. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for hair cells by T. Whitfield.)

ZFA:0001098.label: immature hair cell anterior macula
ZFA:0001098.definition: A hair cell which is immature and located in the anterior macula. It  will develop into a hair cell of the anterior macula.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: immature sensory hair cells anterior macula

ZFA:0001099.label: immature hair cell posterior macula
ZFA:0001099.definition: A hair cell which is immature and located in the posterior macula. It  will develop into a hair cell of the posterior macula.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: immature sensory hair cells posterior macula

ZFA:0009367.label: neuromast hair cell
ZFA:0009367.definition: Neuromast hair cell is a hair cell that acts as a sensory receptor of the neuromast; it is morphologically polarized as a result of the relative position of the single kinocilium and the clusters of stereocilia on its apical surface.

ZFA:0005565.label: tether cell
ZFA:0005565.definition: A specialized hair cell that has an elongated kinocilium upon which an otolith accretes. The tether cell then anchors the otolith in place.

ZFA:0009274.label: pressoreceptor cell
ZFA:0009274.definition: A receptor in the vascular system, particularly the aorta and carotid sinus, which is sensitive to stretch of the vessel walls.

ZFA:0009397.label: cholangiocyte
ZFA:0009397.definition: An epithelial cell that is part of the bile duct. Cholangiocytes contribute to bile secretion via net release of bicarbonate and water. They are cuboidal epithelium in the small interlobular bile ducts, but become columnar and mucus secreting in larger bile ducts approaching the porta hepatis and the extrahepatic ducts.

ZFA:0009379.label: intrahepatic bile duct epithelial cell
ZFA:0009379.definition: An epithelial cell of the intrahepatic portion of the bile duct.

ZFA:0009380.label: pancreatic ductal cell
ZFA:0009380.definition: Epithelial cell found in the ducts of the pancreas.

ZFA:0009376.label: renal alpha-intercalated cell
ZFA:0009376.definition: A cuboidal epithelial cell of the kidney which secretes acid and reabsorbs base to regulate acid/base balance.

ZFA:0009400.label: epithelial cell of esophagus
ZFA:0009400.definition: An epithelial cell of the esophagus.

ZFA:0009399.label: intestinal epithelial cell
ZFA:0009399.definition: An epithelial cell of the intestine.

ZFA:0009392.label: connective tissue cell
ZFA:0009392.definition: A cell of the supporting or framework tissue of the body, arising chiefly from the embryonic mesoderm and including adipose tissue, cartilage, and bone.

ZFA:0009389.label: kidney cell
ZFA:0009389.definition: Cell that is part of the kidney.

ZFA:0009395.label: vascular lymphangioblast
ZFA:0009395.definition: Lymphatic progenitor cells, derived from the veins, that give rise to lymphatic endothelial cells.

ZFA:0001689.label: anatomical line
ZFA:0001689.definition: Non-material anatomical entity of one dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical surface or is a modulation of an anatomical surface.

ZFA:0001643.label: anatomical space
ZFA:0001643.definition: Non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes; is surrounded by one or more anatomical structures; contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures.

ZFA:0000037.label: anatomical structure
ZFA:0000037.definition: Zebrafish anatomical entity that has inherent 3D shape and is generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

ZFA:0005594.label: anatomical surface
ZFA:0005594.definition: Non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions, that is demarcated by anatomical lines or points on the external or internal surfaces of anatomical structures.

ZFA:0001487.label: portion of organism substance
ZFA:0001487.definition: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

ZFA:0001093.label: unspecified
ZFA:0001093.definition: Annotation with this anatomy term indicates that a structure was not specified by the author.
